    '{"id":"01KBD4A08VA1FGRTS2F6QAC257","title":"Inside Tracker // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Scheduling**\n\nThe team is maintaining a steady podcast production and posting cadence to build listener engagement before the holidays.\n\n- **Gil confirmed posting the Dr. Meyer episode and plans to record and send two more episodes, one today and another next Friday** (02:00)  \n    - This steady flow ensures a consistent backlog of episodes for timely posting.  \n    - Gil’s plan to review and possibly edit the “parents” episode reflects a focus on quality control and audience fit.  \n    - Baylee acknowledged the editing challenges with that episode but emphasized its potential audience appeal.  \n    - Maintaining this schedule supports audience retention and growth through fresh content.\n\n## **Audience Metrics and Engagement**\n\nDownloads have surpassed a major milestone, indicating significant audience growth and content reach.\n\n- **Gil reported exceeding 1 million total downloads with over 15,000 downloads in the last 30 days** (02:15)  \n    - This metric shows strong listener engagement and validates the production strategy.  \n    - Baylee highlighted the milestone as an impressive achievement that underscores the podcast''s market presence.  \n    - Sustaining or increasing monthly downloads will be critical for attracting sponsorships and advertisers.  \n    - The download data will help prioritize episode topics and promotional efforts.\n\n## **Content Review and Quality Assurance**\n\nThe team is exercising deliberate content review to maintain brand alignment and audience relevance.\n\n- **Gil plans to spend the weekend reviewing the “parents” episode before deciding on posting or further editing** (01:45)  \n    - This cautious approach ensures content aligns with audience expectations and brand voice.  \n    - Baylee’s note on the episode’s editing complexity suggests potential rework is needed.  \n    - Delaying the decision avoids rushing content that could impact listener perception negatively.  \n    - This review process supports long-term brand trust and content quality consistency.\n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Collaboration**\n\nThe team is formalizing a biweekly meeting schedule to maintain alignment and workflow momentum.\n\n- **Gil confirmed moving meetings to every other week to balance work and review cycles** (02:50)  \n    - This cadence allows sufficient time for episode production and content review between meetings.  \n    - Baylee and Gil’s coordination supports clear communication and timely issue resolution.  \n    - Regular check-ins help track progress on posting schedules and audience metrics.  \n    - Keeping meetings concise maximizes productivity and minimizes disruption.","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast production","episode backlog","social media posting","audience downloads","episode review","meeting schedule"],"overview":"- **Podcast Production:** Steady production of episodes leads to timely posting, enhancing listener engagement before the holidays.  \n- **Audience Growth:** Exceeded 1 million downloads total; 15,000 downloads in the last month indicate strong listener interest.  \n- **Content Quality:** Focused review process planned for “parents” episode to ensure alignment with audience expectations and brand voice.  \n- **Meeting Frequency:** Biweekly meetings established to balance production cycles and improve communication among team members.  \n- **Content Strategy:** Download data will guide future episode topics and promotional strategies to attract sponsorships.  \n- **Editing Challenges:** Acknowledgment of editing difficulties suggests careful attention to content quality for audience retention.","action_items":"\n**Gil**\nReview and decide on the episode with parents, including potential edits, scheduled for the weekend (01:47)\nContinue posting social and video content related to recently posted episodes (00:32)\nRecord new podcast episodes today and next Friday, then send the recordings with documentation to the team (00:32)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide feedback support and assistance on posted episodes and upcoming edits as needed (00:00)\n"},"duration":3.119999885559082,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":1,"name":"Gil"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Yeah.","index":0,"end_time":0.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":1.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.28,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"What''s new with you?","index":2,"end_time":3.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.64,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Nothing.","index":3,"end_time":7.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nothing crazy.","index":4,"end_time":8.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just.","index":5,"end_time":8.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, Thanksgiving was great last week.","index":6,"end_time":11.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gotta spend lots of time with family and.","index":7,"end_time":14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just been lots of podcast episodes lately.","index":8,"end_time":19.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ve got lots of other clients.","index":9,"end_time":22.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.84,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think lots of them try to do a lot of episodes right before the holidays so they can have a bit of a backlog.","index":10,"end_time":29.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":11,"end_time":30.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just been busy with that.","index":12,"end_time":31.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":13,"end_time":32.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.03,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"It''s good to be.","index":14,"end_time":33.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.63,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":34.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":33.87,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Happy for.","index":16,"end_time":35.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.99,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Happy to hear that.","index":17,"end_time":37.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.19,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":39.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":38.99,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"For my side, I got the one with my parents.","index":19,"end_time":42.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":39.39,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I haven''t had a chance to review it yet.","index":20,"end_time":44.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.95,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I was busy.","index":21,"end_time":46.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":45.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I posted the Dr. Meyer today, actually yesterday, and I''m now posting the social and the videos.","index":22,"end_time":56.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.27,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Looks much better, so thank you so much.","index":23,"end_time":58.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I''m recording another one today, later today, so I. I''m expecting to send it to you guys and I have another one next Friday.","index":24,"end_time":69.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.58,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So.","index":25,"end_time":71.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.74,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":26,"end_time":71.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.1,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So great.","index":27,"end_time":72.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":28,"end_time":73.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.14,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So everything is moving.","index":29,"end_time":75.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.78,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":77.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.14,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And I will let you guys know if I have any question on it, but it looks like all is good right now.","index":31,"end_time":83.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.54,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":32,"end_time":84.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve got just a few quick slides we can go through.","index":33,"end_time":88.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sure.","index":34,"end_time":88.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.42,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So sounds like you''ve already posted this episode.","index":35,"end_time":96.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let us know what you think about the one with your parents too.","index":36,"end_time":100.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was a bit of a tricky one to edit, but I think the audience will enjoy it.","index":37,"end_time":106.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not sure I need to listen to it.","index":38,"end_time":110.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.44,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"I''m not sure if I want to post it or not, so I need to.","index":39,"end_time":114.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.56,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And maybe we''ll need to edit it a bit.","index":40,"end_time":117.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.28,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":117.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":117.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":118.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.11,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So.","index":43,"end_time":118.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.55,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So that''s why I said I will take maybe the weekend when I will have a bit more time and marinate into that and see what can we do with that.","index":44,"end_time":127.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.91,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":45,"end_time":128.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Because it''s not a normal episode.","index":46,"end_time":131.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.55,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"It''s.","index":47,"end_time":131.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.23,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a bit out of the mainstream.","index":48,"end_time":134.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.59,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yep.","index":49,"end_time":136.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":50,"end_time":137.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just for your downloads, recently, you''ve had over 15,000 downloads over the last 30 days.","index":51,"end_time":145.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":146.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.31,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So, yeah, we are way past the million, which is good.","index":53,"end_time":150.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.87,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, that.","index":54,"end_time":152.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s amazing.","index":55,"end_time":153.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":154.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154.31,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":57,"end_time":157.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.43,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Anything else that we should discuss today?","index":58,"end_time":160.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.99,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"No, that''s everything.","index":59,"end_time":162.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, excellent.","index":60,"end_time":163.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.71,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"So thank you so much.","index":61,"end_time":164.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.71,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And as soon as I will have the recording, I will send it to.","index":62,"end_time":169.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":165.35,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"To the team in the right document and.","index":63,"end_time":171.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.19,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah, have a great week.","index":64,"end_time":174.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.79,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"And we will meet in two weeks.","index":65,"end_time":175.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.23,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Correct.","index":66,"end_time":176.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.91,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"We move to every other.","index":67,"end_time":177.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.31,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":178.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.59,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":178.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.15,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"Thank you so much, Bailey, and have a great day.","index":70,"end_time":181.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.67,"speaker_name":"Gil"},{"text":"You too.","index":71,"end_time":182.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll see you.","index":72,"end_time":182.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2025-12-04T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87632173885?pwd=tg6VuBc6ZqpqwnUGjPIACYH5GrE0KC.1","participants":["gil@se