    2281,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1',
    '{"id":"01KAXVD52VKB2V68345E24ZFG6","title":"Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaign and Mailing Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to proceed with a phased mailing campaign using a reduced list to better manage budget and workload (07:36).\n\n- **A 5,000-mailer batch was negotiated for $4,200**, significantly lower than the initial 12,000-mailer plan that risked overwhelming the team and budget (07:36).\n    - Christina explained the phased approach would split mailings across January and March to avoid inundating the smaller branch team.\n    - Victor is developing a tracking method requiring recipients to present the mailer for a bonus, helping control response volume and costs.\n    - The dense urban Manhattan branch market requires a smaller radius for future branch-specific campaigns to improve targeting and reduce overspending.\n    - Equal opportunity laws restrict filtering by income or demographics, limiting targeting options.\n\n- **The postcard design is pending compliance language and final offer details**, with updates made to logos following compliance feedback (06:28).\n    - Christina is coordinating a team meeting before her planned leave to finalize offer tracking and language.\n    - The campaign kickoff is targeted for January to coincide with the new branch opening and avoid holiday season noise.\n    - This timing aligns with improved digital experiences expected from the website launch, enhancing campaign effectiveness (29:22).\n\n## **Product Collateral and Sales Materials**\n\nThe team agreed on developing two key product documents: a laminated two-sided product sheet and a general trifold brochure, with clear timelines and content scope (11:00).\n\n- **The laminated sheet will present retail products on one side and small business/commercial products on the other**, organized by customer lifecycle and target user segments (12:31).\n    - Christina emphasized including product features, benefits, terms, and ideal customer profiles to guide branch staff conversations.\n    - Cash management products are missing from current drafts; Christina plans to provide the cash management brochure to complete content.\n    - Rebecca is revising content, with Christina coordinating document consolidation from retail and net teams.\n    - Delivery of the sales sheet is targeted within the next **four weeks** to align with ongoing website development and brand discovery efforts (14:06).\n\n- **The trifold brochure will provide an overview of PON’s offerings**, intended for broader distribution and team use before year-end.\n    - Design will incorporate new brand icons and color schemes to maintain consistency.\n    - The team will insert placeholders in drafts for verification of target audiences and product details.\n    - PowerPoint templates and other brand collateral will be provided as blank assets initially, with potential future presentations on brand history and timeline (22:07).\n\n## **HubSpot Implementation and Marketing Automation**\n\nHubSpot implementation is progressing with clear next steps on email templates, social media integration, and project planning for marketing automation (18:00).\n\n- **Email templates for PON Bank and PON Bank Direct are to be developed in the new brand style**, with an initial set expected as part of the HubSpot project plan (19:41).\n    - Christina wants these templates ready to demonstrate progress to executives despite data dependency delays.\n    - Social accounts access needs verification; Meta Manager and Google Ads Manager access is partially granted, with additional coordination needed for LinkedIn, Twitter, and Google.\n    - Sprout Social will sunset in April, so HubSpot social listening and posting functions will replace it, supplemented by a low-cost third-party tool for enhanced metrics.\n\n- **Project plans require detailed breakdowns of deliverables and subtasks**, enabling better resource allocation and timeline management (20:58).\n    - Christina is requesting clear timelines to provide teams with sufficient lead time, as initial deadlines caused pushback.\n    - Weekly status updates and use of Pulse will track hours spent versus budget to enable monthly budget adjustments and capacity planning.\n    - The team will align on utilizing Pulse for project visibility, reducing reliance on Asana for project management.\n\n- **Multiple brand flows in HubSpot will be configured** to manage different email streams for PON Bank, PON Bank Direct, investor relations, and foundation communications (25:48).\n    - Brand asset libraries will be created with controlled access for team members like Jane to maintain consistency.\n    - Replication of existing email designs into HubSpot will be reviewed for efficiency.\n\n## **Data Integration and Salesforce Coordination**\n\nThe integration of Salesforce and HubSpot data is a priority to ensure marketing effectiveness and data accuracy, with a phased approach planned (31:00).\n\n- **A meeting with Salesforce team is scheduled to clarify data mapping, masking needs, and phased data migration** (30:48).\n    - Christina stressed the importance of Salesforce as the source of truth, with HubSpot serving marketing-specific data mining.\n    - Data masking may be required due to risk rating reviews, affecting which fields are included in marketing automation.\n    - The website project remains independent of data migration timelines, but email sends and tracking depend heavily on timely data availability.\n    - A batch of test data will be provided early to support development before full migration begins.\n\n- **Timeline clarity is requested to align data migration with marketing activities**, with recommendations on when data must be live in HubSpot (33:24).\n    - Suggested starting dates range from December to February, depending on dependencies.\n    - The team is preparing to discuss sandbox environment availability for testing, critical for safe development cycles.\n\n- **Sandbox environments for HubSpot are under investigation**, with potential constraints due to account tier limitations (35:00).\n    - Christina referenced past use of sandbox accounts, but Colin and Tristan noted that Enterprise tier is required for full sandbox capabilities.\n    - The team will confirm current HubSpot capabilities and pricing tiers to ensure testing needs are met.\n\n## **Budget Management and Resource Planning**\n\nThe team is implementing a more granular monthly budget tracking process to optimize spend and resource use across projects (16:13).\n\n- **Pulse will be used to monitor project hours and budgets**, with weekly status reports to identify unused hours and reallocate resources efficiently (16:13).\n    - Christina will submit new projects with estimated hours and adjust plans based on available capacity.\n    - Options to outsource work, increase hours, or borrow hours from future months will be considered based on status updates.\n    - This approach aims to provide clearer visibility into Creative Retainer usage and inform 2027 budget decisions.\n\n- **Campaign budgets have been adjusted and pushed into the new year**, reflecting product changes and prioritization shifts (28:09).\n    - Christina indicated that a campaign calendar will be developed in early 2024 to coordinate timing with website launch and marketing initiatives.\n    - This delay is expected to improve campaign ROI by leveraging better digital experiences.\n\n## **Brand Assets and Internal Communications**\n\nBrand asset development is underway to support consistent design and messaging across teams and external vendors (22:07).\n\n- **A zip file with icons, illustrations, and templates will be provided**, starting with blank versions for PowerPoint, letterhead, and business cards (22:07).\n    - Christina emphasized the need for a toolkit that teams and third parties can use to maintain brand integrity.\n    - Access to Canva or similar platforms will be arranged for easy asset distribution and updates.\n    - Over time, the team may develop a comprehensive brand presentation covering history, timeline, and messaging.\n\n- **Internal communication and project tracking tools are being aligned**, with a preference for Pulse supplemented by Asana task lists managed by Christina (29:54).\n    - Weekly meetings will include progress updates to avoid missed deadlines and ensure alignment.\n    - Christina requested clear communication on project status to compensate for different tools and workflows used by team members.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Lead List Campaign","Product Sheet","Brand Assets","Salesforce Integration","Pulse Project Management"],"overview":"- **Phased Mailing Strategy:** 5,000-mailer batch set at $4,200, aiming to better manage budget and workload distribution across timelines.  \n- **New Marketing Collaterals:** Two key documents will be developed: a laminated product sheet and a trifold brochure, targeting a four-week delivery timeframe.  \n- **HubSpot Progress:** Email templates in new brand style under development; project plans will enhance resource management and deliverable tracking across teams.  \n- **Salesforce Integration Focus:** Prioritizing accurate data mapping and migration to align marketing effectiveness; early test data batch planned before full migration.  \n- **Budget Management Improvements:** Pulse for tracking hours/budgets, adjusting campaign budgets into 2024 for enhanced ROI linked to website launch.  \n- **Brand Asset Consistency:** Development of design toolkits and internal communication tools to maintain brand integrity and effective project tracking across teams.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide updated product info including cash management brochure for product sheet completion (12:18)\nSubmit detailed subtasks and resource needs for HubSpot and related projects by December 12 (20:58)\nSend remaining social media admin access invites (Meta, LinkedIn, Twitter) to MiD team (27:23)\nOrganize new project requests and budget priorities for monthly status meetings (17:30)\nCoordinate with Victor on tracking integration for mailer campaigns and email system access (07:36)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated mailing list quote reflecting 5,000 mailers for $4,200 for budget review and approval (07:36)\nVerify social media accounts access and confirm setup with Jane and Victor; ensure Meta and LinkedIn access is granted (18:06)\nDeliver proof of concept for two-sided laminated sales sheet and tri-fold brochure draft within 4 weeks (12:18)\nPrepare email templates and workflows in HubSpot per new brand identity and submit for review; replicate previous Constant Contact designs as applicable (18:06)\nProvide a timeline update for brand asset development and Pulse integration in next weekly meeting (30:28)\nCheck availability and feasibility of HubSpot sandbox environment and report back (35:08)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nLead Salesforce meeting preparation with Gabe’s team focusing on data mapping, flow, masking, and phased implementation plan (30:48)\nConfirm and coordinate test data batch delivery to allow HubSpot setup before full migration (34:08)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nVerify and facilitate Meta Manager and Google Ads Manager access to MiD team; review current email template access and permissions (18:06)\n"},"duration":38.02000045776367,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Tristan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Foreign.","index":0,"end_time":179.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina.","index":1,"end_time":191.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":2,"end_time":193.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":3,"end_time":193.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just got back from first vacation I''ve taken in a long time.","index":4,"end_time":197.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, why a long time?","index":5,"end_time":201.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Were they working you to the bone over there?","index":6,"end_time":203.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No, no, never that.","index":7,"end_time":204.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just uh, I don''t know, my mentality is like get all the work done as soon as I can and then time will clear up eventually.","index":8,"end_time":212.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, and then it never does.","index":9,"end_time":213.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh, geez.","index":10,"end_time":214.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":11,"end_time":215.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, listen, I don''t know, I used to have that mentality but now I try, I don''t know, try to take time.","index":12,"end_time":225.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s important.","index":13,"end_time":227.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":227.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a good vacation.","index":15,"end_time":229.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was.","index":16,"end_time":230.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":17,"end_time":230.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We flew down to Florida.","index":18,"end_time":232.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Father in law was getting married so.","index":19,"end_time":235.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got to take our daughter on her first plane ride and everything.","index":20,"end_time":238.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":235.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":21,"end_time":238.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":238.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Unfortunately she got sick, so she got the rest of us sick.","index":22,"end_time":242.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you know, all good.","index":23,"end_time":245.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s always, it''s always like, you know, the little ones.","index":24,"end_time":249.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes, my, my daughter did that when we took my older one.","index":25,"end_time":252.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.61,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we took my older one to Canada, a road trip to see Taylor Swift last November and she ended up getting a pneumonia and Covid all in one, so we had to leave a day early and drive home with that.","index":26,"end_time":268.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Insane.","index":27,"end_time":269.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But yeah, I''m, I couldn''t be proud of this.","index":28,"end_time":272.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She was a real trooper on the plane.","index":29,"end_time":274.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even though she was sick, she like, even the people around us were like, wow.","index":30,"end_time":277.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Never expected her to like be a good baby on the plane.","index":31,"end_time":280.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":277.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How old is she?","index":32,"end_time":281.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"She just turned 10 months.","index":33,"end_time":283.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, so she''s a baby.","index":34,"end_time":285.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Baby.","index":35,"end_time":285.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Oh a so cute.","index":36,"end_time":287.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My daughter''s turning three in a week on December 9th.","index":37,"end_time":292.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I feel like it was just yesterday.","index":38,"end_time":295.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":293.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, she was a beast on the plane coming back from Orlando just recently, so that''s awesome.","index":39,"end_time":301.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I prayed for the people that were behind us.","index":40,"end_time":303.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey, Tristan Eggie.","index":41,"end_time":306.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":42,"end_time":306.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s going on?","index":43,"end_time":307.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":306.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Happy Monday.","index":44,"end_time":308.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":308.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Happy Monday.","index":45,"end_time":310.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, I guess Colin, you''re going to have 100 million emails from me to review so you know, I can give you the 30,000 foot view if you want that now.","index":46,"end_time":325.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, go ahead with that.","index":47,"end_time":327.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.879,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also, I don''t need to share screen.","index":48,"end_time":329.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have an agenda dedicated to the email that you sent over with all of the items to knock out so we can roll through that.","index":49,"end_time":334.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, if you don''t mind getting.","index":50,"end_time":335.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Started with your 30,000 foot view for your end.","index":51,"end_time":337.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":52,"end_time":337.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, well then you might be farther into back to work than I thought, but no, just essentially that''s the, the, the main thing, you know, just closing out some things before the end of the year more just kind of, you know, prep and some Logistical kind of admin, things that would help for.","index":53,"end_time":360.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For the new year, just more also related to some new process that we''re putting into place for.","index":54,"end_time":365.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For PONCE generally and how we work with vendors.","index":55,"end_time":368.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, just continuation of the.","index":56,"end_time":371.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The HubSpot project is really what I kind of want to focus on over the next, you know, rest of the.","index":57,"end_time":377.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":371.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The year.","index":58,"end_time":377.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, yeah, I mean, I guess since you do have the agenda and seems like you read my.","index":59,"end_time":383.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"My emails, maybe I don''t need to give you that much of a review and we could just dive, you know, dive deep in.","index":60,"end_time":388.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":389.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":389.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the postcard we''d sent back.","index":63,"end_time":391.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":389.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I met with Jane.","index":64,"end_time":392.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This might have been two weeks ago.","index":65,"end_time":394.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, or maybe three weeks ago.","index":66,"end_time":396.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was right before we got into.","index":67,"end_time":397.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of the HubSpot series meetings.","index":68,"end_time":399.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":397.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we updated.","index":69,"end_time":400.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":399.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She said Compliance said to make the FDIC and the other logo larger, so we made that update.","index":70,"end_time":406.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other changes, though, were very like, we need language from compliance or we just need to know exactly what the offer is.","index":71,"end_time":412.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":406.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know in your email you said you guys are working on that, so we''re just kind of on standby for that.","index":72,"end_time":415.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":412.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":416.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So the postcards, fine.","index":74,"end_time":418.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I just wanted to make sure that, you know, you had got the edits from compliance.","index":75,"end_time":423.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I guess I had told her, like, hey, rather than, you know, waste time and hours, just, like, wait until you get all the collective information.","index":76,"end_time":431.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because what happened was we met as a team to discuss the offer and just figure out how we''re going to track it.","index":77,"end_time":437.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so that''s why things moved.","index":78,"end_time":438.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s good.","index":79,"end_time":439.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":80,"end_time":440.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll get you more information.","index":81,"end_time":441.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think I''m meeting with the team Wednesday or Thursday of this week that I''m going to be out from the 5th to the 10th.","index":82,"end_time":446.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just a heads up.","index":83,"end_time":447.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":446.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the only thing that I did want to know if you got an update on was the lead list.","index":84,"end_time":455.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":457.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So after your last round of feedback, I had them reduce it.","index":86,"end_time":459.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, like, right when I got the email from them, you said, like.","index":87,"end_time":463.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let''s pause on this.","index":88,"end_time":464.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why I didn''t send it over.","index":89,"end_time":466.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we got them to do 5,000 mailers for $4,200.","index":90,"end_time":470.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s where my question was, just if, if you have a budget in mind, I can get.","index":91,"end_time":474.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can, like, work directly with the.","index":92,"end_time":476.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With them on.","index":93,"end_time":477.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, this is our budget.","index":94,"end_time":478.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, let''s just get as much as.","index":95,"end_time":479.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can in this area with this budget, or if you wanted to approach.","index":96,"end_time":483.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It a Different way.","index":97,"end_time":484.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s a little more manageable.","index":98,"end_time":486.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what I would say is send that over, let me submit that and, and get Betty''s feedback.","index":99,"end_time":492.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What we may do is just purchase them, have them on hand, but maybe, maybe do like a, you know, part A, part B mailing.","index":100,"end_time":500.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because the concern was that we would inundate the team.","index":101,"end_time":506.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s a smaller team.","index":102,"end_time":507.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the other concern was on the financial side that we would bring in too many.","index":103,"end_time":512.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, it''s never a bad thing to bring in too many.","index":104,"end_time":515.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But when you''re thinking about budget for the campaign, every account open would be 300.","index":105,"end_time":520.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But Victor is working on something.","index":106,"end_time":522.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"He''s actually on a call to discuss that now, so he''s not on today, but he''s working on something that would allow us to track the prospect list more efficiently.","index":107,"end_time":533.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we may be able to in the disclaimer say like you have to present this mailer to receive the, the bonus or to be able to qualify.","index":108,"end_time":542.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that would reduce the amount and make the budget like more manageable.","index":109,"end_time":548.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So what we might do is say mail the first, like maybe half in January, mail the first, you know, the second, I mean, the second half in, you know, March or whatever.","index":110,"end_time":558.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that''s okay if, if we approach it that way.","index":111,"end_time":561.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think the original one was like 12,000 or something.","index":112,"end_time":565.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, that, that''s just like a crazy number because that could be upwards of 1200 accounts if we get like the standard 1%.","index":113,"end_time":572.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":114,"end_time":572.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":115,"end_time":574.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":573.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When they''re pulling that half mile radius, I mean there''s a lot of people.","index":116,"end_time":577.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Living right around that location.","index":117,"end_time":579.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":118,"end_time":580.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I forget that because that''s a Manhattan branch.","index":119,"end_time":583.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You''re pulling in the more densely populated areas.","index":120,"end_time":586.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess when we do anything for the branches specifically for next year, we''ll modify the radius depending on if it''s urban or not.","index":121,"end_time":597.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":586.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":122,"end_time":598.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I know we can''t impact any filters with.","index":123,"end_time":600.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":601.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":601.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because it''s equal.","index":125,"end_time":602.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":126,"end_time":602.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can''t, we can''t say like.","index":127,"end_time":603.729,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This income or anything like that.","index":128,"end_time":605.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.729,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right, right.","index":129,"end_time":607.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":605.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then we''re doing good there.","index":130,"end_time":608.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The other thing I think I had on there was the product.","index":131,"end_time":612.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":609.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":614.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So right before I get into that, you had said we''re going to kick this off in January position as a new year special, limited to one to two.","index":133,"end_time":620.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let you know the turnaround time.","index":134,"end_time":622.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was that in reference to this postcard that we already have designed and we''re.","index":135,"end_time":625.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just waiting on feedback or is this a new postcard?","index":136,"end_time":627.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no.","index":137,"end_time":628.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":138,"end_time":628.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s the thing where.","index":139,"end_time":629.559,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''re going to probably kick it off in, in, in, in January.","index":140,"end_time":633.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.559,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":141,"end_time":633.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":142,"end_time":634.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the second.","index":143,"end_time":634.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":144,"end_time":635.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re trying to do it with the new branch and then the system issues.","index":145,"end_time":638.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I said to Betty, I''m like, you know what, I don''t really recommend it around the holidays because like who''s gonna care about, you know, Although maybe an extra $300 to buy gifts would have been a good thing.","index":146,"end_time":650.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But anyway, that''s why we decided to do that.","index":147,"end_time":653.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":148,"end_time":655.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":149,"end_time":656.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the product sheet, this is the latest version that we have.","index":150,"end_time":659.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And when we met a few weeks ago, Christina, you had mentioned that Rebecca was working on something that you''re going to send over regarding this.","index":151,"end_time":665.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just haven''t seen that come over.","index":152,"end_time":667.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to check in on that.","index":153,"end_time":668.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so this is where there''s a thousand things going on.","index":154,"end_time":672.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I.","index":155,"end_time":673.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Essentially what I did was I looked at, when I spoke with retail and the net, I looked at a different document that she provided and so I essentially asked her to do this.","index":156,"end_time":686.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so when I then saw this document, I was like, well that''s kind of the same thing.","index":157,"end_time":690.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then realized you guys had it already.","index":158,"end_time":693.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So apologies on.","index":159,"end_time":695.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"On that.","index":160,"end_time":696.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essentially what we can start is looking at this kind of document as our starting point.","index":161,"end_time":702.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then when the branch gets the brochure, one pager or whatever it is, they could kind of, you know, edit it there.","index":162,"end_time":711.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I did in my summary for the products and services in the HubSpot meeting mentioned, there''s a couple other things and I attached a couple other documents so we can put those in there.","index":163,"end_time":724.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":712.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the only other thing I think is missing from here is some of the cash management stuff.","index":164,"end_time":730.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Not sure if it''s in there.","index":165,"end_time":732.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It may be in the most recent version because they had loans.","index":166,"end_time":737.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Loans are in here.","index":167,"end_time":739.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t think the cash management stuff is in there.","index":168,"end_time":743.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we can probably get you the cash management brochure.","index":169,"end_time":750.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":170,"end_time":751.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that would be everything.","index":171,"end_time":752.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essentially just to recap, again, what we''re looking for is we want a two sided.","index":172,"end_time":757.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we want two things product related.","index":173,"end_time":760.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We want one two sided sheet that could be laminated and used by the branch staff to help them have like a big picture view of everything that we offer.","index":174,"end_time":772.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you think about it, you know, one side is retail, the kind of consumer focus and the other side is, you know, small business, you know, commercial focus.","index":175,"end_time":781.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And it''s, it''s essentially just very general to here, here''s what we offer and here''s maybe kind of the best target person for it.","index":176,"end_time":792.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":781.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like, you know, you might want to say going back to the, the stages and kind of the thinking about the, the website and even the brand discovery.","index":177,"end_time":804.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"When we kind of say like if you''re student, like kind of these things would work for you, right?","index":178,"end_time":811.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.71,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Break it up kind of like almost like a life cycle.","index":179,"end_time":814.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think by having like the product, like features, benefits, like terms and then like who is this best for would be like a good starting point front and back.","index":180,"end_time":828.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the other thing that we want to do is just create a general trifold brochure all about kind of what PON offers.","index":181,"end_time":836.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we could get something to kind of show the teams, you know, before the end of the year on both.","index":182,"end_time":846.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Great.","index":183,"end_time":846.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you need more time for the general brochure, that''s fine.","index":184,"end_time":849.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The sales sheet is something that I would like to see, you know, something within the next four weeks.","index":185,"end_time":855.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But let me know how that kind of pans in with everything.","index":186,"end_time":858.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know obviously working on the, on for the website.","index":187,"end_time":860.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Um, and, and you know, those are the two things there.","index":188,"end_time":864.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I think there was.","index":189,"end_time":865.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Was there one other thing that I had put on the.","index":190,"end_time":867.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Your email just asked for like an update on this.","index":191,"end_time":872.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":868.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":192,"end_time":873.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know we talked about it in a meeting, but it had to be over a month ago.","index":193,"end_time":877.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.98,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know that it was in the works, but I, I couldn''t remember exactly where.","index":194,"end_time":884.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we know.","index":195,"end_time":884.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I was just waiting to see because you, you had mentioned that document like I said from Rebecca.","index":196,"end_time":888.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":884.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if this is or if you have just the one more updated that has the money services.","index":197,"end_time":893.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":888.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Quickly, the, the team.","index":198,"end_time":896.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":199,"end_time":903.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":904.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":903.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so once you send that over, we''ll, we''ll mock this up for, for both designs, you know, the front and back laminated and then the, the trifold.","index":201,"end_time":911.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We might have some placeholders in there that we just ask you to verify.","index":202,"end_time":915.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like who this is exactly for making sure we''re on the same page there.","index":203,"end_time":918.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, yeah, that''s fine.","index":204,"end_time":920.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know, maybe just like design wise you can layer in like a few like of those new icons and some of the new colors and things, you know, very simple and you know, leveraging some of the stuff that that''s here.","index":205,"end_time":932.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":920.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I didn''t even know that she had this document.","index":206,"end_time":935.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like this is my, like that''s what I was asking essentially put together.","index":207,"end_time":939.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":208,"end_time":940.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so there''s a lot going on and I guess I must have missed that.","index":209,"end_time":943.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":940.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But so that''s that.","index":210,"end_time":945.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then was there anything else in my email?","index":211,"end_time":948,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I Couldn''t remember.","index":212,"end_time":948.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I couldn''t remember.","index":213,"end_time":949.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":949.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":215,"end_time":949.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we had 20, 26 planning.","index":216,"end_time":951.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":217,"end_time":952,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Um, so you had, like, weekly status update meetings mid month to assess hours and plans, and then a weekly status report, which I know we have a meeting tomorrow.","index":218,"end_time":961.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":952,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I believe it''s tomorrow to go through.","index":219,"end_time":965.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, no, it''s on Wednesday to go through Pulse.","index":220,"end_time":967.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":965.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Make sure that you guys are familiar with using that, and then we''ll have the updated email sent out of that.","index":221,"end_time":971.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As well to you each week.","index":222,"end_time":972.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":223,"end_time":973.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.28,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just quickly, just to.","index":224,"end_time":975.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.84,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m not sure if you had a time to sync with Tristan, but we talked a little bit about this in the last meeting that we had for the website.","index":225,"end_time":980.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But essentially what we were looking at in Pulse is like, the hours.","index":226,"end_time":985.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But it was a little wonky with how things are categories, so it didn''t look like the hours are being used up.","index":227,"end_time":992.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":985.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so one of the things that we wanted to do was for budget purposes, the we''re putting to a new, like, process to kind of budget monthly and then kind of go back and say, hey, this is actually how much I''m spending.","index":228,"end_time":1006.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is actually how much I''m not.","index":229,"end_time":1008.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1006.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then at the year end for 2027 planning, we''ll have a better idea of do we need to keep the budget the same, increase, decrease, or what have you.","index":230,"end_time":1016.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1008.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So right now, like, everything is staying the same for, you know, for the Creative Retainer, but what we want to start to do is kind of say, okay, for this project, we spent, you know, 10 hours.","index":231,"end_time":1029.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Another reason why I want to do that is because I want to also understand how many more hours we can allocate towards projects that my team is working on right now to free up some space.","index":232,"end_time":1040.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so it''ll be helpful if we could kind of just plan ahead, and then I can let you guys know on these status planning meetings, like, okay, guys, we have 10 more hours.","index":233,"end_time":1050.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Great.","index":234,"end_time":1050.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m going to send you a new project.","index":235,"end_time":1051.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":236,"end_time":1052.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1052.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you have too much, then I can kind of decide, you know, where I need to take stuff back or outsource or maybe even increase your hours, borrow from the next month, whatever it is.","index":237,"end_time":1062.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1052.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":238,"end_time":1063.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":239,"end_time":1064.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll make sense.","index":240,"end_time":1065.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the next thing was HubSpot.","index":241,"end_time":1068.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1067.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"HubSpot''s in a good saying, but we should start working on some email templates.","index":242,"end_time":1071.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One for Ponte bank and one for Ponte Bank Direct, and then the social media.","index":243,"end_time":1077.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1071.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think we just need access or, Jane, we can invite you to HubSpot if you''re already logged into the social accounts and you can connect them.","index":244,"end_time":1082.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1077.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just depends on what, however you guys want to do that.","index":245,"end_time":1084.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think, Jane, I think.","index":246,"end_time":1088.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yep.","index":247,"end_time":1088.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1088.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If I''m not mistaken, I believe access was already granted to you guys because I saw we got something in Meta or in Google.","index":248,"end_time":1097.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So check that for me.","index":249,"end_time":1100.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then it has to, because I think that you guys provided me like a standard email to like add.","index":250,"end_time":1107.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just check on both, on both fronts.","index":251,"end_time":1109.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like if Mid, you guys could check and Jane, if you could check and make sure.","index":252,"end_time":1112.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So they should have access to Facebook and, you know, Instagram through like the Meta Manager and then the Google Ads Manager.","index":253,"end_time":1123.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You might have to just sync with Victor on that one if you can''t give access.","index":254,"end_time":1128.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then Twitter and LinkedIn.","index":255,"end_time":1130.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Essentially what we''re going to do is ask Mid to kind of set up our profile so we can start to do the social listening, identify the posting, you know, structure and all of that.","index":256,"end_time":1145.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1132.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because Sprout Social is going to sunset.","index":257,"end_time":1150.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I believe April was the contract end date.","index":258,"end_time":1153.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.08,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I, I can, I can check.","index":259,"end_time":1154.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so we can start to kind of test how things work.","index":260,"end_time":1157.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Social listening is also a little bit.","index":261,"end_time":1161.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s not as robust as Sprout.","index":262,"end_time":1165.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we just have to get alignment with what we can do in, in HubSpot and then where we need to fill the gap, I think there''s an third party, like, very cheap service that we can integrate in for additional metrics and then use Google and all that.","index":263,"end_time":1181.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s the plan there for email.","index":264,"end_time":1184.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now a lot''s going to happen, you know, in the data calls.","index":265,"end_time":1188.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":266,"end_time":1188.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what I want to start to do is have you guys get in there, start building out new templates in the new brand design so we can at least start to look at them, get things approved, you know, maybe even start to think about some of the email workflows that we would send out.","index":267,"end_time":1205.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you could start to map those out, I would say that''s part of the HubSpot implementation project.","index":268,"end_time":1213.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So include those components for social and email in the, in the project plan.","index":269,"end_time":1218.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so, like set a date when we can expect to see those, because I think that''ll be helpful when I go to Betty and executive management to say, okay, like, I know you''re not really seeing a lot of progress, but progress is being made behind the scenes.","index":270,"end_time":1230.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1218.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We can''t, we just can''t execute anything until we have data in the system.","index":271,"end_time":1234.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1230.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I just don''t want them to feel like we signed this contract in June and it''s six months and like, we''re not doing anything.","index":272,"end_time":1242.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Essentially, like, three months was by design.","index":273,"end_time":1243.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we didn''t want to start until August.","index":274,"end_time":1247.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''s why we had them give us the extra three months.","index":275,"end_time":1249.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was just a contract kind of thing.","index":276,"end_time":1252.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But, yeah, if we could start that and put that into the plan.","index":277,"end_time":1257.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the only other thing that I think is.","index":278,"end_time":1261.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is going to be necessary for the project plan is for you guys to start to break out each of the main categories in the timeline.","index":279,"end_time":1271.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.14,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, like, you know, the one that we showed everybody in the meeting, like, that''s fine, but, like, each, I guess, Deliverable is going to have subtasks, so I need to start to understand what those subtests are so I can determine, like, where my team is needed, where we need.","index":280,"end_time":1287.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.54,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we need other teams.","index":281,"end_time":1289.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I sent an email out with the summary of the meetings, and then I asked everyone to send me something by December 5th.","index":282,"end_time":1299.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1290.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And I gave them.","index":283,"end_time":1300.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think I sent.","index":284,"end_time":1301.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1300.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think Victor sent it out on Tuesday, and we gave them until December 5th.","index":285,"end_time":1305.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that was what, two days?","index":286,"end_time":1307.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1305.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It''s almost like seven working days.","index":287,"end_time":1309.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And everybody barked at me saying, like, it''s not enough time.","index":288,"end_time":1313.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Granted, people were out of the office, so we extended it to the 12th.","index":289,"end_time":1317.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1313.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay.","index":290,"end_time":1318.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But you''ll see, like, I''m gonna get barked at, so, like, where I can give them as much advance notice of any, like, lead time is.","index":291,"end_time":1325.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is.","index":292,"end_time":1325.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is needed.","index":293,"end_time":1327.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally hear you.","index":294,"end_time":1328.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":295,"end_time":1330.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1329.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the other items in the email were just the brand assets, so zip file with icons, illustration samples, PowerPoint templates, letterheads, business cards, all the things like that.","index":296,"end_time":1342.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1330.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is there any content that you had in mind for us to populate this with, or are we set to, like, just do Lorem Ipsum and then.","index":297,"end_time":1349.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1342.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can update, you know, as needed?","index":298,"end_time":1351.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think those are.","index":299,"end_time":1353.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1351.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let me take a step back.","index":300,"end_time":1354.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1353.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So one thing, you know, we have the.","index":301,"end_time":1356.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1354.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The new brand guide that you.","index":302,"end_time":1358.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1356.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You sent that was good.","index":303,"end_time":1359.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1358.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we''re going to start to.","index":304,"end_time":1360.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1359.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To leverage that.","index":305,"end_time":1361.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The.","index":306,"end_time":1361.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1361.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The thing that we need to have a consensus on is, like, how do we translate the brand that you guys helped us put together when we have to send it out to either a third party or design it ourselves.","index":307,"end_time":1377.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1362.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s why I want some of the assets, right?","index":308,"end_time":1381.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we always have, like, a little bit of a toolkit, and we can load those in Canva or give you guys access to Canva and you can load them, whichever one.","index":309,"end_time":1388.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1381.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then most of the templates are going to be blank.","index":310,"end_time":1391.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, like, the PowerPoint template it''s just the raw, like, template at this point.","index":311,"end_time":1396.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1391.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like a title and transition and.","index":312,"end_time":1398.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1399.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Over time, we might say, hey, can you put together a brand like.","index":314,"end_time":1404.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like a brand presentation for us that talks about our history, timeline, all that kind of stuff?","index":315,"end_time":1408.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1404.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Um, but we''re.","index":316,"end_time":1410.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.99,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re doing a.","index":317,"end_time":1411.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A bunch of things right now, so I want to just prioritize getting at least a template so we can start using it.","index":318,"end_time":1417.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1411.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then we''re also working to put together a few, like, updates to our, like, Internet SharePoint site, so we can use some of those, you know, so now that it''s been a.","index":319,"end_time":1428.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"At least a good month since the brand has technically been, like, approved, you know, I''d love to kind of see some of those things.","index":320,"end_time":1435.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, of course.","index":321,"end_time":1437.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll have that timeline for you.","index":322,"end_time":1438.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1437.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In Wednesday''s meeting for those items as well.","index":323,"end_time":1442.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, thank you.","index":324,"end_time":1445.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I appreciate it.","index":325,"end_time":1446.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But that was everything in the list.","index":326,"end_time":1451.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1448.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll get all of that updated and over to you, and I''ll send.","index":327,"end_time":1455.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1451.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You the mailing list, also that quote to review, and then we''ll get moving on.","index":328,"end_time":1460.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, the product sheet and the email templates we do have.","index":329,"end_time":1463.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the email, I think you''re referencing the design that we sent to.","index":330,"end_time":1467.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1464.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Victor to load into.","index":331,"end_time":1468.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I believe it was constant contact.","index":332,"end_time":1470.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that what you''re referring to?","index":333,"end_time":1472.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1474.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":335,"end_time":1474.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you guys did, I think, like a banner head or something like that for constant contact.","index":336,"end_time":1478.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Originally, we were trying to get you system access, and then they said, yeah.","index":337,"end_time":1482.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1479.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We sent over a full HTML file.","index":338,"end_time":1484.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With like, a whole.","index":339,"end_time":1485.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, so I''ll.","index":340,"end_time":1487.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll look at that with.","index":341,"end_time":1488.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"With Victor.","index":342,"end_time":1489.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we may have said, like, hold off on it until we could get you guys regraded so you guys could build it for us.","index":343,"end_time":1495.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1489.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But that.","index":344,"end_time":1496.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s separate from what I''m suggesting and, you know, obviously in the hub spot.","index":345,"end_time":1499.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1496.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I can look at it.","index":346,"end_time":1501.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1499.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe if you just flip it to me, too, because I don''t recall seeing it.","index":347,"end_time":1505.099,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":348,"end_time":1505.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know I was out a bunch, you know, the last couple of weeks, so we didn''t get to sync up on it, but if you could just flip that back to me, I''ll look at it.","index":349,"end_time":1514.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because if we.","index":350,"end_time":1515.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1514.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If it''s good, maybe just replicate it right.","index":351,"end_time":1517.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1515.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For.","index":352,"end_time":1517.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1517.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For that.","index":353,"end_time":1519.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m not sure if we''ll have to put together a separate brand flow for investor relations in the foundation.","index":354,"end_time":1526.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just take a.","index":355,"end_time":1528.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Take that as a mental note for when we''re setting up HubSpot.","index":356,"end_time":1532.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1528.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, there might need to be.","index":357,"end_time":1533.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1532.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think we had in our contract three or four different brand flows.","index":358,"end_time":1540.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1534.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Definitely one for Ponce and Ponce Bank Direct because of the way the emails go out.","index":359,"end_time":1548.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1542.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":360,"end_time":1548.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1548.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like Ponce Bank Direct will be incorporated into the main website.","index":361,"end_time":1553.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I think from an email perspective we''re going to be targeting different people.","index":362,"end_time":1559.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1554.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll just keep that email flow and like any brand assets separate.","index":363,"end_time":1563.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1559.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So even in HubSpot when you set up if there''s like a brand asset library, like can start to give Jane access to that.","index":364,"end_time":1573.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1564.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know.","index":365,"end_time":1576.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know when you guys would be ready to maybe start to share some of those things, but maybe we set like a target meeting date for you guys to like review some of those things and even just bring up HubSpot and show us some of the stuff.","index":366,"end_time":1589.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because my team will probably lean on you guys just to give us like a high level overview of, of some of the HubSpot features.","index":367,"end_time":1597.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1590.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ve used HubSpot before, so I''m pretty good.","index":368,"end_time":1599.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1597.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you know, obviously it''s a new, it''s a new environment so.","index":369,"end_time":1602.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1599.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it sounds good.","index":370,"end_time":1605.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1604.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have to check exactly how many brands are associated with the account, but I know that it was more than.","index":371,"end_time":1609.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1605.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One that we can build.","index":372,"end_time":1610.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1609.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":373,"end_time":1610.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1610.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and then, you know, let me know if, and if we have to kind of figure out which one takes priority then, you know, we will.","index":374,"end_time":1618.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":375,"end_time":1618.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1618.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":376,"end_time":1619.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1618.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll check again on all the social accounts.","index":377,"end_time":1622.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1620.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that when I just checked.","index":378,"end_time":1623.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Quickly we have an invite to Canva.","index":379,"end_time":1628.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Google my business.","index":380,"end_time":1630.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But those are the only ones actually.","index":381,"end_time":1636.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1633.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we got Google Analytics as well, but I didn''t see any social accounts.","index":382,"end_time":1639.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1636.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll go through and re verify that.","index":383,"end_time":1641.579,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1639.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, I just on a quick check, see those.","index":384,"end_time":1643.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1641.579,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":385,"end_time":1644.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I think you are correct.","index":386,"end_time":1646.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We had decided to do it in phases, but yes.","index":387,"end_time":1650.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.1,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, so Jean, so send them the rest of them.","index":388,"end_time":1653.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.9,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So send them the meta and you know, the LinkedIn and all and Twitter and all that.","index":389,"end_time":1658.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1653.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because then they can, you know, while it''s quiet over the next few weeks and then we can figure out kind of the, you know, the posting, the yes.","index":390,"end_time":1667.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Posting strategy or what have you.","index":391,"end_time":1669.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because I''d like to start to get Rebecca trained on that and I think what we talked about was holding off on the, on the Sprout social for her because it was going to change some.","index":392,"end_time":1680.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1669.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":393,"end_time":1683.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything that we didn''t cover today that.","index":394,"end_time":1685.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1684.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys were hoping to talk through?","index":395,"end_time":1686.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1685.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I mean, I think, you know, I think just wrapping up for the.","index":396,"end_time":1693.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You Know, year end, you know, January might be a little bit, you know, a slow start on new stuff because we''re just finishing some of the other things eventually in one of the, you know, maybe closer to the year end.","index":397,"end_time":1706.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1693.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, you guys just, I would, I always like to, to kind of just do a debrief and, you know, get your, you know, feedback.","index":398,"end_time":1713.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If there''s anything else that, you know, maybe we could have did better, you know, either on our side or just collectively as a, as a team, you know, let me know.","index":399,"end_time":1722.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then the one thing we''ll have to talk about earlier in the, in the new year is the campaigns and what we''re doing with that.","index":400,"end_time":1733.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m waiting to see where the budget netted, but I know that the budget needed to be cut and there''s a few things on the product side that were happening.","index":401,"end_time":1743.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I think we pushed our campaign budget up a couple of months into the new year.","index":402,"end_time":1749.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we''ll talk about, about that and then, you know, see how we''re.","index":403,"end_time":1755.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''ll plan out like a campaign calendar for what, for when the, the actual campaign, like for Tina and all that kind of stuff starts with the, and stuff.","index":404,"end_time":1762.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1755.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":405,"end_time":1762.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":406,"end_time":1763.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it might actually work out better because by the time it kicks off, you know, we''ll be closer to like the launch of the website and can drive people to a better, a better digital experience with the campaigns, so.","index":407,"end_time":1777.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1763.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":408,"end_time":1778.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1777.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":409,"end_time":1779.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":410,"end_time":1779.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I will send you the quote on the list.","index":411,"end_time":1782.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll have to get them to send.","index":412,"end_time":1783.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1782.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A new one just because they, in their sales practice, they have them expire very quickly.","index":413,"end_time":1787.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1783.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":414,"end_time":1787.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1787.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I''ll send you.","index":415,"end_time":1789.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, no worries.","index":416,"end_time":1789.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll also send you the email designs to review and see if.","index":417,"end_time":1792.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You just want us to replicate that in HubSpot.","index":418,"end_time":1794.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1792.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":419,"end_time":1795.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then, you know, for the meeting that I requested for, for next year, definitely when we go through Pulse, will, it''ll be more top of mind, but like I said, it''s hard for me sometimes because my project management mindset is in Asana and we don''t use that for here.","index":420,"end_time":1811.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''m going to try to put some of the things in Asana for you guys, but not have you have a license, but just in kind of those meetings.","index":421,"end_time":1819.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1811.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If you could call out like, here''s everything that we have, here''s where it stands, just to like refresh my memory so nothing falls through the cracks, that would be great.","index":422,"end_time":1827.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1819.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":423,"end_time":1828.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1828.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once we go through that, our meeting like this will change to me having.","index":424,"end_time":1832.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1828.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pulse pulled up and we''ll be going through all of those projects so you can see, you know, up to date.","index":425,"end_time":1836.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1832.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think that that will be super helpful.","index":426,"end_time":1838.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":427,"end_time":1839.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, that''s, that''s pretty much it on my side.","index":428,"end_time":1842.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Tristan, was there anything final or anything on the HubSpot that we needed to talk about today?","index":429,"end_time":1847.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":430,"end_time":1848.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1848.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"We have our Salesforce meeting tomorrow with Gabe and his team, so.","index":431,"end_time":1852.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1848.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, excited to go through that.","index":432,"end_time":1854.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1852.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Maybe just your, your thoughts on, on how that runs.","index":433,"end_time":1858.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1855.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"I mean, we were going to come with with obviously some questions on our side, but how did you think, what''s the best way to maybe approach that with Gabe and his team?","index":434,"end_time":1866.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1858.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, with, with him it definitely is.","index":435,"end_time":1869.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1866.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, we sent you guys the, the, the mapping.","index":436,"end_time":1873,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":437,"end_time":1873.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1873,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So the side by side.","index":438,"end_time":1874.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1873.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know how if you guys had had a chance to review that, but definitely kind of giving him an understanding of, of like here''s the recommended approach for like the first round of, you know, kind of required data for us to be successful with what we''re doing, how it kind of translates would be successful.","index":439,"end_time":1894.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1874.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Then we''ll, we''ll have to talk also about some of the, the data masking requirements or some of the things that they would have to do in Mulesoft.","index":440,"end_time":1904.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1894.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So essentially it''s talking through, you know, the flow of data, what you''re seeing so far, what you''re recommending, maybe breaking it out into two phases would be good.","index":441,"end_time":1914.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I''ll mention the review of your risk rating too, that we''re doing that.","index":442,"end_time":1922.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1916.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so, you know, depending obviously where that goes, it''ll determine whether or not we need certain fields masked.","index":443,"end_time":1932.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1923.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I''m probably going to recommend that anyway just because to your point, Salesforce should be like the source of truth.","index":444,"end_time":1939.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1932.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"This is just more marketing data.","index":445,"end_time":1941.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1939.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think you mentioned it in one of the last meetings and I think it was a good, a good way to look at it where it''s like we''re not trying to have, you know, HubSpot be the source of truth, we''re just having it be the source of truth.","index":446,"end_time":1954.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1941.929,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"More for marketing to be able to like data mine essentially.","index":447,"end_time":1957.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1954.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":448,"end_time":1958.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1957.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that''s a good way to kind of make sure they understand.","index":449,"end_time":1962.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1959.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, you know, when we''re setting it up, there''s no confusion around us kind of needing the full social.","index":450,"end_time":1969.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1963.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like we just need to make sure that the system, you know, however they household or, you know, segment the data it matches.","index":451,"end_time":1978.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1970.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we don''t need social in the system for anything, then we don''t need it in the system for anything.","index":452,"end_time":1982.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1978.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I guess it''s those questions explaining to them kind of some of the journeys and some of the things that we want to achieve with the campaigns and the review of the data in the system will help kind of determine the next steps.","index":453,"end_time":1995.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1982.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":454,"end_time":1997.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1995.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll have like a, you know, an agenda to walk through there.","index":455,"end_time":2000.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1997.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"But it will be getting into some of that, that nitty, nitty gritty stuff which.","index":456,"end_time":2004.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2000.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, that, that''s fine.","index":457,"end_time":2005.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2004.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The only thing I didn''t mention was just if you have a timeline where you you know, know in the time overall timeline, like when we need to start having data in the system, like almost build out a recommendation there.","index":458,"end_time":2019.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2005.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because in my mind for us building the website and all that would kind of be be you know, not dependent on the, the data but like obviously sending emails is dependent on data and tracking is depending on data.","index":459,"end_time":2033.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2019.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So you know, if, if you don''t need them to start the data migration until like February, like that''s a good thing for them to know.","index":460,"end_time":2041.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2033.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But if you needed, if you need them to start it, you know, December, like they, they should know that too.","index":461,"end_time":2046.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2041.76,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just look at the overall and.","index":462,"end_time":2048,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.04,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well and the big thing, I mean.","index":463,"end_time":2049.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2048.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Cause the website is like it''s its own separate project for a reason.","index":464,"end_time":2053.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2049.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Right.","index":465,"end_time":2053.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2053.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like a.","index":466,"end_time":2054.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2053.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Completely independent from like the, the actual data and users and marketing automation emails, all that stuff.","index":467,"end_time":2060.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2054.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So yeah, we could talk about that as well.","index":468,"end_time":2062.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2060.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And.","index":469,"end_time":2063.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2062.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And then there''s also Christina like some test data.","index":470,"end_time":2065.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2063.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"You know, there''s probably middle ground.","index":471,"end_time":2067,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2065.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Let''s get a batch of test data like just a CSV file that we can continue to test.","index":472,"end_time":2072.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2067.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"We could probably operate that way for quite a bit of time before.","index":473,"end_time":2077.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2073.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":474,"end_time":2078.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2077.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Real life.","index":475,"end_time":2078.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":476,"end_time":2079.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2078.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that makes sense.","index":477,"end_time":2080.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2079.44,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then I know they''ll ask but the sandbox, they had asked for a sandbox so we can build a sandbox environment in HubSpot.","index":478,"end_time":2089.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2080.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you can help with that or how that for.","index":479,"end_time":2093.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2089.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The website or for both.","index":480,"end_time":2095.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2093.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they like to do things in like dev mode.","index":481,"end_time":2099.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2096.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s not unfortunately HubSpot doesn''t really have that.","index":482,"end_time":2101.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2099.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It''s either published or not.","index":483,"end_time":2103.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2102.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"There''s not really a sandbox environment that we can, we can operate with.","index":484,"end_time":2108.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2103.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"They do.","index":485,"end_time":2109.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2108.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on one second.","index":486,"end_time":2110.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2109.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on because I did it.","index":487,"end_time":2122.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2119.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":488,"end_time":2127.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2126.86,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a super admins can create standard sandbox account to test functionalities with impacting on your main account.","index":489,"end_time":2134.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2128.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Let me send this to you because I don''t Know if it''s maybe something that changed recently, but I know I did, I did something similar to.","index":490,"end_time":2144.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2136.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":491,"end_time":2145.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2145.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''m trying to like, send this to you in teams.","index":492,"end_time":2147.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2146.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"One second, hold on.","index":493,"end_time":2148.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2147.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, so just, just check on that for me because I, I, I know.","index":494,"end_time":2158.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2153.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That was something that they, there is.","index":495,"end_time":2160.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2158.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a separate Pete, but that only comes with Enterprise, which, yeah, so that''s with Enterprise.","index":496,"end_time":2167.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2160.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":497,"end_time":2168.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2168.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Because they know, they know that we needed a sandbox.","index":498,"end_time":2173.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2169.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t, I don''t know what, what.","index":499,"end_time":2177.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2176.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What is our, yeah, let''s check with that.","index":500,"end_time":2181.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2177.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically, it''s not.","index":501,"end_time":2182.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2181.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"All right, we''ll, we''ll look into that.","index":502,"end_time":2184.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2183.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, just, just look for me.","index":503,"end_time":2187.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2185.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''ll check into that and I''ll follow up on it.","index":504,"end_time":2195.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2191.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and if we need to get like regular, like the regular HubSpot or I''m saying the regular Colin.","index":505,"end_time":2201.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2195.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"How funny am I?","index":506,"end_time":2202.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2201.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, well.","index":507,"end_time":2203.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2202.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And honestly, Christina, Christina, HubSpot''s pricing and tiers change constantly.","index":508,"end_time":2208.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2203.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"So we, we could be wrong with that as well.","index":509,"end_time":2211.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2208.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"And like I''m saying, I could have, I could.","index":510,"end_time":2213.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2212.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, the last time I, I worked with HubSpot was what, two and a half years ago, so who knows?","index":511,"end_time":2219.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2213.73,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, their pricing is probably the most complex software pricing we''ve ever seen.","index":512,"end_time":2224.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2219.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"It literally changes all the time.","index":513,"end_time":2226.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2224.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":514,"end_time":2226.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2226.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, hopefully, hopefully it has it, but I''d be very surprised if, if it doesn''t because it''s a, it''s a, it''s one of the main pain points that we described to them when we were going through our, like, contract or pre, pre contract kind of requirements because we said we have a hard time with edits in the queue having to be removed in order for us to publish things.","index":515,"end_time":2259.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2227.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So, like, we wanted something that was totally, you know, separate for testing and stuff.","index":516,"end_time":2264.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2259.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So just check on that and let me know because that''s, I think that''s one of the questions they''re going to come up with tomorrow.","index":517,"end_time":2268.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2264.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right, all right, cool.","index":518,"end_time":2270.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2269.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll do.","index":519,"end_time":2270.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2270.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan"},{"text":"All right, thanks.","index":520,"end_time":2271.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2270.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Thank you guys so much for your time.","index":521,"end_time":2272.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2271.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to see you.","index":522,"end_time":2273.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2272.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":523,"end_time":2273.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2273.35,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"}],"dateString":"2025-12-01T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85439302813?pwd=qMBHtkNo4lURIrnTCVFhLG0k15ZQca.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,jane.trachet@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,victor.garcia@poncebank.net,rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,christina.zanca@poncebank.net","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","jane.trachet@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net","rebecca.cruz@poncebank.net","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","christina.zanca@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KAXVD52VKB2V68345E24ZFG6","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed updated postcard design is pending final offer details from compliance team by Thursday’s meeting.","Agreed to split mailing campaign into January and March phases to manage team and budget load.","Assigned Mid to begin producing HubSpot email and social templates using refreshed brand design by year-end.","Decided to prioritize laminated sales sheet within four weeks and defer general brochure if needed.","Outlined plan to audit and allocate creative hours using Pulse weekly reports starting in mid-December."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Progress is being made behind the scenes... we just can’t execute anything until we have data in the system.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"The sales sheet is something that I would like to see... within the next four weeks.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"We’ll mock this up for... both designs, you know, the front and back laminated and then the trifold.","speaker":"colincostigan"}],"topics":["delivery","budget","launch","process","branding"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-05T18:37:21Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaign and Mailing Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to proceed with a phased mailing campaign using a reduced list to better manage budget and workload (07:36).\n\n- **A 5,000-mailer batch was negotiated for $4,200**, significantly lower than the initial 12,000-mailer plan that risked overwhelming the team and budget (07:36).\n    - Christina explained the phased approach would split mailings across January and March to avoid inundating the smaller branch team.\n    - Victor is developing a tracking method requiring recipients to present the mailer for a bonus, helping control response volume and costs.\n    - The dense urban Manhattan branch market requires a smaller radius for future branch-specific campaigns to improve targeting and reduce overspending.\n    - Equal opportunity laws restrict filtering by income or demographics, limiting targeting options.\n\n- **The postcard design is pending compliance language and final offer details**, with updates made to logos following compliance feedback (06:28).\n    - Christina is coordinating a team meeting before her planned leave to finalize offer tracking and language.\n    - The campaign kickoff is targeted for January to coincide with the new branch opening and avoid holiday season noise.\n    - This timing aligns with improved digital experiences expected from the website launch, enhancing campaign effectiveness (29:22).\n\n## **Product Collateral and Sales Materials**\n\nThe team agreed on developing two key product documents: a laminated two-sided product sheet and a general trifold brochure, with clear timelines and content scope (11:00).\n\n- **The laminated sheet will present retail products on one side and small business/commercial products on the other**, organized by customer lifecycle and target user segments (12:31).\n    - Christina emphasized including product features, benefits, terms, and ideal customer profiles to guide branch staff conversations.\n    - Cash management products are missing from current drafts; Christina plans to provide the cash management brochure to complete content.\n    - Rebecca is revising content, with Christina coordinating document consolidation from retail and net teams.\n    - Delivery of the sales sheet is targeted within the next **four weeks** to align with ongoing website development and brand discovery efforts (14:06).\n\n- **The trifold brochure will provide an overview of PON’s offerings**, intended for broader distribution and team use before year-end.\n    - Design will incorporate new brand icons and color schemes to maintain consistency.\n    - The team will insert placeholders in drafts for verification of target audiences and product details.\n    - PowerPoint templates and other brand collateral will be provided as blank assets initially, with potential future presentations on brand history and timeline (22:07).\n\n## **HubSpot Implementation and Marketing Automation**\n\nHubSpot implementation is progressing with clear next steps on email templates, social media integration, and project planning for marketing automation (18:00).\n\n- **Email templates for PON Bank and PON Bank Direct are to be developed in the new brand style**, with an initial set expected as part of the HubSpot project plan (19:41).\n    - Christina wants these templates ready to demonstrate progress to executives despite data dependency delays.\n    - Social accounts access needs verification; Meta Manager and Google Ads Manager access is partially granted, with additional coordination needed for LinkedIn, Twitter, and Google.\n    - Sprout Social will sunset in April, so HubSpot social listening and posting functions will replace it, supplemented by a low-cost third-party tool for enhanced metrics.\n\n- **Project plans require detailed breakdowns of deliverables and subtasks**, enabling better resource allocation and timeline management (20:58).\n    - Christina is requesting clear timelines to provide teams with sufficient lead time, as initial deadlines caused pushback.\n    - Weekly status updates and use of Pulse will track hours spent versus budget to enable monthly budget adjustments and capacity planning.\n    - The team will align on utilizing Pulse for project visibility, reducing reliance on Asana for project management.\n\n- **Multiple brand flows in HubSpot will be configured** to manage different email streams for PON Bank, PON Bank Direct, investor relations, and foundation communications (25:48).\n    - Brand asset libraries will be created with controlled access for team members like Jane to maintain consistency.\n    - Replication of existing email designs into HubSpot will be reviewed for efficiency.\n\n## **Data Integration and Salesforce Coordination**\n\nThe integration of Salesforce and HubSpot data is a priority to ensure marketing effectiveness and data accuracy, with a phased approach planned (31:00).\n\n- **A meeting with Salesforce team is scheduled to clarify data mapping, masking needs, and phased data migration** (30:48).\n    - Christina stressed the importance of Salesforce as the source of truth, with HubSpot serving marketing-specific data mining.\n    - Data masking may be required due to risk rating reviews, affecting which fields are included in marketing automation.\n    - The website project remains independent of data migration timelines, but email sends and tracking depend heavily on timely data availability.\n    - A batch of test data will be provided early to support development before full migration begins.\n\n- **Timeline clarity is requested to align data migration with marketing activities**, with recommendations on when data must be live in HubSpot (33:24).\n    - Suggested starting dates range from December to February, depending on dependencies.\n    - The team is preparing to discuss sandbox environment availability for testing, critical for safe development cycles.\n\n- **Sandbox environments for HubSpot are under investigation**, with potential constraints due to account tier limitations (35:00).\n    - Christina referenced past use of sandbox accounts, but Colin and Tristan noted that Enterprise tier is required for full sandbox capabilities.\n    - The team will confirm current HubSpot capabilities and pricing tiers to ensure testing needs are met.\n\n## **Budget Management and Resource Planning**\n\nThe team is implementing a more granular monthly budget tracking process to optimize spend and resource use across projects (16:13).\n\n- **Pulse will be used to monitor project hours and budgets**, with weekly status reports to identify unused hours and reallocate resources efficiently (16:13).\n    - Christina will submit new projects with estimated hours and adjust plans based on available capacity.\n    - Options to outsource work, increase hours, or borrow hours from future months will be considered based on status updates.\n    - This approach aims to provide clearer visibility into Creative Retainer usage and inform 2027 budget decisions.\n\n- **Campaign budgets have been adjusted and pushed into the new year**, reflecting product changes and prioritization shifts (28:09).\n    - Christina indicated that a campaign calendar will be developed in early 2024 to coordinate timing with website launch and marketing initiatives.\n    - This delay is expected to improve campaign ROI by leveraging better digital experiences.\n\n## **Brand Assets and Internal Communications**\n\nBrand asset development is underway to support consistent design and messaging across teams and external vendors (22:07).\n\n- **A zip file with icons, illustrations, and templates will be provided**, starting with blank versions for PowerPoint, letterhead, and business cards (22:07).\n    - Christina emphasized the need for a toolkit that teams and third parties can use to maintain brand integrity.\n    - Access to Canva or similar platforms will be arranged for easy asset distribution and updates.\n    - Over time, the team may develop a comprehensive brand presentation covering history, timeline, and messaging.\n\n- **Internal communication and project tracking tools are being aligned**, with a preference for Pulse supplemented by Asana task lists managed by Christina (29:54).\n    - Weekly meetings will include progress updates to avoid missed deadlines and ensure alignment.\n    - Christina requested clear communication on project status to compensate for different tools and workflows used by team members.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot","Lead List Campaign","Product Sheet","Brand Assets","Salesforce Integration","Pulse Project Management"],"overview":"- **Phased Mailing Strategy:** 5,000-mailer batch set at $4,200, aiming to better manage budget and workload distribution across timelines.  \n- **New Marketing Collaterals:** Two key documents will be developed: a laminated product sheet and a trifold brochure, targeting a four-week delivery timeframe.  \n- **HubSpot Progress:** Email templates in new brand style under development; project plans will enhance resource management and deliverable tracking across teams.  \n- **Salesforce Integration Focus:** Prioritizing accurate data mapping and migration to align marketing effectiveness; early test data batch planned before full migration.  \n- **Budget Management Improvements:** Pulse for tracking hours/budgets, adjusting campaign budgets into 2024 for enhanced ROI linked to website launch.  \n- **Brand Asset Consistency:** Development of design toolkits and internal communication tools to maintain brand integrity and effective project tracking across teams.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nProvide updated product info including cash management brochure for product sheet completion (12:18)\nSubmit detailed subtasks and resource needs for HubSpot and related projects by December 12 (20:58)\nSend remaining social media admin access invites (Meta, LinkedIn, Twitter) to MiD team (27:23)\nOrganize new project requests and budget priorities for monthly status meetings (17:30)\nCoordinate with Victor on tracking integration for mailer campaigns and email system access (07:36)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated mailing list quote reflecting 5,000 mailers for $4,200 for budget review and approval (07:36)\nVerify social media accounts access and confirm setup with Jane and Victor; ensure Meta and LinkedIn access is granted (18:06)\nDeliver proof of concept for two-sided laminated sales sheet and tri-fold brochure draft within 4 weeks (12:18)\nPrepare email templates and workflows in HubSpot per new brand identity and submit for review; replicate previous Constant Contact designs as applicable (18:06)\nProvide a timeline update for brand asset development and Pulse integration in next weekly meeting (30:28)\nCheck availability and feasibility of HubSpot sandbox environment and report back (35:08)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nLead Salesforce meeting preparation with Gabe’s team focusing on data mapping, flow, masking, and phased implementation plan (30:48)\nConfirm and coordinate test data batch delivery to allow HubSpot setup before full migration (34:08)\n\n**Jane Trachet**\nVerify and facilitate Meta Manager and Google Ads Manager access to MiD team; review current email template access and permissions (18:06)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"7f8afa72-73a1-4439-857e-4b8f2aa6a119","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
