INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Ponce Bank & MiD: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Marketing Campaign and Mailing Strategy**

The team decided to proceed with a phased mailing campaign using a reduced list to better manage budget and workload (07:36).

- **A 5,000-mailer batch was negotiated for $4,200**, significantly lower than the initial 12,000-mailer plan that risked overwhelming the team and budget (07:36).
    - Christina explained the phased approach would split mailings across January and March to avoid inundating the smaller branch team.
    - Victor is developing a tracking method requiring recipients to present the mailer for a bonus, helping control response volume and costs.
    - The dense urban Manhattan branch market requires a smaller radius for future branch-specific campaigns to improve targeting and reduce overspending.
    - Equal opportunity laws restrict filtering by income or demographics, limiting targeting options.

- **The postcard design is pending compliance language and final offer details**, with updates made to logos following compliance feedback (06:28).
    - Christina is coordinating a team meeting before her planned leave to finalize offer tracking and language.
    - The campaign kickoff is targeted for January to coincide with the new branch opening and avoid holiday season noise.
    - This timing aligns with improved digital experiences expected from the website launch, enhancing campaign effectiveness (29:22).

## **Product Collateral and Sales Materials**

The team agreed on developing two key product documents: a laminated two-sided product sheet and a general trifold brochure, with clear timelines and content scope (11:00).

- **The laminated sheet will present retail products on one side and small business/commercial products on the other**, organized by customer lifecycle and target user segments (12:31).
    - Christina emphasized including product features, benefits, terms, and ideal customer profiles to guide branch staff conversations.
    - Cash management products are missing from current drafts; Christina plans to provide the cash management brochure to complete content.
    - Rebecca is revising content, with Christina coordinating document consolidation from retail and net teams.
    - Delivery of the sales sheet is targeted within the next **four weeks** to align with ongoing website development and brand discovery efforts (14:06).

- **The trifold brochure will provide an overview of PON’s offerings**, intended for broader distribution and team use before year-end.
    - Design will incorporate new brand icons and color schemes to maintain consistency.
    - The team will insert placeholders in drafts for verification of target audiences and product details.
    - PowerPoint templates and other brand collateral will be provided as blank assets initially, with potential future presentations on brand history and timeline (22:07).

## **HubSpot Implementation and Marketing Automation**

HubSpot implementation is progressing with clear next steps on email templates, social media integration, and project planning for marketing automation (18:00).

- **Email templates for PON Bank and PON Bank Direct are to be developed in the new brand style**, with an initial set expected as part of the HubSpot project plan (19:41).
    - Christina wants these templates ready to demonstrate progress to executives despite data dependency delays.
    - Social accounts access needs verification; Meta Manager and Google Ads Manager access is partially granted, with additional coordination needed for LinkedIn, Twitter, and Google.
    - Sprout Social will sunset in April, so HubSpot social listening and posting functions will replace it, supplemented by a low-cost third-party tool for enhanced metrics.

- **Project plans require detailed breakdowns of deliverables and subtasks**, enabling better resource allocation and timeline management (20:58).
    - Christina is requesting clear timelines to provide teams with sufficient lead time, as initial deadlines caused pushback.
    - Weekly status updates and use of Pulse will track hours spent versus budget to enable monthly budget adjustments and capacity planning.
    - The team will align on utilizing Pulse for project visibility, reducing reliance on Asana for project management.

- **Multiple brand flows in HubSpot will be configured** to manage different email streams for PON Bank, PON Bank Direct, investor relations, and foundation communications (25:48).
    - Brand asset libraries will be created with controlled access for team members like Jane to maintain consistency.
    - Replication of existing email designs into HubSpot will be reviewed for efficiency.

## **Data Integration and Salesforce Coordination**

The integration of Salesforce and HubSpot data is a priority to ensure marketing effectiveness and data accuracy, with a phased approach planned (31:00).

- **A meeting with Salesforce team is scheduled to clarify data mapping, masking needs, and phased data migration** (30:48).
    - Christina stressed the importance of Salesforce as the source of truth, with HubSpot serving marketing-specific data mining.
    - Data masking may be required due to risk rating reviews, affecting which fields are included in marketing automation.
    - The website project remains independent of data migration timelines, but email sends and tracking depend heavily on timely data availability.
    - A batch of test data will be provided early to support development before full migration begins.

- **Timeline clarity is requested to align data migration with marketing activities**, with recommendations on when data must be live in HubSpot (33:24).
    - Suggested starting dates range from December to February, depending on dependencies.
    - The team is preparing to discuss sandbox environment availability for testing, critical for safe development cycles.

- **Sandbox environments for HubSpot are under investigation**, with potential constraints due to account tier limitations (35:00).
    - Christina referenced past use of sandbox accounts, but Colin and Tristan noted that Enterprise tier is required for full sandbox capabilities.
    - The team will confirm current HubSpot capabilities and pricing tiers to ensure testing needs are met.

## **Budget Management and Resource Planning**

The team is implementing a more granular monthly budget tracking process to optimize spend and resource use across projects (16:13).

- **Pulse will be used to monitor project hours and budgets**, with weekly status reports to identify unused hours and reallocate resources efficiently (16:13).
    - Christina will submit new projects with estimated hours and adjust plans based on available capacity.
    - Options to outsource work, increase hours, or borrow hours from future months will be considered based on status updates.
    - This approach aims to provide clearer visibility into Creative Retainer usage and inform 2027 budget decisions.

- **Campaign budgets have been adjusted and pushed into the new year**, reflecting product changes and prioritization shifts (28:09).
    - Christina indicated that a campaign calendar will be developed in early 2024 to coordinate timing with website launch and marketing initiatives.
    - This delay is expected to improve campaign ROI by leveraging better digital experiences.

## **Brand Assets and Internal Communications**

Brand asset development is underway to support consistent design and messaging across teams and external vendors (22:07).

- **A zip file with icons, illustrations, and templates will be provided**, starting with blank versions for PowerPoint, letterhead, and business cards (22:07).
    - Christina emphasized the need for a toolkit that teams and third parties can use to maintain brand integrity.
    - Access to Canva or similar platforms will be arranged for easy asset distribution and updates.
    - Over time, the team may develop a comprehensive brand presentation covering history, timeline, and messaging.

- **Internal communication and project tracking tools are being aligned**, with a preference for Pulse supplemented by Asana task lists managed by Christina (29:54).
    - Weekly meetings will include progress updates to avoid missed deadlines and ensure alignment.
    - Christina requested clear communication on project status to compensate for different tools and workflows used by team members.',
  '2025-12-01 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide updated product info including cash management brochure for product sheet completion (12:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Submit detailed subtasks and resource needs for HubSpot and related projects by December 12 (20:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Send remaining social media admin access invites (Meta, LinkedIn, Twitter) to MiD team (27:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Organize new project requests and budget priorities for monthly status meetings (17:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Victor on tracking integration for mailer campaigns and email system access (07:36)","completed":false},{"text":"Send updated mailing list quote reflecting 5,000 mailers for $4,200 for budget review and approval (07:36)","completed":false},{"text":"Verify social media accounts access and confirm setup with Jane and Victor; ensure Meta and LinkedIn access is granted (18:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Deliver proof of concept for two-sided laminated sales sheet and tri-fold brochure draft within 4 weeks (12:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare email templates and workflows in HubSpot per new brand identity and submit for review; replicate previous Constant Contact designs as applicable (18:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide a timeline update for brand asset development and Pulse integration in next weekly meeting (30:28)","completed":false},{"text":"Check availability and feasibility of HubSpot sandbox environment and report back (35:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Lead Salesforce meeting preparation with Gabe’s team focusing on data mapping, flow, masking, and phased implementation plan (30:48)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm and coordinate test data batch delivery to allow HubSpot setup before full migration (34:08)","completed":false},{"text":"Verify and facilitate Meta Manager and Google Ads Manager access to MiD team; review current email template access and permissions (18:06)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
