-- Meeting: GSS // MID Weekly Meeting (2025-12-03 16:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6061d0c2-de11-40b9-8824-1ccd80a970d6',
    '2025-12-03 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KB0JHA44REY2GMXE4T4V2KQM',
    'GSS // MID Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Nick S (GSS)","Baylee Gunnell","Will Fleming","Guille Santana"}'::text[],
    1231,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1',
    '{"id":"01KB0JHA44REY2GMXE4T4V2KQM","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Development and Publishing**\n\nThe content team has completed key deliverables and is preparing new material to boost engagement and support sales efforts.\n\n- **The blog post titled “Building a Finance Function at Every Stage” is finalized and ready to publish** following Will Fleming''s review, ensuring alignment with business messaging and client education goals (02:38).  \n    - The post resulted from a strong interview and received positive internal feedback validating its quality.  \n    - This content will serve as a cornerstone for ongoing marketing and thought leadership efforts.  \n    - The team plans to distribute the blog widely, including through Carrie’s channels, to drive targeted traffic and lead generation.  \n    - This approach supports nurturing prospects with valuable insights tied directly to client needs and market positioning.\n\n- **SEO optimization for the accounting services landing page is complete and live on the development site** after Will’s review, ready for final launch (03:12).  \n    - This update is expected to improve organic search visibility and generate higher-quality inbound leads.  \n    - Next week’s content will include a blog based on the podcast episode featuring Karimaue, scheduled to maintain momentum with fresh, relevant material (03:12).  \n    - Sharing this content through internal and partner networks is advised to maximize reach and traffic impact.  \n    - These ongoing content efforts aim to build credibility and continuously engage prospective clients.\n\n## **Email and LinkedIn Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to overhaul the outreach messaging to improve engagement rates by making it more concise, timely, and action-driven.\n\n- **Nick S proposed a shift to shorter, more direct email sequences focused on sparking immediate responses, rather than lengthy informational messages** that prospects skim and delete (04:02).  \n    - His example of successfully engaging a Papa John''s franchisee by sending a brief, relevant LinkedIn connection message shows the power of personalized, sharp outreach.  \n    - Nick emphasized the need for subject lines and body copy that highlight specific client successes, such as “how a GSS client added $2 million in EBITDA,” to immediately grab attention (08:31).  \n    - The goal is to prompt prospects to reply with interest rather than passively consume content, accelerating the move to phone conversations.  \n    - This approach reflects Nick’s consistent prospecting style that values authenticity and trust over scripted sales pitches.\n\n- **Will Fleming supported trimming the sequences and focusing on credibility and results first, then brief follow-ups, deferring to Nick’s expertise on prospect engagement** (12:03).  \n    - They agreed on refining the sequence to **three to four messages**, balancing persistence with respect for prospect attention spans (14:33).  \n    - Nick will draft revised subject lines and content today or early tomorrow for rapid review and deployment (16:28).  \n    - The marketing team will continue handling list curation and campaign execution, while Nick focuses on messaging tone and calls to action (13:14).  \n    - This new test aims to increase response rates from lukewarm leads, leveraging targeted research and personalized outreach.\n\n## **Campaign Performance and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is monitoring campaign engagement and preparing to launch the next phase with refreshed content and target lists.\n\n- **Recent campaign results were steady but slowed due to the holiday period and exhaustion of the initial prospect list, prompting a need for new outreach efforts soon** (18:20).  \n    - Baylee Gunnell noted low activity consistent with seasonal trends, signaling urgency to start the next campaign cycle.  \n    - Nick confirmed the updated prospect list is ready for a new campaign once the revised content is approved and deployed (15:05).  \n    - The plan is to avoid resending to the exhausted list and instead focus on fresh targets to maintain efficiency and avoid over-contacting prospects (14:59).  \n    - This cycle approach aligns with prospect behavior trends, where typically 5 to 7 touches are needed for engagement, now dropping closer to 5 due to mobile responsiveness (14:58).\n\n- **The team aims for a quick turnaround on content approval to launch the next campaign by early next week, ensuring continuity in lead generation efforts** (18:58).  \n    - Baylee and Will will coordinate with the marketing team’s availability to confirm launch timing and monitor post-launch issues proactively.  \n    - Any website or campaign glitches will be addressed swiftly to minimize disruption to lead flow.  \n    - Maintaining campaign momentum through timely iteration and quick fixes is a key operational priority.  \n    - This readiness reflects the team’s commitment to sustaining pipeline health despite external seasonality.\n\n## **Website and Client Portal Updates**\n\nThe website is near launch readiness, and the client portal is actively managed to support ongoing content delivery and client engagement.\n\n- **The new website has undergone review with minimal comments and is expected to launch imminently, pending team availability, with Baylee anticipating potential minor post-launch fixes** (18:49).  \n    - Will confirmed only a single blog comment remains outstanding, indicating strong overall site readiness.  \n    - The team is prepared to quickly resolve any technical issues that arise after launch to maintain a seamless user experience.  \n    - This site upgrade is designed to enhance user navigation and better showcase service offerings, supporting lead conversion.  \n    - The website update also integrates with content marketing and outreach strategies for a unified front.\n\n- **The client portal is actively updated with recent content and points available for additional services, offering flexibility to scale marketing efforts as needed** (20:00).  \n    - Baylee highlighted unused points that can fund extra blog posts or other content initiatives to expand reach.  \n    - The portal provides transparency and real-time tracking of content progress, facilitating collaboration between teams.  \n    - This platform supports agile content planning and resource allocation aligned with business priorities.  \n    - Will and Nick were encouraged to propose any new content needs to capitalize on available resources.\n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Team Roles**\n\nClear role delineation and collaboration frameworks are set to optimize campaign success and messaging authenticity.\n\n- **Nick emphasized his focus on crafting authentic, personalized messaging that matches his prospecting style, while relying on the marketing team for list management and campaign execution** (13:14).  \n    - This division leverages each party’s strengths, combining Nick’s frontline sales experience with the team’s technical and creative support.  \n    - Nick’s approach aims to build trust through consistency and brevity in outreach, enhancing prospect engagement.  \n    - Will supports this model, reinforcing the importance of credibility and brevity in sales messaging from leadership perspective.  \n    - This alignment ensures messaging stays true to the brand while benefiting from data-driven list targeting and operational support.\n\n- **The team agreed on a feedback loop and rapid iteration cycle, with Nick delivering revised sequences quickly for review and testing** (16:28).  \n    - This fast feedback ensures campaigns stay relevant and adapt to prospect responses and market shifts.  \n    - Baylee expressed enthusiasm for testing Nick’s proven methods across industries, showing openness to optimized workflows.  \n    - The collaborative approach reflects a culture of continuous improvement grounded in frontline insights.  \n    - This dynamic setup is expected to improve overall campaign effectiveness and pipeline development.","outline":null,"keywords":["email sequence","prospect engagement","content updates","SEO optimization","campaign strategy","client portal"],"overview":"- **Content Development:** New blog post “Building a Finance Function at Every Stage” finalized for publication, supporting engagement and sales.  \n- **SEO Updates:** Accounting services landing page is optimized to boost organic search and inbound leads, set for launch.  \n- **Outreach Strategy:** Email sequences to be shorter and focused on urgent responses, using client successes for better engagement.  \n- **Campaign Performance:** Slow activity noted; new prospect list ready for campaign launch by early next week to sustain lead generation.  \n- **Website Progress:** New website nearing launch; client portal updated with content, ready to support marketing efforts flexibly.  \n- **Team Collaboration:** Roles clarified for better campaign success, emphasizing personalized messaging backed by marketing team support for execution.","action_items":"\n**Nicholas Stauff**\nDraft and revise the email messaging sequence incorporating shorter, direct, conversational style with clear calls-to-action. Submit for team review by later today or early next morning (16:50)\nCollaborate with marketing team for list curation and campaign launches, focusing on targeted messaging and maintaining authentic persona in outreach (13:30)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nShare the scheduled blog post from the podcast with Carrie for distribution to generate traffic (03:47)\nCoordinate with the team to check availability and plan for website launch tomorrow or early next week, managing fixes post-launch as needed (18:55)\nPrepare to launch a new email campaign upon receiving Nick’s revised content and finalize campaign slot (18:20)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nContinue content development including upcoming blog post based on podcast and past projects, supporting team with content production and SEO enhancements (02:40)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nReview and provide feedback on blog and updated content as needed (18:45)\n"},"duration":20.510000228881836,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Will Fleming"},{"id":3,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Little Internet latency issue.","index":0,"end_time":3.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2.16,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I keep getting a note saying, yeah, it''s no big deal.","index":1,"end_time":7.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.88,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s just saying, like, I don''t know.","index":2,"end_time":11.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":7.08,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It keeps giving me warnings.","index":3,"end_time":13.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.68,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So I''m just gonna stay off of video today.","index":4,"end_time":14.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.08,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Fair enough.","index":5,"end_time":16.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Always frustrating, though.","index":6,"end_time":19.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":20.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.76,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I can see you just fine, though.","index":8,"end_time":21.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.28,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So that''s good.","index":9,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":10,"end_time":23.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":23.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":24.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.16,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How was your Thanksgiving?","index":12,"end_time":26.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was.","index":13,"end_time":29.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It was a little different.","index":14,"end_time":31.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We had a nice family get together, but then we got snowed in here.","index":15,"end_time":37.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":31.87,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We got, like, 10 inches of snow over the weekend.","index":16,"end_time":39.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":37.31,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Wow.","index":17,"end_time":40.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":40.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":18,"end_time":42.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So we had a weekend full of activities all canceled, and, you know, church got canceled, and then basketball games got canceled, and we''re like, what do we do?","index":19,"end_time":53.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.43,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And, oh, boy, when you got a, you know, family of four and the walls cave in pretty fast on you.","index":20,"end_time":60.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So.","index":21,"end_time":61.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.05,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, that changes things a lot.","index":22,"end_time":63.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":61.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":64.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.41,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I mean, we got to do some sledding and.","index":24,"end_time":67.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.21,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, all that stuff.","index":25,"end_time":68.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But you''re like, all right, we gotta get out of the house.","index":26,"end_time":70.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.33,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":27,"end_time":71.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":71.37,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Very, very different activities.","index":28,"end_time":74.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":75.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":75.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":76.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.01,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How was yours?","index":31,"end_time":77.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.41,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, it was great.","index":32,"end_time":78.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We got some snow too, but not.","index":33,"end_time":81.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not enough to go sledding or anything.","index":34,"end_time":83.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But our dogs love it.","index":35,"end_time":86.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, they run around, they eat it like they are in heaven right now.","index":36,"end_time":91.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":92.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.24,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":38,"end_time":93.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":92.88,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You should see how much snow we got we.","index":39,"end_time":96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.16,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Once it snows here.","index":40,"end_time":97.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":96,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":97.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.52,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"For the most part, the snow will stay on the ground until probably like, mid March, late March.","index":42,"end_time":106.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.96,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":43,"end_time":108.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":109.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":110.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The rest of your year, the next six months.","index":46,"end_time":112.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":47,"end_time":113.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s crazy.","index":48,"end_time":114.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":113.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''ll, like.","index":49,"end_time":115.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":114.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, melt a little bit, and then it''ll snow again and melt a little bit and snow again.","index":50,"end_time":119.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You''re like, okay, we''re in snow season.","index":51,"end_time":121.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.34,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It started.","index":52,"end_time":123.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":124.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":54,"end_time":126.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":125.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, good, thanks.","index":55,"end_time":127.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"How are you?","index":56,"end_time":128.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":127.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, doing great.","index":57,"end_time":130.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Glad to be here.","index":58,"end_time":131.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Be here.","index":59,"end_time":131.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":60,"end_time":133.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":132.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Well, we''ve got quite a bit to go over, so I''ll just share my screen and we''ll get into it.","index":61,"end_time":138.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":62,"end_time":140.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.6,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we''ve got content updates, then we''ll also want to go through the email sequence and abm, and then we''ll take a look at your client portal.","index":63,"end_time":151.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":142.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ll just kick it over to Guille to chat through this.","index":64,"end_time":156.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":153.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":65,"end_time":157.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So here''s a quick rundown on where we''re at on content.","index":66,"end_time":162.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":158.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The first one is the blog post that we did together, like the building a finance function at every stage.","index":67,"end_time":171.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":163,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I reviewed the comment you left Will, and it''s set and ready to publish.","index":68,"end_time":176.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":172.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":69,"end_time":178.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it was really good.","index":70,"end_time":179.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.24,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So thanks for putting that together.","index":71,"end_time":181.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":179.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yay.","index":72,"end_time":182.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":182.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No, it was a great interview.","index":73,"end_time":184.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":182.76,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I think this is a good blog post, so we should like send it all over.","index":74,"end_time":189.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":184.55,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Great.","index":75,"end_time":190.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Then the SEO optimization that we did on the accounting services landing page, that''s now live on the dev website, which is the one that you also reviewed.","index":76,"end_time":203.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":192.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So that one''s done and ready to go.","index":77,"end_time":207.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":204.47,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And for next week, we are doing a blog based on the podcast episode that you guys recorded with Karimaue.","index":78,"end_time":217.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":208.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That one is in progress and is scheduled for next week.","index":79,"end_time":223.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":219.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"That''s also a great episode.","index":80,"end_time":225.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":223.87,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I.","index":81,"end_time":225.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My advice is that when it goes out, you also share this blog post with Cari so she can like send it over and we get some traffic over there.","index":82,"end_time":236.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":227.51,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sure.","index":83,"end_time":238.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.07,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yep.","index":84,"end_time":241.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And that scene on content, the email sequence that we added like a four message LinkedIn sequence to it.","index":85,"end_time":251.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":242.16,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And Nick, you mentioned that you had some notes on the sequencing.","index":86,"end_time":255.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":251.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Maybe we can work through those together.","index":87,"end_time":258.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":255.36,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I have some general comments.","index":88,"end_time":261.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.92,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Will and I were kind of talking about, you know, we''re always kind of pushing and pulling levers and trying to figure out what lever prospects and clients are, you know, wanting to pull or needing to pull and how do we get their attention in regards to that.","index":89,"end_time":281.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.16,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I just wanted to let you guys know, like when I send out emails, well, Will ask me this.","index":90,"end_time":286.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"He goes, why do you think the success rate of the responses for the email campaign for RFDC went so well?","index":91,"end_time":293.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We said, well, timing and it was relative.","index":92,"end_time":296.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.01,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, hey, we''re going to the show and they''re going to the show.","index":93,"end_time":300.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And it was a warm lead.","index":94,"end_time":301.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.09,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But also what I found in my experience is I''m.","index":95,"end_time":306.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.05,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m pretty good at grabbing people''s attention for the most part.","index":96,"end_time":311.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.53,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''ll give you an example.","index":97,"end_time":313.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.93,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So two days ago, I read a industry publication about a Papa John''s franchisee purchasing 85 new locations.","index":98,"end_time":321.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":313.69,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It doubled overnight.","index":99,"end_time":323.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.34,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Wow.","index":100,"end_time":324.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And yeah, it was crazy.","index":101,"end_time":326.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I''m like, well, this is a prime target for us.","index":102,"end_time":328.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.14,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And so I''m like, how do I find out about him?","index":103,"end_time":333.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.02,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Did my whole channel research, did all this stuff, didn''t have much on this, this company at all.","index":104,"end_time":338.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Found him on LinkedIn.","index":105,"end_time":339.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.74,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, how do I get his attention on LinkedIn?","index":106,"end_time":343.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.34,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Sent him an invitation, like a request.","index":107,"end_time":346.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But my note was very simple and brief.","index":108,"end_time":349.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And he got, he got the invitation request, accepted it, and all I did is I made it relative.","index":109,"end_time":358.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.99,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I said, hey, saw the acquisition of the 85 stores.","index":110,"end_time":361.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Congrats, best of luck.","index":111,"end_time":363.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.63,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Let''s connect share networks.","index":112,"end_time":365.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It was like sharp, simple, to the point, boom.","index":113,"end_time":368.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.39,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then he accepted.","index":114,"end_time":370.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.31,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then my response was, hey, if you ever want to you know, talk about your infrastructure, your financial back office infrastructure as you double oversize, let us know if we can provide any insights.","index":115,"end_time":382.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And he said, that''s something we''re thinking about.","index":116,"end_time":385.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So, yeah, I mean it was like.","index":117,"end_time":389.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So basically what I''m trying to say is the email sequence the written very, very well.","index":118,"end_time":396.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But I''m trying to put my shoes into a prospect, right?","index":119,"end_time":400.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I read the subject line and I''m like, okay, all right.","index":120,"end_time":406.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.43,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then I open it up and I see it''s three.","index":121,"end_time":408.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I see it''s three paragraphs long.","index":122,"end_time":411.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.95,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m going to delete it within six seconds.","index":123,"end_time":416.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.71,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":417.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":417.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think we''re all, we all do that.","index":125,"end_time":420.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It has to grab your attention right away, has to be short, has to be brief, has to have a call to action.","index":126,"end_time":426.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s these sequences that in my opinion, it looks like a newsletter.","index":127,"end_time":431.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.74,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s lengthy, it''s very well written, but I think it needs to be relative, timely, quick with it with like kind of an action.","index":128,"end_time":444.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.78,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like a, like a response is needed, not just a, hey, take a look at this.","index":129,"end_time":448.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.58,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Because even if they do take a look at it and they do open it and say we get a 40% open rate and then we look at the emails like, hey, this guy''s actually looked at it six times.","index":130,"end_time":458.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.66,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Be like, well, he''s reading it, but there''s no call to action there.","index":131,"end_time":463.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.91,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Maybe there is.","index":132,"end_time":463.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, hey, I''ll schedule a meeting with somebody.","index":133,"end_time":466.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.67,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We don''t do that.","index":134,"end_time":467.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t do that.","index":135,"end_time":468.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.95,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t, like, hey, if this is, if, if this is of need or you''re interested, schedule a call with me.","index":136,"end_time":475.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.83,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, yeah, people, people like, no, no, no, no, no, no.","index":137,"end_time":478.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I want to respond to the quick thing.","index":138,"end_time":479.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":478.34,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You schedule something with me.","index":139,"end_time":481.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.74,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Or does that make sense?","index":140,"end_time":483.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.06,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like I''m, I''m thinking of, yeah, just like making it like.","index":141,"end_time":489.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.06,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So I had a note for like the first one was the subject was great.","index":142,"end_time":495.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It was, you know how a client added $2 million of EBITDA and then it was like, okay, great.","index":143,"end_time":505.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.18,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But it was like, this is going to be an information type of an article that''s going to pop up.","index":144,"end_time":510.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.11,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So like what I wanted to do is change that subject to be like, be like, make it about GSS and then say how a GSS client made $2 million in EBITDA and then click it there and then get right into it.","index":145,"end_time":527.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":511.47,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Get right into it.","index":146,"end_time":528.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.71,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Be like, hi, Mike.","index":147,"end_time":529.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":528.83,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Be like, did you know that GSS was able to add $2 million of EBITDA to a 40, 40 multi unit restaurant?","index":148,"end_time":537.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.82,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We noticed by looking at your business, you know, this might provide some value, like, worth a chat.","index":149,"end_time":545.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then that''s it, Nick.","index":150,"end_time":547.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, a lot faster.","index":151,"end_time":550.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":547.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just like boom, boom, boom.","index":152,"end_time":551.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then instead of.","index":153,"end_time":553.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, instead of like.","index":154,"end_time":554.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So what I wanna do is I want them to engage.","index":155,"end_time":557.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.06,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I want them to call me, I want them to respond to that email.","index":156,"end_time":561.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.06,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t want them to get all the information they want by reading the email.","index":157,"end_time":565.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.14,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then them think about it.","index":158,"end_time":567.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.7,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then all of a sudden they get a phone call or another email and distracts them.","index":159,"end_time":570.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then they delete that or they put it to the side or whatever.","index":160,"end_time":573.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I want them to go, wait, what this guy?","index":161,"end_time":576.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"They made $2 million of EBITDA.","index":162,"end_time":578.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How?","index":163,"end_time":578.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I gotta.","index":164,"end_time":580.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.58,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I gotta figure.","index":165,"end_time":580.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.18,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I gotta figure out why.","index":166,"end_time":581.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.78,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then they say, like, nick, okay, I bite.","index":167,"end_time":585.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Tell me how.","index":168,"end_time":586.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.99,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Then I''ll be like, cool.","index":169,"end_time":588.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.63,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Be like, I did.","index":170,"end_time":590.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.87,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We did these two things.","index":171,"end_time":591.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.47,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"These two things were priority.","index":172,"end_time":593.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.87,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Be like, would you like to discuss more in detail or discuss your financial infrastructure a little bit more?","index":173,"end_time":598.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"They''re like, how does 30 minutes on Thursday sound?","index":174,"end_time":601.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.35,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then just keep.","index":175,"end_time":602.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":601.87,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Kind of give them a carrot.","index":176,"end_time":604.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then that''s like how I work a sequence.","index":177,"end_time":606.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.03,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then my goal is to get them on the phone.","index":178,"end_time":609.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.99,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Then if I get them on the phone 10, 15 minutes, I can find out all the information I need about them.","index":179,"end_time":616.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.12,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"They know all the information about us.","index":180,"end_time":618.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then it''s a point of advancing that prospect from there.","index":181,"end_time":622.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.24,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":182,"end_time":624.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.96,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that sounds great.","index":183,"end_time":628.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think.","index":184,"end_time":628.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":628.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Get to the point a lot faster and just get.","index":185,"end_time":632.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Ask them to, if they''re interested, to.","index":186,"end_time":635.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hop on a call.","index":187,"end_time":636.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":635.68,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":188,"end_time":640.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.49,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Be like, yeah, like, let''s not.","index":189,"end_time":643.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":640.65,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I hate.","index":190,"end_time":644.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.81,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay, so, like, go through all of the prospecting.","index":191,"end_time":646.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.53,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t know, like, I get a lot of them.","index":192,"end_time":649.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I get a ton, a ton of them from, like, the AI, sales development reps, you know, sdr, AI.","index":193,"end_time":655.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.33,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"This, that, this, that, this, that.","index":194,"end_time":656.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I get a ton.","index":195,"end_time":657.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.29,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And they''re all scripted the same and they''re so generic and they''re so mass produced.","index":196,"end_time":662.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.25,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And.","index":197,"end_time":662.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I don''t see any difference between one company and another with this email.","index":198,"end_time":666.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.01,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And they''re all three paragraphs and they''re all this.","index":199,"end_time":669.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":667.01,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And they''re like.","index":200,"end_time":670.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.45,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, they say, like, would you like to schedule a call or would you like to explore further?","index":201,"end_time":674.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.29,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I just want to say, like, worth the chat.","index":202,"end_time":679.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.57,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Question mark and make it more conversational.","index":203,"end_time":683.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.73,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"As in, like, I would.","index":204,"end_time":685.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":683.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I saw this guy at a show and I got 30 seconds to grab his attention.","index":205,"end_time":691.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s like, I don''t want to be like, you know, should we book a call or be like, just be like, hey Bill, I noticed this.","index":206,"end_time":701.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.79,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":207,"end_time":702.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":701.71,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Hey, did you know this worth a call.","index":208,"end_time":704.829,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Can I follow up?","index":209,"end_time":705.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.829,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And it''s like real quick.","index":210,"end_time":706.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.79,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I, I, I''m just, I''m kind of, I''m like I''m baffled that I haven''t received a response from these campaigns.","index":211,"end_time":716.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":709.07,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I''m thinking that we just literally do a 180 with it.","index":212,"end_time":719.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.56,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":213,"end_time":720.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":214,"end_time":722.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.56,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And Will might have different thoughts.","index":215,"end_time":723.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.08,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I love, I mean I read through the, My first thought on the sequence was leading with the free CFO services that people would just quickly see that this is a some kind of sales ploy and didn''t want to.","index":216,"end_time":736.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":723.56,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then I felt like we needed to start with the results and the credibility.","index":217,"end_time":740.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.68,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So the, that was put together like that.","index":218,"end_time":743.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean the team responded to that.","index":219,"end_time":748.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.75,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think that and, but I like the discussion and I think you''re right in terms of making it more pithy.","index":220,"end_time":756.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.23,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":757.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.51,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And, and just, yeah, brief.","index":222,"end_time":762.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But I, I mean this is, yeah, I''ll defer to Nick and, and what you and the marketing team can come up with to make it more to the point.","index":223,"end_time":775.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":764.15,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I guess.","index":224,"end_time":776.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.61,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean we want it to be successful.","index":225,"end_time":778.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.05,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean but you all have more experience than I do.","index":226,"end_time":785.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":778.61,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But obviously Nick has a lot of experience in prospecting too.","index":227,"end_time":789.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.01,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I think the combination should get us to the right place.","index":228,"end_time":793.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.57,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":229,"end_time":794.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.17,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"If I can rely on, on your team for list curation, sequencing and sending it out and then I think I can focus on the message and the carrot per se.","index":230,"end_time":808.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.53,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then I mean, because, because what we''re doing is on the blogs and the articles and all the other content that''s being created.","index":231,"end_time":817.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.17,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s, there''s backup and there''s proof in the pudding there.","index":232,"end_time":823.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.61,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So if I get somebody to bite the carrot and they go like, yeah, I would love to learn more.","index":233,"end_time":827.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.55,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Send me something.","index":234,"end_time":828.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":827.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Well, I''ve got it.","index":235,"end_time":829.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.75,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''ve got a link for a blog.","index":236,"end_time":830.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.63,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''ve got, you know, content I can send in a PDF if I want to do email or if a call or whatever or we get on the phone, I can do a presentation or something of that nature.","index":237,"end_time":840.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830.91,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Well, what''s the right next steps?","index":238,"end_time":844.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.27,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Do you trim it down and do it in your formula, Nick, or what, what, what do you think we do next?","index":239,"end_time":850.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":844.27,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Well, I think so.","index":240,"end_time":852.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And, and what I would like to do is so we''re, we have it set up for three or four sequences.","index":241,"end_time":860.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.18,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think it''s four.","index":242,"end_time":861.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Right.","index":243,"end_time":861.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think we''re at five, five, five emails and four LinkedIn messages.","index":244,"end_time":869.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":245,"end_time":870.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":870.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Let me.","index":246,"end_time":874.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.9,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''ve been tooling around with it a little bit.","index":247,"end_time":876.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"What I''ll do is something similar to what I did for rfdc.","index":248,"end_time":881.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.44,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"What I would like to do is develop the content, subject and content for each one.","index":249,"end_time":890.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.36,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I think we trim it down a little bit.","index":250,"end_time":893.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.6,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think we do three to four, and then we refresh the list.","index":251,"end_time":898.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.24,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":252,"end_time":899.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":898.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And then I don''t think we sent.","index":253,"end_time":902.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.64,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Any to the list we last sent over to you.","index":254,"end_time":904.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Right, I know that.","index":255,"end_time":906.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I updated that list and I know that''s what we''re waiting on is to get content approved and then we attack that list.","index":256,"end_time":912.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.74,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then, and I think, I think we should do.","index":257,"end_time":915.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":912.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Let me give it some thought.","index":258,"end_time":917.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Maybe three, four.","index":259,"end_time":919.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I know it takes on average, it''s actually dropped a little bit to get engagement.","index":260,"end_time":924.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.06,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It used to be seven pokes, now it''s like five and a half, six.","index":261,"end_time":928.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Just because people are always on their phones and they''re more reactive these days.","index":262,"end_time":932.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But I don''t like to overkill it.","index":263,"end_time":936.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.37,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, I like to, you know, like, you go out and do a savannah and you see a bunch of gazelles out there.","index":264,"end_time":943.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.85,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"They''re like, all right, I''m gonna give it three attempts.","index":265,"end_time":945.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.73,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Well, guess what?","index":266,"end_time":946.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.69,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"All those gazelles are going to be gone.","index":267,"end_time":947.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.33,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I want to go to a new savannah.","index":268,"end_time":949.249,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.69,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, I''m like, yeah.","index":269,"end_time":950.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.33,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m like, all right, I gave it my shot.","index":270,"end_time":952.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.61,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Let me go over here now.","index":271,"end_time":953.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Because there''s gazelles everywhere.","index":272,"end_time":954.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.25,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t want to keep hunting the same damn gazelle that keeps getting out of my hands if there''s gazelle''s over there.","index":273,"end_time":960.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.01,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So let me do that.","index":274,"end_time":963.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.82,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Let me.","index":275,"end_time":963.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":963.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then I''m really focused on the content just because one, it''s coming from me and I want it to sound like it''s from me.","index":276,"end_time":974.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":963.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And when I do hook somebody, you know, the biggest compliment I get from prospects, clients or whatever is, Nick, you''ve always been the same person from day one till five years later.","index":277,"end_time":987.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.58,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, I don''t change.","index":278,"end_time":989.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.06,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I don''t like throw it some fluffiness and promises and all this.","index":279,"end_time":993.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m just like, I don''t change.","index":280,"end_time":995.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.74,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It takes a little while to establish trust in a relationship sometimes, but I don''t change.","index":281,"end_time":1001.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So I want to start it the right way and start it like how I would start it.","index":282,"end_time":1006.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1002.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then, and then we have all the content to back it up.","index":283,"end_time":1010.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So let me work on that today and I''ll probably like, I have a framework and I''ll get you you and something probably later today, maybe early tomorrow morning.","index":284,"end_time":1020.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":285,"end_time":1022.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks for the feedback.","index":286,"end_time":1023.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m excited to, to run this new test.","index":287,"end_time":1026.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Every industry is a little different, so if you''ve had a lot of success with this, let''s roll it.","index":288,"end_time":1033.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Roll with it.","index":289,"end_time":1034.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, I don''t.","index":290,"end_time":1035.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.41,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Let''s level the expectation.","index":291,"end_time":1037.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.85,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, you know, it''s, it''s prospecting is you send out a hundred.","index":292,"end_time":1045.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.65,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"If you get like literally 5%, that''s amazing.","index":293,"end_time":1049.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.79,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s cold prospecting, but what we''re doing is we''re honing it in a little bit and it''s, it''s, it''s a lukewarm lead.","index":294,"end_time":1061.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1050.03,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s not a warm lead.","index":295,"end_time":1063.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1062.03,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s lukewarm because you''ve guys done the research on the list curation.","index":296,"end_time":1067.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.15,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I went over it and I looked at some of these companies and I''m like, yeah, these are targets.","index":297,"end_time":1072.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1068.49,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s relative.","index":298,"end_time":1074.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So it''s a little warm.","index":299,"end_time":1075.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.33,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"They should be aware.","index":300,"end_time":1076.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.69,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"If they''re not aware of us already, let''s go after them.","index":301,"end_time":1080.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.85,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So it should be a little bit successful, but let''s try it this way.","index":302,"end_time":1084.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.81,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Awesome game.","index":303,"end_time":1087.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll, we''ll get rolling with that.","index":304,"end_time":1089.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And yeah, once you get that over to the, to us, we can get the, the new campaign slot launched.","index":305,"end_time":1096.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.61,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":306,"end_time":1097.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":307,"end_time":1098.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.67,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Great.","index":308,"end_time":1100.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1100.51,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So then just hopping into some stats over the last few weeks.","index":309,"end_time":1105.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nothing crazy going on here.","index":310,"end_time":1107.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There were the holidays.","index":311,"end_time":1108.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I do expect things to slow down.","index":312,"end_time":1109.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''ve pretty much gone through the, the initial list.","index":313,"end_time":1113.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll definitely want to get a new campaign running here again soon.","index":314,"end_time":1116.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then exciting updates on your website.","index":315,"end_time":1121.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It seems like you''ve looked at everything too, so I think the new website is ready to.","index":316,"end_time":1126.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Were there any other.","index":317,"end_time":1128.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think you mentioned you''d left one.","index":318,"end_time":1129.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1128.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Comment, but that was just on the blog.","index":319,"end_time":1132.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.73,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I didn''t see anything on the website.","index":320,"end_time":1135.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.09,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, well, if it''s looking good, we''ll check our team''s availability to see if we can launch tomorrow.","index":321,"end_time":1144.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1138.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If not, then we''ll recommend launching early next week.","index":322,"end_time":1148.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1145.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think I''ve said this before, but we can just expect like some.","index":323,"end_time":1155.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1148.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Something will break.","index":324,"end_time":1156.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s totally normal, but we''ll be really quick to fix anything if that happens.","index":325,"end_time":1160.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just always want to prepare like stuff happens, but anything is fixable.","index":326,"end_time":1165.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll keep an eye on it over, over the next few weeks and we can always fix things quickly.","index":327,"end_time":1172.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":328,"end_time":1173.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1172.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":329,"end_time":1175.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then last, we''ll just take a look at your client portal so you can see what''s going on.","index":330,"end_time":1182.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Planning on distributing that episode with Carrie here soon.","index":331,"end_time":1187.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1182.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gay''s already talked about some of these blogs that we''re working through as well.","index":332,"end_time":1191.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then your points are looking really good.","index":333,"end_time":1196.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve got a lot of stuff currently working, but you do have some points available for additional things.","index":334,"end_time":1203.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1196.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we''ve got some, like, extra blog posts and other stuff that we could also work on.","index":335,"end_time":1209.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1203.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But if.","index":336,"end_time":1210.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If there''s anything else that you''re like, oh, that would be really helpful, or we could use some help there, just let us know.","index":337,"end_time":1216.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":338,"end_time":1218.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1217.8,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":339,"end_time":1219.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":340,"end_time":1220.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Great.","index":341,"end_time":1221.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.76,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Great to see you.","index":342,"end_time":1222.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1221.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Have a good day.","index":343,"end_time":1223.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1222.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"You too.","index":344,"end_time":1224.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":345,"end_time":1224.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1224.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":346,"end_time":1225.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"See ya.","index":347,"end_time":1226.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.4,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"}],"dateString":"2025-12-03T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nstauff@gsslp.com,wfleming@gsslp.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nstauff@gsslp.com","wfleming@gsslp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KB0JHA44REY2GMXE4T4V2KQM","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed accounting services landing page is optimized and live on the dev site.","Agreed to rework outbound email and LinkedIn sequence to shorter, more compelling messaging.","Nick will draft revised, bite-sized campaign copy; delivery expected within a day.","Team aligned on reducing email touches to 3–4 with more targeted subject lines.","New website reviewed; pending launch depending on team availability, possibly as early as tomorrow."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We did these two things. These two things were priority.","speaker":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"quote":"I think the combination should get us to the right place.","speaker":"Will Fleming"},{"quote":"If you''ve had a lot of success with this, let''s roll with it.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["email","content","delivery","launch"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-05T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Development and Publishing**\n\nThe content team has completed key deliverables and is preparing new material to boost engagement and support sales efforts.\n\n- **The blog post titled “Building a Finance Function at Every Stage” is finalized and ready to publish** following Will Fleming''s review, ensuring alignment with business messaging and client education goals (02:38).  \n    - The post resulted from a strong interview and received positive internal feedback validating its quality.  \n    - This content will serve as a cornerstone for ongoing marketing and thought leadership efforts.  \n    - The team plans to distribute the blog widely, including through Carrie’s channels, to drive targeted traffic and lead generation.  \n    - This approach supports nurturing prospects with valuable insights tied directly to client needs and market positioning.\n\n- **SEO optimization for the accounting services landing page is complete and live on the development site** after Will’s review, ready for final launch (03:12).  \n    - This update is expected to improve organic search visibility and generate higher-quality inbound leads.  \n    - Next week’s content will include a blog based on the podcast episode featuring Karimaue, scheduled to maintain momentum with fresh, relevant material (03:12).  \n    - Sharing this content through internal and partner networks is advised to maximize reach and traffic impact.  \n    - These ongoing content efforts aim to build credibility and continuously engage prospective clients.\n\n## **Email and LinkedIn Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to overhaul the outreach messaging to improve engagement rates by making it more concise, timely, and action-driven.\n\n- **Nick S proposed a shift to shorter, more direct email sequences focused on sparking immediate responses, rather than lengthy informational messages** that prospects skim and delete (04:02).  \n    - His example of successfully engaging a Papa John''s franchisee by sending a brief, relevant LinkedIn connection message shows the power of personalized, sharp outreach.  \n    - Nick emphasized the need for subject lines and body copy that highlight specific client successes, such as “how a GSS client added $2 million in EBITDA,” to immediately grab attention (08:31).  \n    - The goal is to prompt prospects to reply with interest rather than passively consume content, accelerating the move to phone conversations.  \n    - This approach reflects Nick’s consistent prospecting style that values authenticity and trust over scripted sales pitches.\n\n- **Will Fleming supported trimming the sequences and focusing on credibility and results first, then brief follow-ups, deferring to Nick’s expertise on prospect engagement** (12:03).  \n    - They agreed on refining the sequence to **three to four messages**, balancing persistence with respect for prospect attention spans (14:33).  \n    - Nick will draft revised subject lines and content today or early tomorrow for rapid review and deployment (16:28).  \n    - The marketing team will continue handling list curation and campaign execution, while Nick focuses on messaging tone and calls to action (13:14).  \n    - This new test aims to increase response rates from lukewarm leads, leveraging targeted research and personalized outreach.\n\n## **Campaign Performance and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is monitoring campaign engagement and preparing to launch the next phase with refreshed content and target lists.\n\n- **Recent campaign results were steady but slowed due to the holiday period and exhaustion of the initial prospect list, prompting a need for new outreach efforts soon** (18:20).  \n    - Baylee Gunnell noted low activity consistent with seasonal trends, signaling urgency to start the next campaign cycle.  \n    - Nick confirmed the updated prospect list is ready for a new campaign once the revised content is approved and deployed (15:05).  \n    - The plan is to avoid resending to the exhausted list and instead focus on fresh targets to maintain efficiency and avoid over-contacting prospects (14:59).  \n    - This cycle approach aligns with prospect behavior trends, where typically 5 to 7 touches are needed for engagement, now dropping closer to 5 due to mobile responsiveness (14:58).\n\n- **The team aims for a quick turnaround on content approval to launch the next campaign by early next week, ensuring continuity in lead generation efforts** (18:58).  \n    - Baylee and Will will coordinate with the marketing team’s availability to confirm launch timing and monitor post-launch issues proactively.  \n    - Any website or campaign glitches will be addressed swiftly to minimize disruption to lead flow.  \n    - Maintaining campaign momentum through timely iteration and quick fixes is a key operational priority.  \n    - This readiness reflects the team’s commitment to sustaining pipeline health despite external seasonality.\n\n## **Website and Client Portal Updates**\n\nThe website is near launch readiness, and the client portal is actively managed to support ongoing content delivery and client engagement.\n\n- **The new website has undergone review with minimal comments and is expected to launch imminently, pending team availability, with Baylee anticipating potential minor post-launch fixes** (18:49).  \n    - Will confirmed only a single blog comment remains outstanding, indicating strong overall site readiness.  \n    - The team is prepared to quickly resolve any technical issues that arise after launch to maintain a seamless user experience.  \n    - This site upgrade is designed to enhance user navigation and better showcase service offerings, supporting lead conversion.  \n    - The website update also integrates with content marketing and outreach strategies for a unified front.\n\n- **The client portal is actively updated with recent content and points available for additional services, offering flexibility to scale marketing efforts as needed** (20:00).  \n    - Baylee highlighted unused points that can fund extra blog posts or other content initiatives to expand reach.  \n    - The portal provides transparency and real-time tracking of content progress, facilitating collaboration between teams.  \n    - This platform supports agile content planning and resource allocation aligned with business priorities.  \n    - Will and Nick were encouraged to propose any new content needs to capitalize on available resources.\n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Team Roles**\n\nClear role delineation and collaboration frameworks are set to optimize campaign success and messaging authenticity.\n\n- **Nick emphasized his focus on crafting authentic, personalized messaging that matches his prospecting style, while relying on the marketing team for list management and campaign execution** (13:14).  \n    - This division leverages each party’s strengths, combining Nick’s frontline sales experience with the team’s technical and creative support.  \n    - Nick’s approach aims to build trust through consistency and brevity in outreach, enhancing prospect engagement.  \n    - Will supports this model, reinforcing the importance of credibility and brevity in sales messaging from leadership perspective.  \n    - This alignment ensures messaging stays true to the brand while benefiting from data-driven list targeting and operational support.\n\n- **The team agreed on a feedback loop and rapid iteration cycle, with Nick delivering revised sequences quickly for review and testing** (16:28).  \n    - This fast feedback ensures campaigns stay relevant and adapt to prospect responses and market shifts.  \n    - Baylee expressed enthusiasm for testing Nick’s proven methods across industries, showing openness to optimized workflows.  \n    - The collaborative approach reflects a culture of continuous improvement grounded in frontline insights.  \n    - This dynamic setup is expected to improve overall campaign effectiveness and pipeline development.","outline":null,"keywords":["email sequence","prospect engagement","content updates","SEO optimization","campaign strategy","client portal"],"overview":"- **Content Development:** New blog post “Building a Finance Function at Every Stage” finalized for publication, supporting engagement and sales.  \n- **SEO Updates:** Accounting services landing page is optimized to boost organic search and inbound leads, set for launch.  \n- **Outreach Strategy:** Email sequences to be shorter and focused on urgent responses, using client successes for better engagement.  \n- **Campaign Performance:** Slow activity noted; new prospect list ready for campaign launch by early next week to sustain lead generation.  \n- **Website Progress:** New website nearing launch; client portal updated with content, ready to support marketing efforts flexibly.  \n- **Team Collaboration:** Roles clarified for better campaign success, emphasizing personalized messaging backed by marketing team support for execution.","action_items":"\n**Nicholas Stauff**\nDraft and revise the email messaging sequence incorporating shorter, direct, conversational style with clear calls-to-action. Submit for team review by later today or early next morning (16:50)\nCollaborate with marketing team for list curation and campaign launches, focusing on targeted messaging and maintaining authentic persona in outreach (13:30)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nShare the scheduled blog post from the podcast with Carrie for distribution to generate traffic (03:47)\nCoordinate with the team to check availability and plan for website launch tomorrow or early next week, managing fixes post-launch as needed (18:55)\nPrepare to launch a new email campaign upon receiving Nick’s revised content and finalize campaign slot (18:20)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nContinue content development including upcoming blog post based on podcast and past projects, supporting team with content production and SEO enhancements (02:40)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nReview and provide feedback on blog and updated content as needed (18:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"4690d3b5-6076-4d43-81e8-7f378d381889","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
