WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'e50afe94-037e-49d6-8f2e-8c05ac7e3294',
    '2025-12-05 14:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KB5M0D59RQRV673GHF7ERSH5',
    'Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","osbal","Axel Völker","Colin Costigan","Eli Bebinger"}'::text[],
    1512,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1',
    '{"id":"01KB5M0D59RQRV673GHF7ERSH5","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Lead Engagement**\n\nThe team is still in the early phase of the new outreach campaign, with initial connection and messaging activity underway but limited replies received so far (09:11).\n\n- **Since Tuesday, 36 new connections** have been sent through the new sequence, with **3 accepted and 2 messages sent** from Eli''s profile (09:11).\n    - Earlier replies are still coming from the old sequence, with no responses yet from the new sequence.\n    - Eli noted some feedback from one lead about unclear responses, prompting follow-up to clarify messaging.\n    - The new email sequence launched Tuesday morning, reflecting a strategic refresh to improve engagement.\n    - Monitoring this early activity helps determine if the new approach drives faster, clearer responses and better lead quality.\n\n- Colin explained that system notifications for LinkedIn replies are sent automatically when a reply hits Eli’s profile linked to the campaign (06:07).\n    - The team has access to the Hayreach platform for managing leads and can track conversation threads.\n    - Coordination around message content and sequence personalization remains important to avoid repetitive back-and-forth exchanges.\n    - Eli and Axel plan to review and possibly refine the new sequence messaging for clarity and effectiveness.\n\n## **Content Production and Media Strategy**\n\nThe team is preparing to produce and distribute recorded episodes and success stories to boost marketing and customer engagement (14:12).\n\n- **Riverside has been set up as the primary recording platform** for producing high-quality HD video and audio episodes with transcripts and AI-generated previews (16:32).\n    - Riverside records separate feeds for each participant, ensuring clean production unaffected by internet blips.\n    - The system supports planning sessions, sending calendar invites, and hosting rehearsals or test runs before recording.\n    - Colin offered to act as a producer for the first recording to assist with technical setup and smooth execution.\n    - Axel agreed to forward Riverside access and recording instructions to the team member managing meetings.\n\n- Success story interviews are scheduled but impacted by sick leave; these will be recorded via Riverside or Teams, with Riverside preferred for higher quality (16:09).\n    - The goal is to create rich social and website content from these interviews, including short-form videos, quote cards, and long-form podcasts.\n    - Colin outlined that typical post-production turnaround is about **7 days**, delivering multiple asset formats for broad use (20:15).\n    - The team will build a dedicated podcast landing page and integrate testimonials throughout the website to enhance brand storytelling.\n\n## **Script Development and Messaging Tone**\n\nThe team is refining narrative frameworks for recorded episodes to balance structure with natural conversation (21:43).\n\n- David prepared a detailed 2-page outline covering relevant topics and marketplace trends, especially around AI-related content, for review by Axel (22:24).\n    - Axel needs to confirm technical accuracy before finalizing content to align messaging with product capabilities.\n    - Eli prefers a conversational tone over a strict script to allow natural flow and authenticity in recordings.\n    - Colin emphasized flexible frameworks rather than rigid scripts, aiming to highlight David’s career journey and customer perspective naturally.\n\n- Scheduling constraints mean Axel will join detailed review sessions starting Wednesday after workshops, delaying some approvals (22:56).\n    - The team agreed to meet Wednesday to finalize script details and technical input before recording.\n    - Colin encouraged the team to be relaxed during recordings, noting post-production can edit out mistakes, ums, and interruptions.\n\n## **AI Features and Internal Tools Progress**\n\nThe AI-powered profile assistance and search features are in early beta but showing promising capabilities to enhance user experience (10:32).\n\n- Eli and Hendrick have been creating screen recordings to showcase AI functionalities, focusing on profile help and complex people search (12:27).\n    - Axel noted the current AI mostly links to documentation but can answer specific queries about resource availability and profile quality.\n    - The team plans to customize AI prompts and responses to improve relevance and usability based on feedback.\n    - The complex search tool was recommended over the basic free search for better demonstration and user value.\n\n- Colin and Axel discussed further developing AI capabilities to support profile improvements and resource planning insights.\n    - This aligns with longer-term plans to integrate AI as a value differentiator in product offerings.\n    - The team will continue refining AI features while managing expectations around current beta limitations.\n\n## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**\n\nClear ownership and timelines were established to advance both content production and campaign activities efficiently (19:36).\n\n- Axel will connect with Eli and Hendrick to finalize screen recording content and priorities for animation and voiceover production (19:36).\n    - Once recorded, the production turnaround is about **7 days** to deliver polished assets.\n    - Colin offered to schedule and produce the first recording session with Eli and David on Monday, pending availability.\n    - David confirmed Monday availability except for a 10 AM commitment; Eli preferred a later time.\n\n- A follow-up meeting is planned for Wednesday to review scripts and technical points with Axel after his workshops (22:56).\n    - This ensures all messaging aligns with product capabilities and marketplace positioning.\n    - The team will use this session to finalize next steps on both the media content and campaign messaging fronts.\n\n- Colin emphasized flexible asset production, adapting formats and quantities (short videos, quote cards) based on team preferences and audience response over time.\n    - This iterative approach aims to maximize content impact and efficiency.\n    - The end goal is a cohesive marketing ecosystem with podcasts, testimonials, and lead nurturing integrated smoothly.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Campaign","Riverside Recording","AI Profile Assistant","Video Production","Marketing Assets","Podcast Recording"],"overview":"- **New Campaign Status:** 36 new connections sent; 3 accepted so far, with follow-ups needed for clearer messaging.\n\n- **Content Production Setup:** Riverside established for recording; aiming for high-quality episodes and quick turnaround of about 7 days.\n\n- **Script Development Focus:** Balance structure and natural tone in recordings; detailed outlines and flexible frameworks encouraged for authenticity.\n\n- **AI Tool Progress:** AI features in beta show promise; plans to enhance capabilities for better user experience and resource insights.\n\n- **Operational Coordination:** Clear timelines set; follow-up meeting scheduled to review scripts and finalize production details for content.\n\n- **Flexible Asset Production:** Adapt format based on feedback; goal is integrated marketing ecosystem with podcasts, testimonials, and lead nurturing.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nResend Hayreach system login credentials to the team to enable access and review of new campaign replies (07:34)\nSchedule and facilitate initial podcast recording session with Eli and David, acting as producer to help with technical support (15:40)\nProduce marketing assets from recordings including long form podcasts, short videos, quote cards, and transcripts within 7 days turnaround after recording (19:54)\n\n**Eli Bebinger**\nFollow up on LinkedIn responses and manage messaging sequences, ensure new campaign messages are being sent out (07:16)\nShare screen recordings and AI interaction videos in SharePoint/chat and collaborate with Axel and Hendrick on content for animations (10:58)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nReview and provide feedback on script and technical points shared by David Osbaldeston prior to recordings (21:10)\nCoordinate with Hendrick on recording and screening videos and provide prompts for AI capabilities demonstrations (12:52)\n\n**David Osbaldeston**\nForward updated script and technical details to Axel for review (21:27)\n\n**Eli Bebinger & David Osbaldeston**\nPrepare and conduct recording session on Monday, keeping it conversational and flexible for edits (20:38)\n\n**Axel Völker & Eli Bebinger**\nPlan follow-up meeting on Wednesday to review recordings and script adjustments post-Axel’s workshop (23:10)\n\n**Bettina (via Axel)**\nManage scheduling of customer success stories interviews using Riverside platform (18:09)\n"},"duration":25.200000762939453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"osbal"},{"id":2,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Eli Bebinger"}],"sentences":[{"text":"It.","index":0,"end_time":204.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, David.","index":1,"end_time":236.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.45,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"You okay?","index":2,"end_time":237.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.13,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":3,"end_time":239.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":4,"end_time":240.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":239.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, not so bad.","index":5,"end_time":241.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.73,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":6,"end_time":242.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.77,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Go to here.","index":7,"end_time":244.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s your week been so far?","index":8,"end_time":251.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":9,"end_time":254.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.85,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Okay.","index":10,"end_time":255.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.57,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Weather here has been atrocious, but other than that, yeah, it''s been okay.","index":11,"end_time":259.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.82,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":12,"end_time":260.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I saw maybe you were doing some traveling, if I read that correctly.","index":13,"end_time":263.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was two weeks ago now.","index":14,"end_time":266.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.34,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Yeah, I went out to Morocco for a few days with the guys playing golf.","index":15,"end_time":273.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.46,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":16,"end_time":274.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was nice.","index":17,"end_time":275.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":274.42,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"Good evening or morning?","index":18,"end_time":290.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":288.83,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''ll have a mix of evenings and mornings and afternoons.","index":19,"end_time":295.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":296.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":295.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Hi.","index":21,"end_time":308.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hey, Axel.","index":22,"end_time":310.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":23,"end_time":311.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hi.","index":24,"end_time":312.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.8,"speaker_name":"osbal"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":25,"end_time":313.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well.","index":26,"end_time":314,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":313.8,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How about yourself?","index":27,"end_time":314.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":28,"end_time":318.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Busy.","index":29,"end_time":319.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":320.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Busy.","index":31,"end_time":322.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":32,"end_time":323.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Busy.","index":33,"end_time":323.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":34,"end_time":325.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A lot of people are on sick leave here.","index":35,"end_time":327.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.96,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s really.","index":36,"end_time":328.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":327.72,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"A bit.","index":37,"end_time":330.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":330.04,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Hard this week.","index":38,"end_time":333.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.44,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, that time of the year.","index":39,"end_time":335.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Eli should join hopefully.","index":40,"end_time":340.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.6,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":341.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":340.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today looks like he got some replies.","index":42,"end_time":343.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.24,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I get these mails from LinkedIn, but they mostly they all end up in my spam that they look a bit strange.","index":43,"end_time":350.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They say.","index":44,"end_time":351,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Without any subject as a LinkedIn reply, new LinkedIn reply received lead and then everything is empty.","index":45,"end_time":361.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Action required.","index":46,"end_time":362.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.71,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Please respond.","index":47,"end_time":363.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Is that that coming from.","index":48,"end_time":365.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.19,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because it''s also sent to you.","index":49,"end_time":366.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s more of a notification that''s.","index":50,"end_time":370.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Coming from our system.","index":51,"end_time":371.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they''re all hooked up in Eli''s.","index":52,"end_time":374.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When is that sent?","index":53,"end_time":377.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":376.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"When Eli gets reply or.","index":54,"end_time":380.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, when a reply is sent to.","index":55,"end_time":382.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The profile that''s associated with Hayreach, which is Eli''s profile.","index":56,"end_time":386.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":382.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Eli, it looks like you got a few replies.","index":57,"end_time":388.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"One.","index":58,"end_time":391.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":391.41,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"One came through yesterday.","index":59,"end_time":395.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One is from today.","index":60,"end_time":397.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It says I responded to a few.","index":61,"end_time":400.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":397.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, that may be yesterday for you.","index":62,"end_time":402.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":63,"end_time":402.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":64,"end_time":403.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"What is it?","index":65,"end_time":405.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.09,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Was any.","index":66,"end_time":406.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.69,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I see.","index":67,"end_time":408.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.73,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Actually there''s two from Tuesday.","index":68,"end_time":410.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.21,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Once.","index":69,"end_tim