## **Content Production and Media Strategy**

The team is preparing to produce and distribute recorded episodes and success stories to boost marketing and customer engagement (14:12).

- **Riverside has been set up as the primary recording platform** for producing high-quality HD video and audio episodes with transcripts and AI-generated previews (16:32).
    - Riverside records separate feeds for each participant, ensuring clean production unaffected by internet blips.
    - The system supports planning sessions, sending calendar invites, and hosting rehearsals or test runs before recording.
    - Colin offered to act as a producer for the first recording to assist with technical setup and smooth execution.
    - Axel agreed to forward Riverside access and recording instructions to the team member managing meetings.

- Success story interviews are scheduled but impacted by sick leave; these will be recorded via Riverside or Teams, with Riverside preferred for higher quality (16:09).
    - The goal is to create rich social and website content from these interviews, including short-form videos, quote cards, and long-form podcasts.
    - Colin outlined that typical post-production turnaround is about **7 days**, delivering multiple asset formats for broad use (20:15).
    - The team will build a dedicated podcast landing page and integrate testimonials throughout the website to enhance brand storytelling.

## **Script Development and Messaging Tone**

The team is refining narrative frameworks for recorded episodes to balance structure with natural conversation (21:43).

- David prepared a detailed 2-page outline covering relevant topics and marketplace trends, especially around AI-related content, for review by Axel (22:24).
    - Axel needs to confirm technical accuracy before finalizing content to align messaging with product capabilities.
    - Eli prefers a conversational tone over a strict script to allow natural flow and authenticity in recordings.
    - Colin emphasized flexible frameworks rather than rigid scripts, aiming to highlight David’s career journey and customer perspective naturally.

- Scheduling constraints mean Axel will join detailed review sessions starting Wednesday after workshops, delaying some approvals (22:56).
    - The team agreed to meet Wednesday to finalize script details and technical input before recording.
    - Colin encouraged the team to be relaxed during recordings, noting post-production can edit out mistakes, ums, and interruptions.

## **AI Features and Internal Tools Progress**

The AI-powered profile assistance and search features are in early beta but showing promising capabilities to enhance user experience (10:32).

- Eli and Hendrick have been creating screen recordings to showcase AI functionalities, focusing on profile help and complex people search (12:27).
    - Axel noted the current AI mostly links to documentation but can answer specific queries about resource availability and profile quality.
    - The team plans to customize AI prompts and responses to improve relevance and usability based on feedback.
    - The complex search tool was recommended over the basic free search for better demonstration and user value.

- Colin and Axel discussed further developing AI capabilities to support profile improvements and resource planning insights.
    - This aligns with longer-term plans to integrate AI as a value differentiator in product offerings.
    - The team will continue refining AI features while managing expectations around current beta limitations.

## **Operational Coordination and Next Steps**

Clear ownership and timelines were established to advance both content production and campaign activities efficiently (19:36).

- Axel will connect with Eli and Hendrick to finalize screen recording content and priorities for animation and voiceover production (19:36).
    - Once recorded, the production turnaround is about **7 days** to deliver polished assets.
    - Colin offered to schedule and produce the first recording session with Eli and David on Monday, pending availability.
    - David confirmed Monday availability except for a 10 AM commitment; Eli preferred a later time.

- A follow-up meeting is planned for Wednesday to review scripts and technical points with Axel after his workshops (22:56).
    - This ensures all messaging aligns with product capabilities and marketplace positioning.
    - The team will use this session to finalize next steps on both the media content and campaign messaging fronts.

- Colin emphasized flexible asset production, adapting formats and quantities (short videos, quote cards) based on team preferences and audience response over time.
    - This iterative approach aims to maximize content impact and efficiency.
    - The end goal is a cohesive marketing ecosystem with podcasts, testimonials, and lead nurturing integrated smoothly.',
