    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1',
    '{"id":"01KBDAZC45BGM4XZR7JYWM1Q7T","title":"PTO Exchange // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Automation and Contact Management**\n\nThe team finalized automations to capture and update LinkedIn lead data in HubSpot, streamlining follow-up and owner assignment processes.\n\n- **Colin Costigan built a workflow using N8N that automatically creates or updates HubSpot contacts and logs LinkedIn conversations when connection requests are accepted or messages are received** (04:58)  \n    - This automation captures key contact info including email, job title, and LinkedIn URL.  \n    - Colin will implement auto-assignment of contacts to either Josh Reinhard or Dan/Igoe based on which LinkedIn profile initiated the connection.  \n    - The system will also disable email sequences once any type of LinkedIn reply is received, preventing disjointed outreach.  \n    - This forward-looking solution excludes backdating and supports a clean handoff when new sales director Steph starts.\n\n- **Josh Reinhard confirmed the planned transition of LinkedIn lead ownership from him to Steph, mirroring existing territory splits** (08:20)  \n    - Colin can switch the LinkedIn profile sending the connection requests to Steph’s when ready.  \n    - Existing contacts remain under Josh’s ownership, while new leads post-switch will assign to Steph automatically.  \n    - Territory logic in HubSpot will update accordingly without disrupting lead routing.\n\n- **Lead routing refinements addressed geographic inconsistencies to ensure proper assignment** (14:21)  \n    - Colin added alternative location names like “District of Columbia” and “Washington D.C.” to the lead routing rules.  \n    - This prevents misassignments due to naming variations and ensures leads route correctly to assigned reps.\n\n- **Task creation timing for LinkedIn ad leads was adjusted to improve responsiveness** (11:14)  \n    - The follow-up task due date was shortened from **three business days** to **next business day** to accelerate lead engagement.  \n    - Josh acknowledged this change and committed to following up promptly on new tasks.\n\n## **Lead Quality and Lead Generation Insights**\n\nThe team reviewed recent incoming leads from LinkedIn campaigns, confirming quality and engagement trends.\n\n- **Recent leads included senior titles such as Director of Payroll and Executive Director of Global Talent at companies ranging from 3,000 to 5,000 employees** (14:08)  \n    - Josh and Colin agreed these contacts represent solid prospects for PTO Exchange outreach.  \n    - Colin noted several notable companies like NeighborWorks and Worldwide, reinforcing lead list quality.  \n    - Leads entered HubSpot through LinkedIn forms with consistent territory assignment applied.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead generation forms use a shared form name that causes some confusion but will remain unchanged to avoid rebuild complexity** (12:06)  \n    - Josh emphasized avoiding naming forms after individuals to reduce future confusion.  \n    - Colin clarified that territory routing occurs post-submission based on company HQ, regardless of form name.\n\n## **Website Content and User Experience Enhancements**\n\nThe team planned improvements to integration pages and calls-to-action (CTAs) to increase visitor engagement and conversion.\n\n- **Sam Lieberman requested condensing the integrations page by replacing large vertical images with a more compact horizontal design** (15:24)  \n    - Sam shared a Gantt chart to better explain integration workflows and suggested reducing scrolling.  \n    - Colin agreed to explore formatting options and asked for clarification if needed.\n\n- **CTA language will shift from “Request a Demo” to softer phrases like “See the platform in action” or “Understand how it works” to improve user response** (16:12)  \n    - Additional content rows will promote the benchmark report and biweekly webinar to increase lead capture.  \n    - Colin confirmed plans for a Calendly pop-up triggered by benchmark report submissions, customized by user area.\n\n- **Navigation updates will add a prominent benchmark report button to increase visibility and lead generation** (19:29)  \n    - Sam supported this change to drive more traffic to key conversion assets.\n\n## **Sales Presentation Deck Redesign**\n\nJosh and Colin discussed revamping the PTO Exchange partner slide deck for clearer messaging and better engagement.\n\n- **The current deck is too wordy and inconsistent in style, causing confusion and poor integration with partner presentations** (22:03)  \n    - Josh emphasized that slides were designed as leave-behinds but are rarely reviewed post-meeting, so visuals need to be more engaging and less text-heavy.  \n    - Multiple background styles and fonts create a disjointed look; a consistent template and cleaner design are needed.  \n    - The team will build slide templates and reorganize content to emphasize charts, testimonials, key stats, and client impact with minimal text.\n\n- **Font choices cause technical issues when partners like Gallagher incorporate slides into their decks, leading to broken layouts** (27:02)  \n    - Josh highlighted font embedding challenges that distort sizing and appearance without standardized Microsoft fonts.  \n    - Sam suggested exploring alternative file formats or technical fixes to preserve brand fonts without forcing recipients to install packages.\n\n- **Colin proposed recording Josh or Dave presenting the deck to better understand flow and guide redesign priorities** (31:20)  \n    - This would inform slide placement, color use, and content emphasis to enhance audience engagement.  \n    - Josh noted limited availability before Thursday but agreed it would be helpful if feasible.\n\n- **Josh and Colin agreed a simplified, downloadable whitepaper-style asset could complement the deck for HR audiences preparing for leadership meetings** (32:03)  \n    - This document would succinctly summarize PTO Exchange benefits and client data for easy sharing.\n\n## **Ongoing Workflow and System Updates**\n\nThe team committed to continuous improvements in lead workflows and system integrations to support sales and marketing.\n\n- **Colin will update LinkedIn lead generation forms to remove Dan’s name from links and maintain dynamic updates without extra workload** (32:28)  \n    - Josh requested minimizing extra work and accepted leaving existing links as is if changes are costly.\n\n- **Lead owner assignment workflows were adjusted to reflect LinkedIn ad leads’ territories and ensure tasks are created promptly** (10:48)  \n    - Colin ensured tasks are assigned to the appropriate rep based on territory logic after form submission.\n\n- **The team will finalize updates on landing page copy and design tweaks based on Sam’s feedback for a smoother user experience** (15:22)  \n    - Once completed, pages will go live after final approval from Sam and Josh.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Automation","HubSpot Integration","Sales Deck","Lead Routing","Website Optimization","PTO Exchange"],"overview":"- **Lead Automation Finalized:** Automation captures LinkedIn lead data in HubSpot for easier follow-up and assignment. \n\n- **Ownership Transition:** LinkedIn leads will transition from Josh to Steph; territory logic remains intact for new assignments. \n\n- **Lead Routing Improvements:** Geographic name variations added to prevent misassignment of leads, ensuring correct routing. \n\n- **Task Timing Enhanced:** Follow-up tasks for LinkedIn leads shortened to next business day to boost engagement responsiveness. \n\n- **Lead Quality Review:** Recent leads from senior titles confirm strong prospects for outreach, entering through LinkedIn forms with proper territory assignment. \n\n- **Sales Deck Redesign Needed:** Current slide deck is inconsistent and overly wordy; a cleaner, more engaging format is necessary for partner presentations.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nBuild LinkedIn message reply automation to disable email sequences upon any reply (07:03)\nUpdate HubSpot workflow to assign leads to new sales director Steph per assigned territories (08:12)\nCreate new LinkedIn lead gen form excluding personnel names and update routing accordingly (32:28)\nAdjust lead follow-up task due dates in HubSpot to trigger next business day (10:48)\nIncorporate geographical variations in lead routing logic for more accurate territory assignments (14:53)\nImplement website navigation update to add benchmark report button (19:29)\nExecute website copy and design tweaks based on Sam’s feedback, including integrating CTAs for benchmark report and webinar (15:22)\nDevelop area-specific Calendly pop-ups triggered after benchmark report submissions (17:23)\nReview and redesign sales deck content and template style; prepare sample template slides for consistent look and feel (23:50)\nSupport recorded presentation walkthrough if provided by Josh or Dave for better design context (31:20)\nUpdate automation to remove contacts from Smart Lead system upon LinkedIn reply (32:53)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nProvide clarifying content on PTO cash out differentiators for website update (18:13)\nConfirm if recorded presentation walkthrough can be created for design team (31:20)\nSend slide deck and preliminary design feedback ahead of Thursday meeting (21:44)\nMonitor and assess quality of incoming LinkedIn leads and provide feedback (20:14)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nCommunicate changes needed for website integration page design and CTA wording to Colin for implementation (15:22)\nCoordinate internally to determine how joint calendars can support scheduling for Steph’s upcoming lead ownership (08:28)\nEvaluate and approve updated designs and copy on website pages once revised (19:28)\n"},"duration":33.65999984741211,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Josh Reinhard"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Alan.","index":0,"end_time":258.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.7,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"How''s it going, guys?","index":1,"end_time":261.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":262.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":3,"end_time":263.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.42,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":4,"end_time":264.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What''s going on?","index":5,"end_time":266.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.78,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Been working through building some stuff.","index":6,"end_time":270.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Josh, I saw your message.","index":7,"end_time":274.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if maybe we had just taken our notes wrong from the transcription, but I thought that you had mentioned that it was easy for you and Danny to create the contacts, so.","index":8,"end_time":284.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, it''s much easier to not.","index":9,"end_time":288.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":286.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":10,"end_time":289.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":288.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we were like pulling it from Zoom info and it was kind of like, it''s kind of a pain.","index":11,"end_time":295.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if there is a way to do that, that''s preferred.","index":12,"end_time":298,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, so what I built.","index":13,"end_time":300.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We started on this anyways, just because I had a feeling we might end up here.","index":14,"end_time":305.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is I built a flow through N8N so that anytime a connection request is accepted, a message is sent from your profile or a message is received from the other person that will create or update a contact in HubSpot and then also pass through the conversation as notes on the contact in HubSpot.","index":15,"end_time":327.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":307.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":16,"end_time":328.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":328.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So just to make sure this will work the way that we''re thinking it''s going to work, somebody comes in, they accept my connection request because you''ve sent them templated stuff to try to get them to connect with me.","index":17,"end_time":344.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":330.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, they say yes on my side.","index":18,"end_time":348.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":345.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I am then sending them a.","index":19,"end_time":351.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":348.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"A LinkedIn message to say, thanks for connecting, would love to schedule time with you, blah, blah, blah.","index":20,"end_time":361.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":355.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When I put that in, it''s going to automatically get logged in HubSpot.","index":21,"end_time":366.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":361.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it should.","index":22,"end_time":367.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that everything''s set up.","index":23,"end_time":368.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so Sam.","index":24,"end_time":369.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":368.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we don''t have to change anything on our side.","index":25,"end_time":374.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":370.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam.","index":26,"end_time":374.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":374.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just have like, it''s already the same, the sequence.","index":27,"end_time":376.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":374.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I''m just checking, like once I cut and paste it, I''m just completing that step of the sequence, which I need to talk to you about also separately.","index":28,"end_time":386.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":378.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but it shouldn''t change anything in our process.","index":29,"end_time":390.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":387.93,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"It shouldn''t change anything in our process.","index":30,"end_time":392.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":390.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it, it''s not.","index":31,"end_time":393.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":392.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This doesn''t.","index":32,"end_time":393.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":393.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s not going to like backdate to people.","index":33,"end_time":395.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":393.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is like a go forward thing.","index":34,"end_time":396.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":395.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Correct, Colin?","index":35,"end_time":397.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":396.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Correct.","index":36,"end_time":397.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also when they reply, that''ll also be added as a note to their contact record.","index":37,"end_time":402.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s the next question I had.","index":38,"end_time":404.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":403.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So then they reply back to me and say, great, let''s set up a meeting, or no, thanks, whatever reason, when they say no thanks and it gets logged into HubSpot there, whatever they say back to me on LinkedIn, are they then taken out of the email sequence that you guys have?","index":39,"end_time":422.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":404.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I can make that step happen.","index":40,"end_time":424.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":41,"end_time":425.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s pretty easy to.","index":42,"end_time":425.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To implement.","index":43,"end_time":426.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":425.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":44,"end_time":427.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":426.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we.","index":45,"end_time":428.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":427.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes, we.","index":46,"end_time":428.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":428.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right, Sam, we want that also.","index":47,"end_time":430.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":428.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":48,"end_time":430.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Otherwise it looks disjointed.","index":49,"end_time":432.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.739,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":432.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once they reply, we turn off emails.","index":51,"end_time":435.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With any kind of reply that they have, we turn off emails.","index":52,"end_time":439.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":435.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":53,"end_time":440.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":54,"end_time":440.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":440.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll build that.","index":55,"end_time":441.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":441.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":56,"end_time":453.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":454.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I can walk through this a little bit.","index":58,"end_time":455.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":454.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s basically just.","index":59,"end_time":456.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s a webhook coming from heyreach that''s sending a bunch of data and then we have a switch here that is basically determining are they accepting or request.","index":60,"end_time":466.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you send a message or did we receive a message from there?","index":61,"end_time":471.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then routes to create the contact and add in like their email address, first name, job title, last name, LinkedIn URL.","index":62,"end_time":479.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other thing that I need to build into this is understanding if it''s from your profile or Dan''s and assigning you guys as the lead owner or contact owner.","index":63,"end_time":489.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":480.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wait, say that again.","index":64,"end_time":493,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":492.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I''m going to build into this to also auto assign you or Dan as the contact owner, depending whose profile it was sent from.","index":65,"end_time":499.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":66,"end_time":500.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":500.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And just to throw one little extra monkey wrench into this, on Monday we have our new sales director starting.","index":67,"end_time":508.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":501.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":68,"end_time":508.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":508.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the first couple of months, I''m gonna.","index":69,"end_time":514.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":509.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m gonna be running them.","index":70,"end_time":516.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I want her setting the stuff up, but I''m gonna be running the meetings that.","index":71,"end_time":520.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":516.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, that gets set up under her name.","index":72,"end_time":523.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":521.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it should be if we can somehow like our joint calendars to set stuff up, which I think, Sam, we have to figure out on our side.","index":73,"end_time":534.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":525.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it should be Steph.","index":74,"end_time":536.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":534.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, I''m not gonna say immediately on her first day, but like in the next couple of weeks it''s going to be her who''s answering these and who is like.","index":75,"end_time":545.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":537.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re gonna swap her LinkedIn profile.","index":76,"end_time":547.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In for yours and for mine.","index":77,"end_time":548.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Correct.","index":78,"end_time":549.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":548.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No problem.","index":79,"end_time":549.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll run out the ones that obviously that are already in, in my name.","index":80,"end_time":553.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":549.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But anything new as of like a certain date, which will give you like a week''s heads up what date that''s going to be, it will be switched over like it was before when it was John and Dan.","index":81,"end_time":564.699,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":554.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''ll be.","index":82,"end_time":565.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":564.699,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":83,"end_time":566.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":84,"end_time":566.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s totally fine.","index":85,"end_time":568.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because when, when it comes in from the profile, it''ll have the sender''s first name and last name.","index":86,"end_time":573.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can just filter based on that.","index":87,"end_time":574.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":88,"end_time":575.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":575.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And this is the one of the tests that I sent through.","index":89,"end_time":579,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So John Doe, CEO@Test.com.","index":90,"end_time":581.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"so this is like what the note would look like.","index":91,"end_time":585.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":583.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is the Outbound message, the campaign who sent it.","index":92,"end_time":589.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that would be like your name or Steph or Dan.","index":93,"end_time":592.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then what?","index":94,"end_time":592.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The actual message content was.","index":95,"end_time":594.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":96,"end_time":596.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":596.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":97,"end_time":599.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":598.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":98,"end_time":600.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''m going to go ahead and delete this contact.","index":99,"end_time":602.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys have 230,000 of them.","index":100,"end_time":613.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if one more is.","index":101,"end_time":614.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going to hurt things, but don''t want.","index":102,"end_time":615.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To add to the number if we don''t need to.","index":103,"end_time":617.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":104,"end_time":620.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":105,"end_time":626.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll get the workflow updated also to.","index":106,"end_time":629.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To remove them from smart lead.","index":107,"end_time":634.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sam, based on our conversation Monday, we also went in and updated the workflow for contact owner assignment and task creation for LinkedIn ad leads that come in.","index":108,"end_time":644.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Josh, you probably saw you had a few tasks today.","index":109,"end_time":646.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":644.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw one LinkedIn come in.","index":110,"end_time":650.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I saw one LinkedIn come in today and checked on it.","index":111,"end_time":655.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.31,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And Josh, you have a task in your name to follow up with this person.","index":112,"end_time":658.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.83,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The way the workflow is set up, I. I changed it.","index":113,"end_time":663.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":660.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t change it in the workflow.","index":114,"end_time":664.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just changed it on the contact.","index":115,"end_time":665.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s set up to wait three business days for the task to be due.","index":116,"end_time":669.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we want to update that to, like, next business day?","index":117,"end_time":671.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":118,"end_time":674.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":119,"end_time":675.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.179,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wait, so sorry, say that again.","index":120,"end_time":681.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":677.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is.","index":121,"end_time":681.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":681.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"These are people that are like the, The.","index":122,"end_time":684.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":681.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Tamara Ziegler.","index":123,"end_time":687.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":685.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is someone that.","index":124,"end_time":690.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":689.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I got something that says follow up lead.","index":125,"end_time":692.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":690.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":693.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you get a task assignment.","index":127,"end_time":695.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We get the lead that comes in from LinkedIn ads.","index":128,"end_time":698.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did this.","index":129,"end_time":701.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":700.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Come in three days ago or this came in today?","index":130,"end_time":707.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":704.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"One of them probably came in yesterday, like last night.","index":131,"end_time":713.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This one came in today.","index":132,"end_time":716.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can see when they came in if you look at the.","index":133,"end_time":720.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":134,"end_time":723.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":721.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you scroll through their activity, it''ll.","index":135,"end_time":724.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They filled out the form on LinkedIn today.","index":136,"end_time":726.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so that was today.","index":137,"end_time":727.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So how come it says plus Dan Igoe?","index":138,"end_time":730.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":727.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think that''s just the name of the form if we want it.","index":139,"end_time":735.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.95,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, that''s the name of the form that we.","index":140,"end_time":737.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s just what it''s called on LinkedIn on our side.","index":141,"end_time":740.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Sam, we should probably change that so that it''s.","index":142,"end_time":743.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":740.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s what we have built into LinkedIn.","index":143,"end_time":745.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just the.","index":144,"end_time":745.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What, the name of the lead generation form.","index":145,"end_time":747.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":146,"end_time":749.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":748.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Which thing are you talking about, Colin?","index":147,"end_time":755.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":754.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This submitted PTO Exchange booking form plus.","index":148,"end_time":758.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, wait, I should share my screen.","index":149,"end_time":760.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":758.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":150,"end_time":760.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":760.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Oh, I have mine shared now.","index":151,"end_time":761.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":760.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So this is like what I see on my side.","index":152,"end_time":763.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":761.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, so that PTO name of the form.","index":153,"end_time":765.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.81,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s the name of the form in LinkedIn lead generation.","index":154,"end_time":768.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the way that.","index":155,"end_time":771.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s Set up is.","index":156,"end_time":772.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the same form that they''re filling out no matter what territory they''re in.","index":157,"end_time":776.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when it comes into HubSpot, it checks their company HQ and then reassigns to you or Dan based on the map.","index":158,"end_time":781.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we might want to change the name of that to make it less confusing.","index":159,"end_time":787.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":784.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sam, I don''t know if that then change if that screws things up with Colin.","index":160,"end_time":791.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":787.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just have to build a new one.","index":161,"end_time":793.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn doesn''t like.","index":162,"end_time":794.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You have to like build.","index":163,"end_time":795.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.92,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You have to like build a.","index":164,"end_time":796.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":795.64,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"A whole new one, don''t you?","index":165,"end_time":798.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.88,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Okay, then we don''t need to do that.","index":166,"end_time":799.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we shouldn''t name things with people''s names if it''s going to multiple people in the future.","index":167,"end_time":803.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":799.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":168,"end_time":806.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.2,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, I. Yeah, that was New North.","index":169,"end_time":809.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.88,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That wasn''t me.","index":170,"end_time":810.479,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":809.48,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":810.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.479,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or whoever''s me.","index":172,"end_time":811.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, but yeah, just.","index":173,"end_time":814.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.68,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah, don''t worry about that.","index":174,"end_time":815.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.56,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''ll keep it as it is.","index":175,"end_time":816.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":815.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But you know, I don''t.","index":176,"end_time":819.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":816.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We want people looking at where the what form it is.","index":177,"end_time":823.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So just to make it so it''s not as confusing.","index":178,"end_time":825.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":823.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just shouldn''t have, you know, if Dan leaves for whatever reason or whatever.","index":179,"end_time":829.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":825.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We just wouldn''t want.","index":180,"end_time":830.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":829.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, this makes sense.","index":181,"end_time":833.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":832.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I will get on this task.","index":182,"end_time":836.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":834.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m obviously behind.","index":183,"end_time":838.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":837.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All good.","index":184,"end_time":840.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think there was a few because another one was another name that.","index":185,"end_time":843.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wasn''t going to pronounce.","index":186,"end_time":844.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":187,"end_time":845.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Alamayehu.","index":188,"end_time":848,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":189,"end_time":849,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":848.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Director of payroll at NeighborWorks.","index":190,"end_time":851.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they were pretty good sized companies.","index":191,"end_time":853.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When I was checking them out, the one I think that you just had up, I think there was like 3,000 people.","index":192,"end_time":857.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":853.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"3,000 employees.","index":193,"end_time":858.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":857.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":194,"end_time":860.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then this one is NeighborWorks, which from Quick Research seemed like a big company.","index":195,"end_time":866.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"NW.org.","index":196,"end_time":869.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":867.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean I have no idea what they do.","index":197,"end_time":876.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sam, another thing that I fixed was in the lead routing.","index":198,"end_time":879.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure you''re aware, like locations get kind of weird in HubSpot, especially for a place like DC.","index":199,"end_time":886.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So some people say Washington D.C. some people say District of Columbia for there.","index":200,"end_time":889.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just added both options.","index":201,"end_time":891.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":202,"end_time":894.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then so when Steph comes, is she going to have a territory where we need to update all of that logic?","index":203,"end_time":900.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just like mirrors with John.","index":204,"end_time":903.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":901.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, it''s just she''s gonna take John''s territory.","index":205,"end_time":905.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":903.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just John''s whole territory.","index":206,"end_time":906.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":905.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":207,"end_time":906.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything that''s going to me right now should be going to her.","index":208,"end_time":909.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":906.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":209,"end_time":910.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":210,"end_time":914.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":211,"end_time":916.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.499,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Sam, I saw that you went through and left some feedback in markup for the pages.","index":212,"end_time":922.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":213,"end_time":923.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.98,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Anything that you want to specifically call out on those.","index":214,"end_time":927.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can pull them up.","index":215,"end_time":928.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":927.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I just put some, like, copy tweaks mostly.","index":216,"end_time":935.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":931.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I guess.","index":217,"end_time":936.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"The biggest design change was like.","index":218,"end_time":939.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.78,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And we talked about this last time was like, on the integrations page, you have that, like, long list of big images.","index":219,"end_time":946.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.98,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":947.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I sent you the project plan.","index":221,"end_time":949.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.7,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We have that Gantt chart that should be able to inform you a little bit more about, like, how our integration works.","index":222,"end_time":953.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.14,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I''d like it to be a little bit more condensed and like, you know, within kind of like one.","index":223,"end_time":961.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.02,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Maybe it''s horizontal instead of vertical, but I feel like it''s like a lot of.","index":224,"end_time":965.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.94,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You have to, like, you''re a lot of scrolling and the images are like, very large, so it takes up a lot of space.","index":225,"end_time":972.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yep.","index":226,"end_time":972.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me know if you have any questions on.","index":227,"end_time":977.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"On how to format that.","index":228,"end_time":978.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But that was good.","index":229,"end_time":978.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.22,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Um, I did have a couple, like.","index":230,"end_time":983.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know, the CTAs we have on there a lot is like, it''s a lot requested demo or.","index":231,"end_time":991.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.23,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Or pushing to people to that.","index":232,"end_time":992.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Which is.","index":233,"end_time":993.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Which is good.","index":234,"end_time":993.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But I''d like to.","index":235,"end_time":995.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.11,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Number one, let''s not say request a demo.","index":236,"end_time":999.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":996.59,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Let''s, you know, I would rather have it say, you know, see the platform in action or understand how it works.","index":237,"end_time":1006.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.55,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like something that''s moving away from demo.","index":238,"end_time":1008.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.03,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And I was hoping that we could also, you know, they might just be buttons or even adding, you know, like some content rows on some of the pages to push people to the benchmark report and push people to the webinar that we have every other week.","index":239,"end_time":1025.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":240,"end_time":1026.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one change we were making for all those pages was changing this bottom piece to that benchmark report.","index":241,"end_time":1030.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":1031.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.46,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then we also.","index":243,"end_time":1033.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s the webinar pop up.","index":244,"end_time":1035.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also built.","index":245,"end_time":1037.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anita, maybe you can speak to this as well.","index":246,"end_time":1039.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the calendly pop up or we''re building that tomorrow.","index":247,"end_time":1043.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":248,"end_time":1044.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.71,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So the calendly pop up will be, as you said, to show up every time somebody fills in a benchmark report and also for it to be area specific.","index":249,"end_time":1054.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1045.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sweet.","index":250,"end_time":1056.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1055.63,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"That''s great.","index":251,"end_time":1057.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1057.07,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":252,"end_time":1058.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1058.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think there was one of the one comment you said to check.","index":253,"end_time":1062.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1059.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With Josh if I remember correctly or.","index":254,"end_time":1064.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1062.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":255,"end_time":1065.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1064.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Looks like it was up.","index":256,"end_time":1074.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not this one.","index":257,"end_time":1075.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.89,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1076.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.01,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Go to browse.","index":259,"end_time":1077.289,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Open up.","index":260,"end_time":1078.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1077.37,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Is it different from PTO Cash out?","index":261,"end_time":1081.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I didn''t know if this was correct.","index":262,"end_time":1083.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.33,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Josh, if you could read this.","index":263,"end_time":1085.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.69,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"No, that''s not.","index":264,"end_time":1094.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1093.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, I mean, the.","index":265,"end_time":1098.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1097.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The part.","index":266,"end_time":1099.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1098.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The second part of it where it''s like essentially is if the question is, is it Different PTO catch.","index":267,"end_time":1106.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Incorporates PTO cash out, but it also allows these other options beyond just a cash out.","index":268,"end_time":1116.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, like, you know, when we do.","index":269,"end_time":1119.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1117.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"When we say someone does a cash out, it doesn''t increase payroll and salary spend.","index":270,"end_time":1124.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1119.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Neither would them if they did it themselves.","index":271,"end_time":1127.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1124.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the other delineating factor is like, PTO cash out is typically like one time a year or something.","index":272,"end_time":1136.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.029,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Or like they give a set window where ours can be evergreen and it''s like people can do it when they need it, which is like our biggest.","index":273,"end_time":1144.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1136.27,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"One of our biggest differentiators.","index":274,"end_time":1146.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.41,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"So let me just.","index":275,"end_time":1148.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1147.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m just gonna, like, screenshot this and I''ll send you, like, a little.","index":276,"end_time":1151.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1148.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Who might just send this to Colin.","index":277,"end_time":1152.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1151.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just like a little blurb of what?","index":278,"end_time":1153.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1152.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, just in the Slack channel.","index":279,"end_time":1155.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1154.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":280,"end_time":1156.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1155.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":281,"end_time":1158.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1158.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''ll do that as soon as we''re done.","index":282,"end_time":1160.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1158.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":283,"end_time":1160.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1160.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":284,"end_time":1161.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I really appreciate that.","index":285,"end_time":1162.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":286,"end_time":1163.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, Sam, we''ll get these updated and then sent back over to you.","index":287,"end_time":1166.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so we get the thumbs.","index":288,"end_time":1167.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Up, we''ll roll them live.","index":289,"end_time":1168.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1167.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":290,"end_time":1169.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1168.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":291,"end_time":1170.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.66,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":292,"end_time":1171.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1170.38,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We''re also talking about making updating the navigation to have the benchmark report as a button.","index":293,"end_time":1176.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any thoughts on that?","index":294,"end_time":1177.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I would.","index":295,"end_time":1179.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.3,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I would like that.","index":296,"end_time":1180.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.18,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":297,"end_time":1183.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":298,"end_time":1187.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve seen a few leads come in this week, which has been good to see.","index":299,"end_time":1191.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, people accepting the connection request, and we''re building the automation for that to go into HubSpot with all the factors that we''ve talked about.","index":300,"end_time":1201.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1192.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, it sounds like you just.","index":301,"end_time":1203.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ve been busy and haven''t had a.","index":302,"end_time":1205.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Chance to look at the lead.","index":303,"end_time":1206.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let me know what you think on the quality of them.","index":304,"end_time":1210.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, a Director of Payroll.","index":305,"end_time":1212.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And forget what the other title was.","index":306,"end_time":1214.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The other one was a good title also.","index":307,"end_time":1216.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1214.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1220.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1219.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Catherine Erskine went in there from LinkedIn.","index":309,"end_time":1223.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Abigail Duca was another one.","index":310,"end_time":1227.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yes.","index":311,"end_time":1235.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1234.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tamara Z.","index":312,"end_time":1237.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Executive Director of Global Talent.","index":313,"end_time":1240.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1237.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1241.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1241.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At Worldwide.","index":315,"end_time":1242.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1241.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that was the one with like, 3,000 employees.","index":316,"end_time":1246.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":317,"end_time":1249.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.45,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Great.","index":318,"end_time":1251.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1254.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lincoln says 1 to 5k.","index":320,"end_time":1255.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw like 3k on their website somewhere.","index":321,"end_time":1257.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1255.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":322,"end_time":1259.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.73,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"All right.","index":323,"end_time":1259.689,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like we shared a lot of updates on Monday, so.","index":324,"end_time":1265.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so now that we have the feedback on the landing pages, we''ll get through those, we''ll get the.","index":325,"end_time":1269.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1265.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Automation updated so that we''ll remove them from Smart Lead and have the contact owner and everything set.","index":326,"end_time":1276.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1271.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then once you guys want me to flip to Steph''s profile, just let me know and we can make that change.","index":327,"end_time":1281.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Will do.","index":328,"end_time":1283.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.19,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"And then, Josh, I know that we''re meeting.","index":329,"end_time":1286.949,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I Think next week, Thursday.","index":330,"end_time":1291.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, for that slide deck.","index":331,"end_time":1293.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But is there anything you wanted to preface with anything there?","index":332,"end_time":1295.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we kind of talked, touched on it on Monday.","index":333,"end_time":1297.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I, I can kind of show you.","index":334,"end_time":1302.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1300.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So you get a little prep for it.","index":335,"end_time":1304.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''d be.","index":336,"end_time":1305.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1304.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t want this to be the full conversation because I know Dave wants to be part of this, but.","index":337,"end_time":1328.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1323.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I gotcha.","index":338,"end_time":1329.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1328.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we would probably, if this works, we would probably do this again with another deck that we use quite often.","index":339,"end_time":1341.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1332.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But.","index":340,"end_time":1342.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1341.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But basically what our feeling is, this is our partner deck.","index":341,"end_time":1347.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1342.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We feel big picture.","index":342,"end_time":1350.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, look, some of these slides just have a lot of words on them, and we need to figure out one, how to decrease the number of words, but also have something engaging on the screen at the same time.","index":343,"end_time":1366.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1350.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What we did when we created a lot of these PowerPoint decks in the past was we were thinking of them as leave behinds.","index":344,"end_time":1373.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1366.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if somebody wasn''t like fully engaged in the conversation, they could take them away with them.","index":345,"end_time":1378.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1373.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What we realize now is nobody looks at these afterwards.","index":346,"end_time":1380.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1378.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it''s.","index":347,"end_time":1382.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1381.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have too many words on the screen.","index":348,"end_time":1384.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1382.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we have.","index":349,"end_time":1385.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1385.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is our, you know, whatever title slide.","index":350,"end_time":1388.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1385.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is like, setting the tone for, like, why did we create PTO Exchange?","index":351,"end_time":1393.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1389.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So this is these two charts.","index":352,"end_time":1394.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1393.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is a.","index":353,"end_time":1395.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1395.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Just a, like a, you know, image of a chart that we have here.","index":354,"end_time":1402.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1395.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know that we need these words on the right.","index":355,"end_time":1405.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1403.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, you know, there''s, there''s comments here and just.","index":356,"end_time":1408.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1405.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Should we just have charts?","index":357,"end_time":1409.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1408.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''d want your opinion on that.","index":358,"end_time":1411.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1409.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is a newer slide where we don''t want the words on the screen.","index":359,"end_time":1415.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1411.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We want three images that represent what we have on here.","index":360,"end_time":1420.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1415.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The other part of this, like, again, kind of like big picture is we have a lot of slides that have this, like, dark green background that kind of gets lighter as it goes left to right.","index":361,"end_time":1429.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1421.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have some slides that have little images in the background.","index":362,"end_time":1434.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1430.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have some slides that are white on half and dark on the right half.","index":363,"end_time":1439.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1435.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, should we have a more consistent template that, that these slides are on?","index":364,"end_time":1443.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we have this slide here.","index":365,"end_time":1445.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1443.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have this.","index":366,"end_time":1447.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1446.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So the idea here is, here''s why we created Pito Exchange.","index":367,"end_time":1451.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1448.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Here''s why it''s important to you as the person that''s listening to this.","index":368,"end_time":1455.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1451.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So for the brokers, this is like, what, something that should hook them and say, okay, yes, my clients are dealing with these challenges.","index":369,"end_time":1463.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1455.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"These are the types of conversations I''m having all the time.","index":370,"end_time":1465.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1463.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Here''s what PTO Exchange is.","index":371,"end_time":1468.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1466.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There is a lot that''s on this slide right now.","index":372,"end_time":1470.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1468.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we want to keep all of the different ways that employees can use the platform on the right.","index":373,"end_time":1478.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1470.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I try to strategically pick out some testimonials from users that use our platform in different ways so that they get to feel of, like, real life.","index":374,"end_time":1488.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1478.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we also don''t love just like, a white box with text on it.","index":375,"end_time":1494.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1488.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is too much.","index":376,"end_time":1496.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1494.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But this used to be on another slide.","index":377,"end_time":1497.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1496.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But this is like a good.","index":378,"end_time":1499.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1497.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"These are good statistics for us that need to be somewhere on here.","index":379,"end_time":1505.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1499.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But right now it''s, like, dumped onto the same slide.","index":380,"end_time":1507.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1505.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then we have four different.","index":381,"end_time":1509.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1507.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Essentially, like, they''re kind of like case studies, but it''s short client impact.","index":382,"end_time":1513.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1509.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All different things.","index":383,"end_time":1515.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1514.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Financial wellness, reduction in turnover.","index":384,"end_time":1518.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1515.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"HSA.","index":385,"end_time":1520.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1519.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is retirement.","index":386,"end_time":1522.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1521.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This one is HSA and 529.","index":387,"end_time":1524.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1522.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then this is liability reduction, which then goes into the next slide of the financial benefits of PTO exchange.","index":388,"end_time":1531.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1524.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But again, lots of words that are on here that we want to figure out how to not have.","index":389,"end_time":1537.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1531.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then in here, it''s who is, like, the perfect client for us to give them an idea of, like, who they should have.","index":390,"end_time":1545.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1538.44,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t really love this slide.","index":391,"end_time":1548.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1546.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This slide 8.","index":392,"end_time":1550.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1549.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We can actually take this out if we want to, but Dave had been using this.","index":393,"end_time":1555.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1550.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if you could figure out a way to, like, incorporate this somewhere else.","index":394,"end_time":1558.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1555.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But then it''s.","index":395,"end_time":1559.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1558.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How easy is it to implement?","index":396,"end_time":1561.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1559.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What are some takeaways that your clients.","index":397,"end_time":1564.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1562.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Can ask us for or that we can offer to your clients?","index":398,"end_time":1568.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1566.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because again, this is like a partner that would be bringing it to their client.","index":399,"end_time":1571.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1568.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then again, this is like, too busy.","index":400,"end_time":1574.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1571.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But we want to have Dave''s contact information and then a QR code of where they can go to get more information.","index":401,"end_time":1579.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1574.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it''s like a specific link to a landing page that has their own data on it or their own information on it.","index":402,"end_time":1587.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1579.78,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Case studies, this deck, FAQs, all that stuff is on that part of page.","index":403,"end_time":1593.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1587.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":404,"end_time":1594.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1593.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a lot of.","index":405,"end_time":1595.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1594.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of green background with green text.","index":406,"end_time":1598.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A lot of noise going on.","index":407,"end_time":1601.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1600.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we can definitely do that.","index":408,"end_time":1603.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1601.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think what we''ll do is we''ll come up with, like, here''s how we would reorganize the content or restructure it, like, onto the slide, but also just have like a.","index":409,"end_time":1612.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A template deck of, like, if you want to add a new slide or, like, change the.","index":410,"end_time":1617.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The look and feel of this one.","index":411,"end_time":1618.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''ll just have the several slide.","index":412,"end_time":1620.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1618.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Templates built into it.","index":413,"end_time":1622,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1620.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the one thing, I mean, we need to work within the confines of, like, what Our style guide is.","index":414,"end_time":1628.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1622,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1629.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1628.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And, you know.","index":416,"end_time":1631.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1629.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I''m not the biggest fan of the fonts that we chose, but these are the fonts that we''ve.","index":417,"end_time":1638.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1632.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That we''ve chosen.","index":418,"end_time":1639.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1638.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I actually think.","index":419,"end_time":1641.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1641.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I actually like the fonts themselves, but they''re not standard Microsoft fonts, and when we send it to somebody else, they break and they open it.","index":420,"end_time":1649.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1641.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, they look, you know, it''s.","index":421,"end_time":1651.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1649.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s different.","index":422,"end_time":1651.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So the sizing is different and all of that.","index":423,"end_time":1653.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, like, I do think that''s something, Sam, that maybe we need to think about.","index":424,"end_time":1658.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1653.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, we can have different fonts on our webpage again.","index":425,"end_time":1661.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1658.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I know, like, brand is important and you want it consistent, but, like, that''s a problem.","index":426,"end_time":1665.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1661.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are you sending them PowerPoint files?","index":427,"end_time":1667.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not normally, but, like, I''m doing this presentation for Gallagher, and they were like, send me your slides.","index":428,"end_time":1674.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1669.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And they want to include our slides in their master deck.","index":429,"end_time":1678.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1674.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But when they put our slides in, it looks like shit.","index":430,"end_time":1681.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1678.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And that happens.","index":431,"end_time":1682.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1681.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not a ton, but it happens.","index":432,"end_time":1684.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1683.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Once or twice a month that we''re in a situation like that where someone, like a partner wants us to give them slides.","index":433,"end_time":1692.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1687.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it looks terrible because it''s like the default fonts that Microsoft picks up because they don''t have our font package in there.","index":434,"end_time":1700.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1693.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It just, like, makes it more complicated than it needs to be based on the fonts that we''ve chosen.","index":435,"end_time":1706.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1701.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think there''s a technology.","index":436,"end_time":1709.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.62,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Way that we can fix that rather than, like, change all the fonts.","index":437,"end_time":1714.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1710.98,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":438,"end_time":1717.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1716.58,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t know how.","index":439,"end_time":1723.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1722.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Unless every time we send somebody, we''re also sending them our font package.","index":440,"end_time":1726.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1723.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":441,"end_time":1728.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.75,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I. I would send them a different file type or something like that.","index":442,"end_time":1731.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.47,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Like, I think when you.","index":443,"end_time":1732.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1731.39,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"But they have to be able to take slides and put them into their slide deck.","index":444,"end_time":1736.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1732.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That, that, like.","index":445,"end_time":1738.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1737.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I was just on a call with Gallagher for a thing I''m doing on Monday, and now they''re changing it where they''re going to stop their presentation so I can start my presentation.","index":446,"end_time":1745.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1738.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because our stuff, the sizing is all fucked up when they put our.","index":447,"end_time":1749.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1745.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But they could also just insert, like, a PNG file, like an image file as the whole slide.","index":448,"end_time":1755.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, like, I''ll give you an example.","index":449,"end_time":1762.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1759.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is Gallagher thing.","index":450,"end_time":1762.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1762.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We send them our slides they want to put in our deck, and then we''re working with them on making edits to the.","index":451,"end_time":1768.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1763,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"To what''s in the slide.","index":452,"end_time":1770.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1768.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"In a workshop, we can''t send them, like, a PNG of our thing.","index":453,"end_time":1775.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1771,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":454,"end_time":1775.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1775.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just like we become the difficult one to work with where everybody else is.","index":455,"end_time":1778.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1775.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, here.","index":456,"end_time":1780.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1778.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Here''s our slides.","index":457,"end_time":1780.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1780.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Dump them in.","index":458,"end_time":1781.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1780.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, again, something we need to think about.","index":459,"end_time":1786.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1783.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it is.","index":460,"end_time":1788.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1787.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s.","index":461,"end_time":1789.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1788.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s.","index":462,"end_time":1789.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1789.53,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s annoying.","index":463,"end_time":1790.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1789.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I guess.","index":464,"end_time":1792.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1792.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And like, it''s.","index":465,"end_time":1793.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1792.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''ve even had issues where, like, Dave''s and Dan''s look different than mine because we don''t know if they downloaded the font package correctly.","index":466,"end_time":1801.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1793.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, just something.","index":467,"end_time":1804.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1802.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I know, Serge, like these fonts, but something we need to think about whether it''s worth it.","index":468,"end_time":1810.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1806.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":469,"end_time":1814.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.1,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"We can figure it out.","index":470,"end_time":1815.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1814.06,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":471,"end_time":1815.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1815.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could also see if there''s any Microsoft, like, out of the box fonts that are at least close to it.","index":472,"end_time":1821.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1815.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but that''s not a.","index":473,"end_time":1825.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1823.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s not a new north problem, but that''s a pizza exchange thing we need to think about.","index":474,"end_time":1829.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1825.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":475,"end_time":1832.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1831.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So do you want me to send this to you ahead of time or do you want to wait, see if Dave has any additional.","index":476,"end_time":1836.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1832.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":477,"end_time":1837.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d look, honestly, I might play around with it this weekend before I give it to the designers to work magic.","index":478,"end_time":1841.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1837.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I like finding out how bad I am at design sometimes.","index":479,"end_time":1845.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I also don''t know.","index":480,"end_time":1846.709,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1845.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Does it help, like, when we''re doing this?","index":481,"end_time":1848.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1846.709,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I know one of the things that''s difficult when it''s somebody else doing your slide deck is, like, not knowing really, like, what the.","index":482,"end_time":1855.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1848.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"What the flow is.","index":483,"end_time":1856.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1855.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I don''t know if it makes sense for us to.","index":484,"end_time":1859.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1856.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Do you have a recording of a call where you present to this.","index":485,"end_time":1862.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1860.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not that we.","index":486,"end_time":1864.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1864.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We''re just changing this deck so we don''t, like, you know, we''re not going out, you know, with like, this slide yet.","index":487,"end_time":1872.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1864.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We have a different slide.","index":488,"end_time":1873.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1872.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we don''t have anything that''s exactly like what this is like.","index":489,"end_time":1875.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1873.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":490,"end_time":1876.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1876.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if that.","index":491,"end_time":1878.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1877.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If that''s necessary or if that helps.","index":492,"end_time":1880.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1878.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I think it would be an added benefit.","index":493,"end_time":1882.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1880.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if.","index":494,"end_time":1882.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1882.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you would have any time to just, like, record yourself going through this and how you would present it, because that might influence, like, where we place things or how we color them or things like that.","index":495,"end_time":1893.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1882.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you don''t have time, don''t worry about it.","index":496,"end_time":1895.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":497,"end_time":1899.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1898.96,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"I don''t myself or Dave to have time to do this before Thursday.","index":498,"end_time":1903.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1899.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You said he don''t.","index":499,"end_time":1905.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no.","index":500,"end_time":1906.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1905.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I would think that one of the two of us could just like, go on a zoom and record it and then.","index":501,"end_time":1911.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1906.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that would.","index":502,"end_time":1911.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that would just be an added benefit if you can.","index":503,"end_time":1913.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1912.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That way we have, like, full Context of the end of the life cycle of what this slide deck serves right.","index":504,"end_time":1919.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1913.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":505,"end_time":1920.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1919.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Seeing this, though, I feel like something like this could be a great asset just to have.","index":506,"end_time":1925.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1921.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I know white papers and everything like that are so common and popular in all of marketing, but just a simplified, like, download file of what PTO exchange is, so that if someone from HR comes here, they''re about to hop into a meeting with leadership, they can be like, look at what I downloaded.","index":507,"end_time":1941.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Look at what this company does.","index":508,"end_time":1942.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1941.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Could be another thing we can think through.","index":509,"end_time":1944.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1942.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":510,"end_time":1945.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1945.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":511,"end_time":1949.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1948.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":512,"end_time":1951.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1950.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":513,"end_time":1954.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1953.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, all right, we''ll update those flows.","index":514,"end_time":1957.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1954.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll go ahead and also take a look.","index":515,"end_time":1960.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1958.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just creating a new LinkedIn lead gen form so you don''t see Dan''s name in there.","index":516,"end_time":1963.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1960.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll update the task creation for you that comes from HubSpot to be.","index":517,"end_time":1969.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1965.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Next business day instead of three business days.","index":518,"end_time":1971.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1969.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And don''t worry about changing the link for Dan if it''s a pain.","index":519,"end_time":1976.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1973.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Let''s just, like, be cognizant of that going forward.","index":520,"end_time":1978.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1976.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like, if that''s gonna cause extra work on.","index":521,"end_time":1979.999,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1978.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s not that big a deal.","index":522,"end_time":1981.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1979.999,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s just something to think about.","index":523,"end_time":1983.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1981.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it was when we originally set him up.","index":524,"end_time":1985.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1983.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had one for Dan and we had one for John, and then John left.","index":525,"end_time":1989.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1985.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we figured out a way to, like, make the links dynamically update, so we just kept Dan''s.","index":526,"end_time":1994.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1990.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":527,"end_time":1995.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1994.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":528,"end_time":1995.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1995.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so don''t worry about changing it.","index":529,"end_time":1996.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1995.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":530,"end_time":1997.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1997.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t want to put it.","index":531,"end_time":1998.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1997.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You guys are doing a ton of work.","index":532,"end_time":1999.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1998.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t want you to do any more work.","index":533,"end_time":2000.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1999.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":534,"end_time":2002.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2000.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":535,"end_time":2002.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2002.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, well, keep me posted on those leads that came in.","index":536,"end_time":2006.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2002.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me know if there''s anything else we can provide there.","index":537,"end_time":2008.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2006.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":538,"end_time":2009.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2008.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":539,"end_time":2009.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2009.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":540,"end_time":2011.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2010.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See you, guys.","index":541,"end_time":2011.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2011.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":542,"end_time":2012.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2011.91,"speaker_name":"Sam Lieberman"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":543,"end_time":2012.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2012.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"}],"dateString":"2025-12-04T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87477024015?pwd=gVpnKPDuNsoZ0giaFoA7gicVcI6afV.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,sam@ptoexchange.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,josh@ptoexchange.com","sam@ptoexchange.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","josh@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBDAZC45BGM4XZR7JYWM1Q7T","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Built N8N automation to sync LinkedIn interactions with HubSpot, reducing manual contact creation.","Colin confirmed replies will remove leads from email sequences automatically to prevent overlap.","Sam requested CTA language updates and new benchmark/webinar content promotion sitewide.","Colin and Josh aligned on slide deck redesign to reduce word count and unify presentation style.","Lead routing workflows updated to accommodate staffing changes; Steph will soon take over John''s territory."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Once they reply, we turn off emails.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Let’s not say request a demo... something that’s moving away from demo.","speaker":"Sam Lieberman"},{"quote":"We realize now is nobody looks at these afterwards.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"}],"topics":["automation","delivery","crm","content","leads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-04T20:16:56Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Automation and Contact Management**\n\nThe team finalized automations to capture and update LinkedIn lead data in HubSpot, streamlining follow-up and owner assignment processes.\n\n- **Colin Costigan built a workflow using N8N that automatically creates or updates HubSpot contacts and logs LinkedIn conversations when connection requests are accepted or messages are received** (04:58)  \n    - This automation captures key contact info including email, job title, and LinkedIn URL.  \n    - Colin will implement auto-assignment of contacts to either Josh Reinhard or Dan/Igoe based on which LinkedIn profile initiated the connection.  \n    - The system will also disable email sequences once any type of LinkedIn reply is received, preventing disjointed outreach.  \n    - This forward-looking solution excludes backdating and supports a clean handoff when new sales director Steph starts.\n\n- **Josh Reinhard confirmed the planned transition of LinkedIn lead ownership from him to Steph, mirroring existing territory splits** (08:20)  \n    - Colin can switch the LinkedIn profile sending the connection requests to Steph’s when ready.  \n    - Existing contacts remain under Josh’s ownership, while new leads post-switch will assign to Steph automatically.  \n    - Territory logic in HubSpot will update accordingly without disrupting lead routing.\n\n- **Lead routing refinements addressed geographic inconsistencies to ensure proper assignment** (14:21)  \n    - Colin added alternative location names like “District of Columbia” and “Washington D.C.” to the lead routing rules.  \n    - This prevents misassignments due to naming variations and ensures leads route correctly to assigned reps.\n\n- **Task creation timing for LinkedIn ad leads was adjusted to improve responsiveness** (11:14)  \n    - The follow-up task due date was shortened from **three business days** to **next business day** to accelerate lead engagement.  \n    - Josh acknowledged this change and committed to following up promptly on new tasks.\n\n## **Lead Quality and Lead Generation Insights**\n\nThe team reviewed recent incoming leads from LinkedIn campaigns, confirming quality and engagement trends.\n\n- **Recent leads included senior titles such as Director of Payroll and Executive Director of Global Talent at companies ranging from 3,000 to 5,000 employees** (14:08)  \n    - Josh and Colin agreed these contacts represent solid prospects for PTO Exchange outreach.  \n    - Colin noted several notable companies like NeighborWorks and Worldwide, reinforcing lead list quality.  \n    - Leads entered HubSpot through LinkedIn forms with consistent territory assignment applied.\n\n- **LinkedIn lead generation forms use a shared form name that causes some confusion but will remain unchanged to avoid rebuild complexity** (12:06)  \n    - Josh emphasized avoiding naming forms after individuals to reduce future confusion.  \n    - Colin clarified that territory routing occurs post-submission based on company HQ, regardless of form name.\n\n## **Website Content and User Experience Enhancements**\n\nThe team planned improvements to integration pages and calls-to-action (CTAs) to increase visitor engagement and conversion.\n\n- **Sam Lieberman requested condensing the integrations page by replacing large vertical images with a more compact horizontal design** (15:24)  \n    - Sam shared a Gantt chart to better explain integration workflows and suggested reducing scrolling.  \n    - Colin agreed to explore formatting options and asked for clarification if needed.\n\n- **CTA language will shift from “Request a Demo” to softer phrases like “See the platform in action” or “Understand how it works” to improve user response** (16:12)  \n    - Additional content rows will promote the benchmark report and biweekly webinar to increase lead capture.  \n    - Colin confirmed plans for a Calendly pop-up triggered by benchmark report submissions, customized by user area.\n\n- **Navigation updates will add a prominent benchmark report button to increase visibility and lead generation** (19:29)  \n    - Sam supported this change to drive more traffic to key conversion assets.\n\n## **Sales Presentation Deck Redesign**\n\nJosh and Colin discussed revamping the PTO Exchange partner slide deck for clearer messaging and better engagement.\n\n- **The current deck is too wordy and inconsistent in style, causing confusion and poor integration with partner presentations** (22:03)  \n    - Josh emphasized that slides were designed as leave-behinds but are rarely reviewed post-meeting, so visuals need to be more engaging and less text-heavy.  \n    - Multiple background styles and fonts create a disjointed look; a consistent template and cleaner design are needed.  \n    - The team will build slide templates and reorganize content to emphasize charts, testimonials, key stats, and client impact with minimal text.\n\n- **Font choices cause technical issues when partners like Gallagher incorporate slides into their decks, leading to broken layouts** (27:02)  \n    - Josh highlighted font embedding challenges that distort sizing and appearance without standardized Microsoft fonts.  \n    - Sam suggested exploring alternative file formats or technical fixes to preserve brand fonts without forcing recipients to install packages.\n\n- **Colin proposed recording Josh or Dave presenting the deck to better understand flow and guide redesign priorities** (31:20)  \n    - This would inform slide placement, color use, and content emphasis to enhance audience engagement.  \n    - Josh noted limited availability before Thursday but agreed it would be helpful if feasible.\n\n- **Josh and Colin agreed a simplified, downloadable whitepaper-style asset could complement the deck for HR audiences preparing for leadership meetings** (32:03)  \n    - This document would succinctly summarize PTO Exchange benefits and client data for easy sharing.\n\n## **Ongoing Workflow and System Updates**\n\nThe team committed to continuous improvements in lead workflows and system integrations to support sales and marketing.\n\n- **Colin will update LinkedIn lead generation forms to remove Dan’s name from links and maintain dynamic updates without extra workload** (32:28)  \n    - Josh requested minimizing extra work and accepted leaving existing links as is if changes are costly.\n\n- **Lead owner assignment workflows were adjusted to reflect LinkedIn ad leads’ territories and ensure tasks are created promptly** (10:48)  \n    - Colin ensured tasks are assigned to the appropriate rep based on territory logic after form submission.\n\n- **The team will finalize updates on landing page copy and design tweaks based on Sam’s feedback for a smoother user experience** (15:22)  \n    - Once completed, pages will go live after final approval from Sam and Josh.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Automation","HubSpot Integration","Sales Deck","Lead Routing","Website Optimization","PTO Exchange"],"overview":"- **Lead Automation Finalized:** Automation captures LinkedIn lead data in HubSpot for easier follow-up and assignment. \n\n- **Ownership Transition:** LinkedIn leads will transition from Josh to Steph; territory logic remains intact for new assignments. \n\n- **Lead Routing Improvements:** Geographic name variations added to prevent misassignment of leads, ensuring correct routing. \n\n- **Task Timing Enhanced:** Follow-up tasks for LinkedIn leads shortened to next business day to boost engagement responsiveness. \n\n- **Lead Quality Review:** Recent leads from senior titles confirm strong prospects for outreach, entering through LinkedIn forms with proper territory assignment. \n\n- **Sales Deck Redesign Needed:** Current slide deck is inconsistent and overly wordy; a cleaner, more engaging format is necessary for partner presentations.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nBuild LinkedIn message reply automation to disable email sequences upon any reply (07:03)\nUpdate HubSpot workflow to assign leads to new sales director Steph per assigned territories (08:12)\nCreate new LinkedIn lead gen form excluding personnel names and update routing accordingly (32:28)\nAdjust lead follow-up task due dates in HubSpot to trigger next business day (10:48)\nIncorporate geographical variations in lead routing logic for more accurate territory assignments (14:53)\nImplement website navigation update to add benchmark report button (19:29)\nExecute website copy and design tweaks based on Sam’s feedback, including integrating CTAs for benchmark report and webinar (15:22)\nDevelop area-specific Calendly pop-ups triggered after benchmark report submissions (17:23)\nReview and redesign sales deck content and template style; prepare sample template slides for consistent look and feel (23:50)\nSupport recorded presentation walkthrough if provided by Josh or Dave for better design context (31:20)\nUpdate automation to remove contacts from Smart Lead system upon LinkedIn reply (32:53)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nProvide clarifying content on PTO cash out differentiators for website update (18:13)\nConfirm if recorded presentation walkthrough can be created for design team (31:20)\nSend slide deck and preliminary design feedback ahead of Thursday meeting (21:44)\nMonitor and assess quality of incoming LinkedIn leads and provide feedback (20:14)\n\n**Sam Lieberman**\nCommunicate changes needed for website integration page design and CTA wording to Colin for implementation (15:22)\nCoordinate internally to determine how joint calendars can support scheduling for Steph’s upcoming lead ownership (08:28)\nEvaluate and approve updated designs and copy on website pages once revised (19:28)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"5aa478d6-c050-4f7e-8630-eb1568374d72","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
