-- Meeting: Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North) (2025-12-04 17:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '9e72e3f5-f31f-4c70-870d-79db54b271b2',
    '2025-12-04 17:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KB35HD28SEYBMPD36EW3ERSN',
    'Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)',
    '{"Nina Belina","Edwin Huertas","Misty Smith","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1122,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1',
    '{"id":"01KB35HD28SEYBMPD36EW3ERSN","title":"Weekly Marketing Meeting (Shockoe <> New North)","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Management and Lead Follow-up**\n\nThe team decided to prioritize the **Vibe Coding campaign with LinkedIn ads** while handling **Foxwoods and St. Andrews as email and LinkedIn outreach only** to avoid budget conflicts and maximize impact (14:32).\n\n- **Colin Costigan recommended focusing ads solely on Vibe Coding**, allowing Foxwoods and St. Andrews to run via email and LinkedIn outreach, which Edwin Huertas approved for timing and budget reasons.\n    - The Vibe Coding audience includes **69,000 targeted professionals** like CTOs and founders, generating **5 clicks at a lower-than-usual cost per click** and **3 form openings**.\n    - Colin plans to monitor form opens versus completions and update the lead form messaging to improve conversion rates.\n    - Switching from maximum delivery to **manual bidding** was agreed to control budget pacing and distribution over the month.\n    - The strategy aims to sustain momentum on Vibe Coding while extending reach on other campaigns without ad budget overlap.\n- **Lead follow-up on the Vibe Coding campaign requires immediate attention**, as a lead converted two days ago but no outreach occurred yet.\n    - Edwin Huertas committed to following up directly if no action is taken by Kai, who was expected to respond but has not confirmed.\n    - Misty Smith confirmed no standard response email exists for leads, highlighting a process gap to be addressed.\n    - Colin clarified the lead gen form intentionally lowers barriers by skipping quiz questions and promises follow-up contact, necessitating prompt outreach to maintain interest.\n    - This lead follow-up is critical to capitalize on early campaign success and improve conversion rates.\n\n## **Landing Pages and Creative Assets**\n\nLanding pages for **Foxwoods and St. Andrews** have been updated based on feedback and are live in draft mode on the production site, ready for final review and launch (04:14).\n\n- Colin Costigan confirmed all requested updates from markup were implemented and assets, including the **SBJ ad in three sizes**, are ready for delivery.\n    - Edwin Huertas will confirm the required file formats (JPEG/PNG) and tracking link parameters for ad delivery.\n    - The team agreed to send all finalized assets immediately after the meeting to meet the next week’s deadlines.\n    - Nina Belina and Misty Smith are coordinating with Daniela to supply the **video files for the Zenda landing page**, expected by the end of the day.\n    - Daniela’s past reliability supports confidence in receiving complete assets on time.\n- The landing pages are scheduled to be pushed to production today, enabling campaign launches by Monday, aligning with the preferred email send day to maximize engagement.\n    - This timeline supports quick campaign ramp-up and allows for performance monitoring in the final weeks of the year.\n    - The team emphasized ensuring all creative and technical elements are fully integrated before live deployment.\n\n## **Offboarding and Data Transition**\n\nThe offboarding process will begin shortly with clear communication on access, deliverables, and timelines to ensure a smooth transition (15:13).\n\n- Colin Costigan outlined that final communications will include:\n    - Outstanding invoice balances and payment deadlines.\n    - Dates when Pulse access will be revoked, urging customers to download all deliverables beforehand.\n    - A wrap-up message listing all tools and services that will lose access, such as Paid Reach.\n- Edwin Huertas requested a detailed list of tools and assets affected to prepare for internal transitions.\n    - CSV exports of lead lists will be provided, but email account transfers are not possible due to shared client infrastructure.\n    - The team agreed CSV files suffice for lead data continuation.\n- Colin emphasized ongoing support via Slack for any post-offboarding questions, underscoring the positive working relationship and willingness to assist despite contract closure.\n    - This approach aims to maintain goodwill and reduce operational disruption during the handover.\n\n## **Technical and Operational Improvements**\n\nSignificant progress was made on technical SEO issues and system integrations to improve site performance and tracking (06:03).\n\n- Over **1,000 Google Search Console issues** were addressed, reducing critical errors and improving site health.\n    - The team submitted an updated sitemap to Google and is awaiting recrawl, which depends on Google’s schedule.\n    - Edwin Huertas confirmed scans show a marked reduction in flagged issues, indicating successful remediation.\n- Tracking integration was discussed for ads, with **UTM parameters** planned to monitor traffic sources and campaign effectiveness.\n    - Colin assured the team that tracking links would be included in all outgoing ad files.\n- Operationally, the team aligned on file formats and delivery protocols to streamline asset handoffs and avoid delays.\n    - This includes confirming image formats and ensuring all files are properly packaged in shared Google Drive folders.\n- These improvements support better measurement of campaign impact and provide a foundation for optimizing future marketing efforts.\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed on a clear schedule to finalize campaigns and complete year-end activities to maximize remaining time (15:01).\n\n- Campaign launches for Foxwoods and St. Andrews via email and LinkedIn outreach are set for **Monday**, after landing pages go live today.\n- The Vibe Coding campaign will continue with manual bidding and ongoing data review to refine lead generation.\n- Edwin Huertas will follow up on outstanding leads and asset formats immediately, ensuring no delays in execution.\n- Offboarding communications and access revocation are planned for the coming weeks, with detailed instructions forthcoming from Colin.\n- The team agreed to maintain weekly meetings through the end of the engagement to track progress and resolve issues promptly.\n- This schedule balances campaign momentum with a controlled handover to maintain operational continuity and meet year-end goals.","outline":null,"keywords":["Vibe Coding","LinkedIn Lead Gen","Landing Pages","Campaign Launch","Offboarding","Video Assets"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus:** Prioritize Vibe Coding ads on LinkedIn; Foxwoods and St. Andrews via email to avoid budget overlap.  \n- **Lead Follow-up Urged:** Immediate outreach needed for recent lead; no current follow-up email process in place.  \n- **Landing Page Updates:** Live in draft mode, ready for final review; all creative assets prepared for delivery this week.  \n- **Offboarding Process:** Clear communication on access and deliverables necessary for smooth data transition, including CSV exports for lead lists.  \n- **Technical Improvements:** Resolved over 1,000 Google Search Console issues; ongoing integration of tracking for ads with UTM parameters.  \n- **Next Steps Confirmed:** Campaign launches on Monday; continued weekly meetings to track progress and address any issues.","action_items":"\n**Edwin Huertas**\nFollow up urgently with Kai on the Vibe Coding LinkedIn lead to confirm outreach and next steps (08:50)\nCoordinate sending required links, feedback, and final approval for ads and landing pages to launch campaigns (04:50)\nFollow up on the email response process to define standard messaging for leads not completing the quiz from LinkedIn ads (09:30)\nMonitor campaign performance and assist with any pending questions or adjustments post-launch (14:35)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nPing Daniela to confirm and expedite delivery of video files for Zenda landing page assets into the Google Drive folder, aiming for end of day delivery (07:20)\nFollow up with Kai regarding lead outreach and ensure visibility of task by tagging her in Slack (11:20)\nSupport coordination with Daniela for any additional asset needs and confirm status updates (17:40)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare links for review of updated Foxwoods and St. Andrews landing pages and SVJ ad files with UTM parameters included (05:35)\nSubmit wrap-up message and offboarding checklist including tool access revocation, final invoices, and deliverables handoff (15:00)\nCoordinate campaign launch readiness ensuring landing pages go live today and outreach starts Monday (17:20)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nProvide and confirm sender files and any other Figma file updates needed for campaigns (17:50)\n"},"duration":18.700000762939453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":1,"name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"id":2,"name":"Misty Smith"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Oh, for the footer they like.","index":0,"end_time":15.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think Kylie asked for, like, the image, but there''s no version that''s like, full width of the monitored image.","index":1,"end_time":23.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":24.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.24,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It.","index":3,"end_time":26.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":25.77,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Nina, how are you?","index":4,"end_time":76.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.3,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"How are you doing, Edwin?","index":5,"end_time":78.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":77.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":6,"end_time":80.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.99,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Pretty good.","index":7,"end_time":81.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.79,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That was Thanksgiving.","index":8,"end_time":84.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":82.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanksgiving.","index":9,"end_time":85.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.03,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It was good.","index":10,"end_time":87.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.55,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":87.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":87.23,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I had lots of fun.","index":12,"end_time":88.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.51,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Lots of food, of course.","index":13,"end_time":89.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":14,"end_time":91.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":90.87,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, it was great.","index":15,"end_time":92.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Spend the afternoon at the friend''s house.","index":16,"end_time":94.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.71,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And that''s what.","index":17,"end_time":96.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.43,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s what normally.","index":18,"end_time":97.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.31,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Or Thanksgiving is the next day.","index":19,"end_time":98.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.15,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Friday, we.","index":20,"end_time":100.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.67,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, we didn''t do much.","index":21,"end_time":102.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We stay home.","index":22,"end_time":103.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.63,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And then Saturday, had to.","index":23,"end_time":105.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Fly down here to Ecuador.","index":24,"end_time":108.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.92,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"My.","index":25,"end_time":109.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.48,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"My mom had a planned surgery that I.","index":26,"end_time":113,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.8,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They wanted me to be here, so I came over down to Ecuador.","index":27,"end_time":117,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.64,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So I''ve been traveling in.","index":28,"end_time":119.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":117.32,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"In hospitals and that kind of stuff until last night.","index":29,"end_time":122.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.6,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So finally, I hope everything''s all right.","index":30,"end_time":125.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":122.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":126.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":126.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":126.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That you''re able to get some.","index":33,"end_time":127.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":126.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Catch up on some rest maybe from all that travel as well.","index":34,"end_time":130.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":127.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":131.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Finally.","index":36,"end_time":131.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yes.","index":37,"end_time":131.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.69,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s been.","index":38,"end_time":132.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"It''s been a kind of crazy four days.","index":39,"end_time":134.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":132.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":40,"end_time":134.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":134.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bad.","index":41,"end_time":135.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":134.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How about you?","index":42,"end_time":137.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Everything good with the Thanksgiving weekend?","index":43,"end_time":140.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":137.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, it was.","index":44,"end_time":142.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":141.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a good time.","index":45,"end_time":143.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":142.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got to take my daughter on a plane for the first time, so that was an adventure.","index":46,"end_time":146.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":143.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but it was.","index":47,"end_time":148.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":147.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a mixed bag of, like, really planned and having to do a lot of things and then, like, towards the latter half, being able to relax a little bit.","index":48,"end_time":157.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":150.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":49,"end_time":158.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Right.","index":50,"end_time":158.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.22,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Wow.","index":51,"end_time":159.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.86,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I hope that she was okay during the flight.","index":52,"end_time":163.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":159.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No crying?","index":53,"end_time":163.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.02,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No.","index":54,"end_time":163.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.66,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Like.","index":55,"end_time":164.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":164.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":164.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, she got a little cold, of course, because everyone gets sick on planes.","index":57,"end_time":169.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":164.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But no, she actually did pretty well.","index":58,"end_time":171.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":169.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":59,"end_time":172.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":60,"end_time":173.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.46,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hi, Misty.","index":61,"end_time":174.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":62,"end_time":174.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":174.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":63,"end_time":175.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Doing all right, and you?","index":64,"end_time":176.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":175.58,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":65,"end_time":177.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you have a good Thanksgiving?","index":66,"end_time":178.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":67,"end_time":181.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.02,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, it was.","index":68,"end_time":182.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.46,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"My grandmother''s funeral was Saturday, so most of my Thanksgiving was spent prepping for that and doing things, but got to see all my kids were there for.","index":69,"end_time":193.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":182.62,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"In town, which was great because my oldest was not supposed to be here.","index":70,"end_time":197.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.64,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I got to see my brother.","index":71,"end_time":199.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"He flew in from Arizona.","index":72,"end_time":200.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":199.28,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Got to see lots of all my family, basically.","index":73,"end_time":203.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.12,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Which was.","index":74,"end_time":204.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.6,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Which.","index":75,"end_time":204.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.08,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That part was really nice.","index":76,"end_time":205.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.36,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And she was 104, so totally.","index":77,"end_time":209.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.08,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It was her time, so.","index":78,"end_time":212.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.76,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":79,"end_time":212.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.24,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So it was, you know, bitter, bittersweet.","index":80,"end_time":215.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.72,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It wasn''t very restful, let''s put it that way.","index":81,"end_time":217.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":82,"end_time":218.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":217.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":83,"end_time":219.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But still, lots to give thanks for.","index":84,"end_time":221.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":219.27,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So, you know, that was.","index":85,"end_time":222.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.51,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That part was.","index":86,"end_time":223.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That was nice.","index":87,"end_time":225.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":223.71,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":88,"end_time":225.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it was nice to get a surprise from someone you weren''t expecting to see.","index":89,"end_time":228.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":225.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, exactly.","index":90,"end_time":229.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":91,"end_time":229.949,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Got to spend.","index":92,"end_time":230.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.949,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"He came in even early.","index":93,"end_time":232.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.79,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"He came in the day before Thanksgiving, so we get extra time with him, which was fantastic.","index":94,"end_time":238.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":232.07,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":95,"end_time":239.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":238.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, I was out all last week, and I know Nina sent over some messages.","index":96,"end_time":243.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":240.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll go through the assets that are ready today.","index":97,"end_time":246.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":243.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then anything that''s on your side, of course.","index":98,"end_time":249.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":247.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, can everyone see my screen?","index":99,"end_time":253.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":100,"end_time":254.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":253.84,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":101,"end_time":254.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.24,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":102,"end_time":255.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":254.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I also got a new computer on Sunday, so just making sure that everything''s operating smoothly.","index":103,"end_time":260.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":255.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did update all the landing pages after all the feedback that came in through markup.","index":104,"end_time":266.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":262,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So Foxwoods and St. Andrews landing pages were updated.","index":105,"end_time":269.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re on the staging site.","index":106,"end_time":272.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":270.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They are live on the.","index":107,"end_time":273.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":272.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the actual production site.","index":108,"end_time":274.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":273.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re in draft mode, of course, but everything was implemented in here that was left in markup.","index":109,"end_time":278.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And for the Foxwoods page as well.","index":110,"end_time":282.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":280.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As well as.","index":111,"end_time":285.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know I sent this over the other day, the SBJ ad.","index":112,"end_time":289.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":285.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in that PDF that they shared, there was, like three different sizes.","index":113,"end_time":292.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":289.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was like a logo or a banner at the top and then a larger banner and then the actual ad itself.","index":114,"end_time":298.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":292.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all three of those are in that file.","index":115,"end_time":300.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":298.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":116,"end_time":303.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.59,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"What do you need, Edwin, to be able to send this to them?","index":117,"end_time":308.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.03,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"What kind of file do you need?","index":118,"end_time":310.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.15,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Or are you.","index":119,"end_time":311.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.43,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I mean, I think this is good.","index":120,"end_time":312.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Unless you have feedback there.","index":121,"end_time":315.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.87,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I know you need to send that by next week.","index":122,"end_time":318.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.79,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"This time next week.","index":123,"end_time":320.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":124,"end_time":321.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":320.67,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But if you obviously get them to them early, that''s, I''m sure, not the end of the world.","index":125,"end_time":325.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.54,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"No, I think this is good.","index":126,"end_time":330.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I think the ads are good.","index":127,"end_time":331.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"What I''m.","index":128,"end_time":331.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The format.","index":129,"end_time":332.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I think it was in that email.","index":130,"end_time":334.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.66,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it''s like a JPEG or a png.","index":131,"end_time":336.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":334.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":132,"end_time":336.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":336.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check.","index":133,"end_time":337.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":336.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would do.","index":134,"end_time":338.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.299,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I would need that.","index":135,"end_time":339.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The links that we need to use, I think there''s also.","index":136,"end_time":342.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"They also mentioned format.","index":137,"end_time":346.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.5,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No.","index":138,"end_time":346.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"1.","index":139,"end_time":346.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.66,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Not the format, but the link itself.","index":140,"end_time":348.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And if we want to include some tracking, I don''t know if that''s part of the.","index":141,"end_time":352.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.26,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll put in some UCM parameters on that.","index":142,"end_time":354.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":352.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":143,"end_time":357.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.82,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That was.","index":144,"end_time":357.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":357.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what we needed.","index":145,"end_time":358.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.86,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":146,"end_time":359.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":358.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send that over when we hop off of this call.","index":147,"end_time":362.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":359.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":148,"end_time":363.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":362.82,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We''ve also been going through still with all of the Google search console stuff.","index":149,"end_time":367.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":363.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we addressed over a thousand issues that were in there.","index":150,"end_time":369.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unfortunately, with Google, as I''m sure you guys are aware, we''re kind of at mercy of when they crawl it again.","index":151,"end_time":375.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":370.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we submitted the site map.","index":152,"end_time":376.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve followed up with them to try and rush it, but they.","index":153,"end_time":379.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":376.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, it''s up to them when they just address the new sitemap.","index":154,"end_time":383.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":379.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that.","index":155,"end_time":385.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.78,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That''s going to help.","index":156,"end_time":385.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.02,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I ran another scan with kind of what I was using.","index":157,"end_time":392.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.42,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I noticed the reduction of.","index":158,"end_time":393.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.02,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"There''s still about.","index":159,"end_time":394.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.5,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t know if you know, there''s going to be a few.","index":160,"end_time":397.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m not this.","index":161,"end_time":398.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.22,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"The 1000 plus was a big problem.","index":162,"end_time":401.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"At least looked like it was a big problem, but it was not a lot last time I checked.","index":163,"end_time":407.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.3,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So yeah, hopefully it should.","index":164,"end_time":409.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.92,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Happen soon.","index":165,"end_time":411.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.96,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":166,"end_time":413.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":412.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we want to talk to the Zenda landing page.","index":167,"end_time":418.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":415.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Nina, feel free to hop in here as well because I know that some things were communicated while I was out.","index":168,"end_time":424.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":418.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re currently developing the webpage.","index":169,"end_time":426,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":424.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Nina, you noted that we need the video element that was included in that figma file is a placeholder.","index":170,"end_time":430.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":426.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":171,"end_time":431.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Daniela said that she would send a Google Drive folder and videos for.","index":172,"end_time":436.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"To complete the webpage templates.","index":173,"end_time":439.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So I was just wondering, could you give us some context of what''s expected from.","index":174,"end_time":444.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"What we need to expect from Daniela with additional files?","index":175,"end_time":449.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I will send her.","index":176,"end_time":451.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.4,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''ll ping her right now and ask her to.","index":177,"end_time":453.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":451.44,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Well, I''ll ping her in this channel so she knows where to put.","index":178,"end_time":456.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.96,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Put the information.","index":179,"end_time":457.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.36,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But.","index":180,"end_time":457.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.52,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"But I''ll say Daniela.","index":181,"end_time":459.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.91,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Oh, that''s not it.","index":182,"end_time":462.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.79,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But yeah, so I''m.","index":183,"end_time":464.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I think that she''s already got that stuff ready.","index":184,"end_time":467.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.47,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"But we.","index":185,"end_time":468.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":467.55,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You should.","index":186,"end_time":468.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.11,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We can promise that to you by the end of the day.","index":187,"end_time":470.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.79,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"How about that?","index":188,"end_time":471.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I do believe she.","index":189,"end_time":473.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.95,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"If she has it ready, she can package it up or get it downloaded and put onto the drive to give you a link by the end of the day.","index":190,"end_time":480.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.99,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"If for some reason it''s not ready, meaning she hasn''t created it yet.","index":191,"end_time":483.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.51,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Which doesn''t make sense to me because I think she''s got all of her part done.","index":192,"end_time":488.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Then it might be a little longer.","index":193,"end_time":490.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":489.09,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Either way, either expect to hear from her or me today.","index":194,"end_time":493.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":195,"end_time":494.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":493.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Neither update is good.","index":196,"end_time":495.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just in the small projects we''ve worked with Daniela on.","index":197,"end_time":498.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":495.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She''s always been on top of it, so I''d be surprised if she doesn''t have it ready.","index":198,"end_time":502.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":498.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":199,"end_time":504.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds great.","index":200,"end_time":505.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":504.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll send over the links to review the updated landing pages and everything.","index":201,"end_time":510.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":506.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll send over the SVJ ad.","index":202,"end_time":511.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One thing I do want to talk about.","index":203,"end_time":513.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":512.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had that lead convert on the LinkedIn ad for the vibe coding.","index":204,"end_time":518.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not sure if.","index":205,"end_time":521.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":519.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me check the activities.","index":206,"end_time":522.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":521.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doesn''t look like anyone''s done anything here.","index":207,"end_time":527.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":524.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you guys check it out?","index":208,"end_time":529.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":527.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you take a look at the person who converted?","index":209,"end_time":532.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I did Not.","index":210,"end_time":533.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":532.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I think that was between you and Kai.","index":211,"end_time":535.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Misty, I don''t typically handle this, but Kai had said she was going to reach out.","index":212,"end_time":540.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.61,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know that she.","index":213,"end_time":541.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know that she has.","index":214,"end_time":543.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.85,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"She asked, hey, is there tip.","index":215,"end_time":545.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.61,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Is there a typical response email that we send when we, when we hear.","index":216,"end_time":549.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.13,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"When we hear back from people?","index":217,"end_time":551.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And I was like, I don''t think so, but I would check.","index":218,"end_time":553.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":551.17,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''ll follow up with her to make sure she''s.","index":219,"end_time":555.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.93,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"She''s got this.","index":220,"end_time":556.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.57,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"She''s tackling this.","index":221,"end_time":557.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.49,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think she''s on tomorrow.","index":222,"end_time":560.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.97,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Right.","index":223,"end_time":560.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"She''s.","index":224,"end_time":562.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.77,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I think she''s.","index":225,"end_time":563.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I think she''s on in the morning.","index":226,"end_time":565.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.97,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":227,"end_time":566.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If you don''t hear anything.","index":228,"end_time":568.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Let me.","index":229,"end_time":570.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m guessing that''s what she was asking.","index":230,"end_time":573.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.91,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"What''s the information?","index":231,"end_time":574.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":573.35,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"This is from the LinkedIn that went to our website.","index":232,"end_time":577.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.87,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Fill out the form.","index":233,"end_time":578.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":577.75,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"No.","index":234,"end_time":579.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":579.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we swapped it to a lead gen form to lessen the barrier of someone having to click on the ad, then go to the landing page and fill out a form.","index":235,"end_time":586.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":579.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I sent the form details like what they filled out and basically what the form says.","index":236,"end_time":591.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":586.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t answer the vibe coding questions because we wanted to just again, make it less of a barrier, but they expressed interest in it.","index":237,"end_time":597.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":591.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so the confirmation message that pops up after is like, we''ll be in touch with you to talk about vibe coding.","index":238,"end_time":603.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":597.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":239,"end_time":604.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Did you put it on the channel?","index":240,"end_time":607.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s all in Slack.","index":241,"end_time":610.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":607.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let me.","index":242,"end_time":610.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":610.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll follow up with that.","index":243,"end_time":612.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If.","index":244,"end_time":613.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Mr.","index":245,"end_time":614.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":613.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If you don''t hear anything from Kai tomorrow, I mean, it''s too.","index":246,"end_time":617.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":614.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"When did this.","index":247,"end_time":618.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":617.81,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m sorry, I''ve been you.","index":248,"end_time":620.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.53,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"He said Tuesday at 2:12pm and she responded on yesterday at 10:14.","index":249,"end_time":627.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.37,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Because she''s like, hey, I''ll take the next steps and put together the document because she thought he did the quiz.","index":250,"end_time":634.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.26,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And then Colin responded back at 10 minutes later, nine minutes later, saying, no, they didn''t take the quiz.","index":251,"end_time":641.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":634.74,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"They just filled out the lead gen form.","index":252,"end_time":643.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.7,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And she asked me, do we have a standard email to send to these leads?","index":253,"end_time":647.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.66,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I was like, I don''t think so, but I''d check.","index":254,"end_time":648.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.22,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think we have a standard.","index":255,"end_time":651.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.66,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"We set up the process flow to be like, hey, here''s your quiz.","index":256,"end_time":656.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.34,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"And you know, okay, but if you.","index":257,"end_time":660.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.89,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Want to just tackle that, I''ll follow up.","index":258,"end_time":662.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll follow up.","index":259,"end_time":663.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m just gonna put up.","index":260,"end_time":664.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.45,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right.","index":261,"end_time":667.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.45,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, so you''re gonna send.","index":262,"end_time":669.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":668.25,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"You''re gonna email him and just see what''s going on.","index":263,"end_time":671.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.57,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":264,"end_time":672.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":671.77,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"And then if you hear anything from K tomorrow.","index":265,"end_time":674.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"She did already or something.","index":266,"end_time":675.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.09,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We''ll figure it out.","index":267,"end_time":677.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.17,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Edwin is going to follow up on this lead if assuming you haven''t already because you don''t see anything in Hub, but.","index":268,"end_time":698.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.21,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Okay, I, I. Oh, let me tag Kai in this so that she''s.","index":269,"end_time":704.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.01,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"It''s clear.","index":270,"end_time":704.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.01,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"She.","index":271,"end_time":705.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":704.65,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"She sees it.","index":272,"end_time":705.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.05,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":273,"end_time":708.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":707.93,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"She''ll see it sometime today, I imagine.","index":274,"end_time":713.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.66,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Doesn''t mean she''ll respond, but she''s usually checks.","index":275,"end_time":716.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.1,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, we need to follow up with this right away.","index":276,"end_time":718.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, two days ago.","index":277,"end_time":720.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.74,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, I sent it, like, I think within 10 minutes of them filling out the form.","index":278,"end_time":724.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":720.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":279,"end_time":726.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.54,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay.","index":280,"end_time":726.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Well, we''ll figure out.","index":281,"end_time":728.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":282,"end_time":728.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.34,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":283,"end_time":730.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":729.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And one reason I wanted to bring that up is because, you know, we did have a lead come in this week on the vibe coding campaign we have been talking about, and we made designs for this Foxwoods and St. Andrews campaign.","index":284,"end_time":739.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":730.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We really don''t recommend having both campaigns going because we would just run into the same budget constraints that we were previously.","index":285,"end_time":746.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":740.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we can do, one avenue is we can launch the St. Andrews Foxwoods campaign as purely email and LinkedIn outreach with no ads, and keep the ads dedicated to vibe coding.","index":286,"end_time":759.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":747.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can go completely Foxwoods St. Andrews.","index":287,"end_time":762.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":759.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would recommend Avenue one, since we''ve seen a result come through on the Vibe coding, and I think it''s a pretty timely offer.","index":288,"end_time":767.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":762.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I agree.","index":289,"end_time":770.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.81,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I think that that would be ideal for now.","index":290,"end_time":772.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Let''s go with email for the other ones.","index":291,"end_time":775.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.33,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":292,"end_time":776.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":775.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":293,"end_time":777.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":777.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And once I send over those, if you guys just give the final thumbs up, then we can launch that.","index":294,"end_time":780.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":777.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tomorrow''s not a good day to send emails, so we can get that live Monday.","index":295,"end_time":783.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":780.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, everything''s ready to just hit go.","index":296,"end_time":785.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":783.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":297,"end_time":786.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.21,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":298,"end_time":788.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.05,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Then looking at some metrics.","index":299,"end_time":792.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":790.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the vibe getting campaign, the audience that we have built for that is 69,000 people based on job titles, industries and their interest.","index":300,"end_time":799.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":793.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Um, with the budget, we''re, we''re trying to get as deep as we can into that.","index":301,"end_time":804.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, LinkedIn is very competitive, but it is a very strong B2B marketing channel.","index":302,"end_time":809.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":804.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re getting in front of CTOs, VP of product and founders.","index":303,"end_time":812.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":809.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously, we had the founder of that wicked cool software that converted.","index":304,"end_time":815.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":813.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Saw five clicks, actually at a lower cost per click than we''ve been seeing in the past few weeks.","index":305,"end_time":821.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":817.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So trending in the right direction there.","index":306,"end_time":823.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":821.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And three of those actually opened up the form.","index":307,"end_time":826.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in the next week or so, I want to keep watching the data.","index":308,"end_time":830.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":827.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we have more opens without fills, then I Want to update the form to just give a little bit more of what they can expect of the process.","index":309,"end_time":837.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":830.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that''ll increase the likelihood to actually fill out the form.","index":310,"end_time":840.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":837.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then yeah, we pretty much already went through these recommendations but we''re going to switch from maximum delivery to manual bidding just so we can have complete control over the budget and how we''re spreading it over the month.","index":311,"end_time":857.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":845.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And based on what we had just agreed on.","index":312,"end_time":861.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll, we''ll keep the vibe coding campaign going, monitor, update the lead gen form and then we''ll spin up the St. Andrews and Foxwoods email campaigns and LinkedIn outreach.","index":313,"end_time":870.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":861.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":314,"end_time":872.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.11,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That is actually everything that we had.","index":315,"end_time":875.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":873.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that Nina had sent over a few updates so I wanted to recap on all those from last week and just make sure we''re all good to get these campaigns live and out into the market.","index":316,"end_time":884.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":876.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":317,"end_time":885.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":885.6,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"So remind me what''s.","index":318,"end_time":887,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":885.92,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know we''re two weeks before we finish the year.","index":319,"end_time":892.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"What''s the plan for the next couple weeks?","index":320,"end_time":895.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.44,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I talked to Justin a few minutes ago about shutting that well off boarding process.","index":321,"end_time":901.359,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.84,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yep.","index":322,"end_time":902.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":901.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Guessing some of that time is going to dedicate it to that.","index":323,"end_time":905.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.12,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Can you just give me an idea what that means boarding and what is next step for us to complete this campaign?","index":324,"end_time":912.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":906.64,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":913.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":913.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why I want to get these campaigns going like right now so we at least have some Runway of those going.","index":326,"end_time":918.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":913.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But the off roading process we will.","index":327,"end_time":920.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll send an email or slack message that outlines like you know, points the balance when your last invoice is coming through, things like that when the last day you''ll have access to Pulse to download anything that we''ve created for you guys to date.","index":328,"end_time":934.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":920.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ll all be in that final deliverables tab there.","index":329,"end_time":936.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But at any point I''m also just open if you guys slack me if you have a question or if you need something not just shutting the valve off to you guys it''s been a great relationship so far so don''t want to ruin anything there.","index":330,"end_time":948.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":938.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah but basically we''ll just send a wrap up and say like here''s invoices, points, balance and when you''ll have access to Pulse revoked so that you download everything before then.","index":331,"end_time":959.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":949.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''Re on mute.","index":332,"end_time":963.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":962.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Edwin, I know we have a few things with the emails, domains, lists, anything that you can think we can use.","index":333,"end_time":973.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s going to be impulse does all of those details or I know yeah going to be there but I know it''s files and things like that.","index":334,"end_time":979.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.16,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, we can share the.","index":335,"end_time":981.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":980.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The CSVs of the lists.","index":336,"end_time":983.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":981.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have those readily accessible.","index":337,"end_time":984.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":983.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The emails are a little bit more difficult because we purchased those through our account and we can''t like transfer access without giving access to all of the emails we create for all of our clients.","index":338,"end_time":994.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":985.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":339,"end_time":996.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":996.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s fine.","index":340,"end_time":998.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can do a CSV file of the leads.","index":341,"end_time":1000.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":998.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"CSV files are good.","index":342,"end_time":1001.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.41,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"All right, so connections to other tools, things like that.","index":343,"end_time":1005.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.49,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know we have paid reach access.","index":344,"end_time":1007.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.61,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I''m guessing all of those will be shut down.","index":345,"end_time":1009.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.53,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I just want to.","index":346,"end_time":1009.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.21,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"If you have a list of things that you guys had access to this.","index":347,"end_time":1013.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.09,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We''re not going to have access after this date.","index":348,"end_time":1015.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"That way we know.","index":349,"end_time":1016.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.78,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hey, we need to go in and do whatever we need to do.","index":350,"end_time":1018.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.42,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can.","index":351,"end_time":1020.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1019.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll include that in the.","index":352,"end_time":1021.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1020.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In the wrap up message that we''ll send.","index":353,"end_time":1023.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just all the tools.","index":354,"end_time":1024.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1023.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":355,"end_time":1024.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, reach will be revoked because again, that''s tied into our parent account, so.","index":356,"end_time":1029.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":357,"end_time":1030.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1029.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":358,"end_time":1030.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I don''t have any more questions right in this second.","index":359,"end_time":1033.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.619,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"I know.","index":360,"end_time":1034.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.62,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We want to make sure that those pages are out.","index":361,"end_time":1036.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.66,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Email campaigns, all of these work out and then.","index":362,"end_time":1039.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.14,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, whenever we get to the point of.","index":363,"end_time":1041.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.94,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Okay, what else we need to get back on or play just, you know, we''ll follow up that with email questions after that.","index":364,"end_time":1047.539,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.1,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, sure thing.","index":365,"end_time":1049.539,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.659,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we''re all going to the landing pages, they can go live in the push to production today and then we can turn those campaigns on for email and LinkedIn outreach on Monday.","index":366,"end_time":1059.619,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1049.699,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":367,"end_time":1061.619,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.659,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":368,"end_time":1062.259,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.699,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Misty, anything else from your end?","index":369,"end_time":1064.179,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1062.659,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, other than Daniella gave a thumbs up to the slack about posting, giving the link to the drive.","index":370,"end_time":1070.579,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1065.139,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"So I think we should not asap.","index":371,"end_time":1073.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.579,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":372,"end_time":1074.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1074.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Nina, keep me saying anything I''m missing.","index":373,"end_time":1076.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1074.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, no, not really.","index":374,"end_time":1079.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, for the sender file, we have the FIG file.","index":375,"end_time":1082.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And if you have any context that you need to share that''s new, please do.","index":376,"end_time":1087.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":377,"end_time":1089.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1087.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, as always, thank you all so much for your time.","index":378,"end_time":1092.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1089.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, bittersweet might be.","index":379,"end_time":1095.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1094.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Might be the word for it, right, that you used Missy earlier.","index":380,"end_time":1098.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1095.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s been so awesome working with you guys.","index":381,"end_time":1100.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1098.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully an opportunity opens up in the future as well, but hoping to see what impact we can get in these last few weeks with these campaigns.","index":382,"end_time":1108.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1101.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":383,"end_time":1109.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.65,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you.","index":384,"end_time":1110.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.29,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Well, see you next week, I guess.","index":385,"end_time":1111.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.13,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Hub, right?","index":386,"end_time":1111.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.25,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":387,"end_time":1112.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.73,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"},{"text":"We''ll still have our meeting next week.","index":388,"end_time":1113.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":389,"end_time":1114.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.77,"speaker_name":"Misty Smith"},{"text":"All right, Colleen.","index":390,"end_time":1116.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.93,"speaker_name":"Edwin Huertas"}],"dateString":"2025-12-04T17:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88965765122?pwd=mPL1aFvxXYMYFRYawSa6f5Ez7s5Uv6.1","participants":["kylee.anger@shockoe.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,edwin@shockoe.com,misty.smith@shockoe.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","kylee.anger@shockoe.com","edwin@shockoe.com","misty.smith@shockoe.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KB35HD28SEYBMPD36EW3ERSN","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Pushed updated Foxwoods and St. Andrews landing pages to staging and draft mode on production.","Aligned to prioritize Vibe Coding campaign for paid ads based on recent lead conversion.","Over 1,000 Google Search Console issues resolved; sitemap resubmitted pending Google crawl.","Confirmed deliverables timeline and wrap-up plan for offboarding with documented asset access.","Lead gen process clarified; Edwin to follow up with LinkedIn lead if no update from Kai."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We addressed over a thousand issues that were in there.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I agree. I think that that would be ideal for now.","speaker":"Edwin Huertas"},{"quote":"We really don''t recommend having both campaigns going because we would just run into the same budget constraints.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","ads","offboarding","handoff"],"model":"gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-04T20:45:12Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Management and Lead Follow-up**\n\nThe team decided to prioritize the **Vibe Coding campaign with LinkedIn ads** while handling **Foxwoods and St. Andrews as email and LinkedIn outreach only** to avoid budget conflicts and maximize impact (14:32).\n\n- **Colin Costigan recommended focusing ads solely on Vibe Coding**, allowing Foxwoods and St. Andrews to run via email and LinkedIn outreach, which Edwin Huertas approved for timing and budget reasons.\n    - The Vibe Coding audience includes **69,000 targeted professionals** like CTOs and founders, generating **5 clicks at a lower-than-usual cost per click** and **3 form openings**.\n    - Colin plans to monitor form opens versus completions and update the lead form messaging to improve conversion rates.\n    - Switching from maximum delivery to **manual bidding** was agreed to control budget pacing and distribution over the month.\n    - The strategy aims to sustain momentum on Vibe Coding while extending reach on other campaigns without ad budget overlap.\n- **Lead follow-up on the Vibe Coding campaign requires immediate attention**, as a lead converted two days ago but no outreach occurred yet.\n    - Edwin Huertas committed to following up directly if no action is taken by Kai, who was expected to respond but has not confirmed.\n    - Misty Smith confirmed no standard response email exists for leads, highlighting a process gap to be addressed.\n    - Colin clarified the lead gen form intentionally lowers barriers by skipping quiz questions and promises follow-up contact, necessitating prompt outreach to maintain interest.\n    - This lead follow-up is critical to capitalize on early campaign success and improve conversion rates.\n\n## **Landing Pages and Creative Assets**\n\nLanding pages for **Foxwoods and St. Andrews** have been updated based on feedback and are live in draft mode on the production site, ready for final review and launch (04:14).\n\n- Colin Costigan confirmed all requested updates from markup were implemented and assets, including the **SBJ ad in three sizes**, are ready for delivery.\n    - Edwin Huertas will confirm the required file formats (JPEG/PNG) and tracking link parameters for ad delivery.\n    - The team agreed to send all finalized assets immediately after the meeting to meet the next week’s deadlines.\n    - Nina Belina and Misty Smith are coordinating with Daniela to supply the **video files for the Zenda landing page**, expected by the end of the day.\n    - Daniela’s past reliability supports confidence in receiving complete assets on time.\n- The landing pages are scheduled to be pushed to production today, enabling campaign launches by Monday, aligning with the preferred email send day to maximize engagement.\n    - This timeline supports quick campaign ramp-up and allows for performance monitoring in the final weeks of the year.\n    - The team emphasized ensuring all creative and technical elements are fully integrated before live deployment.\n\n## **Offboarding and Data Transition**\n\nThe offboarding process will begin shortly with clear communication on access, deliverables, and timelines to ensure a smooth transition (15:13).\n\n- Colin Costigan outlined that final communications will include:\n    - Outstanding invoice balances and payment deadlines.\n    - Dates when Pulse access will be revoked, urging customers to download all deliverables beforehand.\n    - A wrap-up message listing all tools and services that will lose access, such as Paid Reach.\n- Edwin Huertas requested a detailed list of tools and assets affected to prepare for internal transitions.\n    - CSV exports of lead lists will be provided, but email account transfers are not possible due to shared client infrastructure.\n    - The team agreed CSV files suffice for lead data continuation.\n- Colin emphasized ongoing support via Slack for any post-offboarding questions, underscoring the positive working relationship and willingness to assist despite contract closure.\n    - This approach aims to maintain goodwill and reduce operational disruption during the handover.\n\n## **Technical and Operational Improvements**\n\nSignificant progress was made on technical SEO issues and system integrations to improve site performance and tracking (06:03).\n\n- Over **1,000 Google Search Console issues** were addressed, reducing critical errors and improving site health.\n    - The team submitted an updated sitemap to Google and is awaiting recrawl, which depends on Google’s schedule.\n    - Edwin Huertas confirmed scans show a marked reduction in flagged issues, indicating successful remediation.\n- Tracking integration was discussed for ads, with **UTM parameters** planned to monitor traffic sources and campaign effectiveness.\n    - Colin assured the team that tracking links would be included in all outgoing ad files.\n- Operationally, the team aligned on file formats and delivery protocols to streamline asset handoffs and avoid delays.\n    - This includes confirming image formats and ensuring all files are properly packaged in shared Google Drive folders.\n- These improvements support better measurement of campaign impact and provide a foundation for optimizing future marketing efforts.\n\n## **Timeline and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed on a clear schedule to finalize campaigns and complete year-end activities to maximize remaining time (15:01).\n\n- Campaign launches for Foxwoods and St. Andrews via email and LinkedIn outreach are set for **Monday**, after landing pages go live today.\n- The Vibe Coding campaign will continue with manual bidding and ongoing data review to refine lead generation.\n- Edwin Huertas will follow up on outstanding leads and asset formats immediately, ensuring no delays in execution.\n- Offboarding communications and access revocation are planned for the coming weeks, with detailed instructions forthcoming from Colin.\n- The team agreed to maintain weekly meetings through the end of the engagement to track progress and resolve issues promptly.\n- This schedule balances campaign momentum with a controlled handover to maintain operational continuity and meet year-end goals.","outline":null,"keywords":["Vibe Coding","LinkedIn Lead Gen","Landing Pages","Campaign Launch","Offboarding","Video Assets"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus:** Prioritize Vibe Coding ads on LinkedIn; Foxwoods and St. Andrews via email to avoid budget overlap.  \n- **Lead Follow-up Urged:** Immediate outreach needed for recent lead; no current follow-up email process in place.  \n- **Landing Page Updates:** Live in draft mode, ready for final review; all creative assets prepared for delivery this week.  \n- **Offboarding Process:** Clear communication on access and deliverables necessary for smooth data transition, including CSV exports for lead lists.  \n- **Technical Improvements:** Resolved over 1,000 Google Search Console issues; ongoing integration of tracking for ads with UTM parameters.  \n- **Next Steps Confirmed:** Campaign launches on Monday; continued weekly meetings to track progress and address any issues.","action_items":"\n**Edwin Huertas**\nFollow up urgently with Kai on the Vibe Coding LinkedIn lead to confirm outreach and next steps (08:50)\nCoordinate sending required links, feedback, and final approval for ads and landing pages to launch campaigns (04:50)\nFollow up on the email response process to define standard messaging for leads not completing the quiz from LinkedIn ads (09:30)\nMonitor campaign performance and assist with any pending questions or adjustments post-launch (14:35)\n\n**Misty Smith**\nPing Daniela to confirm and expedite delivery of video files for Zenda landing page assets into the Google Drive folder, aiming for end of day delivery (07:20)\nFollow up with Kai regarding lead outreach and ensure visibility of task by tagging her in Slack (11:20)\nSupport coordination with Daniela for any additional asset needs and confirm status updates (17:40)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare links for review of updated Foxwoods and St. Andrews landing pages and SVJ ad files with UTM parameters included (05:35)\nSubmit wrap-up message and offboarding checklist including tool access revocation, final invoices, and deliverables handoff (15:00)\nCoordinate campaign launch readiness ensuring landing pages go live today and outreach starts Monday (17:20)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nProvide and confirm sender files and any other Figma file updates needed for campaigns (17:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"953fc1a6-7db3-4206-aab3-243de5d32418","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
