INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Data Assessment Solutions reconnect',
  '## **Campaign Launch Preparation**

The team is finalizing key assets to launch a new candidate recruitment campaign next week.

- **The registration page is developed but requires final tweaks today** to reduce multiple call-to-action buttons down to two: "Book a Demo" and "Try Free," with "Talk to an Expert" prioritized at the top (06:38)
    - Axel flagged too many CTAs as confusing, prompting this simplification for clearer user direction
    - Tristan and Guille will complete these landing page updates today and share the final version via Teams
    - The streamlined CTAs are expected to improve conversion rates by clarifying user options
    - This adjustment aligns with feedback from Axel to enhance user flow and reduce drop-offs

- **The ads deployed have multiple sizes but need messaging refinements** to better target the audience and avoid confusion around terms like "AI resource management" (10:07)
    - Axel pointed out that "resource management" can be misread as cloud computing or technical resources, so switching to "workforce management" better signals the product focus on people management
    - Ads also required wording tweaks around consultant profiles and skill data to better reflect actual product features
    - Bulk changes to ad copy and targeting will be made today to refine audience precision and messaging clarity
    - These refinements aim to increase qualified clicks by reducing irrelevant traffic caused by ambiguous terms

- **Email and LinkedIn sequences have been updated based on feedback** to clarify product offerings and free trial mentions for consistency across outreach (17:01)
    - Axel noted the free product was only mentioned in the third LinkedIn message, so the team will move this highlight to earlier messages to boost early engagement
    - Tristan confirmed these edits will be incorporated before launch to ensure messaging alignment
    - Launch timing was discussed, deciding to start LinkedIn outreach Friday to avoid holiday low engagement, with emails going out Monday for higher open rates
    - This phased approach balances audience availability and maximizes campaign impact

## **Technical and Communication Setup**

Resolving access issues for collaboration tools was key to smooth campaign coordination.

- **Guille was added as a guest to the Teams channel after initial invite issues, enabling real-time collaboration on campaign assets** (06:38)
    - Multiple attempts and alternative approaches were needed as email invites failed to reach Guille
    - Eli and Axel facilitated adding Guille directly to the Teams chat, resolving delays in sharing assets and feedback
    - This quick resolution allowed the team to maintain momentum on edits and approvals
    - Reliable access to shared platforms remains critical for timely campaign execution

## **Campaign Timing and Coordination**

The team aligned on a launch schedule that avoids holiday disruptions and optimizes audience engagement.

- **LinkedIn sequences will launch Friday, with Smart Lead email campaigns and ads starting Monday to maximize reach and response** (22:54)
    - Tristan recommended avoiding sending emails during the midweek holiday slowdown to prevent low open rates
    - Axel agreed that LinkedIn browsing might still happen during holidays, so a Friday start there could capture attention early
    - Next sync meeting scheduled for **9:00 AM on Tuesday, April 2nd** to review campaign progress and initial results (23:52)
    - This timeline allows the team to finalize all adjustments during the current week and monitor initial engagement closely post-launch

- **Tristan and Guille will finalize all updates today and share links through Teams for final review before rollout** (22:54)
    - This ensures all stakeholders have access to the latest versions of landing pages, ads, and sequences
    - Ongoing communication in Teams will track progress and address any last-minute issues quickly
    - Clear ownership and deadlines help keep the campaign on track for the set launch dates

## **Messaging and Audience Targeting Strategy**

The team refined messaging and targeting to reduce misinterpretation and improve lead quality.

- **Switching from "AI resource management" to "workforce management" in ads aims to avoid confusion with cloud computing products** (12:39)
    - Axel emphasized that many users only read headlines, so clarifying terminology upfront reduces irrelevant clicks
    - Adjusting terms like “skill matrices” to “skill management” and rephrasing consultant profile descriptions further aligns messaging with actual features
    - This careful wording is designed to increase the relevance of leads by clearly signaling the product''s HR focus
    - Targeting adjustments will also refine the custom audience to exclude unrelated industries and increase conversion efficiency

- **Consistency between email and LinkedIn messages on free product offerings is being improved** to ensure prospects receive clear value propositions early (20:35)
    - Axel’s feedback led to moving free trial mentions into earlier outreach messages to boost interest
    - Tristan agreed to adjust phrasing to explicitly mention a free version in the first or second LinkedIn sequence message
    - This alignment helps maintain trust and avoids confusion, improving engagement rates
    - The approach fits the broader strategy of lowering barriers to trial adoption before pushing demos

## **Resource Availability and Team Planning**

The team planned around upcoming absences to maintain steady progress on campaign tasks.

- **Tristan will be intermittently available tomorrow but mostly out Thursday and Friday, like Colin, so key edits must happen today and early next week** (23:36)
    - Axel suggested scheduling the next detailed sync for Tuesday morning to accommodate this availability
    - This ensures leadership can review campaign readiness and initial results promptly after launch
    - Guille is actively involved today to finalize assets and coordinate with Tristan
    - Clear scheduling helps avoid delays caused by limited availability during the holiday period',
  '2025-11-25 15:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Share updated registration page after implementing Axel’s feedback on call-to-action buttons and messaging (05:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Send final link to registration page and other campaign assets via Microsoft Teams once changes are complete (09:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Adjust LinkedIn sequence messaging to introduce free product version earlier in the communication flow (21:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate timing for LinkedIn sequence launch on Friday and email campaign launch on Monday post-holiday (22:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Reschedule next campaign progress meeting to Tuesday, 9:00 AM, and send updated invites (24:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide detailed feedback on ads’ wording, targeting, and clarity for avoiding ambiguous terms such as “AI Resource Management” by suggesting “Workforce Management” (10:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Review updated landing page, ads, and messaging once changes are shared (00:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist Tristan in making final adjustments to the registration page based on feedback before sharing updated assets (02:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage acceptance and sharing of Microsoft Teams invitations for smooth collaboration (06:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist in troubleshooting and adding Guille to Microsoft Teams channel to enable collaborative access to campaign materials (06:44)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2025-12-03 20:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '72cdc11e-fd4f-4d90-8688-1fc1484de2b0',
    '2025-12-03 20:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KBBERVM8VTDES0A0WPP6GE58',
    'KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Guille Santana","Michael Kersten","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1806,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KBBERVM8VTDES0A0WPP6GE58","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Brand Positioning**\n\nThe team agreed on a comprehensive content plan centered on establishing **KTC Search** as a leading authority in executive search for private equity-backed companies (08:15).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** outlined the content engine driven by interviews with team members, clients, and prospects, generating diverse assets such as articles, case studies, infographics, social media posts, and long-form videos.\n    - This content will target all buyer journey stages, from immediate hiring needs to long-term leadership evaluation, ensuring continuous engagement.\n    - The mission statement positions KTC Search as the go-to for **private equity operating partners** and portfolio executives seeking leadership insights to solve urgent hiring challenges.\n    - This strategy aims to support sales enablement and accelerate decision cycles, with content tailored around six categories including executive search, private equity talent, industry leadership, and talent strategy.\n    - The content will include a stealth library of episodes held until a key deal closes in late **March or early April**, optimizing timing for maximum impact.\n\n- The **Executive Advantage series** was selected as the flagship content name, emphasizing the unique edge KTC Search offers in leadership placements (13:42).\n    - Episodes will include interviews with placed executives and clients, showcasing how the right leadership transforms performance within **90 days**.\n    - This series will generate multi-format assets like short videos (30–60 seconds) optimized for social and website distribution.\n    - **Michael Kersten** confirmed alignment with this naming and content direction, trusting the experts’ judgment for maximum reach.\n\n- Brand positioning will leverage the existing **KTC Search** domain and identity, emphasizing the brand’s strength and recognition while preparing for a future integration with **Richie May Global Talent** (08:15, 18:38).\n    - Colin highlighted the importance of keeping the brand consistent across all channels and content types, including website, social media, email, and ads.\n    - The content strategy incorporates a \"customer as hero\" approach using the StoryBrand framework, focusing on clients’ pain points and how KTC Search solves them.\n    - Calls to action will be tightly integrated to funnel prospects toward engagement and conversions.\n\n## **Website and Visual Design Roadmap**\n\nThe website redesign will align with the new content strategy, focusing on a modern, engaging user experience that supports sales and brand authority (26:20).\n\n- The team plans to deliver wireframes, sitemaps, and brand color palettes by the end of the week for review and approval.\n    - The new site will include reorganized homepage content emphasizing private equity-backed companies and distinct industry vertical pages.\n    - Proposed color palettes will balance industry norms (blue and green) with differentiation to avoid blending in with competitors.\n    - **Michael Kersten** requested alignment with **Richie May’s** existing style guide and color schemes to ease future brand integration and reduce rework.\n\n- Visual assets for the content series will include design elements like quote cards, lower thirds, logo usage guidelines, and long-form video templates (21:22).\n    - These assets will be packaged and shared for approval before syndication on platforms such as Spotify and Apple Podcasts.\n    - The team will produce email signature templates and a comprehensive brand kit with logos and color values to maintain consistent branding internally and externally (28:51).\n    - HTML email signatures will be created to ensure proper formatting across email clients.\n\n## **Content Production Workflow and Timeline**\n\nA clear, repeatable content production process was established to efficiently generate and deliver high-quality assets (22:16).\n\n- The workflow begins with topic identification based on customer questions or keywords, followed by guest selection, outline creation, scheduling, and recording via **Riverside**, a high-quality video recording tool (22:48).\n    - This method allows remote recording with separate video tracks for better editing and asset creation.\n    - Post-recording, the team produces multiple deliverables: two to three short videos, a long-form video, MP3 audio, title slides, and quote cards to maximize content reuse.\n\n- The expected turnaround time for content asset delivery is **about seven days** after design approval, assuming no strategic holdbacks (23:23).\n    - Michael confirmed the importance of having the website live and consistent with the content messaging before releasing videos and social media posts.\n    - The content plan supports ongoing adjustments based on performance monitoring and industry trends to maintain relevance and engagement.\n\n## **Strategic Brand Transition and Market Positioning**\n\nThe conversation acknowledged an impending brand transition integrating KTC Search under the **Richie May Global Talent** umbrella, expected as early as the first quarter (27:59).\n\n- Michael explained the strategic rationale: Richie May aims to leverage KTC’s talent acquisition success to increase overall company valuation and market appeal.\n    - The transition will essentially rebrand KTC Search as a service line within Richie May, preserving the core offerings but aligning with the larger corporate identity.\n    - Visual and messaging assets are being designed with flexibility to accommodate this shift by simply swapping logos and color flags without major overhauls.\n    - This approach minimizes disruption and cost while maximizing brand equity retention.\n\n- Leadership emphasized the urgency of quickly demonstrating KTC’s differentiated \"secret formula\" in talent acquisition and sales marketing to capture market interest and accelerate deal flow (26:07, 28:23).\n    - Colin and Michael agreed that the rebranding timeline depends on internal decisions but could happen sooner if PE stakeholders push for consolidation.\n    - Michael’s team will continue to provide insights and materials to ensure smooth transitions and consistent market positioning.\n\n## **Sales Enablement and Collateral Development**\n\nThe meeting highlighted the need for professional sales collateral and back-office support to enhance outreach and client engagement (06:55).\n\n- Michael introduced a consultant currently supporting Richie May’s CMO with presentation decks and sales assets, who could assist in developing polished sales enablement materials.\n    - Colin confirmed the capacity to handle design work internally, including refreshing and \"sexicizing\" decks to align with the new content strategy.\n    - This will help fast-track collateral production and maintain brand consistency across all communications.\n\n- The content assets produced from interviews and other materials will directly feed into sales sheets and outreach campaigns, strengthening ABM efforts (06:48, 23:50).\n    - Guest outreach campaigns will be used strategically to bring in industry voices and generate inbound interest, effectively expanding the prospect pool.\n    - This approach has proven effective in other client cases for converting content marketing into tangible sales conversations.","outline":null,"keywords":["Private Equity","Content Strategy","Executive Search","Branding","ABM Campaigns","Richie May Transition"],"overview":"- **Content Strategy**: KTC Search is positioned as a leading authority for executive search in private equity-backed firms.  \n- **Executive Advantage Series**: Flagship content features interviews showcasing leadership impact within 90 days to engage target audiences.  \n- **Website Design**: Redesign aligns with content strategies, emphasizing modern design for private equity sectors and future brand integration.  \n- **Production Workflow**: Established a repeatable content creation process with seven-day turnaround for asset delivery post-approval.  \n- **Brand Transition**: KTC Search will integrate into Richie May, enhancing market appeal while retaining core offerings and brand equity.  \n- **Sales Enablement**: Need for polished sales collateral supported by content assets to improve outreach and drive conversions.","action_items":"\n**Michael Kersten**\nSend consultant contact and Richie May’s logos/marks to marketing team for design reference (07:44)\nShare internal pitch deck and any consultant-developed presentations for refinement and “sexyfication” by the marketing team (22:06)\nReview and approve website wireframes, brand color palettes, and content plan upon delivery later this week (26:20)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize and send the detailed content plan document and recorded episode briefs for review (07:49)\nDevelop content series branding assets: quote cards, lower thirds, logos, design templates; create brand kit including logos, color values, and email signatures in HTML (21:22)\nDeliver website wireframes, sitemap mockups, and proposed new brand color palettes by end of week for client feedback (26:20)\nCoordinate interview frameworks and research materials to aid smooth content recording sessions (16:15)\nEnsure multi-format content asset production workflow is operational using Riverside tool for remote recording and fast turnaround (22:48)\nMonitor content performance and plan guest outreach campaigns aligned with ABM strategies (23:46)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nAssist in internal communication coordination, pull up shared materials and presentations as needed during meetings (22:13)\nSupport content and design review process and maintain meeting documentation (22:13)\n"},"duration":30.100000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":1,"name":"Michael Kersten"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi, Colin.","index":0,"end_time":255.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.21,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":257.219,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.579,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Good, good, good.","index":2,"end_time":260.179,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.099,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":3,"end_time":262.779,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.259,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Well.","index":4,"end_time":263.139,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.779,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Nice.","index":5,"end_time":265.539,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.059,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Let it go through this content plan.","index":6,"end_time":268.099,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.499,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll have the website plan ready later this week.","index":7,"end_time":270.419,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.099,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":8,"end_time":273.299,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.819,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, I have some questions around the tasks, but maybe we can go over those tomorrow.","index":9,"end_time":280.819,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.779,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":281.699,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":281.219,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we have our one on one tomorrow or after this call I can hop on for a few minutes, whatever you prefer.","index":11,"end_time":290.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think let''s do it in our one on one.","index":12,"end_time":294.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.62,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":13,"end_time":295.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.54,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Hey, Michael, how are you doing?","index":14,"end_time":319.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":15,"end_time":320.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":16,"end_time":320.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":320.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Busy as.","index":17,"end_time":322.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Which I guess.","index":18,"end_time":323.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Good.","index":19,"end_time":324.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Busy.","index":20,"end_time":325.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":324.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, busy.","index":21,"end_time":326.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":326.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And there''s not enough time in the day right now, so.","index":23,"end_time":328.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":326.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":329.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I guess that''s a good problem to have, so, so yeah.","index":25,"end_time":331.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hopefully you guys are going to add to that problem for me.","index":26,"end_time":334.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":27,"end_time":334.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We like, we like making busy, good busy problems.","index":28,"end_time":337.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":29,"end_time":339.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So do you have a good Thanksgiving?","index":30,"end_time":341.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":31,"end_time":341.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Try to catch up on some stuff, but the plan never seems to work the way, you know, you plan, so.","index":32,"end_time":347.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":33,"end_time":349.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Baltimore and Flame back last night, so it''s been a whirlwind.","index":34,"end_time":354.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":350.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So did you find a bwi?","index":35,"end_time":356.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":36,"end_time":357.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Well, I was going into originally my flight, I had multiple flights.","index":37,"end_time":361.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I had Oaktree, which is, I think I shared with you guys or maybe on one of the calls is one of my big pes.","index":38,"end_time":367.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":361.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And they introduced me to another portfolio.","index":39,"end_time":369.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I got a call Friday saying, hey, the, the, the chief people officer wants to talk to you on Monday.","index":40,"end_time":374.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I had to change my flight to later in the day.","index":41,"end_time":376.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":374.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Had a call with him in the morning, went well, then I flew out that night.","index":42,"end_time":381.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I had meetings all day and then I get texting goes, hey, I need your contract.","index":43,"end_time":383.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I need it by 5 o''.","index":44,"end_time":384.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Clock.","index":45,"end_time":385.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":384.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I''m in that, like in my, in, you know, freaking sitting at the gate trying to get a contract out and, and, and, and, and, and then get it over to him so he, you know, so he gets it executed.","index":46,"end_time":393.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m like, I.","index":47,"end_time":393.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"A couple days to get this turned around.","index":48,"end_time":395.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I guess not.","index":49,"end_time":395.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":50,"end_time":396.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so yeah, so it''s been a whirlwind, but anyhow.","index":51,"end_time":399.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":400.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, well, we''re gonna go through.","index":53,"end_time":402.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We drafted up a content plan and then later this week we''re gonna have the website plan.","index":54,"end_time":407.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":55,"end_time":408.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we''ll really be able to get humming on these projects and out of those we''ll have, we''ll be able to produce the ABM plan as well.","index":56,"end_time":414.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":57,"end_time":415.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, I was gonna send this, put this in the chat.","index":58,"end_time":419.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":59,"end_time":422.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This person right here, I''M going to send to you as we change stuff or things like that.","index":60,"end_time":426.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"She is the consultant that the CMO over at Richie May uses kind of for PowerPoints and stuff like that.","index":61,"end_time":433.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I put a deck together and I''ll share.","index":62,"end_time":435.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''ll send that over to you too.","index":63,"end_time":436.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"As you guys, I had to put one together, kind of talked about some of the stuff to see.","index":64,"end_time":439.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":436.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But as we change stuff, you know, graphic or we change stuff kind of messaging or stuff like that or kind of have.","index":65,"end_time":445.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"One of the things I know we were working on was kind of the sales enablement.","index":66,"end_time":448.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, she''ll be somebody that kind of helps, kind of put some of the back at back office or back at back office assets together, sales sheets, things like that.","index":67,"end_time":458.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So just as an FYI, I think you guys can do some of that, but I didn''t know.","index":68,"end_time":461.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But that''s the one person that has some of this stuff right now.","index":69,"end_time":463.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":70,"end_time":464.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":71,"end_time":464.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":72,"end_time":465.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can do any of that design work that you need.","index":73,"end_time":467.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":465.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":74,"end_time":468.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":75,"end_time":468.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.33,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, so we''re going to run through this content strategy.","index":76,"end_time":471.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is a pretty long form document because it goes into a lot of detail.","index":77,"end_time":474.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m going to cover the highlights and send it over to you to review in your time.","index":78,"end_time":478.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":79,"end_time":479.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":478.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"One of the big things, we had a conversation about the brand in our last.","index":80,"end_time":484.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, Guillen, we.","index":81,"end_time":486.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re seeing your slack.","index":82,"end_time":487.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":83,"end_time":489.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.93,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"How about now?","index":84,"end_time":491.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":85,"end_time":493.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There we go.","index":86,"end_time":493.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":87,"end_time":495.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.85,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Thank you, Guille.","index":88,"end_time":496.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":495.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":89,"end_time":496.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we had to talk about the brand and possibly looking at a name change and you already have the domain KTC Search.","index":90,"end_time":505.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We think that that is very strong to go with not only talking to you and you allude to yourself as ktc past conversations, all of that thing, all of that.","index":91,"end_time":513.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":506.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s where we''re going to lean into with the new website, the new branding and this whole content series as well.","index":92,"end_time":519.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":93,"end_time":520.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So what this content plan really puts together is any form of content.","index":94,"end_time":525.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":521.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we''re thinking website, we''re thinking social media, we''re thinking ads, we''re thinking email content, all of this needs to flow from an engine.","index":95,"end_time":533.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the, the biggest catalyst of that engine is going to be the interviews that you''re able to conduct with team members, with past clients, with current clients, with prospects, really just like getting their insight on the space, talking about the problems that they''re experiencing and how KTC Search is able to resolve those issues that turns into a bunch of different content asset types.","index":96,"end_time":555.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":534.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, we take into account all of the.","index":97,"end_time":561.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I Know, we''ve shown you slides in your roadmap document of the ideal customer profiles, everyone that we always have in mind when we''re crafting this content and really keeping all of that in mind.","index":98,"end_time":571.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we break down all the asset types again.","index":99,"end_time":574.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we came up with for the mission statement of KTC Search for Content is your content is where private equity operating partners and portfolio company executives turn to find leadership and talent insights that help them solve urgent hiring challenges so they can secure high impact leaders who accelerate performance and value creation.","index":100,"end_time":594.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that resonate with you?","index":101,"end_time":596.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That resonates perfect.","index":102,"end_time":598.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then so we break down, we have all the asset types here.","index":103,"end_time":603.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So articles, case studies, infographics, different web pages.","index":104,"end_time":606.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we talked about getting, you know, industry vertical pages and things created, having the homepage kind of reorganized to talk a little bit more in depth, but also have, you know, just more around the PE backed companies that you.","index":105,"end_time":618.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Want to work with.","index":106,"end_time":619.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.78,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Social the episodes.","index":107,"end_time":621.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":620.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like I mentioned in our previous call, we''re going to have like this kind of stealth library that we''re going to hold on to as you''re recording episodes.","index":108,"end_time":627.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to produce them, but we''re not going to release them until that deal comes through in late March, early April.","index":109,"end_time":633.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Long form videos, ebooks, white papers, everything like that.","index":110,"end_time":638.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that we think about all the content we produce is we, we like to have things that are throughout every stage of the buyer''s journey.","index":111,"end_time":645.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":639.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So every prospect can be at a different point.","index":112,"end_time":648.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":645.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it''s like I need this hire two weeks ago, which I''m sure is a lot of the conversations that you have, they''re really in that decision or customer success phase.","index":113,"end_time":656.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":648.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we still want to be in front of the people who maybe are a little bit ahead, maybe they''re thinking a little deeper into 2026.","index":114,"end_time":663.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":657.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have this need or we''re evaluating this team member right now on the leadership team and we might need to make a switch.","index":115,"end_time":669.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we want to make sure that we''re producing content that resonates with people at every stage of that journey.","index":116,"end_time":674.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Overall, what this does, it establishes you as an authority in the space.","index":117,"end_time":679.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It enables sales conversations.","index":118,"end_time":682.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":680.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we can make that sales collateral that we were just talking about through some of these things.","index":119,"end_time":685.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":682.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to support the ABM campaigns that we''re running because you know, we all get hundreds of emails a day, right.","index":120,"end_time":692.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you get like the first couple seconds of a video that''s really interesting, you''re going to spend a few more seconds watching that and Then all of a sudden KTC searches in the back of your mind, get an email, see an ad.","index":121,"end_time":701.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It kind of just all adds to that journey.","index":122,"end_time":703.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":701.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''ve seen these before, let me know if you want me to read through any of them.","index":123,"end_time":708.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But these are the ideal customer profiles that you and the team work through.","index":124,"end_time":712.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so we came up with also six categories.","index":125,"end_time":716.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":713.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the executive search and leadership placement.","index":126,"end_time":719.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":716.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will be content that highlights how your expertise in identifying, evaluating and placing high impact executives who accelerate performance for PE firms and portfolio companies.","index":127,"end_time":728.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The next one more focused on the private equity talent and value creation.","index":128,"end_time":733.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So PE backed leaders driving operational momentum that scales and you know, just moves through the company industry leadership.","index":129,"end_time":741.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where we can get a little bit guess, you know, just adjacent to the PE backed so that we''re not just positioning you as PE backed, but still have that opening to other industries.","index":130,"end_time":751.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":741.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So leadership trends, role requirements, organizational challenges, this, and this can even come if you want to do a solo episode of a conversation you just had.","index":131,"end_time":760.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we can do a million of those.","index":132,"end_time":762.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can hop on and interview you.","index":133,"end_time":763.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, there''s a million different ways that we can do this.","index":134,"end_time":765.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Next one is talent, strategy and organizational performance.","index":135,"end_time":770.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So how you truly evaluate when they come to you with a problem, we, you know, we need to fill this role.","index":136,"end_time":776.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s what we''re looking for.","index":137,"end_time":777.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":776.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you going a layer deeper than a Korn fairy who''s like, okay, cool, we just have this system, we''re going to plug you in in 30 days.","index":138,"end_time":783.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to reach back out.","index":139,"end_time":784.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But also the inverse.","index":140,"end_time":787.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you evaluating the talent?","index":141,"end_time":789.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what are the things that you''re looking for?","index":142,"end_time":790.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why are you different.","index":143,"end_time":791.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hiring velocity?","index":144,"end_time":794.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":792.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again to that 30 day timeline that a lot of other companies do, you mentioned a lot in our conversations that you move a lot faster because you feel the urgency of these people coming to you.","index":145,"end_time":804.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You want to match that and I think that''s why you get people coming back to you very often.","index":146,"end_time":809.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And all of this also encapsulates into the series name that we came up with.","index":147,"end_time":815.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have a few alternatives, but the one that I really liked was the Executive Advantage series.","index":148,"end_time":821.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":815.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":822.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So these are the recorded interviews that will turn into multi format content.","index":150,"end_time":826.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will be conversations with people that you''ve placed, people that have come to you that need help.","index":151,"end_time":832.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It could be solo conversations, it could be all sorts of things.","index":152,"end_time":834.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, going with the Executive Advantage series, the advantage that you''re able to provide.","index":153,"end_time":838.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s just another page that goes through all the asset types in a little bit more detail.","index":154,"end_time":846.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":842.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I have an extra bold P in here.","index":155,"end_time":851.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":848.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But again, it''s all about positioning you as the go to expert in high impact executive placements for PE firms and portfolio companies and then enabling sales, enabling outreach, enabling, you know, the proven or proving the outcomes that you have and accelerating the decision cycle for these companies as well.","index":156,"end_time":869.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here are just two sample briefs of episodes that we could record or content that we could come up with.","index":157,"end_time":877.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One a little bit more towards.","index":158,"end_time":880.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":879.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are actually both PE backed.","index":159,"end_time":882.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":880.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But why PE back companies stall without the right leader in the first 90 days?","index":160,"end_time":885.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if they don''t do enough research or if they go through one of the boilerplate firms or they just go with the big company, are they just being handed someone that kind of fits the bill from a resume standpoint and not actually a fit for the company?","index":161,"end_time":897.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we find, you know, in, in our research when we were doing this, a lot of PE back firms are struggling with this.","index":162,"end_time":904.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":899.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They come in, there''s the money, they just made an investment, they''re trying to plug a hole as fast as possible, but slow, as smooth, smooth as fast in a way.","index":163,"end_time":911.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":164,"end_time":911.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":911.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even if it''s only taking you a week or two versus the 30 days, you''re actually taking the time to get to know these people, what they need, who''s going to actually be the right person to fill the role.","index":165,"end_time":920.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":911.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the other one as a sample was how the right CRO transform revenue performance in a PE backed industrial company.","index":166,"end_time":929.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is some like an interview that you would have with someone that you placed or, or a company where you place someone and really just dive into like, okay, you know, you''ve been there for 30, 60, 90 days.","index":167,"end_time":940.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s talk about how that was able to transform the company from where they were when they were in this search.","index":168,"end_time":946.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so going through brand positioning, you''ve seen the story brand approach that we take.","index":169,"end_time":957.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":952.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ve listed out basically making your customer the hero.","index":170,"end_time":960.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":957.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why do they need to come to KTC search?","index":171,"end_time":963.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":961.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are they experiencing as a pain point, how you''re able to help them.","index":172,"end_time":966.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this also drives like the calls to actions that we''ll have throughout the website and throughout the content that we create.","index":173,"end_time":970.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I want to get to the fun stuff.","index":174,"end_time":977.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":975.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So getting into your content program.","index":175,"end_time":980.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here we go.","index":176,"end_time":985.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.67,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So the setup.","index":177,"end_time":987,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know, we''ll go through the, we''ll develop frameworks for these as well.","index":178,"end_time":991,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do research for the people that you''re interviewing.","index":179,"end_time":992.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Give you, I don''t like to create full scripts because I don''t want to put words in your mouth.","index":180,"end_time":997.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":992.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we tend to do is create a framework like here''s a list of questions, here''s maybe some industry trends that we''re seeing, some things that you can bring up in the conversation organically and that will really.","index":181,"end_time":1007.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":997.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also even give some fodder to the prospect that is joining the call.","index":182,"end_time":1013.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if they need some ideas or if they''re a little nervous, which tends to happen until we have a few episodes produced and out there and they can kind of see how it turns out, then we can say like, you know, no worries, here''s what we''re going to go through.","index":183,"end_time":1025.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1013.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s the conversation.","index":184,"end_time":1025.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1025.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here are some things that you might want to bring up, but feel free to, you know, take this as you as you may and then we''ll just have a conversation.","index":185,"end_time":1032.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1025.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s really all that we''re going to position this as.","index":186,"end_time":1033.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1032.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":1034.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So writing the intro and outro and I''ll send this to you to review as well.","index":188,"end_time":1042.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1037.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Going with the name of the Executive Advantage series.","index":189,"end_time":1046.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So welcome to the Executive Advantage Series, the conversation series for private equity operating partners, portfolio company leaders and executives navigating high stakes growth and transformation.","index":190,"end_time":1055.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''re responsible for driving value creation, building a high performing leadership team or accelerating performance in a fast moving environment, this series is for you.","index":191,"end_time":1063.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Each episode uncovers how exceptional leaders create momentum, overcome exact execution challenges and deliver meaningful impact inside PE backed and high growth companies.","index":192,"end_time":1073.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s dive in.","index":193,"end_time":1074.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1073.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a lot faster and but smoother than I read it because it''ll have nice, you know, music in the background and it''ll have some animation going on the screen and everything.","index":194,"end_time":1081.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1074.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then as it ends.","index":195,"end_time":1083.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks for watching the Executive Advantage series.","index":196,"end_time":1085.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1083.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If leadership gaps are slowing execution, disrupting performance or limiting your ability to hit value creation milestones, visit KTC search.com to learn how KTC Search places high impact executives to accelerate results using every opportunity.","index":197,"end_time":1098.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And again this, this is a little bit more for like the, the longer form videos if people are engaging with those.","index":198,"end_time":1103.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also create a bunch of short videos, 30 to 30 seconds to a minute because of people''s attention span and we''ll be able to populate those on social on the website.","index":199,"end_time":1113.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we''ll have a bunch of different channels that people can go to to engage with this content.","index":200,"end_time":1117.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":201,"end_time":1118.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Now quick question for you is as we develop all these things like you know right now we''re going under ktc, like I mentioned is you Know, part of the ultimate thing.","index":202,"end_time":1126.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, eventually I''ll roll under.","index":203,"end_time":1129.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1126.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Under, you know, Richie May.","index":204,"end_time":1131.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then it will kind of be Richie May Global Talent, which I just sent you a deck.","index":205,"end_time":1135.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1131.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''ll kind of see that.","index":206,"end_time":1135.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once we reproduce this, essentially it''s all the same thing.","index":207,"end_time":1139.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1136.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s really me.","index":208,"end_time":1139.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All we''re doing is changing the flag.","index":209,"end_time":1141.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":1141.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1141.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We start pushing these out and then all of a sudden, hey, this.","index":211,"end_time":1144.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This happens sooner than later.","index":212,"end_time":1146.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1144.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We can re reposition the name.","index":213,"end_time":1149.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, everything else stays in.","index":214,"end_time":1151.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We just drop a different logo or.","index":215,"end_time":1152.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":216,"end_time":1152.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Just want to make sure.","index":217,"end_time":1153.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Easy search every place for you guys.","index":218,"end_time":1154.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":219,"end_time":1155.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1154.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The.","index":220,"end_time":1155.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1155.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The harder part would be like, if we had to rebrand total colors and everything, which as part of the website plan and everything, we are going to propose some new color palettes.","index":221,"end_time":1164.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1155.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally fine.","index":222,"end_time":1164.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Just to see if you want to check out.","index":223,"end_time":1166.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":1166.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"The earth thing.","index":225,"end_time":1167.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Just to save us some time too, just in case eventually we may tran.","index":226,"end_time":1170.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1167.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And probably will happen sooner is check out Richie May''s website.","index":227,"end_time":1173.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1170.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They just redid theirs.","index":228,"end_time":1174.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1173.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can kind of see their colors.","index":229,"end_time":1175.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":230,"end_time":1176.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It''s R I C H E Y may.","index":231,"end_time":1178.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Com and I''ll throw it in the chat.","index":232,"end_time":1180.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1178.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Then you guys can kind of see some of the color.","index":233,"end_time":1182.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Colors they use.","index":234,"end_time":1183.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way, if we.","index":235,"end_time":1184.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"When we transition that way.","index":236,"end_time":1186.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, you''re.","index":237,"end_time":1189.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''re not reinventing the wheel, for lack of a better term.","index":238,"end_time":1192.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1189.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":239,"end_time":1193.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1192.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And like I said, I mean, you guys can do what you need to do since you''re the experts at it.","index":240,"end_time":1200.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":241,"end_time":1200.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hang on, let me just drop this in this chat for you.","index":242,"end_time":1202.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1200.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So you don''t feel a look at.","index":243,"end_time":1203.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I sent you.","index":244,"end_time":1207.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I sent you the deck too, so.","index":245,"end_time":1211.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then here''s the website.","index":246,"end_time":1214.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Put it in the chat.","index":247,"end_time":1215.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There you go.","index":248,"end_time":1221.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":249,"end_time":1226.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.31,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Then they just redid their site too.","index":250,"end_time":1229.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1227.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":251,"end_time":1230.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1229.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":1231.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.87,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You kind of see how they did theirs or whatever.","index":253,"end_time":1233.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once again, do you.","index":254,"end_time":1234.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"As you guys want.","index":255,"end_time":1235.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1234.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But that, that transition will happen when, you know, it could be first quarter, it could be second quarter.","index":256,"end_time":1241.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, once at the end of the day, they''re buying me and my stuff.","index":257,"end_time":1244.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1241.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So everything that you guys are developing really is tied.","index":258,"end_time":1246.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I''ve done, it just set up ktc, you know, might be flagged as RML talent.","index":259,"end_time":1251.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So, you know, at the end of the day, it''s still.","index":260,"end_time":1253.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Still everything''s about me.","index":261,"end_time":1254.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":262,"end_time":1255.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":1255.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, totally gotcha.","index":264,"end_time":1257.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I also want to call out that if you didn''t like the Executive Advantage, name a few other ones that we came up with.","index":265,"end_time":1263.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1257.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One was the leadership impact series.","index":266,"end_time":1265.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1263.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the other one was the Executive Effect.","index":267,"end_time":1267.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1265.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh.","index":268,"end_time":1268.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1267.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Whatever one you guys think is catches the most is fine with me.","index":269,"end_time":1271.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.61,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":270,"end_time":1272.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.65,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":271,"end_time":1272.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1272.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yep, you''ll learn real quick.","index":272,"end_time":1274.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1272.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''ll go with your recommendations.","index":273,"end_time":1275.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1274.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You''re the expert.","index":274,"end_time":1276,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1275.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Tell me what you think is going to work.","index":275,"end_time":1277.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1276,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Get the biggest bang for the buck.","index":276,"end_time":1278.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1277.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good to me.","index":277,"end_time":1280.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1278.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":278,"end_time":1281.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, so then we''ll roll with the Executive Advantage series.","index":279,"end_time":1285.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so for the content plan, we''re going to come up with a bunch of designs and this will be quote cards, lower thirds, long form video, how we use the logo, all sorts of things like that.","index":280,"end_time":1296.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1285.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll develop it into a package and share that with you.","index":281,"end_time":1298.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you''ll be able to see just a sample of like when we post this out there or because we''ll be syndicating out on Spotify and Apple podcast as well, what everything''s going to look like from a branding perspective.","index":282,"end_time":1310.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":283,"end_time":1311.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1310.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then do you want me, just so you have them, do you want me to send you the marks, the Richie May RM Marks, just so you see those?","index":284,"end_time":1318.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be great.","index":285,"end_time":1319.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1318.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":286,"end_time":1320.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1319.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''ll send those to you too.","index":287,"end_time":1321.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1320.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":288,"end_time":1322.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then I sent you kind of deck that we put together which kind of talked over the both sides, so.","index":289,"end_time":1332.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":290,"end_time":1333.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.2,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And I''ll pull that actually up in a second.","index":291,"end_time":1335.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.68,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"The other thing I want to walk through is what the workflow typically looks like.","index":292,"end_time":1340.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can swap this, you know, need be, but we would be, you know, if you come to us and say, I want to talk about this, we identify the topic or customer question or keyword, identify who we want to talk to about it.","index":293,"end_time":1352.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then an outline, scheduling it, recording it.","index":294,"end_time":1355.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1352.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a partnership with a tool called Riverside.","index":295,"end_time":1358.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1355.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s basically like hopping on Zoom.","index":296,"end_time":1360.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just records you both separately, but you''re still talking to each other.","index":297,"end_time":1364.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it just allows us to export all those videos at a high quality.","index":298,"end_time":1367.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that we can produce those.","index":299,"end_time":1369.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1368.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":300,"end_time":1370.339,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1369.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And after that, we edit and produce a bunch of different assets.","index":301,"end_time":1373.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1370.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''ll get two or three short form videos, the long form video, long form MP3, a few title slides, and a few quote cards.","index":302,"end_time":1380.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1373.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":303,"end_time":1383.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1383.12,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":304,"end_time":1384.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.4,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And to go over like the timeline.","index":305,"end_time":1386.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So once, once we have all the graphics package and everything approved, I know that we''re going to be holding on to these, but you know, if, if, for example, if we weren''t holding on to these for that late March, early April date, our turnaround time is about seven days for these assets.","index":306,"end_time":1403.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1386.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool, that''s fine.","index":307,"end_time":1405.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then like I said, the key is we''ll have the website and all that stuff done.","index":308,"end_time":1408.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1405.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way, whatever we''re pitching out in the video and, you know, social, digital, it''s all kind of matching what we have up on the site, correct?","index":309,"end_time":1416.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":310,"end_time":1417.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1416.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":311,"end_time":1417.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1417.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yep.","index":312,"end_time":1418.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1417.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, this is not.","index":313,"end_time":1419.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1418.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t want to position this as only like the video series.","index":314,"end_time":1422.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1419.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is all KTC Search content that we''re going to be producing comes from this plan.","index":315,"end_time":1426.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1422.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":316,"end_time":1427.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":317,"end_time":1427.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":318,"end_time":1429.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1428.45,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":319,"end_time":1430.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1429.57,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then.","index":320,"end_time":1430.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1430.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so.","index":321,"end_time":1433.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1432.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we go through a constant flow of this as well.","index":322,"end_time":1435.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1433.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, we''ll look at performance, we''ll see, you know, what industry trends are happening.","index":323,"end_time":1438.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We may say there are also opportunities where we do guest outreach campaigns.","index":324,"end_time":1443.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we identify specific companies or job titles and we want to do some outreach to bring them on as a guest, that also has proven fruitful for almost an ABM campaign style.","index":325,"end_time":1454.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because people who have not heard of you, they might be a little bit interested, they might have a little bit of like, yeah, I want to get in front of the camera and talk.","index":326,"end_time":1461.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then all of a sudden they''re hearing all about KTC Search from you, they''re talking about the problems they''re having and you''re talking about how you can resolve them.","index":327,"end_time":1467.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve seen many of our clients bring on guests and that turns into a long form deal.","index":328,"end_time":1471.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":329,"end_time":1472.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1471.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Cool.","index":330,"end_time":1474.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, well, I know I went through that extremely fast, but I wanted to cover all the high notes.","index":331,"end_time":1480.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There it is, a longer form document.","index":332,"end_time":1481.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send this over to you to review.","index":333,"end_time":1483.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1481.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But any questions before I close out of this?","index":334,"end_time":1486.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":335,"end_time":1487.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1486.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":336,"end_time":1488.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.6,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, and then I''m just going to pull up the slide deck.","index":337,"end_time":1491.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1488.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":338,"end_time":1492.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I got the logos.","index":339,"end_time":1493.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1492.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":340,"end_time":1497.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.13,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And here''s the presentation.","index":341,"end_time":1498.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.33,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":342,"end_time":1505.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1504.73,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Anything specifically you want to call out?","index":343,"end_time":1507.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1506.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I mean, basically what this doing is this kind of.","index":344,"end_time":1510.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1508.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Because we were pitching this to an asset we''re getting ready to buy.","index":345,"end_time":1513.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1510.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So this was kind of flipped the other way where we were talking about what we''ve done internally.","index":346,"end_time":1516.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1513.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So some of the stuff that you''re asking, hey, what makes us different, what makes us special?","index":347,"end_time":1520.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1517.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think addresses some of that in these slides.","index":348,"end_time":1523.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1521.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once again, you guys can redevelop something.","index":349,"end_time":1526.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1523.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This was something I would put together quick and dirty, so, you know, kind of hit it.","index":350,"end_time":1529.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But as you kind of go through it, first couple of things is talks about who we are, what we do, what makes us different, then talk about, you know, the kind of services that we''re offering, which is the second slide.","index":351,"end_time":1539.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1529.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then I Believe the third slide kind of goes into what we, you know, what we''ve gone.","index":352,"end_time":1544.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1539.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":353,"end_time":1545.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1544.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What we''ve done so far internally, you know, this through the calendar year in regards.","index":354,"end_time":1548.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1545.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And what makes us different because one of the things that they''re pushing as we''ve buy other assets is we have the secret formula when it comes to talent acquisition, sales and marketing.","index":355,"end_time":1558.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And, you know, they want to brag about what.","index":356,"end_time":1560.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1558.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What I''ve done in a short period of time.","index":357,"end_time":1562.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1560.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So this kind of touches that.","index":358,"end_time":1563.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1562.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then we kind of go into the retained side and some of that stuff is up on my website.","index":359,"end_time":1567.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1563.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once again, none of this is set in stone.","index":360,"end_time":1569.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1567.45,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys can throw it all away.","index":361,"end_time":1570.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can do whatever the hell you want, but this just kind of gives you some more.","index":362,"end_time":1573.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I think some of the stuff that you were asking about was.","index":363,"end_time":1575.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"It was kind of.","index":364,"end_time":1575.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds great.","index":365,"end_time":1577.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1575.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":366,"end_time":1577.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":367,"end_time":1579.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1578.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right.","index":368,"end_time":1580.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1580.18,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So, yeah, to close out on next steps, so we''re going to develop the designs for the content series and also later this week, we''ll be sending over some wireframes, some brand color palettes, and different things that we''re planning for the website.","index":369,"end_time":1593.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1580.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just to get your feel on, you know, do we go with this color direction?","index":370,"end_time":1596.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1593.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we stay with what we currently have?","index":371,"end_time":1598.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1596.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll certainly say, like, this is where we''re leaning, but we want your approval on that.","index":372,"end_time":1603.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1598.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then start mocking up, like, the sitemap and the wireframes for the.","index":373,"end_time":1606.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1603.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the new site.","index":374,"end_time":1607.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":375,"end_time":1608.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then you guys are like, I think you just said that you''ll.","index":376,"end_time":1610.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Whoops.","index":377,"end_time":1610.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t know why I went off video.","index":378,"end_time":1611.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":379,"end_time":1612.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.82,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys will kind of give me what you''re thinking and.","index":380,"end_time":1616.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1613.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that''s fine.","index":381,"end_time":1617.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1616.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''d rather you guys do the research, tell me what you think looks best, and, you know, nine out of 10 times, we''re probably going to go with your recommendations.","index":382,"end_time":1625.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1619.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Just so.","index":383,"end_time":1625.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1625.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, sounds good.","index":384,"end_time":1627.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1625.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And yeah, it''s always funny with colors, you know, the, the kind of emotions that they can evoke or even, you know, the, the products and services that they''re associated with.","index":385,"end_time":1635.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, blue and green are very prominent in your space.","index":386,"end_time":1637.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1635.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also don''t want to be like every other company.","index":387,"end_time":1640.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1639.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s about finding, like a mix and a balance between all of that.","index":388,"end_time":1644.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1641,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, cool.","index":389,"end_time":1645.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"What, what will end up happening is as you guys kind of design.","index":390,"end_time":1648.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1646.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"That''s what I was saying, as you look at Richie Mae, is what''ll end up happening once we blow that in.","index":391,"end_time":1654.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1648.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know what they''ll want to do is they''ll.","index":392,"end_time":1656.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''ll They''ll.","index":393,"end_time":1657.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1656.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''ll.","index":394,"end_time":1657.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1657.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Everything we have on our site will bump.","index":395,"end_time":1659.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1657.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They basically dump in as another.","index":396,"end_time":1661.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1659.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If you go into Richie Mae and the different service lines basically get a dump line as another service line.","index":397,"end_time":1666.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1661.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So it''s like anything you guys develop would just be repositioned under their umbrel.","index":398,"end_time":1671.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1666.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, once we roll that way.","index":399,"end_time":1672.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":400,"end_time":1673.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, good to know.","index":401,"end_time":1674.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1673.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what''s the timeline on that?","index":402,"end_time":1677.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1676.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are.","index":403,"end_time":1680.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1679.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Potentially first quarter.","index":404,"end_time":1684.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1682.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We may start transitioning some stuff, you know, kind, you know, we''re trying to figure out.","index":405,"end_time":1689.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1684.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We have a lot of internal stuff going on, so they''re trying to figure out the right thing.","index":406,"end_time":1692.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But a lot of our PE.","index":407,"end_time":1694.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1692.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Is very intrigued about what we''ve done in the talent side.","index":408,"end_time":1699.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So they may want to suck me sooner than later because it gives them a higher multip.","index":409,"end_time":1703.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1699.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Are.","index":410,"end_time":1703.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":411,"end_time":1704.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1703.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":412,"end_time":1704.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1704.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":413,"end_time":1705.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1705.28,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Gotta love roll ups.","index":414,"end_time":1708,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1706.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":415,"end_time":1709.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1709.04,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":416,"end_time":1710.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1709.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we''re super excited.","index":417,"end_time":1711.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1710.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, like I said, we''ll get the designs going.","index":418,"end_time":1713.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1711.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll have the website, wireframes and color palettes and everything over to you at the end of this week.","index":419,"end_time":1717.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll.","index":420,"end_time":1719.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1718.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll have some more to discuss next week.","index":421,"end_time":1720.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1719.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":422,"end_time":1721.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then two quick questions for you.","index":423,"end_time":1722.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1721.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So once we decide on the colors and everything like that.","index":424,"end_time":1725.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Do you guys.","index":425,"end_time":1726.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1725.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Will you guys be able to generate me anything that we can drop into signature, you know, email signatures?","index":426,"end_time":1730.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So there''s.","index":427,"end_time":1731.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1730.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, we can create email signatures.","index":428,"end_time":1732.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":1732.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then whatever other type of stuff, like if you change the log logo just so I can get it onto some of my contracts and stuff like that.","index":430,"end_time":1738.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way whatever you''re pushing out there, I''m making sure I''m putting it on the other side.","index":431,"end_time":1743.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1738.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we''re matching if somebody hits different sites.","index":432,"end_time":1745.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll create like a brand kit so it''ll have like logos and colored values and all that sort of stuff.","index":433,"end_time":1749.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1745.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And email signature.","index":434,"end_time":1751.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1750.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can write that in HTML for you as well so that it doesn''t look funky in an email.","index":435,"end_time":1756.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1751.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect, Perfect.","index":436,"end_time":1758.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1757.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then the stuff like I sent you in that deck.","index":437,"end_time":1759.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1758.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"If once I.","index":438,"end_time":1760.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1759.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We developed, you know, Kristen, that I gave you context, she devoted something.","index":439,"end_time":1764.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1760.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can give it to you guys too.","index":440,"end_time":1766.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then that''s stuff that you''ll do too.","index":441,"end_time":1768.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1766.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So we can, you know, I can kind of let her do her thing and then I can flip it back and say, okay, now I need you guys to sexicize it to make it more.","index":442,"end_time":1776.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"More A little bit, you know, kind of going to where we''re trying to accomplish this.","index":443,"end_time":1779.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1776.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, a little bit more attractive.","index":444,"end_time":1780.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":445,"end_time":1781.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1780.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even looking at the.","index":446,"end_time":1781.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s funny because they''re a massive brand.","index":447,"end_time":1783.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1781.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":448,"end_time":1783.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1783.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Richie May this.","index":449,"end_time":1785.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1783.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some of it kind of gives me a headache.","index":450,"end_time":1787.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s so much going on on these slides, it''s really hard to follow.","index":451,"end_time":1790.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1787.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":452,"end_time":1791.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1791.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":453,"end_time":1793.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1792.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":454,"end_time":1793.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1793.32,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Cool.","index":455,"end_time":1795.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":456,"end_time":1795.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right.","index":457,"end_time":1796.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, thank you very much, Michael.","index":458,"end_time":1797.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1796.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You, too.","index":459,"end_time":1798,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Talk to you guys soon.","index":460,"end_time":1798.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1798,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":461,"end_time":1799.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1798.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":462,"end_time":1800.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1799.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye.","index":463,"end_time":1800.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"}],"dateString":"2025-12-03T20:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBBERVM8VTDES0A0WPP6GE58","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Outlined content strategy tied to company branding, ABM, and sales enablement objectives.","Agreed on ''Executive Advantage'' as series name to drive executive-facing multimedia content.","Discussed Q1 rebranding and seamless transition under Richie May with updated site and assets.","Planned content workflows include interviews, asset repurposing, and structured sales collateral.","Owner confirmed design autonomy, approving agency recommendations for faster deployment."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Everything that you guys are developing really is tied... it just set up ktc, you know, might be flagged as RML talent.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"},{"quote":"This is all KTC Search content that we''re going to be producing comes from this plan.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"You''re the expert. Tell me what you think is going to work. Get the biggest bang for the buck.","speaker":"Michael Kersten"}],"topics":["branding","content","launch"],"model":"gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-03T17:21:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Brand Positioning**\n\nThe team agreed on a comprehensive content plan centered on establishing **KTC Search** as a leading authority in executive search for private equity-backed companies (08:15).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** outlined the content engine driven by interviews with team members, clients, and prospects, generating diverse assets such as articles, case studies, infographics, social media posts, and long-form videos.\n    - This content will target all buyer journey stages, from immediate hiring needs to long-term leadership evaluation, ensuring continuous engagement.\n    - The mission statement positions KTC Search as the go-to for **private equity operating partners** and portfolio executives seeking leadership insights to solve urgent hiring challenges.\n    - This strategy aims to support sales enablement and accelerate decision cycles, with content tailored around six categories including executive search, private equity talent, industry leadership, and talent strategy.\n    - The content will include a stealth library of episodes held until a key deal closes in late **March or early April**, optimizing timing for maximum impact.\n\n- The **Executive Advantage series** was selected as the flagship content name, emphasizing the unique edge KTC Search offers in leadership placements (13:42).\n    - Episodes will include interviews with placed executives and clients, showcasing how the right leadership transforms performance within **90 days**.\n    - This series will generate multi-format assets like short videos (30–60 seconds) optimized for social and website distribution.\n    - **Michael Kersten** confirmed alignment with this naming and content direction, trusting the experts’ judgment for maximum reach.\n\n- Brand positioning will leverage the existing **KTC Search** domain and identity, emphasizing the brand’s strength and recognition while preparing for a future integration with **Richie May Global Talent** (08:15, 18:38).\n    - Colin highlighted the importance of keeping the brand consistent across all channels and content types, including website, social media, email, and ads.\n    - The content strategy incorporates a \"customer as hero\" approach using the StoryBrand framework, focusing on clients’ pain points and how KTC Search solves them.\n    - Calls to action will be tightly integrated to funnel prospects toward engagement and conversions.\n\n## **Website and Visual Design Roadmap**\n\nThe website redesign will align with the new content strategy, focusing on a modern, engaging user experience that supports sales and brand authority (26:20).\n\n- The team plans to deliver wireframes, sitemaps, and brand color palettes by the end of the week for review and approval.\n    - The new site will include reorganized homepage content emphasizing private equity-backed companies and distinct industry vertical pages.\n    - Proposed color palettes will balance industry norms (blue and green) with differentiation to avoid blending in with competitors.\n    - **Michael Kersten** requested alignment with **Richie May’s** existing style guide and color schemes to ease future brand integration and reduce rework.\n\n- Visual assets for the content series will include design elements like quote cards, lower thirds, logo usage guidelines, and long-form video templates (21:22).\n    - These assets will be packaged and shared for approval before syndication on platforms such as Spotify and Apple Podcasts.\n    - The team will produce email signature templates and a comprehensive brand kit with logos and color values to maintain consistent branding internally and externally (28:51).\n    - HTML email signatures will be created to ensure proper formatting across email clients.\n\n## **Content Production Workflow and Timeline**\n\nA clear, repeatable content production process was established to efficiently generate and deliver high-quality assets (22:16).\n\n- The workflow begins with topic identification based on customer questions or keywords, followed by guest selection, outline creation, scheduling, and recording via **Riverside**, a high-quality video recording tool (22:48).\n    - This method allows remote recording with separate video tracks for better editing and asset creation.\n    - Post-recording, the team produces multiple deliverables: two to three short videos, a long-form video, MP3 audio, title slides, and quote cards to maximize content reuse.\n\n- The expected turnaround time for content asset delivery is **about seven days** after design approval, assuming no strategic holdbacks (23:23).\n    - Michael confirmed the importance of having the website live and consistent with the content messaging before releasing videos and social media posts.\n    - The content plan supports ongoing adjustments based on performance monitoring and industry trends to maintain relevance and engagement.\n\n## **Strategic Brand Transition and Market Positioning**\n\nThe conversation acknowledged an impending brand transition integrating KTC Search under the **Richie May Global Talent** umbrella, expected as early as the first quarter (27:59).\n\n- Michael explained the strategic rationale: Richie May aims to leverage KTC’s talent acquisition success to increase overall company valuation and market appeal.\n    - The transition will essentially rebrand KTC Search as a service line within Richie May, preserving the core offerings but aligning with the larger corporate identity.\n    - Visual and messaging assets are being designed with flexibility to accommodate this shift by simply swapping logos and color flags without major overhauls.\n    - This approach minimizes disruption and cost while maximizing brand equity retention.\n\n- Leadership emphasized the urgency of quickly demonstrating KTC’s differentiated \"secret formula\" in talent acquisition and sales marketing to capture market interest and accelerate deal flow (26:07, 28:23).\n    - Colin and Michael agreed that the rebranding timeline depends on internal decisions but could happen sooner if PE stakeholders push for consolidation.\n    - Michael’s team will continue to provide insights and materials to ensure smooth transitions and consistent market positioning.\n\n## **Sales Enablement and Collateral Development**\n\nThe meeting highlighted the need for professional sales collateral and back-office support to enhance outreach and client engagement (06:55).\n\n- Michael introduced a consultant currently supporting Richie May’s CMO with presentation decks and sales assets, who could assist in developing polished sales enablement materials.\n    - Colin confirmed the capacity to handle design work internally, including refreshing and \"sexicizing\" decks to align with the new content strategy.\n    - This will help fast-track collateral production and maintain brand consistency across all communications.\n\n- The content assets produced from interviews and other materials will directly feed into sales sheets and outreach campaigns, strengthening ABM efforts (06:48, 23:50).\n    - Guest outreach campaigns will be used strategically to bring in industry voices and generate inbound interest, effectively expanding the prospect pool.\n    - This approach has proven effective in other client cases for converting content marketing into tangible sales conversations.","outline":null,"keywords":["Private Equity","Content Strategy","Executive Search","Branding","ABM Campaigns","Richie May Transition"],"overview":"- **Content Strategy**: KTC Search is positioned as a leading authority for executive search in private equity-backed firms.  \n- **Executive Advantage Series**: Flagship content features interviews showcasing leadership impact within 90 days to engage target audiences.  \n- **Website Design**: Redesign aligns with content strategies, emphasizing modern design for private equity sectors and future brand integration.  \n- **Production Workflow**: Established a repeatable content creation process with seven-day turnaround for asset delivery post-approval.  \n- **Brand Transition**: KTC Search will integrate into Richie May, enhancing market appeal while retaining core offerings and brand equity.  \n- **Sales Enablement**: Need for polished sales collateral supported by content assets to improve outreach and drive conversions.","action_items":"\n**Michael Kersten**\nSend consultant contact and Richie May’s logos/marks to marketing team for design reference (07:44)\nShare internal pitch deck and any consultant-developed presentations for refinement and “sexyfication” by the marketing team (22:06)\nReview and approve website wireframes, brand color palettes, and content plan upon delivery later this week (26:20)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nFinalize and send the detailed content plan document and recorded episode briefs for review (07:49)\nDevelop content series branding assets: quote cards, lower thirds, logos, design templates; create brand kit including logos, color values, and email signatures in HTML (21:22)\nDeliver website wireframes, sitemap mockups, and proposed new brand color palettes by end of week for client feedback (26:20)\nCoordinate interview frameworks and research materials to aid smooth content recording sessions (16:15)\nEnsure multi-format content asset production workflow is operational using Riverside tool for remote recording and fast turnaround (22:48)\nMonitor content performance and plan guest outreach campaigns aligned with ABM strategies (23:46)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nAssist in internal communication coordination, pull up shared materials and presentations as needed during meetings (22:13)\nSupport content and design review process and maintain meeting documentation (22:13)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"32c491ca-0f1b-475f-9e3a-7b9f78f771dc","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
