INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Sales Performance and Lead Management**

The team is seeing positive momentum with a strong sales month in November, signaling a promising holiday season.

- **November marked the best sales month of the year**, indicating customers are starting holiday shopping early, according to Robert (06:25)  
    - This uptick suggests the sales pipeline is active and ready for end-of-year campaigns  
    - Robert’s optimism sets a positive baseline for forecasting December performance  
    - Maintaining this momentum requires close monitoring of lead flow and conversion rates  
    - This context justifies ramping up outreach efforts and marketing support for the holiday period

- **Lead management system issues with HubSpot and Air Call were resolved**, ensuring sales contacts and calls sync properly, Milan confirmed (08:31)  
    - Earlier problems caused duplicate or incomplete contact records, impacting follow-up accuracy  
    - Fixing this restores sales team efficiency and data quality for pipeline tracking  
    - Milan emphasized team adjustment to new systems is ongoing, highlighting training needs  
    - Resolving these sync issues reduces risk of lost leads and missed sales opportunities

## **Website Content and Messaging Updates**

Immediate website content fixes are planned to better reflect the brand’s positioning and improve customer engagement.

- **A video on the website needs replacing with an updated tour video from the content team**, Milan committed to deliver it soon (10:03)  
    - Colin and Nina confirmed they have access to Squarespace but await the new video file  
    - Updating the video will better showcase the facility and enhance visitor conversion  
    - This content refresh supports the upcoming New Year’s resolution marketing push  
    - Timely video replacement is vital to keep the site fresh and competitive

- **The phrase “luxury at a lower price” on the site will be removed or reworded** to align with brand integrity, Milan noted (14:12)  
    - Milan suggested luxury messaging should not imply discounting, to maintain premium appeal  
    - Colin committed to searching the site and making necessary edits quickly  
    - Clear, consistent messaging is key to differentiating from competitors  
    - Adjusting this language supports the brand’s long-term positioning strategy

## **SMS Marketing Strategy and Cost Management**

The team is planning a targeted SMS campaign to boost engagement, balancing message volume with budget constraints.

- **Estimated SMS volume could reach about 25,000 messages per month**, covering new leads, existing pipeline, and past due reminders, Milan explained (16:11)  
    - Colin noted this number is on the high end but plausible given lead flow and member base  
    - HubSpot’s SMS pricing approximates under **$1,000 per month**, depending on volume (17:18)  
    - Milan will reconnect with the SMS vendor rep to explore trial options or discounts (19:56)  
    - Testing limited segments first will help measure ROI before full rollout

- **ROI measurement will focus on response rates and membership activation or payment completion**, Colin outlined (18:08)  
    - Text responses converting to active memberships or payments will demonstrate campaign success  
    - Prioritizing past due payment reminders via SMS may yield immediate revenue impact  
    - This approach reduces wasted spend and informs future scaling decisions  
    - Milan plans to analyze message effectiveness with the team before final commitments

## **Contract Status and Service Availability**

The team confirmed ongoing support and service availability through mid-year, ensuring continuity for upcoming initiatives.

- **Existing service contract with Colin’s team is active through June**, Colin confirmed (20:24)  
    - This provides a runway for additional HubSpot work, including email campaigns and sequences  
    - The team can deploy creative support such as social media posts aligned with seasonal promotions  
    - This flexibility allows for adaptive marketing tactics based on sales trends and customer feedback  
    - Robert and Milan will discuss internal priorities and return with requests to Colin’s team

- **Past due HubSpot invoice from November 29 was identified and acknowledged**, Milan committed to addressing it promptly (11:23)  
    - Timely payment will prevent service disruptions during critical marketing periods  
    - This highlights the need for routine billing oversight to avoid operational hiccups  
    - Colin flagged this proactively to maintain smooth platform access  
    - Resolving it ensures uninterrupted use of essential CRM and marketing tools',
  '2025-12-03 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Notify team that routing call info without data input must be manual due to sync limitations (09:52)","completed":false},{"text":"Obtain updated tour video from content team and send for website update (10:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Address past due HubSpot invoice from November 29 (11:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Locate and revise/remove ''luxury at a lower price'' phrase on website (14:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Reach out to SMS marketing rep to request trial or negotiate terms (19:56)","completed":false},{"text":"Discuss SMS marketing strategy and message volume with Robert before follow-up with marketers (21:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Swap out website video promptly once received from Milan (11:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Assist with SMS marketing rep engagement or join call for negotiation if needed (17:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Support email campaigns, new sequences, social media posts, and website enhancements as needed within contract hours through June (20:21)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate offline discussion with Milan regarding SMS marketing volume and strategy (21:07)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting (2025-12-03 14:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '75b32155-1255-4d17-b437-152e300521a0',
    '2025-12-03 14:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KB35HD2AR67F0N4K8GQ58189',
    'New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","Kate ThreatMark","Colin Costigan","Colin Costigan","Greg Smith"}'::text[],
    2969,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1',
    '{"id":"01KB35HD2AR67F0N4K8GQ58189","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Budget Allocation**\n\nMarketing efforts have shown clear evidence that LinkedIn is the strongest lead generator, but budget increases are needed to improve penetration and form fills.\n\n- **LinkedIn ads generated 27 leads over the last 90 days, split evenly between EMEA and the U.S., with EMEA costs significantly higher due to competition** (08:18)  \n    - The U.S. market remains less saturated, showing better cost efficiency and potential for scaling.  \n    - Budget constraints limited penetration to just 1% of a targeted audience list of **4,300** large banks on LinkedIn.  \n    - Cost per click ranged between **$27 and $70**, reflecting the competitive nature of the target segments.  \n    - Increasing the LinkedIn budget is recommended to capitalize on strong engagement signals and convert more leads.\n\n- **Google Ads delivered 546 clicks at a 4.05% click-through rate, with brand-led targeting achieving exceptional 20-25% CTR on specific keywords** (07:20)  \n    - Broad match keywords initially attracted irrelevant traffic, leading to immediate negative keyword additions.  \n    - Brand keyword campaigns are performing well but require stronger website resources to boost conversions.  \n    - Early December spend on branded terms was **£47**, with average CPC decreasing but ad strength rated as average.  \n    - Plans to refresh ad headlines, site links, and descriptions aim to improve overall ad performance.\n\n- **AdRoll retargeting campaigns showed low spend but delivered several clicks, highlighting cost-effective brand reinforcement** (18:30)  \n    - Geofencing was added to target St. Joseph, Michigan, but spend was low and results modest.  \n    - Greg Smith suggested converting all ad platforms’ currencies to USD in 2026 for consistency and easier budget tracking.\n\n- **Q2 digital banking campaign was switched from a landing page to lead gen forms to improve lead capture, with 7 leads last month mostly in the U.S.** (22:10)  \n    - Greg Smith emphasized prioritizing PDF downloads over landing page conversions to maximize database growth.  \n    - The U.S. campaign uses broader job title and industry filters, while the Q2 list remains narrowly targeted and expensive but valuable.  \n    - Only about 1% of the Q2 target list has been reached due to budget limits, with CTR at a strong **3.34%**, exceeding industry averages.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing and Targeting Strategy**\n\nThe team is shifting towards a focused account-based marketing (ABM) approach, concentrating on segmented, high-value target lists to improve conversion and ROI.\n\n- **Greg Smith outlined plans to segment target accounts into regional and strategic groups, with approximately 100 accounts in Nordics, 400 in UK/Western Europe, and 1,000 in the U.S.** (36:00)  \n    - This segmentation supports both one-to-one and one-to-many marketing approaches tailored to compliance and regional needs.  \n    - The goal is to align ads and landing pages with these specific segments to improve messaging relevance and engagement.\n\n- **Salesforce data cleanup is critical, as approximately one-third of the 3,100 accounts are duplicates, hindering effective targeting** (37:00)  \n    - Greg is leading efforts to clean data and establish target accounts in HubSpot to enable precise tracking and measurement of campaign efficacy.  \n    - This will create a feedback loop between sales reps and marketers to adapt campaigns based on real market insights.\n\n- **Expansion of geographic targeting includes a proposed campaign focused on banks in Michigan, leveraging local client success and market familiarity** (30:00)  \n    - This would be a non-Q2 campaign to complement the existing segmented efforts.  \n    - Customized ads tailored to Michigan’s market characteristics will be developed as part of Account Based Marketing.\n\n- **The strategy emphasizes deeper, narrower targeting over broad campaigns to maximize lead quality and revenue impact, even at higher acquisition costs** (34:00)  \n    - Greg stated willingness to accept high lead costs if the quality and conversion potential justify the spend.\n\n## **Product and Content Development**\n\nContent and product marketing efforts are being refined to support lead generation and engagement with precise messaging and creative updates.\n\n- **The fraud disruption white paper is pending final feedback from Mel, with potential content and design changes expected** (41:10)  \n    - Final sign-off is awaited before integrating this asset fully into campaigns.\n\n- **HubSpot content gating capabilities are limited natively, but custom development options exist to offer partial white paper previews** (13:30)  \n    - Options include showing first few pages on a landing page or developing a custom Mozilla library to support partial content previews.  \n    - Greg preferred holding off on custom builds for now but appreciated knowing the potential paths.\n\n- **Podcast analytics show the most popular episode downloaded 82 times, with plans to integrate Buzzsprout data into the DataBox dashboard for live updates** (44:50)  \n    - Kate requested analytics access to better track engagement.  \n    - Consistent podcast posting on Wednesdays was agreed to maintain regularity and audience expectations.\n\n- **The homepage carousel and newsroom pages are being updated for improved navigation, color consistency, and date display for articles** (14:30)  \n    - Kate requested adding publication dates on article pages and aligning styles between newsroom and Insights tiles, though a full redesign was deprioritized.\n\n- **Discussions are underway to possibly embed a HubSpot form in a currently empty homepage section to drive conversions** (40:25)  \n    - Technical feasibility to embed HubSpot scripts or shortcodes is being explored.\n\n## **Technology and Tracking Enhancements**\n\nTracking and analytics improvements aim to provide better insights and measurement to inform decision-making and campaign optimization.\n\n- **Google Analytics 4 tracking was set up for button registrations on the test website, enhancing conversion monitoring on interactive elements** (12:30)  \n    - Geofencing via AdRoll was configured to target specific locations, starting with St. Joseph, Michigan.\n\n- **AdRoll targeting is based on IP and enriched company lists, providing confidence that ads reach intended audience members** (20:20)  \n    - However, detailed behavioral data on clicks beyond form fills is limited.  \n    - Colin committed to exploring deeper click behavior tracking for better performance evaluation.\n\n- **Discussions included potential benefits of creating new Google Ads accounts to denominate spend in USD and start fresh with advertiser verification** (18:50)  \n    - This was considered to simplify budgeting and reporting but weighed against the cost of re-verification.\n\n- **Plans to improve and refresh Google Ads extensions and headlines aim to increase ad strength and conversion rates on branded terms** (15:55)  \n    - Early data shows room for improvement, with average ad strength currently moderate.\n\n## **Sales and Vendor Coordination**\n\nCloser alignment between marketing and sales tools is planned to improve workflow, reduce overlap, and optimize costs.\n\n- **Greg Smith intends to start conversations with HubSpot Sales about upgrading to Content Enterprise with a mid-Q1 target, leveraging an end-of-year discount offer if signed by December 12** (28:00)  \n    - Colin will introduce Greg to the HubSpot rep and facilitate access to a shared deal room to secure discounts.  \n    - Greg is also exploring consolidating sales tools by replacing Outreach with HubSpot’s sales sequences for better data and integration.\n\n- **Budgeting discussions for 2026 are underway but not finalized; coordination between marketing and sales on tool spend and campaign funding is ongoing** (09:50)  \n    - Colin offered to send detailed budget recommendations once internal conversations progress.\n\n- **An end-of-year or early 2026 planning session was proposed to align budgets, campaigns, tools, and strategies across teams** (45:50)  \n    - Colin will circulate a calendar invite for a 60- to 90-minute brainstorming session.\n\n## **Creative and Competitive Intelligence**\n\nThe team is beginning to benchmark against competitors and test regional market opportunities to refine messaging and targeting.\n\n- **Kate requested a review of competitor ad creatives to understand messaging and positioning differences** (33:40)  \n    - Colin suggested using tools like SpyFu to gather competitive ad data and creative examples.  \n    - Greg noted that competitors like BioCatch avoid events in existing customer regions, opening opportunities in the Nordics.\n\n- **Regional campaigns focusing on Michigan and Nordic markets are being considered to deepen market penetration rather than casting wide nets** (34:40)  \n    - These focused campaigns will complement account-based marketing efforts and leverage local insights.\n\n- **The team agreed on continuing to refine creative assets and testing new formats to improve engagement across channels** (11:20)  \n    - New fraud disruption ad captions and image backgrounds were recently updated to align with landing page styles.\n\n- **Internal discussions include cautious adoption of AI tools for content creation and video editing, balancing innovation with quality control** (46:50)  \n    - Colin and Greg shared experiences with AI tools like Descript and Riverside, acknowledging rapid improvements but also current limitations.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","LinkedIn Ads","HubSpot Upgrade","Salesforce Cleanup","Podcast Analytics","Fraud Disruption White Paper"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Leads:** 27 leads in 90 days; 1% of 4,300 targeted banks reached due to budget limits.  \n- **Google Ads Performance:** 546 clicks, 4.05% CTR; branded keywords achieved 20-25% CTR.  \n- **Q2 Campaign Shift:** Focus switched to lead gen forms; 7 leads captured last month, highlighting budget constraints.  \n- **ABM Strategy:** 1,000 U.S. accounts and segmentation planned for more effective targeting and increased conversions.  \n- **Sales Tool Consolidation:** HubSpot upgrade discussions underway to enhance data integration; December 12 discount opportunity.  \n- **Creative Benchmarking:** Reviewing competitor ads to refine messaging, with regional campaigns targeting Michigan and Nordics.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nIntroduce Greg Smith to HubSpot Sales representative for pilot and upgrade discussions (28:10)\nSend updated fraud disruption ads and asset links (including fraud lifecycle graphic) to Greg and Kate (42:50)\nShare podcast analytics for Data Box integration and provide preliminary download numbers (44:40)\nRefresh Google Ads with new site links, headlines, and descriptions (40:35)\nImplement homepage carousel updates: navigation jump, H1 color consistency, and auto-scroll feature (38:00)\nUpdate Scam Flag title and newsroom pages with date display on listings and articles (14:30)\nWork on end-of-year compilation video from Behind Enemy Lines podcast as a complimentary project (46:55)\nMonitor and report LinkedIn lead gen and AdRoll campaign performance regularly (21:00)\nCollaborate with Julia on event planning and ABM strategy alignments (49:05)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nProvide feedback to Colin and team on fraud disruption white paper after receiving draft from Mel (41:15)\nShare editable slide deck with Colin for fraud lifecycle graphic text editing (43:50)\nOversee Salesforce data cleanup to remove duplicate accounts for more effective ABM targeting (36:59)\nDetermine budget allocation and finalize ABM segmented account lists for Nordics, UK/Europe, and US (36:20)\nCoordinate with Kate to define Michigan-specific targeting approach and audience list updates (30:20)\nTrack Q2 digital banking campaign performance; switch offer to PDF download forms to capture contacts (26:00)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nReview updated fraud disruption ads and provide feedback (11:37)\nConfirm and refine newsroom page date display requirements (14:40)\nContinue website audit and share findings with Colin to improve conversion for branded ad landing pages (16:25)\nShare feedback to add auto-scroll to homepage carousel (39:20)\nDecide on potential matching of Insights and Newsroom resource tile styles (15:30)\nMaintain podcast posting schedule to Wednesdays and request analytics reports (44:40)\nConfirm 2026 budgeting status and update Colin accordingly (09:50)\nCollaborate on end-of-year and 2026 planning session scheduling (46:00)\n\n**Julia Lungu**\nCoordinate with Colin and Kate on sponsored external event planning and ABM strategy support (49:01)\n"},"duration":49.4900016784668,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Greg Smith"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":215.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":1,"end_time":216.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Just a moment.","index":2,"end_time":217.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hello.","index":3,"end_time":227.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.36,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hi.","index":4,"end_time":228.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Keith.","index":5,"end_time":229.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi.","index":6,"end_time":229.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.04,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":7,"end_time":232.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":231.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m good, thanks.","index":8,"end_time":234.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"How was your Thanksgiving?","index":9,"end_time":235.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.21,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It was good.","index":10,"end_time":236.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":235.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got to travel, got to take my daughter on her first plane ride.","index":11,"end_time":242.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":12,"end_time":244.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.97,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Visiting family?","index":13,"end_time":245.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, my father in law got married.","index":14,"end_time":248.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":246.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last week so went down to Florida to see that.","index":15,"end_time":251.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":248.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":16,"end_time":252.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Ah, new team members.","index":17,"end_time":261.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exciting.","index":18,"end_time":261.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everyone.","index":19,"end_time":264.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.7,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":20,"end_time":265.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, good.","index":21,"end_time":266.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.1,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh good.","index":22,"end_time":267.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Nice to meet you.","index":23,"end_time":268.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"You as well.","index":24,"end_time":269.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can do introductions I guess before Greg gets here.","index":25,"end_time":273.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s great to meet you.","index":26,"end_time":274.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":273.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m Colin.","index":27,"end_time":275.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m the head of accounts for Marketers in Demand working.","index":28,"end_time":279.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":275.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ve been working with Kate for almost.","index":29,"end_time":281.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A year now and then Greg as soon as he joined the team.","index":30,"end_time":284.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":281.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m excited to have you join the team as well.","index":31,"end_time":287.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":285,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":32,"end_time":290.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And then this is Nina, she is one of our strategists.","index":33,"end_time":296.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, my name is Nina.","index":34,"end_time":297.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.52,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m a creative strategist at Marketers in Demand and I''m helping calling with whatever needs to be done for Chatmart, so.","index":35,"end_time":305.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":36,"end_time":307.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":37,"end_time":309.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m Julia and I just joined the team, I think about three weeks ago already.","index":38,"end_time":316.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So yeah, I''ve been helping with the sponsored external events and with the ABM strategy.","index":39,"end_time":322.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we''ll be working together with Kate and Greg in the same team.","index":40,"end_time":325.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":322.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":326.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":326.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very exciting.","index":42,"end_time":327.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, do you know if Greg''s joining today?","index":43,"end_time":331.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":329.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know what, I think we should probably crack on and if he can join, he will.","index":44,"end_time":335.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.11,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I know at a conference start.","index":45,"end_time":338.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The conference is tomorrow, but he''s already at the venue.","index":46,"end_time":342.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":338.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":47,"end_time":344.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before I pull up our slide deck, one thing I wanted to just update you guys on.","index":48,"end_time":348.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":344.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we had talked about me starting a conversation with HubSpot Sales for you guys potentially upgrading your account.","index":49,"end_time":354.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":348.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I did meet with them.","index":50,"end_time":355.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":354.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They of course wanted to push for.","index":51,"end_time":358.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys to sign right now.","index":52,"end_time":359.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I said they''re figuring out their budget.","index":53,"end_time":360.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":359.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not ready to sign right now.","index":54,"end_time":361.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":360.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is kind of a.","index":55,"end_time":362.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A mid Q1 initiative.","index":56,"end_time":364.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":362.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What what they did say is they can offer if you guys sign by 1212 to upgrade to Content Enterprise, which I think is what Greg was looking to do, they can apply net 60 terms so that you get the big end of the year discount that they''re offering, but you don''t actually have to pay it until February.","index":57,"end_time":383.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":365.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":58,"end_time":384.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will pass it on.","index":59,"end_time":391.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.87,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":60,"end_time":393.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, I''ll jump into it.","index":61,"end_time":400.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did send over the performance report.","index":62,"end_time":405.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":403.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, have you and Greg had a chance to review that document?","index":63,"end_time":408.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":406.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not in as much detail as I wanted to.","index":64,"end_time":413.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.03,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So maybe we can Just spend a little bit of time on it.","index":65,"end_time":415.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.23,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"If we haven''t, I don''t know how much we''ve got to go through today.","index":66,"end_time":418.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.03,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s not, it''s not an insane.","index":67,"end_time":422.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":419.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Amount of things to go through today.","index":68,"end_time":423.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, it was a 90 day review.","index":69,"end_time":425.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":423.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Basically the, the important things were just looking at the performance of different channels.","index":70,"end_time":431.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":427.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously Google Ads we''ve seen just fair.","index":71,"end_time":435.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":431.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Share of, I don''t want to say.","index":72,"end_time":437.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":435.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Struggles but learning, you know it''s, it''s a very niche topic especially in the United States.","index":73,"end_time":442.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":437.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And really the keywords with volume are.","index":74,"end_time":445.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":443.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Also not always relevant to what Threatmark provides.","index":75,"end_time":448.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did see, you know, when we went a little bit more broad match in the style, we saw some.","index":76,"end_time":453.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":449.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, keywords pop up for matches.","index":77,"end_time":456.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we didn''t and didn''t want to rank for.","index":78,"end_time":458.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":456.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we were immediately adding those to negative keywords but then we shifted to more of a brand LED approach and that actually got the click through rate.","index":79,"end_time":466.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To jump up very high on some of the keywords.","index":80,"end_time":468.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not a lot of impressions but the click through rates are very strong.","index":81,"end_time":471.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":468.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"About 20, 25% which is smashing industry standards.","index":82,"end_time":474.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But across like total search it was.","index":83,"end_time":477.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"546 clicks at a 4.05% click through rate.","index":84,"end_time":481.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then LinkedIn ads has certainly been.","index":85,"end_time":486.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":484.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our biggest lead driver.","index":86,"end_time":487.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The PDFs really are the main piece so and I can open up the document as well.","index":87,"end_time":494.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":488.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just in the last 90 days we generated 27 leads and almost a.","index":88,"end_time":498.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"50, 50 split between EMEA and the.","index":89,"end_time":500.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"U.S. one thing to note there is EMEA has been drastically more expensive than.","index":90,"end_time":505.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":500.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The U.S. yeah, that''s not surprising to me.","index":91,"end_time":509.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I think there''s just much more competition in the space.","index":92,"end_time":511.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":509.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Especially since it''s.","index":93,"end_time":515.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":514.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''S kind of, it''s still new in the United States.","index":94,"end_time":517.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":95,"end_time":519.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The Q2 campaign, we''ve definitely run into some budget constraints with the audience list that Greg had built with the companies.","index":96,"end_time":526.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":520.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re very large banks.","index":97,"end_time":529.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re being targeted a lot on LinkedIn out of.","index":98,"end_time":533.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t even remember the exact amount of people that were in that list but we''ve only been able to, oh.","index":99,"end_time":537.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was 4300 people but we''ve only been able to penetrate 1% based on the budget compared to competitors that are also targeting those people.","index":100,"end_time":544.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How much of the budget do we move across from our other legion?","index":101,"end_time":550.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Nina, do you know off the top of your head?","index":102,"end_time":553.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was 4, 500.","index":103,"end_time":555,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we started with a pretty small budget but we also wanted to make sure.","index":104,"end_time":560,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":556.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, we''re in December now, so we''re getting.","index":105,"end_time":561.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":560,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys are having Budget 2026 conversations as well.","index":106,"end_time":565.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was around 550, but that''s from the top of my head.","index":107,"end_time":571.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.16,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":572.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So somewhere in that 500, 550 range.","index":109,"end_time":574.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, you can see the cost.","index":110,"end_time":577.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Per click being between 27 and $70 per click.","index":111,"end_time":581.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":577.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with $500, you know, you''re getting impressions, you''re able to drive a few clicks.","index":112,"end_time":586.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s really no surprise that we didn''t see form fills coming through.","index":113,"end_time":590.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":591.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.25,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we do have recommendations to increase budget.","index":115,"end_time":595.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":593.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, I think LinkedIn has proven that it is a strong ground for providing leads.","index":116,"end_time":600.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":595.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I don''t know where are you guys right now in your.","index":117,"end_time":604.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":602.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In your 2026 budgeting?","index":118,"end_time":605.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s with Greg.","index":119,"end_time":607.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m afraid I don''t have the answer to that.","index":120,"end_time":608.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":607.41,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":121,"end_time":609.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":122,"end_time":609.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":609.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do have some recommendations and we can send those over as well.","index":123,"end_time":614.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":612.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s really increasing because we are seeing, I mean, strong indication metrics or strong leading indicators and LinkedIn being the strongest.","index":124,"end_time":624.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":615.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With providing the most leads.","index":125,"end_time":626.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":624.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we have more detail throughout the.","index":126,"end_time":629.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":626.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Document where we actually break down the.","index":127,"end_time":631.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Different ads that have been running and their performance.","index":128,"end_time":634.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":631.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":129,"end_time":635.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.07,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":130,"end_time":636.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":131,"end_time":637.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":132,"end_time":640.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did switch the Q2 campaign though, from sending.","index":133,"end_time":644.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":640.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was more of a brand awareness.","index":134,"end_time":645.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":644.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sending them to the landing page.","index":135,"end_time":646.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":645.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We switched it to the lead gen form.","index":136,"end_time":648.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":646.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that went live Monday or Tuesday, I believe.","index":137,"end_time":650.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":648.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Greg.","index":138,"end_time":651.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":651.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":139,"end_time":653.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":652.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":140,"end_time":654.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":653.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No worries.","index":141,"end_time":655.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Heard your conference prepping.","index":142,"end_time":656.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":655.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Are you conference prepping?","index":143,"end_time":659.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, conference prepping.","index":144,"end_time":661.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":660.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Nice.","index":145,"end_time":662.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, Kate, what were you saying?","index":146,"end_time":664.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t remember.","index":147,"end_time":668.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":148,"end_time":669.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"No worries.","index":149,"end_time":670.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was about the legion for the Q2 campaign.","index":150,"end_time":672.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":151,"end_time":673.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.2,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yes.","index":152,"end_time":674.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Glad to see that.","index":153,"end_time":675.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":674.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"When it''d be great to get the new creative once we have it into there as well.","index":154,"end_time":680.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":155,"end_time":683.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":681.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Contact us.","index":156,"end_time":685.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we are working on that.","index":157,"end_time":687.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":685.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we did send over the fraud disruption ads as well.","index":158,"end_time":691.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":687.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you had a chance to take a look at these since we updated the.","index":159,"end_time":694.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The actual captions on the images.","index":160,"end_time":696.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry I missed that.","index":161,"end_time":698.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ll have a look at them when we.","index":162,"end_time":700.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":163,"end_time":701.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also updated the background to match.","index":164,"end_time":706.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":703.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That other landing page style for the video on the Scam Flag page.","index":165,"end_time":709.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":706.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to though.","index":166,"end_time":710.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":710.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Check.","index":167,"end_time":711.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":710.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do we have a specific.","index":168,"end_time":712.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":711.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know, Greg, you''ve been working on.","index":169,"end_time":714.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":712.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the language around Scam Flag.","index":170,"end_time":716.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":714.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like is it Generative AI?","index":171,"end_time":717.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":716.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it something else?","index":172,"end_time":719.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":717.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to come up with like a cool title here, but also don''t want to misspeak to the Product.","index":173,"end_time":723.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we could go as simple as.","index":174,"end_time":729.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":726.47,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like how Scam Flag works.","index":175,"end_time":730.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":729.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I probably would bias towards just keeping it simple.","index":176,"end_time":736.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":734.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, no problem at all.","index":177,"end_time":739.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we also set up Google Analytics.","index":178,"end_time":746.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":743.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"4 tracking for registering on the test website with the sliders that we''re building.","index":179,"end_time":751.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":746.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we started by tracking those buttons.","index":180,"end_time":755.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we added St. Joseph, Michigan.","index":181,"end_time":758.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":755.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To geofencing location on Adroll.","index":182,"end_time":760.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Already went through the performance report.","index":183,"end_time":764.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Other things that we''re working on is addressing the homepage carousel changes that you had requested, Kate.","index":184,"end_time":772.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":765.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re working on those, that being the navigation jump and the red black H1 color consistency and then also for the PDF gating.","index":185,"end_time":782.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":772.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Greg, you asked us to look into HubSpot''s capabilities for providing like a smaller.","index":186,"end_time":786.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":782.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Version or like just the first page.","index":187,"end_time":788.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are two ways that we can do it.","index":188,"end_time":790.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"One, we can just have.","index":189,"end_time":792.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can have the page and have like the.","index":190,"end_time":794.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would say probably first two or three pages of the white papers.","index":191,"end_time":798.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":795.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because the first page is just a.","index":192,"end_time":799.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cover, it''s not going to give much.","index":193,"end_time":800.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":799.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Second page is often the forward.","index":194,"end_time":801.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So maybe the first five pages or something because then we get into table contents.","index":195,"end_time":806.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":803.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But so we can have that like just available on the page and then.","index":196,"end_time":809.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":806.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The form to download the rest.","index":197,"end_time":810.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":809.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or my developers or our developers said that we can also build a Mozilla library that allows more of that path.","index":198,"end_time":818.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Factory style that you were talking about.","index":199,"end_time":820.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s a Mozilla library?","index":200,"end_time":823.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":822.23,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''ve never heard of that before.","index":201,"end_time":824.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":823.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a bit above my development mindset, but they said they can do it.","index":202,"end_time":829.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just wanted to check with you guys.","index":203,"end_time":831.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":829.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":204,"end_time":833.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":832.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s worth jumping off on right now, but it''s good to know that there''s a potential path there.","index":205,"end_time":843.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":833.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it sounds like HubSpot doesn''t even in its higher content tiers have something.","index":206,"end_time":848.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":843.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, not natively.","index":207,"end_time":850.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It would be something we have to.","index":208,"end_time":851.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":850.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Custom build into their cdn.","index":209,"end_time":852.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":851.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":210,"end_time":853.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":853.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":211,"end_time":855.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":855.2,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right.","index":212,"end_time":858.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":213,"end_time":859.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so I''ll update the scan flag title and then Kate, on the newsroom page.","index":214,"end_time":863.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had the.","index":215,"end_time":864.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":863.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I thought I had this pulled up.","index":216,"end_time":867.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we added the dates here.","index":217,"end_time":868.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":867.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want them on the actual.","index":218,"end_time":870.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":868.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Article as well?","index":219,"end_time":873.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":872.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so, okay.","index":220,"end_time":874.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":876.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So firstly, yes, I would like on the.","index":222,"end_time":878.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":876.2,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"On the article page as well.","index":223,"end_time":879.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"When I looked, it didn''t appear.","index":224,"end_time":881.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.52,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And then when you said it had, then it appeared.","index":225,"end_time":884.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I feel like it looked dumb.","index":226,"end_time":886.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.32,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But it.","index":227,"end_time":887.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"When I was checking it, it wasn''t on there yet.","index":228,"end_time":889.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.16,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I believe you.","index":229,"end_time":890.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Internet''s been funky in 2025.","index":230,"end_time":893.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":890.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so you do want it on the actual listing page, too?","index":231,"end_time":898.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":895.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, please.","index":232,"end_time":899.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.07,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":233,"end_time":900.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":234,"end_time":901.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can make that change.","index":235,"end_time":902.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably just drop it right below the.","index":236,"end_time":905.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Title, I think, match it to whatever''s on the Insights.","index":237,"end_time":911.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":905.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, yeah.","index":238,"end_time":912.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":911.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of those resources, Insights and Newsroom look wildly different to me in terms of, like, the structure of the different tiles.","index":239,"end_time":924.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And it annoys me, but it''s not worth actually fixing it, I don''t think.","index":240,"end_time":927.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":924.38,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So if you want us to make.","index":241,"end_time":928.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":927.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any changes, we can.","index":242,"end_time":929.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":928.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll think about it.","index":243,"end_time":931.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":930.3,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I know that we wanted to go a little bit different style.","index":244,"end_time":934.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":931.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we didn''t want to just have the duplicate.","index":245,"end_time":936.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When you and I had talked and we were looking at, like, Feeds Eye.","index":246,"end_time":939.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":936.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And some other competitors and how they do it.","index":247,"end_time":941.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":248,"end_time":942.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.98,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I changed my mind.","index":249,"end_time":943.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":942.34,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, well, if.","index":250,"end_time":946.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":944.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys want, we can.","index":251,"end_time":947.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":946.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''d be pretty simple to.","index":252,"end_time":948.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":947.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Build it to match.","index":253,"end_time":949.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":951.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.83,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":255,"end_time":953.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":953.07,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right, jumping into some data analytics.","index":256,"end_time":960.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":955.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, so far this month, very early on, we spent £47 on branded terms.","index":257,"end_time":965.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":960.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The average cost per click has declined, which is good to see, but the ad strength is average because, you know.","index":258,"end_time":973.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":967.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need stronger resources on the website to point people to.","index":259,"end_time":976.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know that Kate, you''ve been working on a website audit as well and so wanted to check on the progress there and see, you know, what.","index":260,"end_time":983.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":977.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Comprehensive edits we can make so that.","index":261,"end_time":985.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":983.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ads that, if we are driving them.","index":262,"end_time":987.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":985.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Straight to the website, can have stronger conversion orientation.","index":263,"end_time":989.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":264,"end_time":991.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":990.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Craig and I were speaking about this earlier a little bit.","index":265,"end_time":993.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.07,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":266,"end_time":998.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.67,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hopefully I didn''t strike a nerve.","index":267,"end_time":1006.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1004.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re only on branded terms here, so I would expect that we would have a stronger score for our homepage.","index":268,"end_time":1020.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1006.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What I''m wondering is, if we put the rotating carousel in, does that actually make that a more.","index":269,"end_time":1030.479,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1023.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"A more gentle place to land than it is today?","index":270,"end_time":1035.119,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1031.599,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, it could be because it has, you know, when.","index":271,"end_time":1037.879,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1035.919,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When a user lands there, they have.","index":272,"end_time":1039.519,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.879,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Four opportunities right away to convert on something.","index":273,"end_time":1041.919,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1039.519,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":274,"end_time":1042.879,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1042.479,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I think let''s.","index":275,"end_time":1045.518,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1044.239,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I mean, 47 pounds.","index":276,"end_time":1047.519,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1045.679,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":277,"end_time":1048.159,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.679,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not looking at much data this month yet.","index":278,"end_time":1051.079,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1049.519,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, not looking at much data here, but let''s.","index":279,"end_time":1052.839,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1051.079,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Let''s plan on.","index":280,"end_time":1053.719,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1052.839,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"On taking a look at that again once that''s live.","index":281,"end_time":1058.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1053.719,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We did have one person we picked up who filled out our contact form through the branded ad.","index":282,"end_time":1069.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1059.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Now probably still would have filled out the contact form anyway.","index":283,"end_time":1072.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1069.13,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s the deal with the brand protection ads.","index":284,"end_time":1075.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1072.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But £47, I don''t care.","index":285,"end_time":1079.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1075.65,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s great.","index":286,"end_time":1079.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1079.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":287,"end_time":1080.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":288,"end_time":1081.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that was.","index":289,"end_time":1081.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1081.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was in a different language.","index":290,"end_time":1082.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t translate it.","index":291,"end_time":1083.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No yet.","index":292,"end_time":1084.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I saw that come through.","index":293,"end_time":1085.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":294,"end_time":1086.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1085.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":295,"end_time":1087.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so if you guys are good with it, we''re going to make just some more updates to the, the site links and extension and headlines and descriptions on the ads.","index":296,"end_time":1096.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1088.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just give them a nice refresh.","index":297,"end_time":1097.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":298,"end_time":1099.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":299,"end_time":1101.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1100.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for ad roll, I mean it''s a low spend but we are seeing decent results.","index":300,"end_time":1106.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1101.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know it looks like a low click through rate but you know, we''re just having target retargeting ads following someone around.","index":301,"end_time":1111.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1106.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, seeing a couple clicks come through is always good.","index":302,"end_time":1115.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s pretty cheap.","index":303,"end_time":1117.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess.","index":304,"end_time":1119.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1118.3,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The ad roll geofencing.","index":305,"end_time":1129.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1125.739,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hold on, let me just, let me parse this for a second.","index":306,"end_time":1134.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1132.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And why do we have everything in pounds?","index":307,"end_time":1140.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1138.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One thing we, we should probably do is try to get all of our platforms denominated in dollars next year.","index":308,"end_time":1151.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1141.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate.","index":309,"end_time":1151.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1151.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And we can do that one at a time.","index":310,"end_time":1153.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1151.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But yeah, so like for Google for.","index":311,"end_time":1155.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1153.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Example, I think that requires setting up.","index":312,"end_time":1157.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1155.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A whole new account.","index":313,"end_time":1157.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":314,"end_time":1158.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1158.35,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Which I don''t know, maybe, maybe there''s value in that.","index":315,"end_time":1163.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1158.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just clean slate start because we''re only doing the brand protection stuff here.","index":316,"end_time":1166.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1163.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s pretty easy.","index":317,"end_time":1167.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1166.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1168.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1168.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only annoying thing is advertiser verification again.","index":319,"end_time":1171.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1168.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fair.","index":320,"end_time":1173.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1172,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anyway, four clicks, is that four clicks for £455?","index":321,"end_time":1181.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1174.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Am I reading that right?","index":322,"end_time":1182.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1181.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":323,"end_time":1183.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1182.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":324,"end_time":1184.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we able to get any more detail on those clicks in terms of who, like what, what they did on the site?","index":325,"end_time":1200.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1186.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like were they all bounces like just high level stuff?","index":326,"end_time":1203.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1200.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Because like if those are four people that are within the institutions that