 right thing to do.","index":434,"end_time":1605.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1602.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"If we get.","index":435,"end_time":1610.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1609.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, if we basically, if we get anyone off of that campaign will be happy.","index":436,"end_time":1616.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1611.11,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":437,"end_time":1617.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1617.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":438,"end_time":1618.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1617.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we did update it to a lead gen form instead of going to the landing page earlier this week.","index":439,"end_time":1621.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1618.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll switch it to the other Legion forms that are running for the PDF downloads.","index":440,"end_time":1626.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1621.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1627.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1626.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like I just want to get their contact info.","index":442,"end_time":1629.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1627.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":443,"end_time":1629.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we just need to get them into the database.","index":444,"end_time":1632,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1630.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, get them into the database and start, start hitting them with perfect stuff.","index":445,"end_time":1637,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1632.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":446,"end_time":1637.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":447,"end_time":1638.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":448,"end_time":1638.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1638.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And in the.","index":449,"end_time":1638.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1638.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This long form document and I can.","index":450,"end_time":1640.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1639.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Even send over this slide deck.","index":451,"end_time":1642.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1640.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we do have some budget recommendations as well.","index":452,"end_time":1644.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1642.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was asking Kate, you know where you guys are in that conversation, so keep me updated.","index":453,"end_time":1649.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1646.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also one thing I mentioned at.","index":454,"end_time":1651.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1649.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The beginning of the call, I know you asked me to talk to HubSpot.","index":455,"end_time":1653.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1651.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sales, so I met with them.","index":456,"end_time":1655.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What they did offer, I let them know you guys were likely looking to upgrade to content enterprise probably sometime in Q1.","index":457,"end_time":1664.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1656.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They wanted to offer their end of.","index":458,"end_time":1666.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1664.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Year discount because obviously that works out.","index":459,"end_time":1668.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1666.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Better for them if they get their numbers.","index":460,"end_time":1670.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1668.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they said if you sign by 12:2, they''ll give you 60, a net 60 payment.","index":461,"end_time":1675.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1670.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you wouldn''t actually pay until February.","index":462,"end_time":1677.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1675.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":463,"end_time":1681.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1680.76,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would it make sense for you to make an intro over to me to the rep and, and so I can start because The.","index":464,"end_time":1694.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1685.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There''s another conversation.","index":465,"end_time":1696.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1694.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So just, just so you''re in the loop.","index":466,"end_time":1698.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1696.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Um, we use outreach for sales sequences.","index":467,"end_time":1702.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1698.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We use it very poorly.","index":468,"end_time":1704.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1703.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We are over provisioned like bonkers and it costs us a lot of money, as far as I can tell, at least how we''re using it.","index":469,"end_time":1716.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1705.72,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Most of HubSpot has parity around most of the sales tools and, and would have just better data, better integration, better.","index":470,"end_time":1727.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1716.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I want to talk to them about that too, like trying to understand where the overlap sits, maybe doing a pilot that I think I could execute very quickly, pick up some end of year discounts on, and then start the conversation on the content side a little bit too.","index":471,"end_time":1746,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1729.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds great.","index":472,"end_time":1747.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1746.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll introduce you.","index":473,"end_time":1747.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1747.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have a shared deal room that are created with them so that.","index":474,"end_time":1750.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1747.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we''re recognized as your partner so that you guys get that discount as well.","index":475,"end_time":1754.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1750.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":476,"end_time":1755.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1754.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":477,"end_time":1755.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1755.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And you guys, I''m sure, get, get your, your side of the story too.","index":478,"end_time":1758.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1755.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":479,"end_time":1759.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1758.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":480,"end_time":1760.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1759.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":481,"end_time":1760.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1760.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll make that introduction once.","index":482,"end_time":1762.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1760.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We get out of here.","index":483,"end_time":1763.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1762.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":484,"end_time":1767.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1766.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the Q2 digital campaign, we already talked about not seeing, you know, a lot of penetration into that list, but we are seeing a decent Click through rate, 3.34%.","index":485,"end_time":1777.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Honestly, industry averages 0.0 or 0.44%.","index":486,"end_time":1781.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1777.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are, you know, the people.","index":487,"end_time":1783.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1782.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That are seeing it, the impressions that we''re able to gain.","index":488,"end_time":1785.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1783.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People are engaging.","index":489,"end_time":1787.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is why I''m saying it''s the gooey center, man.","index":490,"end_time":1789.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1787.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":491,"end_time":1790.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1789.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like we can, we can spend a little bit on that and it''s okay.","index":492,"end_time":1793.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1790.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":493,"end_time":1795.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1794.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Perfect.","index":494,"end_time":1797.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":495,"end_time":1799.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1798.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had a recommendation of creating a lookalike audience, but I think if we keep it narrow and dedicate more.","index":496,"end_time":1804.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1799.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Budget, then we can see more penetration into that.","index":497,"end_time":1807.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Mm, great.","index":498,"end_time":1809.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1807.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I. Yeah, go ahead.","index":499,"end_time":1811.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1809.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"What do you think about expanding it out to targeting banks in Michigan?","index":500,"end_time":1819.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1812.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Like any bank in Michigan.","index":501,"end_time":1822.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1820.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":502,"end_time":1823.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because they love us there, apparently.","index":503,"end_time":1826.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1823.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Why Michigan specifically?","index":504,"end_time":1831.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t tell you, man.","index":505,"end_time":1833.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1831.86,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":506,"end_time":1834.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1833.38,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t get it.","index":507,"end_time":1834.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1834.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like, they all talk to each other and like, I guess we, we got a chatty client there and we''re not complaining.","index":508,"end_time":1843.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1835.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, not complaining.","index":509,"end_time":1845.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1844.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Detroit''s one of my favorite airports, so there you go.","index":510,"end_time":1851.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1847.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we should.","index":511,"end_time":1854.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1853.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think, I think the answer to that question is yes.","index":512,"end_time":1857.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1854.79,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But I think we need to kind of come up with what our account based marketing strategy is for those different segments which, you know, we''ll, we''ll start ironing out here in the next few weeks.","index":513,"end_time":1872.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1857.59,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That those ads, if I remember correctly, Those ads are Q2 specific.","index":514,"end_time":1879.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1875.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So like that one needs to be Q2 customers only.","index":515,"end_time":1884.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1879.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I do think we can expand the list, Colin, because we''re getting some more data on that and so that''s something that I can work on facilitating.","index":516,"end_time":1894.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1885.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But then I think, Kate, to your point, it probably makes sense for us to do like a Michigan oriented non Q2, just Michigan and there can be overlap.","index":517,"end_time":1907.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1895.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I can happy to compete with myself, but.","index":518,"end_time":1911.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1907.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then we, you know, tailor the ads to, you know, Michigan stuff.","index":519,"end_time":1918.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1911.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I don''t know what it is.","index":520,"end_time":1919.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1918.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''ll figure it out.","index":521,"end_time":1920.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1919.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I was just going to say.","index":522,"end_time":1921.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1920.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The same thing like grinders and soda pop if I remember correctly.","index":523,"end_time":1925.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1921.45,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So.","index":524,"end_time":1927.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1927.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But I think that that definitely is one of the account based segments that we were going to need to start fleshing out.","index":525,"end_time":1937.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1928.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And we''ll talk about this as we get to that part.","index":526,"end_time":1942.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1937.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s everything that we had prepped in our slide deck.","index":527,"end_time":1948.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1946.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Kate, I know that you said that you''re still going through to review some of the things that we sent.","index":528,"end_time":1953.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1948.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Over like the ads and things like that.","index":529,"end_time":1955.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1953.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also for Mike''s addition to the podcast recording, we''re going to be wrapped up on Monday with that and we''ll.","index":530,"end_time":1961.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1955.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be able to share those assets.","index":531,"end_time":1962.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1961.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d like to stick.","index":532,"end_time":1966.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1965.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, I''ve got a few things if we could go through your deck again please, because I''ve got.","index":533,"end_time":1970.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1967.65,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh yeah.","index":534,"end_time":1971.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1970.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But on that podcast one I''d like to stick to just posting on Wednesdays just for consistency.","index":535,"end_time":1975.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1971.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think Tuesday last time.","index":536,"end_time":1978.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1975.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So.","index":537,"end_time":1978.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1978.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":538,"end_time":1980.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1978.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I know we were in a good role for a while when we.","index":539,"end_time":1983.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1981.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Had every two weeks.","index":540,"end_time":1984.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1983.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we''ve got recording tomorrow as well.","index":541,"end_time":1990.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1984.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Was there any specific slide that you.","index":542,"end_time":1993.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1991.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to look at in the deck?","index":543,"end_time":1994.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1993.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had like a thought for everyone.","index":544,"end_time":1997.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1995.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":545,"end_time":1998.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1997.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I didn''t interrupt you while she on your flow, so actually let''s go to the next one, please.","index":546,"end_time":2003.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1998.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I was thinking around creative.","index":547,"end_time":2008.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2007.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Can we just have a look at what our competitors are doing?","index":548,"end_time":2011.159,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2008.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Because we haven''t really explored where we are versus competitors yet.","index":549,"end_time":2015.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2011.32,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We''ve just been looking at our ourselves and, and previous months so on.","index":550,"end_time":2022.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2015.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What are they doing?","index":551,"end_time":2023.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2023.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What does their ads look like?","index":552,"end_time":2025.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2023.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What are they talking about?","index":553,"end_time":2026.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2025.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, we can tap into like spyfu.","index":554,"end_time":2029.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2027.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And see what we can get there for what creative they''re running and things like that.","index":555,"end_time":2034.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2030.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It does seem based on the metrics and the impact that we''re having in.","index":556,"end_time":2038.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2034.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The audience that we are targeting almost the exact same lists across these campaigns.","index":557,"end_time":2044.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2038.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, well that means.","index":558,"end_time":2046.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2044.69,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That means that we''re onto something.","index":559,"end_time":2049.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2046.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s Funny.","index":560,"end_time":2052.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2049.34,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I saw.","index":561,"end_time":2053.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2052.58,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So biocatch is doing events in the Nordics and I happen to know that their company''s strategy is to not do events in places where they have customers.","index":562,"end_time":2065.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2053.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And I''m like, ooh, Nordics is up for grabs.","index":563,"end_time":2070.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2066.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There you go.","index":564,"end_time":2070.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2070.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe we, you know, that was one concern.","index":565,"end_time":2076.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2073.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we were doing a lot of testing, you know, a few months ago with launching, we had a MIA one, EMEA two, us, we had a Canada, we talked about apac, all these different things.","index":566,"end_time":2083.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2076.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It felt like a wide net with not a lot of depth.","index":567,"end_time":2088.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2084.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think if we do have like a Michigan specific campaign, a Nordic.","index":568,"end_time":2092.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2089.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Specific campaign, I think we can make some penetration into those markets.","index":569,"end_time":2096.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2092.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I totally agree.","index":570,"end_time":2097.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2096.14,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So just to round this out in terms of where my head is, I want to really start orienting us towards a true account based approach.","index":571,"end_time":2109.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2098.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Creating those tranches or segments and deploying our ads against those.","index":572,"end_time":2115.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2110.81,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Now what we are about to or getting close to having, which we''ve never had before, are actual target account lists that our AES are trying to prospect into.","index":573,"end_time":2127.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2115.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So similar to the Q2 campaign, where you know it''s going to be expensive to get into the audience, but when we get in, it''s, it''s, it''s much closer to revenue than otherwise.","index":574,"end_time":2140.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2128.97,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I think we''re gonna have to do a bunch of that and break them up into smaller chunks that are much deeper versus wide.","index":575,"end_time":2148.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2142.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":576,"end_time":2148.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2148.33,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we''re trying to figure out what those accounts are as the starting point because that helps us establish the narrative, it helps us figure out where the boundaries are.","index":577,"end_time":2157.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2149.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All that good stuff.","index":578,"end_time":2158.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2157.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Do you have an idea of the.","index":579,"end_time":2159.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2158.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Number of accounts that you''re planning?","index":580,"end_time":2161.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2159.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":581,"end_time":2163.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2162.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So in the Nordics it''s about 100.","index":582,"end_time":2168.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2163.85,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"In the UK Western Europe it''s in the 400s probably.","index":583,"end_time":2175.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2169.05,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And then in the US it''s probably closer to 1000.","index":584,"end_time":2179.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2176.73,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":585,"end_time":2180.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2179.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so we got a one to.","index":586,"end_time":2181.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2180.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Few and a one to many approach.","index":587,"end_time":2182.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2181.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because our question comes from the way that we could orient ads or landing page.","index":588,"end_time":2186.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2182.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if it''s, if it''s a one to one, like we''re just picking like a few specific banks, you know, dedicate or build a landing page dedicated to them.","index":589,"end_time":2193.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2186.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what we could do is have.","index":590,"end_time":2194.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2193.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Region dedicated landing pages.","index":591,"end_time":2196.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2194.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I suspect that''s where we''re going to start landing and like region oriented narratives.","index":592,"end_time":2204.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2196.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean compliance and everything is different, right?","index":593,"end_time":2206.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2204.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":594,"end_time":2207.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2207.09,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So I suspect that''s where we''re going to land.","index":595,"end_time":2209.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2207.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I, I learned there''s, there''s a lot of like data cleanup that we still need to do.","index":596,"end_time":2217.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2211.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I learned last week that we have a thousand duplicate accounts in Salesforce.","index":597,"end_time":2221.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2218.36,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Which.","index":598,"end_time":2224.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2224.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, pisses me off to no end.","index":599,"end_time":2227.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2224.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I like how you pause for impact when you say that.","index":600,"end_time":2233.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2228.92,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, well, a third of the accounts in our Salesforce instance are duplicate.","index":601,"end_time":2238.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2233.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"There are 3,100 accounts in Salesforce.","index":602,"end_time":2241.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2238.63,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"A thousand of them are duplicates.","index":603,"end_time":2242.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2241.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":604,"end_time":2243.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2243.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":605,"end_time":2244.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2243.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, did you ever share when Greg joined the team, the original audit I.","index":606,"end_time":2248.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2244.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did of Salesforce.","index":607,"end_time":2249.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2248.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was.","index":608,"end_time":2253.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2252.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was like, wow, there''s.","index":609,"end_time":2255.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2254.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a lot of deals in here that have a close date of two years ago and no updates in the last three years.","index":610,"end_time":2261.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2255.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":611,"end_time":2262.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2262.15,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So if we''re gonna go account based, that needs to be fixed.","index":612,"end_time":2268.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2263.83,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yep.","index":613,"end_time":2269.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2268.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because otherwise it''s, you know, we don''t really know, like, closed loss isn''t, like, able to be trusted.","index":614,"end_time":2276.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2270.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could have a much bigger list of people to reach out to and target.","index":615,"end_time":2279.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2276.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":616,"end_time":2280.07,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2279.51,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":617,"end_time":2280.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2280.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m.","index":618,"end_time":2281.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2281.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I''m starting to fight the good fight on that one.","index":619,"end_time":2284.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2281.99,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And ultimately what I want to do is establish target accounts in HubSpot by each one of these slices that we''re setting up.","index":620,"end_time":2295.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2285.43,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So that way we can attach all of our efforts into a set of target accounts and measure efficacy across them specifically.","index":621,"end_time":2305.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2296.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And, like, we might take a few of those and do one to one.","index":622,"end_time":2309.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2306.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"You know, if there''s two banks in the US that were like, gosh, they''d be real swell to be a customer of ours.","index":623,"end_time":2316.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2309.53,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We could put that effort in and see if it''s worth it.","index":624,"end_time":2319.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2316.89,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":625,"end_time":2319.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2319.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, like, actually getting focused on this.","index":626,"end_time":2324.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2320.19,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"AE has these accounts that they are going after because otherwise they''re just shooting in the dark and, like, trying to shoot at anything that.","index":627,"end_time":2333.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2324.75,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That moves, basically.","index":628,"end_time":2334.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2333.27,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":629,"end_time":2335.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2334.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":630,"end_time":2337.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2336.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''d be great to have a feedback loop with them as well.","index":631,"end_time":2339.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2337.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, like if.","index":632,"end_time":2340.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2339.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If Amy, for example, is hunting a.","index":633,"end_time":2342.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2340.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Specific group of accounts and she''s.","index":634,"end_time":2344.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2342.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If she has one conversation and they give her some insight of like, yeah, I''m seeing this in the market, then feed that back to us.","index":635,"end_time":2350.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2344.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What can we change on the ads.","index":636,"end_time":2351.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2350.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The landing page, things like that.","index":637,"end_time":2353.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2351.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":638,"end_time":2356.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2356.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":639,"end_time":2357.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2356.91,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Kate, was there anything else on this.","index":640,"end_time":2358.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2357.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Slide that you wanted to go through?","index":641,"end_time":2359.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2358.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nope.","index":642,"end_time":2360.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2359.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Right.","index":643,"end_time":2361.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2361.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the homepage 1.","index":644,"end_time":2365.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2363.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Can we just add to that refinement list?","index":645,"end_time":2367.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2365.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Auto scroll.","index":646,"end_time":2370.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2369.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think I did put in the feedback as well, but just clarifying.","index":647,"end_time":2376.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2372.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, no problem.","index":648,"end_time":2378.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2377.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you also, Greg, you mentioned about on the fourth slide, we haven''t got an asset to the.","index":649,"end_time":2384.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2379.74,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Right.","index":650,"end_time":2385.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2384.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is it.","index":651,"end_time":2387.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2386.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"What.","index":652,"end_time":2388.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2387.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is there a plan to put something there or Are we just leaving that empty?","index":653,"end_time":2390.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2388.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So we originally had in the mockup the image of the platform that was on the website, but we don''t have.","index":654,"end_time":2399.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2391.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Many assets of the actual platform itself.","index":655,"end_time":2402.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2399.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wasn''t sure what we wanted to show there.","index":656,"end_time":2406.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2404.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think when we share the design.","index":657,"end_time":2407.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2406.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You said to just go with the text.","index":658,"end_time":2409.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2407.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but it would have to be center oriented.","index":659,"end_time":2412.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2410.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, so centering it.","index":660,"end_time":2415.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2414.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, because like right now it''s just like text on the left in a big blank space.","index":661,"end_time":2419.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2415.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So it''s like it''s unfinished.","index":662,"end_time":2422.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2420.68,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":663,"end_time":2422.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2422.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":664,"end_time":2423.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2423.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can center that.","index":665,"end_time":2424.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2423.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sorry, can we test putting a form there?","index":666,"end_time":2428.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2426.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I would have to check with the developers.","index":667,"end_time":2432.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2431.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t see why they wouldn''t be.","index":668,"end_time":2434.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2433.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Able to put a short code there for a form.","index":669,"end_time":2436.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2434.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Shortcodes.","index":670,"end_time":2439.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2439.01,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Or HubSpot script, I guess, is.","index":671,"end_time":2444.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2442.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How they share their forms for embeds.","index":672,"end_time":2446.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2444.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we should try that.","index":673,"end_time":2452.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2451.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''d be clever.","index":674,"end_time":2453.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2452.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s not the first thing they see because it''s.","index":675,"end_time":2458,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2456.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think it''s the.","index":676,"end_time":2458.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2458,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The last of the four.","index":677,"end_time":2459.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2458.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The last one.","index":678,"end_time":2460.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2459.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":679,"end_time":2460.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2460.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but I think that''s.","index":680,"end_time":2461.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2460.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":681,"end_time":2462.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2461.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Like.","index":682,"end_time":2462.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2462.44,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, you don''t like, kind of walk them into it.","index":683,"end_time":2466.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2463,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Anything here?","index":684,"end_time":2474.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2473.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was more just to say that disruption white paper is with Mel for feedback.","index":685,"end_time":2480.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2474.84,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I kind of expect him to have some.","index":686,"end_time":2483.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2481.13,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So not fully signed off on that one yet.","index":687,"end_time":2487.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2484.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":688,"end_time":2488.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2487.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you know, do you have a.","index":689,"end_time":2490.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2489.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feeling if there''ll be content changes or.","index":690,"end_time":2492.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2490.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Design changes or both?","index":691,"end_time":2493.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2492.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I don''t.","index":692,"end_time":2495.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2494.57,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Tbd.","index":693,"end_time":2496.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2495.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":694,"end_time":2497.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2496.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s always hard to tell on that one.","index":695,"end_time":2500.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2497.21,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"We''re doing a briefing with Gartner on Monday and we lifted the.","index":696,"end_time":2508.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2501.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The fraud Lifecycle graphic, I think does a nice job kind of representing that, but we just grabbed it as a screenshot with the text.","index":697,"end_time":2520.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2509.41,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Would it be possible to send us over a raw asset for that?","index":698,"end_time":2525.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2520.29,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So we can drop it in the deck and.","index":699,"end_time":2526.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2525.17,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, use it.","index":700,"end_time":2530.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2528.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have that.","index":701,"end_time":2530.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2530.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can just share the link.","index":702,"end_time":2531.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2530.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":703,"end_time":2533.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2532.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw that message and put it together.","index":704,"end_time":2544.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2542.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I must have just forgot to send it having not being in the office last week.","index":705,"end_time":2549.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2544.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I feel like a chicken with my head cut off.","index":706,"end_time":2551.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2549.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Papers.","index":707,"end_time":2557.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2556.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Js.","index":708,"end_time":2559.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2559.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I will share this folder.","index":709,"end_time":2565.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2562.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, we created a PNG version.","index":710,"end_time":2567.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2565.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s a transparent background and then all of the images also.","index":711,"end_time":2570.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2567.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":712,"end_time":2571.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2570.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"So share this with you.","index":713,"end_time":2573.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2572.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would be good.","index":714,"end_time":2575.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2574.39,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I have shared that with Witt already.","index":715,"end_time":2577.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2576.31,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Oh, maybe.","index":716,"end_time":2580.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2578.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hold on.","index":717,"end_time":2580.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2580.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Oh, so maybe we did, I think.","index":718,"end_time":2584.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2581.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"An editable version.","index":719,"end_time":2585.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2584.72,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think so.","index":720,"end_time":2592.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2590.48,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The one that he has in the deck is all the text is just an image.","index":721,"end_time":2600.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2592.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"With what you shared does it have the text in there in the png, or is it just the.","index":722,"end_time":2610.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2605.12,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The chart?","index":723,"end_time":2612.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2611.87,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"The text is in the image.","index":724,"end_time":2614.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2613.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we could share an svg, or if you want to share any slide deck that you''re working on, we could.","index":725,"end_time":2623.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2616.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just rebuild it in that slide deck so that you could edit text if you wanted to.","index":726,"end_time":2627.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2623.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, if I share a slide deck, what would your turnaround be on that?","index":727,"end_time":2634.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2627.95,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Pretty quick.","index":728,"end_time":2635.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2634.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, the images, it''s just.","index":729,"end_time":2636.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2635.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not a creative exercise.","index":730,"end_time":2638.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2637.31,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s.","index":731,"end_time":2638.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2638.71,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":732,"end_time":2639.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2638.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, let me make a copy.","index":733,"end_time":2642.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2639.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, let me make a copy and send it over to you.","index":734,"end_time":2648.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2645.82,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Actually, here, let me download it.","index":735,"end_time":2654.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2652.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, I''ll drop that in the Slack channel in a minute here.","index":736,"end_time":2670.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2668.07,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":737,"end_time":2674.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2673.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Kate, any other questions?","index":738,"end_time":2676.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2674.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Two points.","index":739,"end_time":2677.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2677.27,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Can you share some analytics for the podcast, please?","index":740,"end_time":2682.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2679.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, in the.","index":741,"end_time":2684.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2683.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"In the.","index":742,"end_time":2685.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2684.87,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":743,"end_time":2685.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2685.35,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s called a portal or whatever it''s called.","index":744,"end_time":2689.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2685.71,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll see if we can get.","index":745,"end_time":2693.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2692.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That looped into the data box.","index":746,"end_time":2696.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2693.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Data box, that''s the one.","index":747,"end_time":2697.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2696.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":748,"end_time":2697.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2697.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d have to check with Buzzsprout''s API.","index":749,"end_time":2700.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2697.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On that.","index":750,"end_time":2701.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2700.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I can give some preliminary numbers.","index":751,"end_time":2707.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2705.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It looks like the Aaron Fry episode.","index":752,"end_time":2709.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2707.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was downloaded 14 times so far.","index":753,"end_time":2711.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2709.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bank Teller to Fight Frau Bank Teller to Fraud fighter episodes downloaded 42 times.","index":754,"end_time":2716.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2712.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can give you those types.","index":755,"end_time":2717.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2716.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of numbers as well.","index":756,"end_time":2718.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2717.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":757,"end_time":2719.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2718.6,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The most successful was Fraud response Officer at Mercantile Bank.","index":758,"end_time":2723.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2720.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Had 82 downloads.","index":759,"end_time":2725.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2723.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How.","index":760,"end_time":2726.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2726.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"How do we integrate those stats into something that doesn''t require reading them off?","index":761,"end_time":2737.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2727.16,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what I was.","index":762,"end_time":2738.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2737.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just going to check with Buzzsprout''s.","index":763,"end_time":2740.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2738.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"API so we can get that looped into data box.","index":764,"end_time":2741.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2740.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":765,"end_time":2742.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2741.92,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":766,"end_time":2743.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2742.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"That way it''s a live update for you guys.","index":767,"end_time":2746.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2745.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":768,"end_time":2747.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2746.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"My final point was we''re basically at the end of the year rushing ahead of myself a little bit, but do we want to do an end of year or 20, 26 planning session on top of our normal weekly?","index":769,"end_time":2763.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2750.85,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I would love that.","index":770,"end_time":2765.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2764.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know there''s been a lot of conversations going on and all you guys.","index":771,"end_time":2769.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2766.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are working hard on it and budgets and tools and campaigns and strategies and locations and targeting, you know, all of it.","index":772,"end_time":2776.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2769.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think we do need probably like an hour, you know, hour.","index":773,"end_time":2780.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2776.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And a half session where we just kind of brainstorm a roadmap for next year.","index":774,"end_time":2785.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2780.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''d be great.","index":775,"end_time":2789.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2787.21,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, I can send over calendar link.","index":776,"end_time":2795.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2792.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we can get that booked.","index":777,"end_time":2796.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2795.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s going to be a good idea.","index":778,"end_time":2799.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2797.96,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"One other thing I wanted to gauge your interest in is and this would.","index":779,"end_time":2805.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2800.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Be gifted project, so you guys would not have to worry about points, but.","index":780,"end_time":2808.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2805.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A end of year compilation video from.","index":781,"end_time":2811,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2808.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of the Behind Enemy Lines podcasts.","index":782,"end_time":2813.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2811,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":783,"end_time":2815.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2814.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be cool.","index":784,"end_time":2816.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2815.8,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":785,"end_time":2818.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2817.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, we''ll start working on that.","index":786,"end_time":2819.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2818.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you guys using some of the AI to do that stuff now in.","index":787,"end_time":2829.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2821.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"In Riverside?","index":788,"end_time":2830.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2829.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We.","index":789,"end_time":2831.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2830.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re, like, starting to, but it''s.","index":790,"end_time":2834.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2831.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re still a little nervous of the overall, like, I don''t want to say.","index":791,"end_time":2838.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2834.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Control freak, but, you know, designers are perfectionists, and I. I love that.","index":792,"end_time":2843.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2838.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, AI can mess some things up.","index":793,"end_time":2846.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2843.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I started playing with Descript.","index":794,"end_time":2849.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2846.6,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Mm, yeah.","index":795,"end_time":2851.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2850,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Overlord.","index":796,"end_time":2851.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2851.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":797,"end_time":2852.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2852.08,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"And like, it can do some cool stuff.","index":798,"end_time":2854.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2852.56,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s getting there.","index":799,"end_time":2855.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2854.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think they over promise a little bit, but I think, you know, a year from now, I think it''ll be in an even better spot.","index":800,"end_time":2861.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2855.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we look at image generation in.","index":801,"end_time":2863.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2861.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The last two months with.","index":802,"end_time":2865.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2863.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys have seen all the memes from, like, Flux versus Nano Banana 2.","index":803,"end_time":2870.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2865.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":804,"end_time":2872.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2871.52,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Just from like, September to November.","index":805,"end_time":2874.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2872.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s.","index":806,"end_time":2878.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2877.93,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s crazy how fast that space is improving.","index":807,"end_time":2884.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2878.49,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":808,"end_time":2885.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2885.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a internal Slack channel where.","index":809,"end_time":2887.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2885.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We talk about just new tools that.","index":810,"end_time":2889.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2887.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We want to test out, and it''s.","index":811,"end_time":2890.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2889.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just been blowing out the last two weeks.","index":812,"end_time":2892.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2890.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s like a new thing every day.","index":813,"end_time":2893.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2892.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":814,"end_time":2895.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2894.57,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Okay.","index":815,"end_time":2901.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2901.06,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I just sent over that one slide in the channel.","index":816,"end_time":2904.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2901.62,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"It''s loading.","index":817,"end_time":2905.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2904.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Hotel WI fi.","index":818,"end_time":2906.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2905.78,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Give it a minute.","index":819,"end_time":2908.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2907.7,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Is there anything else?","index":820,"end_time":2912.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2911.54,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"No, that''s all from our end.","index":821,"end_time":2914.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2913.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you get a chance to officially meet Julia?","index":822,"end_time":2920.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2917.22,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Yes.","index":823,"end_time":2921.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2921.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As we had a round of introductions at the very beginning of the call.","index":824,"end_time":2926.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2922.66,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That''s why I joined late.","index":825,"end_time":2928.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2926.9,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"I was like, need that.","index":826,"end_time":2929.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2928.1,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"But all that being said, definitely excited to pick your brain some more, Julia.","index":827,"end_time":2935.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2931.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, you know, anything we can do to help out with any event planning that you''re doing, any abm.","index":828,"end_time":2940.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2935.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, we run a lot of.","index":829,"end_time":2942.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2940.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It over here as well, so would love to brainstorm, you know, so that we''re all operating efficiently.","index":830,"end_time":2946.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2942.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":831,"end_time":2947.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2946.81,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":832,"end_time":2948.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2947.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":833,"end_time":2948.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2948.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, good stuff.","index":834,"end_time":2952.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2950.25,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":835,"end_time":2953.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2952.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, thank you guys very much.","index":836,"end_time":2954.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2953.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hope you have a great rest of your day, and we''ll be in touch.","index":837,"end_time":2957.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2955.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With our action items.","index":838,"end_time":2958.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2957.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":839,"end_time":2959.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2958.4,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Thank you, Colin.","index":840,"end_time":2959.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2959.28,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"Thank you, Nina.","index":841,"end_time":2960.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2959.88,"speaker_name":"Greg Smith"},{"text":"See you.","index":842,"end_time":2960.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2960.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":843,"end_time":2961.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2960.8,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Bye.","index":844,"end_time":2961.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2961.28,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"dateString":"2025-12-03T14:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84564648866?pwd=JR6eWxlxKbgogzCqTNUawSLUUhQoEa.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","iulia.lungu@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KB35HD2AR67F0N4K8GQ58189","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Shifted Q2 LinkedIn campaign to lead gen forms, yielding four U.S. leads last week alone.","Greg approved higher spending to reach Q2 bank audience despite high CPC and narrow penetration.","Colin offered early HubSpot upgrade discount via net-60 terms; Greg to explore further integration.","Agreed to align ad strategies to AE target account lists regionally (Nordics, U.S., U.K.).","Kate requested end-of-year planning session; team supports account-based strategy refinement for 2026."],"highlights":[{"quote":"If we have to spend $750,000 a lead for one of those leads, it''s still profitable.","speaker":"Greg Smith"},{"quote":"LinkedIn has proven that it is a strong ground for providing leads.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"I want to really start orienting us towards a true account based approach.","speaker":"Greg Smith"}],"topics":["lead gen","account-based","budget","ads","hubspot"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-03T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Budget Allocation**\n\nMarketing efforts have shown clear evidence that LinkedIn is the strongest lead generator, but budget increases are needed to improve penetration and form fills.\n\n- **LinkedIn ads generated 27 leads over the last 90 days, split evenly between EMEA and the U.S., with EMEA costs significantly higher due to competition** (08:18)  \n    - The U.S. market remains less saturated, showing better cost efficiency and potential for scaling.  \n    - Budget constraints limited penetration to just 1% of a targeted audience list of **4,300** large banks on LinkedIn.  \n    - Cost per click ranged between **$27 and $70**, reflecting the competitive nature of the target segments.  \n    - Increasing the LinkedIn budget is recommended to capitalize on strong engagement signals and convert more leads.\n\n- **Google Ads delivered 546 clicks at a 4.05% click-through rate, with brand-led targeting achieving exceptional 20-25% CTR on specific keywords** (07:20)  \n    - Broad match keywords initially attracted irrelevant traffic, leading to immediate negative keyword additions.  \n    - Brand keyword campaigns are performing well but require stronger website resources to boost conversions.  \n    - Early December spend on branded terms was **£47**, with average CPC decreasing but ad strength rated as average.  \n    - Plans to refresh ad headlines, site links, and descriptions aim to improve overall ad performance.\n\n- **AdRoll retargeting campaigns showed low spend but delivered several clicks, highlighting cost-effective brand reinforcement** (18:30)  \n    - Geofencing was added to target St. Joseph, Michigan, but spend was low and results modest.  \n    - Greg Smith suggested converting all ad platforms’ currencies to USD in 2026 for consistency and easier budget tracking.\n\n- **Q2 digital banking campaign was switched from a landing page to lead gen forms to improve lead capture, with 7 leads last month mostly in the U.S.** (22:10)  \n    - Greg Smith emphasized prioritizing PDF downloads over landing page conversions to maximize database growth.  \n    - The U.S. campaign uses broader job title and industry filters, while the Q2 list remains narrowly targeted and expensive but valuable.  \n    - Only about 1% of the Q2 target list has been reached due to budget limits, with CTR at a strong **3.34%**, exceeding industry averages.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing and Targeting Strategy**\n\nThe team is shifting towards a focused account-based marketing (ABM) approach, concentrating on segmented, high-value target lists to improve conversion and ROI.\n\n- **Greg Smith outlined plans to segment target accounts into regional and strategic groups, with approximately 100 accounts in Nordics, 400 in UK/Western Europe, and 1,000 in the U.S.** (36:00)  \n    - This segmentation supports both one-to-one and one-to-many marketing approaches tailored to compliance and regional needs.  \n    - The goal is to align ads and landing pages with these specific segments to improve messaging relevance and engagement.\n\n- **Salesforce data cleanup is critical, as approximately one-third of the 3,100 accounts are duplicates, hindering effective targeting** (37:00)  \n    - Greg is leading efforts to clean data and establish target accounts in HubSpot to enable precise tracking and measurement of campaign efficacy.  \n    - This will create a feedback loop between sales reps and marketers to adapt campaigns based on real market insights.\n\n- **Expansion of geographic targeting includes a proposed campaign focused on banks in Michigan, leveraging local client success and market familiarity** (30:00)  \n    - This would be a non-Q2 campaign to complement the existing segmented efforts.  \n    - Customized ads tailored to Michigan’s market characteristics will be developed as part of Account Based Marketing.\n\n- **The strategy emphasizes deeper, narrower targeting over broad campaigns to maximize lead quality and revenue impact, even at higher acquisition costs** (34:00)  \n    - Greg stated willingness to accept high lead costs if the quality and conversion potential justify the spend.\n\n## **Product and Content Development**\n\nContent and product marketing efforts are being refined to support lead generation and engagement with precise messaging and creative updates.\n\n- **The fraud disruption white paper is pending final feedback from Mel, with potential content and design changes expected** (41:10)  \n    - Final sign-off is awaited before integrating this asset fully into campaigns.\n\n- **HubSpot content gating capabilities are limited natively, but custom development options exist to offer partial white paper previews** (13:30)  \n    - Options include showing first few pages on a landing page or developing a custom Mozilla library to support partial content previews.  \n    - Greg preferred holding off on custom builds for now but appreciated knowing the potential paths.\n\n- **Podcast analytics show the most popular episode downloaded 82 times, with plans to integrate Buzzsprout data into the DataBox dashboard for live updates** (44:50)  \n    - Kate requested analytics access to better track engagement.  \n    - Consistent podcast posting on Wednesdays was agreed to maintain regularity and audience expectations.\n\n- **The homepage carousel and newsroom pages are being updated for improved navigation, color consistency, and date display for articles** (14:30)  \n    - Kate requested adding publication dates on article pages and aligning styles between newsroom and Insights tiles, though a full redesign was deprioritized.\n\n- **Discussions are underway to possibly embed a HubSpot form in a currently empty homepage section to drive conversions** (40:25)  \n    - Technical feasibility to embed HubSpot scripts or shortcodes is being explored.\n\n## **Technology and Tracking Enhancements**\n\nTracking and analytics improvements aim to provide better insights and measurement to inform decision-making and campaign optimization.\n\n- **Google Analytics 4 tracking was set up for button registrations on the test website, enhancing conversion monitoring on interactive elements** (12:30)  \n    - Geofencing via AdRoll was configured to target specific locations, starting with St. Joseph, Michigan.\n\n- **AdRoll targeting is based on IP and enriched company lists, providing confidence that ads reach intended audience members** (20:20)  \n    - However, detailed behavioral data on clicks beyond form fills is limited.  \n    - Colin committed to exploring deeper click behavior tracking for better performance evaluation.\n\n- **Discussions included potential benefits of creating new Google Ads accounts to denominate spend in USD and start fresh with advertiser verification** (18:50)  \n    - This was considered to simplify budgeting and reporting but weighed against the cost of re-verification.\n\n- **Plans to improve and refresh Google Ads extensions and headlines aim to increase ad strength and conversion rates on branded terms** (15:55)  \n    - Early data shows room for improvement, with average ad strength currently moderate.\n\n## **Sales and Vendor Coordination**\n\nCloser alignment between marketing and sales tools is planned to improve workflow, reduce overlap, and optimize costs.\n\n- **Greg Smith intends to start conversations with HubSpot Sales about upgrading to Content Enterprise with a mid-Q1 target, leveraging an end-of-year discount offer if signed by December 12** (28:00)  \n    - Colin will introduce Greg to the HubSpot rep and facilitate access to a shared deal room to secure discounts.  \n    - Greg is also exploring consolidating sales tools by replacing Outreach with HubSpot’s sales sequences for better data and integration.\n\n- **Budgeting discussions for 2026 are underway but not finalized; coordination between marketing and sales on tool spend and campaign funding is ongoing** (09:50)  \n    - Colin offered to send detailed budget recommendations once internal conversations progress.\n\n- **An end-of-year or early 2026 planning session was proposed to align budgets, campaigns, tools, and strategies across teams** (45:50)  \n    - Colin will circulate a calendar invite for a 60- to 90-minute brainstorming session.\n\n## **Creative and Competitive Intelligence**\n\nThe team is beginning to benchmark against competitors and test regional market opportunities to refine messaging and targeting.\n\n- **Kate requested a review of competitor ad creatives to understand messaging and positioning differences** (33:40)  \n    - Colin suggested using tools like SpyFu to gather competitive ad data and creative examples.  \n    - Greg noted that competitors like BioCatch avoid events in existing customer regions, opening opportunities in the Nordics.\n\n- **Regional campaigns focusing on Michigan and Nordic markets are being considered to deepen market penetration rather than casting wide nets** (34:40)  \n    - These focused campaigns will complement account-based marketing efforts and leverage local insights.\n\n- **The team agreed on continuing to refine creative assets and testing new formats to improve engagement across channels** (11:20)  \n    - New fraud disruption ad captions and image backgrounds were recently updated to align with landing page styles.\n\n- **Internal discussions include cautious adoption of AI tools for content creation and video editing, balancing innovation with quality control** (46:50)  \n    - Colin and Greg shared experiences with AI tools like Descript and Riverside, acknowledging rapid improvements but also current limitations.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","LinkedIn Ads","HubSpot Upgrade","Salesforce Cleanup","Podcast Analytics","Fraud Disruption White Paper"],"overview":"- **LinkedIn Leads:** 27 leads in 90 days; 1% of 4,300 targeted banks reached due to budget limits.  \n- **Google Ads Performance:** 546 clicks, 4.05% CTR; branded keywords achieved 20-25% CTR.  \n- **Q2 Campaign Shift:** Focus switched to lead gen forms; 7 leads captured last month, highlighting budget constraints.  \n- **ABM Strategy:** 1,000 U.S. accounts and segmentation planned for more effective targeting and increased conversions.  \n- **Sales Tool Consolidation:** HubSpot upgrade discussions underway to enhance data integration; December 12 discount opportunity.  \n- **Creative Benchmarking:** Reviewing competitor ads to refine messaging, with regional campaigns targeting Michigan and Nordics.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nIntroduce Greg Smith to HubSpot Sales representative for pilot and upgrade discussions (28:10)\nSend updated fraud disruption ads and asset links (including fraud lifecycle graphic) to Greg and Kate (42:50)\nShare podcast analytics for Data Box integration and provide preliminary download numbers (44:40)\nRefresh Google Ads with new site links, headlines, and descriptions (40:35)\nImplement homepage carousel updates: navigation jump, H1 color consistency, and auto-scroll feature (38:00)\nUpdate Scam Flag title and newsroom pages with date display on listings and articles (14:30)\nWork on end-of-year compilation video from Behind Enemy Lines podcast as a complimentary project (46:55)\nMonitor and report LinkedIn lead gen and AdRoll campaign performance regularly (21:00)\nCollaborate with Julia on event planning and ABM strategy alignments (49:05)\n\n**Greg Smith**\nProvide feedback to Colin and team on fraud disruption white paper after receiving draft from Mel (41:15)\nShare editable slide deck with Colin for fraud lifecycle graphic text editing (43:50)\nOversee Salesforce data cleanup to remove duplicate accounts for more effective ABM targeting (36:59)\nDetermine budget allocation and finalize ABM segmented account lists for Nordics, UK/Europe, and US (36:20)\nCoordinate with Kate to define Michigan-specific targeting approach and audience list updates (30:20)\nTrack Q2 digital banking campaign performance; switch offer to PDF download forms to capture contacts (26:00)\n\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nReview updated fraud disruption ads and provide feedback (11:37)\nConfirm and refine newsroom page date display requirements (14:40)\nContinue website audit and share findings with Colin to improve conversion for branded ad landing pages (16:25)\nShare feedback to add auto-scroll to homepage carousel (39:20)\nDecide on potential matching of Insights and Newsroom resource tile styles (15:30)\nMaintain podcast posting schedule to Wednesdays and request analytics reports (44:40)\nConfirm 2026 budgeting status and update Colin accordingly (09:50)\nCollaborate on end-of-year and 2026 planning session scheduling (46:00)\n\n**Julia Lungu**\nCoordinate with Colin and Kate on sponsored external event planning and ABM strategy support (49:01)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"29d2a2fe-fea4-4063-a654-4b52db06285b","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
