  'Meeting Notes: New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
  '## **Marketing Performance and Budget Allocation**

Marketing efforts have shown clear evidence that LinkedIn is the strongest lead generator, but budget increases are needed to improve penetration and form fills.

- **LinkedIn ads generated 27 leads over the last 90 days, split evenly between EMEA and the U.S., with EMEA costs significantly higher due to competition** (08:18)  
    - The U.S. market remains less saturated, showing better cost efficiency and potential for scaling.  
    - Budget constraints limited penetration to just 1% of a targeted audience list of **4,300** large banks on LinkedIn.  
    - Cost per click ranged between **$27 and $70**, reflecting the competitive nature of the target segments.  
    - Increasing the LinkedIn budget is recommended to capitalize on strong engagement signals and convert more leads.

- **Google Ads delivered 546 clicks at a 4.05% click-through rate, with brand-led targeting achieving exceptional 20-25% CTR on specific keywords** (07:20)  
    - Broad match keywords initially attracted irrelevant traffic, leading to immediate negative keyword additions.  
    - Brand keyword campaigns are performing well but require stronger website resources to boost conversions.  
    - Early December spend on branded terms was **£47**, with average CPC decreasing but ad strength rated as average.  
    - Plans to refresh ad headlines, site links, and descriptions aim to improve overall ad performance.

- **AdRoll retargeting campaigns showed low spend but delivered several clicks, highlighting cost-effective brand reinforcement** (18:30)  
    - Geofencing was added to target St. Joseph, Michigan, but spend was low and results modest.  
    - Greg Smith suggested converting all ad platforms’ currencies to USD in 2026 for consistency and easier budget tracking.

- **Q2 digital banking campaign was switched from a landing page to lead gen forms to improve lead capture, with 7 leads last month mostly in the U.S.** (22:10)  
    - Greg Smith emphasized prioritizing PDF downloads over landing page conversions to maximize database growth.  
    - The U.S. campaign uses broader job title and industry filters, while the Q2 list remains narrowly targeted and expensive but valuable.  
    - Only about 1% of the Q2 target list has been reached due to budget limits, with CTR at a strong **3.34%**, exceeding industry averages.

## **Account-Based Marketing and Targeting Strategy**

The team is shifting towards a focused account-based marketing (ABM) approach, concentrating on segmented, high-value target lists to improve conversion and ROI.

- **Greg Smith outlined plans to segment target accounts into regional and strategic groups, with approximately 100 accounts in Nordics, 400 in UK/Western Europe, and 1,000 in the U.S.** (36:00)  
    - This segmentation supports both one-to-one and one-to-many marketing approaches tailored to compliance and regional needs.  
    - The goal is to align ads and landing pages with these specific segments to improve messaging relevance and engagement.

- **Salesforce data cleanup is critical, as approximately one-third of the 3,100 accounts are duplicates, hindering effective targeting** (37:00)  
    - Greg is leading efforts to clean data and establish target accounts in HubSpot to enable precise tracking and measurement of campaign efficacy.  
    - This will create a feedback loop between sales reps and marketers to adapt campaigns based on real market insights.

- **Expansion of geographic targeting includes a proposed campaign focused on banks in Michigan, leveraging local client success and market familiarity** (30:00)  
    - This would be a non-Q2 campaign to complement the existing segmented efforts.  
    - Customized ads tailored to Michigan’s market characteristics will be developed as part of Account Based Marketing.

- **The strategy emphasizes deeper, narrower targeting over broad campaigns to maximize lead quality and revenue impact, even at higher acquisition costs** (34:00)  
    - Greg stated willingness to accept high lead costs if the quality and conversion potential justify the spend.

## **Product and Content Development**

Content and product marketing efforts are being refined to support lead generation and engagement with precise messaging and creative updates.

- **The fraud disruption white paper is pending final feedback from Mel, with potential content and design changes expected** (41:10)  
    - Final sign-off is awaited before integrating this asset fully into campaigns.

- **HubSpot content gating capabilities are limited natively, but custom development options exist to offer partial white paper previews** (13:30)  
    - Options include showing first few pages on a landing page or developing a custom Mozilla library to support partial content previews.  
    - Greg preferred holding off on custom builds for now but appreciated knowing the potential paths.

- **Podcast analytics show the most popular episode downloaded 82 times, with plans to integrate Buzzsprout data into the DataBox dashboard for live updates** (44:50)  
    - Kate requested analytics access to better track engagement.  
    - Consistent podcast posting on Wednesdays was agreed to maintain regularity and audience expectations.

- **The homepage carousel and newsroom pages are being updated for improved navigation, color consistency, and date display for articles** (14:30)  
    - Kate requested adding publication dates on article pages and aligning styles between newsroom and Insights tiles, though a full redesign was deprioritized.

- **Discussions are underway to possibly embed a HubSpot form in a currently empty homepage section to drive conversions** (40:25)  
    - Technical feasibility to embed HubSpot scripts or shortcodes is being explored.

## **Technology and Tracking Enhancements**

Tracking and analytics improvements aim to provide better insights and measurement to inform decision-making and campaign optimization.

- **Google Analytics 4 tracking was set up for button registrations on the test website, enhancing conversion monitoring on interactive elements** (12:30)  
    - Geofencing via AdRoll was configured to target specific locations, starting with St. Joseph, Michigan.

- **AdRoll targeting is based on IP and enriched company lists, providing confidence that ads reach intended audience members** (20:20)  
    - However, detailed behavioral data on clicks beyond form fills is limited.  
    - Colin committed to exploring deeper click behavior tracking for better performance evaluation.

- **Discussions included potential benefits of creating new Google Ads accounts to denominate spend in USD and start fresh with advertiser verification** (18:50)  
    - This was considered to simplify budgeting and reporting but weighed against the cost of re-verification.

- **Plans to improve and refresh Google Ads extensions and headlines aim to increase ad strength and conversion rates on branded terms** (15:55)  
    - Early data shows room for improvement, with average ad strength currently moderate.

## **Sales and Vendor Coordination**

Closer alignment between marketing and sales tools is planned to improve workflow, reduce overlap, and optimize costs.

- **Greg Smith intends to start conversations with HubSpot Sales about upgrading to Content Enterprise with a mid-Q1 target, leveraging an end-of-year discount offer if signed by December 12** (28:00)  
    - Colin will introduce Greg to the HubSpot rep and facilitate access to a shared deal room to secure discounts.  
    - Greg is also exploring consolidating sales tools by replacing Outreach with HubSpot’s sales sequences for better data and integration.

- **Budgeting discussions for 2026 are underway but not finalized; coordination between marketing and sales on tool spend and campaign funding is ongoing** (09:50)  
    - Colin offered to send detailed budget recommendations once internal conversations progress.

- **An end-of-year or early 2026 planning session was proposed to align budgets, campaigns, tools, and strategies across teams** (45:50)  
    - Colin will circulate a calendar invite for a 60- to 90-minute brainstorming session.

## **Creative and Competitive Intelligence**

The team is beginning to benchmark against competitors and test regional market opportunities to refine messaging and targeting.

- **Kate requested a review of competitor ad creatives to understand messaging and positioning differences** (33:40)  
    - Colin suggested using tools like SpyFu to gather competitive ad data and creative examples.  
    - Greg noted that competitors like BioCatch avoid events in existing customer regions, opening opportunities in the Nordics.

- **Regional campaigns focusing on Michigan and Nordic markets are being considered to deepen market penetration rather than casting wide nets** (34:40)  
    - These focused campaigns will complement account-based marketing efforts and leverage local insights.

- **The team agreed on continuing to refine creative assets and testing new formats to improve engagement across channels** (11:20)  
    - New fraud disruption ad captions and image backgrounds were recently updated to align with landing page styles.

- **Internal discussions include cautious adoption of AI tools for content creation and video editing, balancing innovation with quality control** (46:50)  
    - Colin and Greg shared experiences with AI tools like Descript and Riverside, acknowledging rapid improvements but also current limitations.',
  '2025-12-03 14:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Introduce Greg Smith to HubSpot Sales representative for pilot and upgrade discussions (28:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Send updated fraud disruption ads and asset links (including fraud lifecycle graphic) to Greg and Kate (42:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Share podcast analytics for Data Box integration and provide preliminary download numbers (44:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Refresh Google Ads with new site links, headlines, and descriptions (40:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Implement homepage carousel updates: navigation jump, H1 color consistency, and auto-scroll feature (38:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Update Scam Flag title and newsroom pages with date display on listings and articles (14:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Work on end-of-year compilation video from Behind Enemy Lines podcast as a complimentary project (46:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor and report LinkedIn lead gen and AdRoll campaign performance regularly (21:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with Julia on event planning and ABM strategy alignments (49:05)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback to Colin and team on fraud disruption white paper after receiving draft from Mel (41:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Share editable slide deck with Colin for fraud lifecycle graphic text editing (43:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Oversee Salesforce data cleanup to remove duplicate accounts for more effective ABM targeting (36:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Determine budget allocation and finalize ABM segmented account lists for Nordics, UK/Europe, and US (36:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Kate to define Michigan-specific targeting approach and audience list updates (30:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Track Q2 digital banking campaign performance; switch offer to PDF download forms to capture contacts (26:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Review updated fraud disruption ads and provide feedback (11:37)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm and refine newsroom page date display requirements (14:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue website audit and share findings with Colin to improve conversion for branded ad landing pages (16:25)","completed":false},{"text":"Share feedback to add auto-scroll to homepage carousel (39:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Decide on potential matching of Insights and Newsroom resource tile styles (15:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Maintain podcast posting schedule to Wednesdays and request analytics reports (44:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm 2026 budgeting status and update Colin accordingly (09:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate on end-of-year and 2026 planning session scheduling (46:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with Colin and Kate on sponsored external event planning and ABM strategy support (49:01)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
