    1498,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81473554029?pwd=oAVAZ4qOWIzyRbxS8zQrkrquELSYaw.1',
    '{"id":"01KBFNZ4Y5EANF1Z2M6AZ5FA6P","title":"Data Assessment Solutions reconnect","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaign Launch and Performance**\n\nThe team successfully launched the updated **LinkedIn ads, emails, and outreach messages** tied to the new registration campaign today (15:43).\n\n- **All feedback on the landing page was addressed, and the page is now ready for campaign launch** as confirmed by **Colin** (01:24).  \n    - The updated page includes buttons linking to registration and demo forms for easier user flow.  \n    - This readiness removed a key barrier, allowing the campaign to start immediately.  \n    - Emails and LinkedIn messages switched focus from offering free profiles to promoting free registration, improving message clarity.  \n    - Early email responses are limited, but this is expected as emails serve primarily for awareness rather than direct replies.\n\n- **The campaign targets a list of 1,500 contacts managed through Smart Lead and LinkedIn outreach tools** (04:00).  \n    - Contacts were sourced from purchased leads via Clay, integrating multiple databases and AI to ensure fit and accuracy.  \n    - Leads are continuously updated to reflect role changes within target companies, maintaining list relevance.  \n    - Colin highlighted that buying leads is necessary for outbound campaigns, as organic prospecting is time-consuming.\n\n- **Current email engagement shows mainly out-of-office replies, with LinkedIn expected to drive direct interactions** (16:32).  \n    - Monitoring is in place via Slack notifications for immediate response tracking.  \n    - Retargeting through multiple channels aims to build recognition before direct lead engagement.\n\n## **Product Explainer Video Development**\n\nThe product explainer video is entering a recording and animation phase with a clear plan to improve user friendliness (04:04).\n\n- **The script was finalized with minor edits removing outdated references and adjusting text based on feedback from Axel and Tina** (04:24).  \n    - Colin will resend the updated script for the team to record screen captures.  \n    - The video will reanimate real platform footage into simplified, user-friendly visuals matching approved screenshots.\n\n- **Screen recordings should focus on key features including the AI-powered interface, resource management dashboard, skills matrix, and resume upload** (05:21).  \n    - Eli confirmed the team will upload recordings to Teams for Colin’s team to download and animate.  \n    - Colin advised against recording via Zoom due to quality loss; local screen recordings are preferred for clarity.  \n    - The team discussed scheduling 15-minute sessions with Axel for guided recordings to optimize content coverage and reduce rework.\n\n- **This approach aims to create a polished video that demonstrates platform value clearly while saving time on multiple takes** (08:00).  \n    - The plan includes flexibility to adjust the script if needed during recordings.\n\n## **Podcast Production and Content Strategy**\n\nA podcast episode recording is planned with Riverside, aiming to create versatile content assets supporting marketing (12:10).\n\n- **The podcast script is complete except for David’s years of experience, which Eli will confirm and provide** (12:47).  \n    - Riverside accounts are set up, offering high-quality, separate audio tracks to avoid recording issues.  \n    - Colin offered to assist with technical setup and recommended a short 5-minute test recording to ensure smooth execution.\n\n- **The podcast content will be repurposed into multiple formats including short videos and quote cards for social and landing pages** (23:44).  \n    - This multi-format content strategy is designed to amplify outreach and support the campaign’s messaging arsenal.\n\n- **Eli aims to complete the initial podcast recording before the upcoming Friday meeting to allow for a 7-day turnaround on assets** (23:15).  \n    - The Friday meeting will review any questions about Riverside and screen recordings, providing a checkpoint for finalizing content.\n\n## **Lead Acquisition and Quality Insights**\n\nLead sourcing relies on integrated databases with a focus on fit rather than behavior-based targeting due to current data limitations (17:09).\n\n- **Leads are purchased through Clay, which aggregates data from LinkedIn, ZoomInfo, Apollo, and AI tools to create targeted lists** (17:50).  \n    - The team filters leads by company size, industry, revenue, and job titles to match the ideal customer profile developed in early strategy sessions.  \n    - Email addresses are validated to reduce bounce rates and maintain campaign efficiency.\n\n- **Colin clarified that buying leads is essential for outbound campaigns as organic prospecting is slow and less scalable** (18:58).  \n    - There is no practical access to data indicating prior product interest or search behavior, limiting highly targeted lead buying.  \n    - Attempts to buy “hot leads” or competitor customer lists often result in unreliable or outdated contacts.\n\n- **The team can enrich leads by identifying tech stacks used via HG Insights to approximate competitor customers, though data accuracy is limited** (21:27).  \n    - Legal and proprietary restrictions prevent accessing competitor lead sources directly.\n\n## **Process and Communication Improvements**\n\nClear communication and streamlined processes are in place to reduce delays and ensure smooth campaign and content delivery (01:24).\n\n- **Feedback loops on landing page, video script, and campaign messaging have been effectively closed, enabling rapid deployment** (01:24).  \n    - Colin monitors campaign responses via Slack, providing real-time alerts on replies and bouncebacks.  \n    - Updates are made to contact lists dynamically to maintain lead accuracy.\n\n- **Sharing of videos, scripts, and instructions occurs through Teams and chat channels for transparency and tracking** (22:39).  \n    - Colin committed to sending tutorial videos for Riverside and screen recording guidelines to Eli for team readiness.  \n    - Eli and David’s responsibilities for podcast recording and screen captures are clearly assigned with due dates before the Friday meeting.\n\n- **The team agreed to use the Friday meeting to address any open items related to podcast recording and screen capture, maximizing efficiency** (15:31).  \n    - This structure reduces the need for extra meetings and keeps focus on deliverables.\n\n## **Strategic Outlook and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is focused on driving awareness and engagement through a multi-channel approach combining paid ads, outreach, and rich content (02:25).\n\n- **Switching campaign focus from free profile offers to registration aligns messaging with clearer value and expected user behavior** (02:47).  \n    - Colin noted the importance of layering touchpoints to build brand familiarity before expecting conversion.\n\n- **Content assets like explainer videos and podcast episodes are critical to supporting the sales funnel and improving user understanding** (23:44).  \n    - These assets will be repurposed across channels to extend reach and engagement.\n\n- **Lead acquisition strategy balances cost and data quality, with ongoing refinement to improve targeting within current ecosystem constraints** (17:09).  \n    - Continued monitoring and list adjustments will optimize campaign efficiency.\n\n- **Eli and Colin will coordinate the upcoming recording sessions with Axel and David to finalize video and podcast materials before the next meeting** (23:04).  \n    - This sequencing ensures content readiness to support ongoing marketing efforts and campaign optimization.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead generation","LinkedIn outreach","Product explainer video","Podcast recording","Campaign launch","Data enrichment"],"overview":"- **Marketing Campaign Launch:** New LinkedIn ads and outreach messages launched, improving clarity on free registration focus.  \n- **Target Contacts:** Campaign targets 1,500 contacts through Smart Lead and LinkedIn, sourced via Clay for accuracy.  \n- **Video Development:** Product explainer video in recording phase, focusing on key features with a user-friendly approach.  \n- **Podcast Strategy:** Podcast episode script is ready, aims for versatile content with a 7-day turnaround on assets.  \n- **Lead Acquisition:** Leads are purchased using Clay, targeting company size and industry; focus on data quality over behavior.  \n- **Process Improvements:** Clear communication and rapid feedback loops established to enhance campaign efficiency and content delivery.","action_items":"\n**Eli Bebinger**\nRecord screen captures of key DesiDollar platform features (AI tool, dashboards, skills matrix, resume upload) and upload to Teams for animation (06:06)\nCollaborate with Axel to review and potentially refine video script and recording checklist (08:00)\nCoordinate with David to record initial podcast episode via Riverside before Friday (23:04)\nPrepare questions or adjustments related to screen recordings and podcast recording for follow-up Friday meeting (23:30)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated explainer video script and checklist for recordings to Eli and team via Teams (05:09)\nProvide instructional video on Riverside podcast recording tool to Eli’s team (13:58)\nMonitor campaign responses and notify team of any lead replies or out-of-office replies via Slack (15:52)\nConfirm updated campaign messaging and lead list details to Axel (24:30)\n\n**Axel**\nReview explainer video recording checklist with Eli and coordinate on specific platform sections to highlight (07:45)\n"},"duration":24.969999313354492,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sweet.","index":0,"end_time":1.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Was a good time.","index":1,"end_time":4.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.44,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, it was fun.","index":2,"end_time":5.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''s.","index":3,"end_time":6.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was Naples, Florida.","index":4,"end_time":7.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like 85 degrees.","index":5,"end_time":8.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can''t complain.","index":6,"end_time":10,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice, right?","index":7,"end_time":11.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.64,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw that.","index":8,"end_time":14.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Axel''s gonna be a few minutes late.","index":9,"end_time":15.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there celebrity?","index":10,"end_time":18.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''d you say?","index":11,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yay.","index":12,"end_time":21.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":20.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Celebrating?","index":13,"end_time":21.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":14,"end_time":23.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":24.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you celebrate Thanksgiving?","index":16,"end_time":26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, we.","index":17,"end_time":27.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I live in Mexico.","index":18,"end_time":28.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":27.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"We don''t celebrate Thanksgiving.","index":19,"end_time":30.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":28.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe you were.","index":20,"end_time":33.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.5,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know if you lived in Mexico, but.","index":21,"end_time":34.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.18,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Cool.","index":22,"end_time":35.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.22,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":36.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":36.1,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"You live in Mexico City or.","index":24,"end_time":38.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.74,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, it''s in Merida, in Yucatan.","index":25,"end_time":42.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":26,"end_time":42.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.179,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I went there one time.","index":27,"end_time":44.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.3,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, that''s cool.","index":28,"end_time":46.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.14,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, it was cool.","index":29,"end_time":47.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.18,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":30,"end_time":49.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":48.34,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Not everyone comes here.","index":31,"end_time":50.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.06,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, it was nice.","index":32,"end_time":52.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":51.38,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":33,"end_time":54.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I saw it.","index":34,"end_time":57.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Axel said he''s gonna be a few minutes late.","index":35,"end_time":58.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you.","index":36,"end_time":59.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there anyone else joining?","index":37,"end_time":60.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want to wait for him to get started?","index":38,"end_time":61.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re good to start.","index":39,"end_time":63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.88,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay.","index":40,"end_time":63.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.4,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He''s finishing up another meeting and we don''t know how long that could take.","index":41,"end_time":72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":42,"end_time":72.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So what I did.","index":43,"end_time":75.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.76,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I think most of the things I put in the chat.","index":44,"end_time":80.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":75.8,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":45,"end_time":81.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.94,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":46,"end_time":81.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll go through this.","index":47,"end_time":82.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":48,"end_time":84.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.62,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yep.","index":49,"end_time":85.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the page was updated.","index":50,"end_time":86.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just wasn''t reflected in markup with checkboxes.","index":51,"end_time":89.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":86.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I went through last night and checked all of those things off, but everything that was left for feedback has been updated on the page.","index":52,"end_time":95.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything is all good here.","index":53,"end_time":100.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"From Axel''s.","index":54,"end_time":101.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He had some rewrites for some sections, but all of that has been updated here.","index":55,"end_time":106.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the buttons will either take you to the registration page or to, like, a demo form that we have here.","index":56,"end_time":118.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":57,"end_time":119.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.15,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Did I see the demo form?","index":58,"end_time":120.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":59,"end_time":121.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":121.07,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":122.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just mirrored the fields that you guys have on your demo.","index":61,"end_time":126.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":122.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kind of pared it down a little bit.","index":62,"end_time":128.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":126.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":63,"end_time":131.319,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.519,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And just from what I understood was that we were waiting to run some LinkedIn ads until this page was ready.","index":64,"end_time":144.279,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.399,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right?","index":65,"end_time":144.599,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":144.279,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":66,"end_time":145.319,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":144.759,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now we''re good to go on that.","index":67,"end_time":147.639,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.799,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":148.239,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.879,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have.","index":69,"end_time":148.999,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.239,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The emails are live.","index":70,"end_time":150.439,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.999,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those went live this morning.","index":71,"end_time":151.879,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":150.519,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the LinkedIn outreach, the messages from your profile.","index":72,"end_time":155.559,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.519,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is live switching to this registration campaign instead of the 50 free profiles campaign?","index":73,"end_time":161.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.669,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wait, sorry, say that again.","index":74,"end_time":166.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.42,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So we had talked a couple weeks ago about switching the focus of the campaign from the, like, free profile package that we were offering to registering for desi dollar for free.","index":75,"end_time":176.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we wrote new emails and LinkedIn messages, and those are live as of this morning, sending out from the emails that we created for you and the.","index":76,"end_time":185.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":176.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your LinkedIn profile.","index":77,"end_time":186.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":78,"end_time":187.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.13,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":79,"end_time":188.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.69,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think that''s better.","index":80,"end_time":189.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":188.13,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I get some responses to the profile thing.","index":81,"end_time":192.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.93,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That just doesn''t quite make sense.","index":82,"end_time":195.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.49,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, they''ll just be like, one guy said, like, okay, yeah, I mean.","index":83,"end_time":199.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.21,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Human behavior is always interesting, especially around the holiday season.","index":84,"end_time":204.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some people are just accept the message, don''t really look at it and do their thing.","index":85,"end_time":208.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":204.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I did see you''re going back and forth with Amy Hess, who looked like a qualified lead.","index":86,"end_time":213.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, they said that they''re pretty happy with their solution though.","index":87,"end_time":218.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, but, you know, definitely good opportunity to continue the conversation.","index":88,"end_time":222.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, you''ll see the new messages coming out today as well.","index":89,"end_time":227.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And here''s a table breakdown of all the 1500 contacts going into Smart Lead.","index":90,"end_time":234.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the emails and then into the hate reach, which is LinkedIn outreach messaging.","index":91,"end_time":237.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":92,"end_time":240.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"The other thing you guys asked about was updates for the product explainer video.","index":93,"end_time":248.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I went through, there''s only a few comments that Axel had made and I can''t remember her name.","index":94,"end_time":255.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Someone else on your team had made one comment as well.","index":95,"end_time":258.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to say it starts with a B.","index":96,"end_time":263.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Her name.","index":97,"end_time":264.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Tina.","index":98,"end_time":265.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.53,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":265.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.01,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yes.","index":100,"end_time":266.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And she was just saying that you guys no longer worked with.","index":101,"end_time":269.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was ag.","index":102,"end_time":270.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we just removed that from the script on the logo section.","index":103,"end_time":275.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then Axel had like two or three more text changes, so we made those.","index":104,"end_time":279.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we''re at with this now is we talked a couple weeks ago about you guys just recording using the platform.","index":105,"end_time":285.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, the features that you want to show that are fit inside the script.","index":106,"end_time":289.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have like the visual and the voiceover.","index":107,"end_time":290.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we''re going to do with that recording is animate it.","index":108,"end_time":294.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to animate it.","index":109,"end_time":296.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Instead of looking directly like your platform, we want it to look more like these screenshots that we have here because we find that they are more user friendly.","index":110,"end_time":304.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":111,"end_time":306.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":112,"end_time":307.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.77,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So do you need me to send you the script again so that you guys can record this?","index":113,"end_time":311.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, please.","index":114,"end_time":315.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Okay, we''ll do.","index":115,"end_time":316.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Record the script.","index":116,"end_time":320.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So all you need to do is just go into the platform, into the desi dollar platform and just record the parts of the tool that you want to show.","index":117,"end_time":330.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like the AI powered interface that Axel had pulled up in our call a couple of weeks ago, resource management dashboard showing time zones and utilization metrics, you know, just basically the different dashboards inside the tool.","index":118,"end_time":345.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''re going to reanimate everything and then put in some other slides, like, you know, logos of companies you guys work with, etc.","index":119,"end_time":351.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so we''re just going to do all these screen recordings and then email and then put them in teams.","index":120,"end_time":357.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.49,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, you can upload them to teams and we can download them and then we''ll just reanimate the entire thing.","index":121,"end_time":361.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":122,"end_time":363.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":362.57,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So.","index":123,"end_time":366.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":367.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How is that gonna work?","index":125,"end_time":374.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.14,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Say, how is it gonna work?","index":126,"end_time":378.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just thinking in terms of logistically, if I just go in and start taking some screen recordings today, probably, or.","index":127,"end_time":385.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.82,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":128,"end_time":388.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you don''t need to worry about the voiceover or anything.","index":129,"end_time":390.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just like the.","index":130,"end_time":390.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The main features that you guys want to showcase in this explainer video, we have the visuals and the voiceover if, you know, and Axel reviewed this.","index":131,"end_time":397.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if when you''re reading it, you want to switch anything, you know, feel free.","index":132,"end_time":400.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":397.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re not locked in, you know, with anything on this.","index":133,"end_time":403.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But.","index":134,"end_time":405.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I would record, like, the AI tool, you know, the dashboards, the skills matrix, you know, resume, upload, things like that.","index":135,"end_time":412.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then once you send us the actual screen recordings, will, you know, design and animate the whole process?","index":136,"end_time":418.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":413.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A conversation with the AI tool or what do you.","index":137,"end_time":423.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, like, almost like you would picture like a ChatGPT commercial.","index":138,"end_time":427.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right?","index":139,"end_time":428,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, they.","index":140,"end_time":428.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They go in and it''s like a basic question that they''re asking or something like that.","index":141,"end_time":431.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or it can be a complex question.","index":142,"end_time":433.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would just.","index":143,"end_time":434.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":433.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need to have the screen recording of you guys using it, and then we''ll reanimate the whole thing.","index":144,"end_time":438.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the screen recording doesn''t have to be like, super high quality or anything.","index":145,"end_time":441.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just have to see what you want to show in the platform and then the layout of it.","index":146,"end_time":445.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll redesign everything to match more like this.","index":147,"end_time":449.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I almost feel like could make sense would be to maybe even this time now, during this meeting, would just be to record a meeting of using the tool.","index":148,"end_time":463.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":449.64,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":465.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, zoom recording, it could work.","index":150,"end_time":467.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I imagine that you also have just like a screen recorder on your computer.","index":151,"end_time":471.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":468.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":472.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.73,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That wouldn''t have to deal with, like, the zoom interference.","index":153,"end_time":474.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In my mind, that would be easier.","index":154,"end_time":477.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you prefer to go through it right now, maybe we can do that.","index":155,"end_time":479.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just thinking then we could kind of bake.","index":156,"end_time":482.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.84,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, go back to that part, do it a little differently, things like that.","index":157,"end_time":486.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.44,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":158,"end_time":487.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, we could do that.","index":159,"end_time":488.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It might be better if Axel''s here, just because I feel like he has, like, specific sections of the tool that or the platform that he wants to show.","index":160,"end_time":496.279,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":489.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I''m thinking now is hopefully he''s going to join soon.","index":161,"end_time":501.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Or maybe we could just.","index":162,"end_time":503.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"If you could.","index":163,"end_time":504.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.6,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Could we schedule another 15 minutes at some point to do that?","index":164,"end_time":507.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.44,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And what we could also potentially do is mark parts of I don''t understand.","index":165,"end_time":512.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You''re busy.","index":166,"end_time":513.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.75,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But in potential, we can mark things in the meeting and I don''t know if you can screen record and screen share at the same time, but in Zoom.","index":167,"end_time":528.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, like, I could.","index":168,"end_time":530.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"If I could share my screen in a meeting and do stream recordings and then you''re just going to be.","index":169,"end_time":536.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, like clip that one.","index":170,"end_time":537.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.33,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":171,"end_time":538.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.81,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":172,"end_time":539.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.41,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":540.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.77,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Do this in like 15 minutes.","index":174,"end_time":541.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.49,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think rather than having my concern.","index":175,"end_time":544.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":541.85,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s my concern about doing it over.","index":176,"end_time":546.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Zoom is just like the interference of the zoom platform versus you.","index":177,"end_time":549.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":546.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just like having your laptop in, like a screen recording tool open.","index":178,"end_time":552.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because, you know, if.","index":179,"end_time":555.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":554.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we''re recording it through Zoom and you''re doing a screen share, we''re going to lose.","index":180,"end_time":558.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, we don''t need those videos, but we''re going to lose some quality.","index":181,"end_time":561.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re going to lose.","index":182,"end_time":561.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like there might be some skips, things like that that we will not, you know, run into.","index":183,"end_time":565.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally.","index":184,"end_time":566.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But I''m wonder, could I do both, do you think?","index":185,"end_time":568.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.47,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Like, could I screen share?","index":186,"end_time":570.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Me screen recording?","index":187,"end_time":571.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.31,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":188,"end_time":572.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I can try right now, actually.","index":189,"end_time":574.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Theoretically, I. I think you could.","index":190,"end_time":576.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That might be the way to do it.","index":191,"end_time":577.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":576.31,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":192,"end_time":577.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Because then we can be like watching it and you''re sharing.","index":193,"end_time":583.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":578.149,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":584.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.99,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Do you want to try doing it?","index":195,"end_time":585.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.19,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No.","index":196,"end_time":586.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.67,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":197,"end_time":586.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.03,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, go for it.","index":198,"end_time":589.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":588.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t have.","index":199,"end_time":591.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":590.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"All right, go ahead.","index":200,"end_time":596.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Here, I''ll stop my share.","index":201,"end_time":619.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, no worries.","index":202,"end_time":621.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.41,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I didn''t see.","index":203,"end_time":621.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.33,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You already gave me the permissions share.","index":204,"end_time":624.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.81,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I just have the old version open here.","index":205,"end_time":630.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.65,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know if you can see.","index":206,"end_time":631.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.49,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":207,"end_time":632.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that might be another.","index":208,"end_time":633.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":632.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Axel might want to show the new user interface.","index":209,"end_time":636.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":633.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m just.","index":210,"end_time":637.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.45,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I''m just have this open.","index":211,"end_time":638.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.09,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":638.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For the testing and I mean, I could use anything to testify.","index":213,"end_time":643.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.99,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What''s the command?","index":214,"end_time":645.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.15,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Command shift five, I think.","index":215,"end_time":646.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.07,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Are you on Mac?","index":216,"end_time":649.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":648.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":217,"end_time":651.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m on Mac.","index":218,"end_time":654.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":219,"end_time":654.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.15,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You''re good.","index":220,"end_time":656.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just.","index":221,"end_time":656.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just got a new Mac on Sunday.","index":222,"end_time":658.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":223,"end_time":660.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.75,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I need to do that.","index":224,"end_time":662.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.03,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You use Mac for work too, or.","index":225,"end_time":664.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.39,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No.","index":226,"end_time":664.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":664.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I had switched to Windows at the beginning of the year and I just switched back.","index":227,"end_time":668.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":228,"end_time":675.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think it works.","index":229,"end_time":677.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.17,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":230,"end_time":683.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, I said capture.","index":231,"end_time":685.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.25,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What did I just do?","index":232,"end_time":686.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.37,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":233,"end_time":689.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.45,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Recording.","index":234,"end_time":690.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Huh?","index":235,"end_time":694.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t think you can do both, but either way.","index":236,"end_time":697.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.01,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, it might be a little.","index":237,"end_time":698.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it might be something like you and Axel just, you know, sync and do a double check on the video script.","index":238,"end_time":704.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like I said, we already updated it based on the feedback, but.","index":239,"end_time":706.889,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then just like create a Checklist of things to record.","index":240,"end_time":709.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":706.889,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Send those over to us and we''ll take care of everything else.","index":241,"end_time":712.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it?","index":242,"end_time":714.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.05,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":243,"end_time":715.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.69,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Wait, but there already is the checklist of things to record directly?","index":244,"end_time":718.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":715.25,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, pretty much.","index":245,"end_time":719.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":720.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":719.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just didn''t.","index":247,"end_time":720.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you wanted to rewrite it in any way.","index":248,"end_time":722.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":720.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":249,"end_time":722.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some people think differently.","index":250,"end_time":723.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":722.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, I think it''s all good.","index":251,"end_time":727.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.75,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So we have that.","index":252,"end_time":728.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.51,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":253,"end_time":729.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.71,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yes, give me one second.","index":254,"end_time":732.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, and then the other thing that you had asked about was the podcast episode.","index":255,"end_time":738.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we had the script and as far as I know, there''s no changes that need to be made to this.","index":256,"end_time":743.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think you guys are all good.","index":257,"end_time":744.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only thing that had to be filled in here was David''s experience in years.","index":258,"end_time":749.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":745.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you know that off the top of your head and then I''m sending it in teams right now, but basically it''s to you guys now you just.","index":259,"end_time":759.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have your Riverside account set up.","index":260,"end_time":762.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Riverside is a podcast recording tool and video recording tool.","index":261,"end_time":765.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":762.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a really cool one.","index":262,"end_time":767.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":766.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":263,"end_time":767.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.62,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"We''re a partner with them, so we get you guys a discounted rate.","index":264,"end_time":770.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It basically is like a zoom call, but it''s recording you both separately so that there''s no like lag or interference or anything going on.","index":265,"end_time":778.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll create a bunch of assets out of your guys conversation.","index":266,"end_time":782.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you just go in, create a studio, you know, call it Eli and David or you know, episode one, Eli and David, whatever you want to call it.","index":267,"end_time":790.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":782.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it''s basically just like starting a zoom chat or a zoom call and you just go through and have your conversation.","index":268,"end_time":797.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I recommend, you know, starting with maybe like a five minute test, you know, as you''re going in or what I can offer is if it works for your guys availability.","index":269,"end_time":807.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":797.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t know because David''s in.","index":270,"end_time":809.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think he''s in Greenwich meantime.","index":271,"end_time":811.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":272,"end_time":811.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s.","index":273,"end_time":812.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":811.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s plus zero.","index":274,"end_time":812.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s.","index":275,"end_time":813.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s already like three o'' clock in the afternoon for him, I think.","index":276,"end_time":816.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or two.","index":277,"end_time":817.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if we could find a time.","index":278,"end_time":819.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I, I''m willing to join and like help with any technical things as well, you know, for the setup of running this recording.","index":279,"end_time":827.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you guys would like that.","index":280,"end_time":828.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that would.","index":281,"end_time":833.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.83,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That could be helpful for the first one, at least.","index":282,"end_time":835.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"For sure.","index":283,"end_time":836.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":284,"end_time":837.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":836.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And I also.","index":285,"end_time":838.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have a video that we can send you of how to.","index":286,"end_time":841.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How to use the tool.","index":287,"end_time":842.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":841.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":288,"end_time":843.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":842.83,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be helpful as well, I think.","index":289,"end_time":845.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.31,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":290,"end_time":846.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.11,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Partly what I was thinking with the screen recording stuff.","index":291,"end_time":848.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.51,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"As well is we.","index":292,"end_time":849.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, by syncing up and doing it correctly the first time, we might be saving time in the long run.","index":293,"end_time":858.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":294,"end_time":860.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Back and forth and stuff.","index":295,"end_time":861.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.68,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":296,"end_time":862.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And in the meantime, I''ll also send you that video so you can review that also.","index":297,"end_time":867.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be perfect, I think, if you could say in the chat, like, here''s a video on how to use Riverside.","index":298,"end_time":874.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"The script is ready.","index":299,"end_time":876.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":874.76,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"We''re just missing David''s work experience.","index":300,"end_time":878.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.12,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And then we can get in there.","index":301,"end_time":881.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":879.17,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You okay, Da?","index":302,"end_time":888.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.01,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You look shocked.","index":303,"end_time":890.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.57,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I think Da is just reading something.","index":304,"end_time":893.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":305,"end_time":894.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.05,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Sorry, did you.","index":306,"end_time":897.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":896.37,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Did you ask me something?","index":307,"end_time":898.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":897.17,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"No, no.","index":308,"end_time":900.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":898.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was just saying that we have the same meeting on Friday.","index":309,"end_time":903.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":900.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I don''t know if.","index":310,"end_time":904.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.05,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Are we.","index":311,"end_time":905.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":905.09,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Are we having that meeting again or.","index":312,"end_time":909.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.41,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":909.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eli, do you think we need our second meeting on Friday, considering we just launched the campaign today?","index":314,"end_time":912.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":315,"end_time":915.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.13,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Maybe we could.","index":316,"end_time":917.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.09,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Or we could try and use that as the.","index":317,"end_time":919.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we could podcast that.","index":318,"end_time":921.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.37,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I think that should be for both, like, you know, to finish up anything we don''t get with the podcast or the stream recordings.","index":319,"end_time":929.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.929,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good to me.","index":320,"end_time":933.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":321,"end_time":933.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":933.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":322,"end_time":936.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.26,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And I think that that''s an update on everything I had.","index":323,"end_time":940.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.78,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So the advertisements are starting today.","index":324,"end_time":942.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":940.94,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":943.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Ads are getting launched today.","index":326,"end_time":945.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":943.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Emails and LinkedIn messages are already live.","index":327,"end_time":947.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":945.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":328,"end_time":949.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.3,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And what''s.","index":329,"end_time":950.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.34,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How.","index":330,"end_time":951.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.9,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"How is the emails going?","index":331,"end_time":952.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.22,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There hasn''t been any leads from that, really.","index":332,"end_time":954.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.74,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Now, email is.","index":333,"end_time":956.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think I''ve mentioned this email is more of, like, an awareness thing.","index":334,"end_time":960.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we don''t see a lot of replies from emails in really any campaign.","index":335,"end_time":965.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s when we''re sending someone an email, we''re also messaging them on LinkedIn.","index":336,"end_time":968.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re also seeing ads.","index":337,"end_time":969.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":968.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They go to the landing page, they''re getting retargeted.","index":338,"end_time":971.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s when.","index":339,"end_time":972.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they get like, a fourth or fifth email.","index":340,"end_time":974.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then they start to know, like, who Desi Dollo is, because they saw that ad, they got a message.","index":341,"end_time":978.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":975.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like it''s just another channel to be in front of them.","index":342,"end_time":981.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":978.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For sure.","index":343,"end_time":982.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.1,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":344,"end_time":982.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":982.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just was asking also because I don''t have any.","index":345,"end_time":985.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.94,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s not my email and stuff.","index":346,"end_time":988.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.54,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I don''t know what''s going on there, if there''s some replies or what''s.","index":347,"end_time":992.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":988.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re monitoring it.","index":348,"end_time":993.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We get.","index":349,"end_time":993.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have slack, so we get a notification anytime there''s a response.","index":350,"end_time":996.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":993.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The only thing that we''ve seen so far is out of office replies.","index":351,"end_time":999.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":352,"end_time":1000.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.78,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":353,"end_time":1000.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.38,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And the other thing that we see is sometimes a company''s like, they''ll.","index":354,"end_time":1004.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1001.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ll Say this person left, but this person is handling that role.","index":355,"end_time":1007.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1004.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we do is we go in and just update the lead to go to the new person.","index":356,"end_time":1011.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sweet.","index":357,"end_time":1012.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011.86,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s all for today.","index":358,"end_time":1014.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.52,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I do have one question if you guys have another minute.","index":359,"end_time":1017.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Have you, like, ever worked with.","index":360,"end_time":1020.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.48,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So sometimes people buy leads direct.","index":361,"end_time":1025.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.88,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Have you ever tried doing that?","index":362,"end_time":1028.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.72,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So we actually do.","index":363,"end_time":1030.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s.","index":364,"end_time":1031.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s how we got all the contacts for this campaign.","index":365,"end_time":1033.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1031.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re not free.","index":366,"end_time":1034.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, we use a tool called Clay.","index":367,"end_time":1037.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was the table that I showed you.","index":368,"end_time":1038.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1037.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can pull that back up.","index":369,"end_time":1039.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what Clay natively utilizes is LinkedIn as a database, but we also have tools like ZoomInfo and all of the, like, big name Apollo, all of those big ones that filter in and help us build this lead list.","index":370,"end_time":1055.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we put them through a rigorous, like, are they a fit?","index":371,"end_time":1058.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.819,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, let''s look at their company description, make sure their titles match what we''re looking for, and then we automatically add them to the campaigns from there.","index":372,"end_time":1065.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we did purchase these leads.","index":373,"end_time":1069.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1067.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":374,"end_time":1070.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.4,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":375,"end_time":1071.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I was talking to a friend who does some like.","index":376,"end_time":1073.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1071.8,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"He, like, sells leads and sounds like a good business, but I was thinking, like, I was thinking about it wrong, I guess.","index":377,"end_time":1082.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.84,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So we.","index":378,"end_time":1083.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.92,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s Zoom Info as well.","index":379,"end_time":1084.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Would be a competitor for that.","index":380,"end_time":1086.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1084.84,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s not necessarily just.","index":381,"end_time":1087.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1086.12,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, so what Clay is.","index":382,"end_time":1088.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a.","index":383,"end_time":1089.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1088.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a massive spreadsheet with integrations.","index":384,"end_time":1091.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":385,"end_time":1091.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1091.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can have Apollo feed into it.","index":386,"end_time":1093.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1091.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can have ZoomInfo feed into it.","index":387,"end_time":1094.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can have.","index":388,"end_time":1095.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1094.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a lot of, like, AI that feeds into it and does a lot of research.","index":389,"end_time":1099.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1095.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a basically just like a big amalgamation of different tools put into a spreadsheet.","index":390,"end_time":1105.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1100.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can set up enrichments for anything.","index":391,"end_time":1106.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1109.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s where we.","index":393,"end_time":1110.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We purchase the leads every time we start a new campaign.","index":394,"end_time":1112.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, got it.","index":395,"end_time":1116.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.56,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Cool.","index":396,"end_time":1117.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.92,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s another thing we offer to you guys at a discounted rate because we''re.","index":397,"end_time":1120.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have a discount through our partnership with them, rather than, like, Zoom Info, which can be like $15,000 for three months.","index":398,"end_time":1128.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so you do.","index":399,"end_time":1131.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.99,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So for any outbound campaign, you need to buy leads.","index":400,"end_time":1137.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.67,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I mean, unless you just do pure organic cold prospecting, which takes a lot of time.","index":401,"end_time":1144.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1138.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":402,"end_time":1145.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.03,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I''m not so familiar with this whole, like, ecosystem and stuff, but yeah.","index":403,"end_time":1151.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.87,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So.","index":404,"end_time":1152.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we do is we start out, you know, when we were in our early meetings, when we were going through the aligned growth engine and everything, I started building this table, and it was based on all of our conversations of what is the ideal customer profile.","index":405,"end_time":1164.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we start with the companies say they''re located in the United States.","index":406,"end_time":1168.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1164.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re in the IT services and consulting industry.","index":407,"end_time":1170.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have this, you know, amount of employees, they might have this revenue range, all of that.","index":408,"end_time":1175.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We start, we get that list and then we say, okay, based on that list of companies, identify people with these job titles.","index":409,"end_time":1183.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we go through and we get their email addresses, their LinkedIn profiles, we validate their email addresses so it''s not a bounce.","index":410,"end_time":1190.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s how we load them into the campaign.","index":411,"end_time":1193.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hmm.","index":412,"end_time":1196.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1195.63,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And so, like, for example, Could we spend more money on better leads or No?","index":413,"end_time":1207.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1197.79,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I mean, what do you mean by better leads?","index":414,"end_time":1211.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, for example, someone who might have requested to have psa, AI automation, or learn more about CV management.","index":415,"end_time":1225.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.63,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, some things that, you know, example of, like if someone''s buying solar leads, Right.","index":416,"end_time":1231.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1226.63,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You could buy like a list of people who live in the neighborhood, or you could probably pay twice as much or five times as much for people who had previously inquired about solar.","index":417,"end_time":1242.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1231.35,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right.","index":418,"end_time":1242.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1242.35,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Well, it all depends on.","index":419,"end_time":1244.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On data that''s available.","index":420,"end_time":1245.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, we don''t.","index":421,"end_time":1246.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1245.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s not really anywhere to grab data of.","index":422,"end_time":1248.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1246.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has someone in their Google searched for, you know, this type of software?","index":423,"end_time":1253.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1248.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":424,"end_time":1254.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1254.02,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"There''s not.","index":425,"end_time":1255.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1255.3,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, not.","index":426,"end_time":1257.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1256.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''re aware of it, please let me know.","index":427,"end_time":1259.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would help us.","index":428,"end_time":1260.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes you get those emails, like, I have a list of really hot list leads and it''s your competitors, clients, and stuff like that.","index":429,"end_time":1268.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1261.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Those are pretty much fake lists.","index":430,"end_time":1271.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, Don''t.","index":431,"end_time":1274.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.7,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s interesting.","index":432,"end_time":1274.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.14,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":433,"end_time":1276.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1275.78,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So then you might have to.","index":434,"end_time":1278.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1277.3,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"They all already have solutions.","index":435,"end_time":1282.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1281.08,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":436,"end_time":1284.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.56,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And.","index":437,"end_time":1284.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so the only thing.","index":438,"end_time":1285.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1284.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Years ago or something.","index":439,"end_time":1286.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":440,"end_time":1287.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And the only thing that we could do there that is not 100% accurate is we can enrich for a tech stack.","index":441,"end_time":1294.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if you guys, you know, if you''re saying, like, this is our main competitor in the US we can see.","index":442,"end_time":1299.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1294.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can look at a tool called HG Insights and basically see if we can grab a list of companies that use that competitor.","index":443,"end_time":1307.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1301.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it''s not super accurate is the only thing.","index":444,"end_time":1310.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1308.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":445,"end_time":1316.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.56,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And you can''t.","index":446,"end_time":1317,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.04,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"What about.","index":447,"end_time":1319.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.32,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"That''s just like spying, right?","index":448,"end_time":1324.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.68,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Or something?","index":449,"end_time":1324.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.08,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I feel like, how do you.","index":450,"end_time":1325.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.36,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Could we get some list of like, what.","index":451,"end_time":1327.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.4,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"The list of what other competitors are getting their leads from?","index":452,"end_time":1332.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.24,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, I mean, that''s like proprietary to every company.","index":453,"end_time":1335.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":454,"end_time":1336.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"They wouldn''t say that.","index":455,"end_time":1337.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right?","index":456,"end_time":1337.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.01,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":457,"end_time":1337.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.25,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"No, this is the same list.","index":458,"end_time":1340.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1337.65,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":459,"end_time":1340.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":460,"end_time":1341.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.73,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":461,"end_time":1342.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.37,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I guess I just hadn''t thought enough about the.","index":462,"end_time":1347.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1342.73,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"You know, I had the market of leads and then I kind of felt like I was neglecting a little bit.","index":463,"end_time":1356.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1349.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"But all good, good rundown.","index":464,"end_time":1358.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1356.53,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Thank you guys.","index":465,"end_time":1359.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.45,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And yeah, so I sent the follow up message in teams already.","index":466,"end_time":1362.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1359.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I sent the video script.","index":467,"end_time":1364.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we need is screen recording or multiple screen recordings of the platform, showcase the AI agent skills matrix, uploading CVS, etc.","index":468,"end_time":1370.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The podcast script, the login for Riverside.","index":469,"end_time":1374.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1371.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And what we need you to do is log in and record the episode.","index":470,"end_time":1378.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Our Friday meeting agenda is going to go through Riverside questions or screen recording questions.","index":471,"end_time":1382.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1378.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds perfect.","index":472,"end_time":1385.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.24,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I can on my end.","index":473,"end_time":1388.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.76,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Try to do the podcast before Friday, do you think?","index":474,"end_time":1395.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1392.55,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, if you and David have the time.","index":475,"end_time":1397.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1395.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There were typically a seven day turnaround on the assets.","index":476,"end_time":1400.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice.","index":477,"end_time":1401.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":478,"end_time":1402.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1401.91,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And maybe we''re gonna need to re record it or something like that.","index":479,"end_time":1407.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1402.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"So I think I''m gonna try to get it, you know, the first version in this week.","index":480,"end_time":1413.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.67,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And then I guess like you said you.","index":481,"end_time":1416.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.43,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s not like a block traditional podcast.","index":482,"end_time":1422.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1418.59,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Right?","index":483,"end_time":1422.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.27,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s more.","index":484,"end_time":1423.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1422.51,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re more looking at it as a video series.","index":485,"end_time":1426.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1424.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so the cool thing, the reason why we''re so dedicated to like having a content engine is because we can use this anywhere.","index":486,"end_time":1437.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, we get a couple quote cards or short videos out of you guys recording.","index":487,"end_time":1441.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, that''s all over social.","index":488,"end_time":1442.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can put it on the landing page.","index":489,"end_time":1443.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can allude to it in emails and messages and ads.","index":490,"end_time":1446.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just gives us more of an arsenal of things to communicate.","index":491,"end_time":1450.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Totally.","index":492,"end_time":1451.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1450.97,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"It''s like gasoline or something, right?","index":493,"end_time":1453.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.57,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":494,"end_time":1454.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pouring kerosene on the fire.","index":495,"end_time":1455.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":496,"end_time":1456.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1455.77,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":497,"end_time":1456.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1456.37,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Nice.","index":498,"end_time":1457.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1457.45,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"All right, well, thanks guys.","index":499,"end_time":1460.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.29,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"I''m glad you had a good vacation, Colin.","index":500,"end_time":1463.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1460.85,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"And you know, you as well.","index":501,"end_time":1467.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1463.81,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Yeah, if you.","index":502,"end_time":1468.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1467.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":503,"end_time":1469.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1469.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"EA was covering my butt while I was out.","index":504,"end_time":1471.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1469.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":505,"end_time":1472.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.28,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":506,"end_time":1474.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1473.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, if any other questions pop up, just let me know.","index":507,"end_time":1476.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, I got those messages in teams, so.","index":508,"end_time":1480.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1476.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and I just let Eli, or I''m sorry, I let Axel know that the campaigns are live and all the feedback was implemented.","index":509,"end_time":1485.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":510,"end_time":1488.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.399,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":511,"end_time":1488.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Talk later.","index":512,"end_time":1489.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.84,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":513,"end_time":1490.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1489.56,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"},{"text":"See you Friday.","index":514,"end_time":1491.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1490.84,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":515,"end_time":1492.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1491.96,"speaker_name":"Eli Bebinger"}],"dateString":"2025-12-02T14:02:54.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81473554029?pwd=oAVAZ4qOWIzyRbxS8zQrkrquELSYaw.1","participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KBFNZ4Y5EANF1Z2M6AZ5FA6P","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Launched new ad campaigns and updated LinkedIn/email messaging as of this morning.","Colin confirmed all page updates and rewrites were implemented ahead of campaign launch.","Product explainer script finalized; team to screen record platform features for animation.","Podcast script ready except David’s experience; Eli to test Riverside recording this week.","Friday''s meeting repurposed for podcast setup and screen recording coordination with Axel."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Emails and LinkedIn messages are already live.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"So now we''re good to go on that.","speaker":"Eli Bebinger"},{"quote":"We''ll design and animate the whole process.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","content","video","ads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2025-12-02T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Campaign Launch and Performance**\n\nThe team successfully launched the updated **LinkedIn ads, emails, and outreach messages** tied to the new registration campaign today (15:43).\n\n- **All feedback on the landing page was addressed, and the page is now ready for campaign launch** as confirmed by **Colin** (01:24).  \n    - The updated page includes buttons linking to registration and demo forms for easier user flow.  \n    - This readiness removed a key barrier, allowing the campaign to start immediately.  \n    - Emails and LinkedIn messages switched focus from offering free profiles to promoting free registration, improving message clarity.  \n    - Early email responses are limited, but this is expected as emails serve primarily for awareness rather than direct replies.\n\n- **The campaign targets a list of 1,500 contacts managed through Smart Lead and LinkedIn outreach tools** (04:00).  \n    - Contacts were sourced from purchased leads via Clay, integrating multiple databases and AI to ensure fit and accuracy.  \n    - Leads are continuously updated to reflect role changes within target companies, maintaining list relevance.  \n    - Colin highlighted that buying leads is necessary for outbound campaigns, as organic prospecting is time-consuming.\n\n- **Current email engagement shows mainly out-of-office replies, with LinkedIn expected to drive direct interactions** (16:32).  \n    - Monitoring is in place via Slack notifications for immediate response tracking.  \n    - Retargeting through multiple channels aims to build recognition before direct lead engagement.\n\n## **Product Explainer Video Development**\n\nThe product explainer video is entering a recording and animation phase with a clear plan to improve user friendliness (04:04).\n\n- **The script was finalized with minor edits removing outdated references and adjusting text based on feedback from Axel and Tina** (04:24).  \n    - Colin will resend the updated script for the team to record screen captures.  \n    - The video will reanimate real platform footage into simplified, user-friendly visuals matching approved screenshots.\n\n- **Screen recordings should focus on key features including the AI-powered interface, resource management dashboard, skills matrix, and resume upload** (05:21).  \n    - Eli confirmed the team will upload recordings to Teams for Colin’s team to download and animate.  \n    - Colin advised against recording via Zoom due to quality loss; local screen recordings are preferred for clarity.  \n    - The team discussed scheduling 15-minute sessions with Axel for guided recordings to optimize content coverage and reduce rework.\n\n- **This approach aims to create a polished video that demonstrates platform value clearly while saving time on multiple takes** (08:00).  \n    - The plan includes flexibility to adjust the script if needed during recordings.\n\n## **Podcast Production and Content Strategy**\n\nA podcast episode recording is planned with Riverside, aiming to create versatile content assets supporting marketing (12:10).\n\n- **The podcast script is complete except for David’s years of experience, which Eli will confirm and provide** (12:47).  \n    - Riverside accounts are set up, offering high-quality, separate audio tracks to avoid recording issues.  \n    - Colin offered to assist with technical setup and recommended a short 5-minute test recording to ensure smooth execution.\n\n- **The podcast content will be repurposed into multiple formats including short videos and quote cards for social and landing pages** (23:44).  \n    - This multi-format content strategy is designed to amplify outreach and support the campaign’s messaging arsenal.\n\n- **Eli aims to complete the initial podcast recording before the upcoming Friday meeting to allow for a 7-day turnaround on assets** (23:15).  \n    - The Friday meeting will review any questions about Riverside and screen recordings, providing a checkpoint for finalizing content.\n\n## **Lead Acquisition and Quality Insights**\n\nLead sourcing relies on integrated databases with a focus on fit rather than behavior-based targeting due to current data limitations (17:09).\n\n- **Leads are purchased through Clay, which aggregates data from LinkedIn, ZoomInfo, Apollo, and AI tools to create targeted lists** (17:50).  \n    - The team filters leads by company size, industry, revenue, and job titles to match the ideal customer profile developed in early strategy sessions.  \n    - Email addresses are validated to reduce bounce rates and maintain campaign efficiency.\n\n- **Colin clarified that buying leads is essential for outbound campaigns as organic prospecting is slow and less scalable** (18:58).  \n    - There is no practical access to data indicating prior product interest or search behavior, limiting highly targeted lead buying.  \n    - Attempts to buy “hot leads” or competitor customer lists often result in unreliable or outdated contacts.\n\n- **The team can enrich leads by identifying tech stacks used via HG Insights to approximate competitor customers, though data accuracy is limited** (21:27).  \n    - Legal and proprietary restrictions prevent accessing competitor lead sources directly.\n\n## **Process and Communication Improvements**\n\nClear communication and streamlined processes are in place to reduce delays and ensure smooth campaign and content delivery (01:24).\n\n- **Feedback loops on landing page, video script, and campaign messaging have been effectively closed, enabling rapid deployment** (01:24).  \n    - Colin monitors campaign responses via Slack, providing real-time alerts on replies and bouncebacks.  \n    - Updates are made to contact lists dynamically to maintain lead accuracy.\n\n- **Sharing of videos, scripts, and instructions occurs through Teams and chat channels for transparency and tracking** (22:39).  \n    - Colin committed to sending tutorial videos for Riverside and screen recording guidelines to Eli for team readiness.  \n    - Eli and David’s responsibilities for podcast recording and screen captures are clearly assigned with due dates before the Friday meeting.\n\n- **The team agreed to use the Friday meeting to address any open items related to podcast recording and screen capture, maximizing efficiency** (15:31).  \n    - This structure reduces the need for extra meetings and keeps focus on deliverables.\n\n## **Strategic Outlook and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is focused on driving awareness and engagement through a multi-channel approach combining paid ads, outreach, and rich content (02:25).\n\n- **Switching campaign focus from free profile offers to registration aligns messaging with clearer value and expected user behavior** (02:47).  \n    - Colin noted the importance of layering touchpoints to build brand familiarity before expecting conversion.\n\n- **Content assets like explainer videos and podcast episodes are critical to supporting the sales funnel and improving user understanding** (23:44).  \n    - These assets will be repurposed across channels to extend reach and engagement.\n\n- **Lead acquisition strategy balances cost and data quality, with ongoing refinement to improve targeting within current ecosystem constraints** (17:09).  \n    - Continued monitoring and list adjustments will optimize campaign efficiency.\n\n- **Eli and Colin will coordinate the upcoming recording sessions with Axel and David to finalize video and podcast materials before the next meeting** (23:04).  \n    - This sequencing ensures content readiness to support ongoing marketing efforts and campaign optimization.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead generation","LinkedIn outreach","Product explainer video","Podcast recording","Campaign launch","Data enrichment"],"overview":"- **Marketing Campaign Launch:** New LinkedIn ads and outreach messages launched, improving clarity on free registration focus.  \n- **Target Contacts:** Campaign targets 1,500 contacts through Smart Lead and LinkedIn, sourced via Clay for accuracy.  \n- **Video Development:** Product explainer video in recording phase, focusing on key features with a user-friendly approach.  \n- **Podcast Strategy:** Podcast episode script is ready, aims for versatile content with a 7-day turnaround on assets.  \n- **Lead Acquisition:** Leads are purchased using Clay, targeting company size and industry; focus on data quality over behavior.  \n- **Process Improvements:** Clear communication and rapid feedback loops established to enhance campaign efficiency and content delivery.","action_items":"\n**Eli Bebinger**\nRecord screen captures of key DesiDollar platform features (AI tool, dashboards, skills matrix, resume upload) and upload to Teams for animation (06:06)\nCollaborate with Axel to review and potentially refine video script and recording checklist (08:00)\nCoordinate with David to record initial podcast episode via Riverside before Friday (23:04)\nPrepare questions or adjustments related to screen recordings and podcast recording for follow-up Friday meeting (23:30)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated explainer video script and checklist for recordings to Eli and team via Teams (05:09)\nProvide instructional video on Riverside podcast recording tool to Eli’s team (13:58)\nMonitor campaign responses and notify team of any lead replies or out-of-office replies via Slack (15:52)\nConfirm updated campaign messaging and lead list details to Axel (24:30)\n\n**Axel**\nReview explainer video recording checklist with Eli and coordinate on specific platform sections to highlight (07:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a2d8435a-9a11-4ea7-b24a-3f9564d07a17","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
