* and **$10 billion in debt** (04:57)  \n    - Fahad described how this case could serve as a powerful case study and marketing tool, given its high profile and media coverage  \n    - The Mint Group requested a joint webinar in early January to showcase the platform, positioning Cedra for significant exposure among major banks and legal players  \n    - Fahad is offering the Mint Group a near-cost deal to secure the case, viewing it as an investment in brand recognition and market positioning  \n\n- **Jackie and Fahad discussed discount offers, agreeing discounts for beta testers of the AI Investment Investigator product are separate from POC campaigns** (08:32)  \n    - Fahad emphasized selective offer application to avoid free work for low-potential clients, reinforcing that public campaigns must be carefully targeted to protect resources  \n\n## **Marketing and Advertising Updates**\n\nThe marketing team is shifting budget focus to LinkedIn ads and finalizing creative assets to support upcoming campaigns.\n\n- **Taylor reported completion of new ad creative for the demo landing page, reallocating budget from Google Ads to LinkedIn based on better performance metrics** (13:12)  \n    - Google Ads will now be limited to branded campaigns only to conserve budget  \n    - The new LinkedIn campaign, including images and ad copy, is ready and will launch after Fahad’s approval for maximum impact  \n\n- **Content scheduling is underway with all main page posts loaded in Publer, and Fahad’s post designs are being finalized based on documents he provided**  \n    - The procurement video animation is being adjusted to feature Cedra at the center with spokes, with graphics work ongoing and expected completion soon  \n\n## **Lead Research and Targeting**\n\nFahad is preparing research to identify and prioritize law firms and individuals for targeted outreach beyond the Mint Group connection.\n\n- **Fahad will send a press release and additional research to Taylor and Jackie to help pinpoint relevant contacts and firms to target for the Mint Group-related opportunity and other prospects** (14:10)  \n    - This research aims to refine the audience for outreach, ensuring campaigns focus on high-potential leads familiar with Cedra’s brand  \n    - Taylor highlighted the value of this targeted approach to increase campaign efficiency and engagement rates  \n\n## **Process and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe team is optimizing campaign management to allow message updates without disrupting ongoing outreach efforts.\n\n- **Taylor explained that Lemlist requires pausing current email sequences to update messages, so the plan is to launch new campaigns with refreshed content and pause existing sequences to avoid wasted sends** (02:45)  \n    - This approach includes potentially purchasing more domains to increase sending capacity and avoid bottlenecks  \n    - The team will restart outreach with new messaging in January after the year-end POC push, maintaining momentum without overlap or fatigue  \n\n## **Strategic Positioning and Vision**\n\nFahad and Jackie underscored the importance of focusing on high-value, targeted engagements rather than broad, untargeted campaigns to maximize ROI and build strategic partnerships.\n\n- **Fahad stressed that deals like the Mint Group’s case put Cedra “on the map” and represent the type of high-profile exposure needed to scale efficiently** (06:34)  \n    - He sees selective paid POCs and beta programs as strategic tools to build credibility and market presence without diluting resources  \n    - Jackie reinforced that messaging must clearly communicate value and urgency around IT budget timing to convert interested prospects into paying customers before year-end (09:57)","outline":null,"keywords":["Year-end budget","Proof of Concept","ABM campaigns","bankruptcy case","LinkedIn outreach","paid POC"],"overview":"- **End-of-Year Strategy:** Focus on targeted paid POCs to utilize leftover IT budgets before December 31st.  \n- **Audience Targeting:** Create a specific list for outreach; avoid broad campaigns to efficiently reach interested contacts.  \n- **Finalized Pricing Model:** Pricing delivered to Weil, with ongoing talks for a high-profile bankruptcy case worth $10 billion in debt.  \n- **Marketing Focus Shift:** Budget moving to LinkedIn ads; new ad creative ready to launch after video approval.  \n- **Lead Research Enhancement:** Press release and research to identify targeted law firms and individuals for outreach.  \n- **Optimizing Campaign Management:** New messages to be launched in January; existing sequences will pause to prevent overlap.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nCreate a targeted audience segment in Lemlist for the year-end POC campaign and prepare to launch in December (01:50)\nPause existing ABM email sequences and prepare new campaigns with updated messaging to launch next week (02:45)\nSend updated procurement video animation for review once graphics complete (12:15)\nShare new LinkedIn and Google ad creative packages with team for approval before going live (12:15)\n\n**Jackie Wheeler**\nRefine messaging for paid POC campaign targeting leftover IT budgets, considering simple LinkedIn posts versus focused email campaigns (11:59)\nContinue ideation on pitch encouraging prospects to do POC to use IT budget and prepare messaging for early next week discussion (11:59)\n\n**Fahad Al Mutawa**\nShare press release and research on Mint Group bankruptcy case and related target law firms to aid campaign targeting strategy (14:10)\nMonitor ongoing discussions and feedback from Mint Group and coordinate webinar plans for early January (05:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"1e5ff732-89ae-4a0f-935d-ff556d21f489","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
